(1033, 'AEgQT02Hpu58hGmA8V', 'Educational Based', 'FEDERAL BANK HORMIS MEMORIAL FOUNDATION SCHOLARSHIPS 2021-22', 'https://forms.office.com/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=txhXLQDs0kmdGP7KKZzac6dKjVYJ9T9EorueVK50CexUOThFQTFWS1E3TzM1RlhYUDBJT0hPOFFCVS4u', '', '', '', '', '', 'Scholarship Details<br/>\r\n1. One seat in each discipline will be kept aside for physically challenged students, which shall be duly evidenced by a certificate issued by a Medical Officer not below the rank of DMO or an approved Medical Officer of the Bank. If applications are not received under physically challenged category, it will be utilized under general category.<br/>\r\n2. Selected students will be reimbursed 100% of tuition fees and other educational expenses paid as per the fee structure of the college, subject to a maximum of Rs.1 Lakh per year. Students are eligible for one Personal Computer (PC)/Laptop (maximum Rs 40,000/-will be reimbursed) during their course of study (within the overall limit of Rs.1.00 Lakh per year).<br/>\r\nScholarship for the Wards of Martyred Armed Forces Personnel<br/><br/>\r\n1. Annual Income criteria is NOT applicable to wards of martyred Armed Forces Personnel<br/>\r\n2. In the case of wards of martyred Armed Forces Personnel, evidence showing the same must\r\nbe produced.<br/>\r\n3. All other conditions are the same as general category.<br/>\r\n\r\nScholarship for Speech/Vision/Hearing impaired students<br/>\r\n1. Students of this category who are pursuing all Degree/Graduation courses or above listed professional courses offered can apply for the scholarship.<br/>\r\n2. Speech/Hearing/Vision impairment shall be evidenced by a certificate issued by a Medical Officer not below the rank of DMO or an approved Medical Officer of the Bank.<br/>\r\n3. All other conditions are the same as general category.<br/><br/>\r\nStudents from the following identified states are eligible to apply for scholarships.<br/>\r\nâ¢ Kerala<br/>\r\nâ¢ Tamil Nadu<br/>\r\nâ¢ Maharashtra<br/>\r\nâ¢ Gujarat<br/><br/>\r\nHow to Apply<br/>\r\n \r\nScholarship can be applied online through the following link in the Bankâs website<br/>\r\nStudents are required to visit the nearest Federal Bank Branch (with the required documents) only on receiving intimation from the Bank via mail.<br/>\r\nKYC documents of the students (in original) have to be shown while visiting the branch.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nInstructions for the students<br/>\r\n1. Apply the scholarship through the following link available in our website<br/>\r\n2. Take a printout of the application submitted online.<br/>\r\n3. Last date of submission of online application is 31.01.2022<br/>\r\nOn receiving intimation via mail from the Bank, visit the nearest. <br/>\r\n4. Federal Bank branch with<br/>\r\nthe print out of the application form and the attachments as mentioned below<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nAttach the following documents:<br/>\r\na. Copy of Admission Letter<br/>\r\nb. Copy of Bonafide certificate from the college.<br/>\r\nc. Copy of course fee structure<br/>\r\nd. Copy of Mark sheets of qualifying Examination(If originals are already submitted to the college and not available for verification, attach copy of the mark sheet attested by the head of the college of study)<br/>\r\ne. Copy of instructions from the University for converting the CGPA/Grade into percentage(mandatory for MBA Applicants)<br/>\r\nf. Copy of Family income certificate & Ration Card issued by government authorities<br/>\r\ng. Copy of Nativity certificate.<br/>\r\nh. Copy of ID proof & Address proof<br/>\r\ni. Copy of Medical Certificate (applicable for physically challenged students & speech/hearing/vision impaired students)<br/>\r\nj. In the case of dependant wards of Martyred Armed Forces Personnel who lost their life while serving the Nation, evidence showing the same.<br/>\r\nVisit Federal Bank branch at the place of domicile of the student along with the Originals & copies of the above documents for verification.\r\n<br/>\r\nIncomplete applications will not be considered.<br/>\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Selected students will be reimbursed 100% of tuition fees and other educational expenses paid as per the fee structure of the college, subject to a maximum of Rs.1 Lakh per year. Students are eligible for one Personal Computer (PC)/Laptop (maximum Rs 40,000/-will be reimbursed) during their course of study (within the overall limit of Rs.1.00 Lakh per year).\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"B.Tech (All)\",\"B.E (All)\",\"Bachelor Of Medicine & Bachelor Of Surgery - M.B.B.S\",\"Bachelor Of Nursing\",\"Bachelor Of Medicine & Bachelor Of Surgery - M.B.B.S\",\"Bachelor Of Nursing\",\"Master Of Business Administration - M.B.A\",\"Bachelor of Agriculture (BScAgri)\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 50.00, 50.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"Gujarat\",\"Kerala\",\"Maharashtra\",\"Tamil Nadu\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, 'null', 300000.00, NULL, 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2021-10-18', '2022-01-31', 'Federal Bank Hormis Memorial Foundation', 100000.00, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-01-20 17:09:16', 1, NULL, '2022-01-20 11:39:16', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL);
