(1035, 'qCzICVGCNb8yzoT1oN', 'Educational Based', 'Reliance Foundation Scholarships for B.E or B.Tech students', 'https://www.scholarships.reliancefoundation.org/#!', '', '', '', '', '', 'To start your application, you will need to fill the online Eligibility Questionnaire below. If you fulfil the eligibility criteria, you will be sent an email invitation with log-in information to apply through our application portal.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nTimings and Deadlines<br/>\r\n1. When is the deadline to submit my application?<br/>\r\n-> The deadline for all applications is 11.59pm IST on Monday the 14th February 2022. <br/>\r\n\r\n2. When is the deadline to submit my reference letters?<br/>\r\n->The deadline for referees to submit their references online is one week after the application deadline, 11.59pm IST on Monday the 21st February 2022.<br/>\r\n\r\n3. When will I be notified about the status of my application?<br/>\r\n->We will inform all candidates of the final decisions by June 2022. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\nEligibility<br/><br/>\r\n1. How do I know if I am eligible to apply?<br/>\r\n-> Students must fulfil the following eligibility criteria in order to apply:<br/>\r\nâ¢ Be a resident Indian citizen<br/>\r\nâ¢ Currently enrolled full-time in an eligible degree and <br/>programme(subjects that fall within the fields of Artificial Intelligence/ Computer Sciences/ Mathematics & Computing/\r\nElectrical and/or Electronics Engineering)<br/>\r\nâ¢ Fulfil the following academic criteria:<br/>\r\nâ¢ Undergraduate Scholarship:<br/>\r\nStudents who secured a rank of 1-35000 in the JEE Main (Paper 1) Examination<br/>\r\nâ¢ Postgraduate Scholarship:<br/>\r\nâ¢ Students who secured a score of 550- 1,000 in the GATE Examination<br/>\r\nOR<br/>\r\nâ¢ Students who have not attempted GATE and have scored 7.5 or above in their Undergraduate CGPA (or % normalised to CGPA)<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br/>\r\nMandatory Supporting Documents \r\nPassport photograph<br/>\r\nâ¢ Address Proof (for address