(1078, '4qVxtGdq2DIAZGorXt', 'Educational Based', 'Google PhD Fellowship', 'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1mGv-QB4yqXygbFiAsSTOE63lfyMZXkjLbncvcYZmaSk/viewform?edit_requested=true', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Students receive named Fellowships which include a monetary award. The funds are given directly to the university to be distributed to cover the studentâs expenses and stipend as appropriate. In addition, the student will be matched with a Google Research Mentor who we hope will become a valuable resource to the student. There is no employee relationship between the student and Google as a result of receiving the fellowship. Fellowship recipients are not subject to intellectual property restrictions unless they complete an internship at Google. Fellowship recipients serving an internship are subject to the same intellectual property and other contractual obligations as any other Google intern. If a Fellowship student is interested, an internship at Google is encouraged, but not guaranteed or required.<br/>\r\n<li>Scholarship amount <br/>\r\n1)Early-stage PhD students<br/>\r\nUp to 4 year Fellowship<br/>\r\nUS $50K to cover stipend and other research related activities, travel expenses including overseas travel<br/>\r\nGoogle Research Mentor<br/>\r\n2)Late-stage PhD students <br/>\r\n1 year Fellowship<br/>\r\nUS $10K to recognise research contributions, cover stipend and other research related activities, travel expenses including overseas travel<br/>\r\nGoogle Research Mentor<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Eligibility requirements<br/>\r\n\r\n1)Full-time graduate students pursuing a PhD and enrolled in an Indian institution.<br/>\r\n2)Undergraduate or Masterâs students and professionals may apply.<br/>\r\n3)Undergraduate and Masterâs student applicants must be currently enrolled, full-time students at an Indian university.<br/>\r\n4)Professionals must be employed/affiliated with an organization registered in India.<br/>\r\n5)For these applicants, the Fellowship award shall be contingent on the awardee registering for a full-time PhD program of an Indian university in computer science (or an adjacent field) within the calendar year of the Fellowship award, or the award shall be forfeited.<br/>\r\n6)Grant of the Fellowship does not mean admission to the PhD program of a university. The awardee must also complete the PhD admission process of the respective institute/university where they wish to register for a PhD.<br/>\r\n7)Grant of the Fellowship will be subject to the rules and guidelines applicable in the institute/university where the awardee registers for the PhD program.<br/>\r\n8)Students must remain enrolled full-time in the PhD program for the duration of the Fellowship or forfeit the award.<br/>\r\n9)Google employees, and their spouses, children, and members of their household are not eligible.<br/>\r\n10)Students that are already supported by a comparable industry award are not eligible. Government or non-profit organization funding is exempt. <br/>\r\n<br/><hr>\r\n<li>Documents required <br/>\r\nStudents will need the following documents in order to complete an application (in English only)<br/>\r\n1)Student applicantâs resume with links to website and publications (if available)<br/>\r\n2)Available transcripts (mark sheets) starting from first year/semester of Bachelor\'s degree to date\r\nResearch proposal (maximum 3 pages, excluding references)<br/>\r\n3)2-3 letters of recommendation from those familiar with the applicant\'s work (at least one from the thesis advisor for current PhD students)<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'htr', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab <br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg <br/>', 'sfgdr', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"PHD (All)\"]', '\"Phd\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, NULL, 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-04-01', '2022-05-18', 'Google', 755900.00, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-01 10:51:45', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-21 09:53:42', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1079, 'f0n7Ge4Yor0AX7FKNX', 'Educational Based', 'Jawaharlal Nehru Scholarship For Doctoral Studies 2022 ', 'http://www.jnmf.in/Information_Sheet_&_Application_Form-2020.pdf', '', '', '', '', '', 'The scholarships are available for Ph.D. study in India .<br/>\r\n<li>A candidate may apply for scholarship in any one of the following areas of specialization : <br/>\r\n-Indian History and Civilization<br/>\r\n-Sociology<br/>\r\n-Comparative Studies in Religion & Culture<br/>\r\n-Economics<br/>\r\n-Geography<br/>\r\n-Philosophy<br/>\r\n-Ecology & Environment<br/>\r\n<li>Eligibility Conditions <br/>\r\nAt the time of submission of the application for scholarship, a candidate should<br/>\r\n-hold a FIRST Class Post-graduate degree with a minimum 60% marks in aggregate in both graduate and post graduate level.<br/>\r\n-Already be registered/admitted for Ph.D. degree with a recognized University/Institution in India. Those who have applied for registration and have not yet been registered at the time of submission of application,\r\nare not eligible to apply.<br/>\r\n-Not be above 35 years of age.<br/>\r\n-Be a full-time Ph.D. Scholar.<br/>\r\n<li>Duration of scholarship up to two years<br/>\r\n<li>Value Of Scholarship <br/>\r\n-Maintenance allowance including Tuition fee Rs. 18,000 per month.<br/>\r\n-Contingent expenses for study tours within\r\nIndia, purchase of books, stationery, etc. Rs. 15,000 per annum.<br/>\r\n<li>Note : <br/>\r\n-Completed application forms together with all the necessary enclosures should reach Administrative Secretary, Jawaharlal Nehru Memorial Fund, Teen Murti House, New Delhi-110 011 on or before 31 May.<br/>\r\n-Shortlisted candidates will be called for an interview any time during\r\nNovember/December.<br/>\r\n<br/><hr>\r\n<li> Documents required<br/>\r\nThe following documents should be securely attached seriatim to the\r\nApplication Form:<br/>\r\n-A passport size photograph of the applicant to be pasted on the form.<br/>\r\n-A synopsis of the proposed project as per the attached format.<br/>\r\n-Doctoral Monitoring Committeeâs report or Supervisorâs report/recommendations.<br/> \r\n-Postal Order/Demand Draft for Rs.100.<br/>\r\n-Ph.D registration certificate.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab <br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg <br/>', '', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"Ph.D. (Geography)\",\"Ph.D. (Philosophy)\",\"Ph.D. (Sociology)\",\"Ph.D. (Economics)\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 35, '[\"\"]', 0.00, NULL, 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-03-30', '2022-05-31', 'Jawaharlal Nehru Memorial Fund', 216000.00, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-01 14:42:11', 1, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-09 05:28:49', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1080, 'cqYYg9yN6pn5RF5ns9', 'Educational Based', 'CCB Scholarship 2022', 'http://app.ccbnic.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'CCB provides scholarship upto 70% in collegeâs fee in its member colleges.  CCB has associated with many colleges of different courses in India. CCB has tie up with leading colleges of India and reserved some seats (10 to 20% seats in different courses and branches) under scholarship scheme for SC/ST/OBC/General/Minority financial backward students. <br/>\r\n<li>CCB Counselling & Scholarship Process<br/>\r\n1)Students must apply online application form and download Application Receipt.<br/>\r\n2)After accepting the application form by CCB Scholarship Department, students will be invited for online counselling of CCB and it will be started on or after 15-May - 2022. Students have to download their Counselling Letter and colleges list on or after 15 - May - 2022<br/>\r\n\r\n3)Students get the benefit of rupees 60,000 to 2.5 lakhs  as discount fee in different courses (depending upon the course and its duration).<br/>\r\n<li>Note : <br/>\r\nIf you are appearing or pass-out student of 10th/12th/final year in UG or PG courses from any recognized Board or college or university and willing to take admission in Technical or Professional courses,  you can apply for CCB scholarship scheme.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>He/She should have scored at least 40-50% marks in the last qualifying examination. The candidate pursuing Polytechnic should have scored at least 33% marks in Class 10 or Class 12 examination.<br/>\r\n<br><hr>\r\n<li>Documents required <br/>\r\n1)2 passport size photograph.<br/>\r\n2)CCB counseling letter/ allotment letter.<br/>\r\n3)Mark sheet of the last qualifying examination.<br/>\r\n4)College ID/ Aadhar card/ Voter ID.<br/>\r\n5)Bank account details.<br/>\r\n6)Caste certificate (if applicable)<br/>\r\n7)Character certificate from high school.<br/>\r\n', '', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/st