(1081, 'vNCvzFaj3jYYl3DHXu', 'Talent Based', 'Documentary Films on the Importance of Millet\'s', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/inviting-documentary-films-importance-millets/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Showcasing the importance of millets and creating awareness in the masses towards it, MyGov along with the Ministry of Agriculture and Farmersâ Welfare is organizing a Short Film Contest on the importance of millets.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Terms and Conditions <br/>\r\n1)Please note that the short documentary film on the importance of millets must be original and should not violate any provision of the Indian Copyright Act, 1957.<br/>\r\n2)Once submitted for competition, copyrights will solely be with the Department of Agriculture & Farmers Welfare.<br/>\r\n3)The entry should not have been previously used/published.<br/>\r\n4)The entry must not contain any provocative, objectionable or inappropriate content.<br/>\r\n5)The winners have to share their consent to the use of their names in any publicity carried out by Department of Agriculture & Farmers Welfare without further compensation.<br/>\r\n6)The winners will be declared either through email or by way of announcing their names on the MyGov blog page.<br/>\r\n7)There will be no notification to participants of entries not selected as winners.<br/>\r\n8)All entries in each category will be judged based on creativity and originality by Department of Agriculture & Farmers Welfare.<br/>\r\n9)Department of Agriculture & Farmers Welfare reserves the right to reject any entry, which it does not feel is suitable or appropriate or which does not conform to any of the conditions listed above.<br/>\r\n10)All disputes/ legal complaints are subject to jurisdiction of Delhi only.<br/>\r\n11)Expenses incurred for this purpose will be borne by the parties themselves.<br/>\r\n12)Department of Agriculture & Farmers Welfare reserves the right to cancel or amend all or any part of the Contest and/or the Terms & Conditions/ Technical Parameters/ Eva