r SMS whenever it comes to you) <br/>\r\n5)Exam Duration â 45 Minutes <br/>\r\n6)No.of Questions â 30 <br/>\r\n7)Total Marks â 60 <br/>\r\n8)Negative Marking â Yes (1 Mark will be deducted for each wrong answer) <br/>\r\n<li> Syllabus<br/>\r\n1)Group 1 : 10 to 13 Years OLD<br/>\r\n-Chain Rule<br/>\r\n-PERCENTAGE<br/>\r\n-SPEED AND DISTANCE<br/>\r\n-AVERAGE<br/>\r\n-Number System<br/>\r\n-Time & Work<br/>\r\n-Profit & Loss<br/>\r\n-Time & Calendar<br/> \r\n2)Group 2 : 14 to 17 Years OLD<br/>\r\n-Comparing Quantities<br/>\r\n-AGES<br/>\r\n-TRAINS<br/>\r\n-TIME & WORK<br/>\r\n-TRUE DISCOUNT<br/>\r\n-CHAIN RULE<br/>\r\n-HCF & LCM<br/>\r\n-Profit & Loss <br/>\r\n3)Group 3 : 18 to 26 Years OLD<br/>\r\n-PROFIT & LOSS<br/>\r\n-Ratio & Proportion<br/>\r\n-SPEED & DISTANCE<br/>\r\n-Simple Interest<br/>\r\n-TIME & WORK<br/>\r\n-TRAINS<br/>\r\n-CHAIN RULE<br/>\r\n-AGES<br/>\r\n<li>Note <br/>\r\n1)Online Exam Date : 21st May 2022<br/>\r\n2)Application processing fee : Rs.290/-<br/>\r\n3)The registrations will get closed at any time once all the seats gets full irrespective of the last date of registration<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab <br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg <br/>', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 10, 26, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-03-26', '2022-04-30', 'All India Council For Technical Skill Development', 150000.00, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-11 11:51:48', 1, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-11 09:09:51', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1095, 'EfwAxqJcN0xwe1bvGq', 'Educational Based', 'Redington Scholarship for Students pursuing in Supply Chain Management Course', 'https://www.vidyasaarathi.co.in/Vidyasaarathi/login', '', '', '', '', '', 'Redington Foundation a philantropic arm of Redington (India) Ltd. has joined hands with Portal for helping students to avail scholarship as they cannot afford quality education due to high fees structure. Redington scholarship would encourage them to counter their financial constraints and pursue academic excellence and career opportunities. Please note that this scholarship would not be applicable for Redington (India) Ltd employees and their children.<br/>\r\n1) Who should apply ?<br/>\r\nStudent pursuing Supply Chain Management Course.<br/>\r\n\r\n2) Which Courses are covered under the scheme ?<br/>\r\nSupply Chain Management Course from recognized institutes of India.<br/>\r\n\r\n3) Whether compulsory to have a bank account ?<br/>\r\nYes<br/>\r\n\r\n4) Any preference to Caste religion ?<br/>\r\nNo (Open to all Students)<br/>\r\n\r\n5) Is this gender based scholarship?<br/>\r\nNo<br/>\r\n6) Any preference will be given based on the location?<br/>\r\nNo, Scholarship is for Pan India<br/>\r\n\r\n7) What is the maximum scholarship amount that will be awarded?<br/>\r\nINR 1,00,000 Total fees whichever is lower.<br/>\r\n\r\n8) What is the minimum percentage ?<br/>\r\nMinimum 60% in Class 10, Minimum 60% in Class 12, Minimum 50% in Graduation.<br/>\r\n<br/><hr>\r\n<li>Documents required<br/>\r\n1) Applicant Photo<br/>\r\n2) Proof of Identity<br/>\r\n3) Proof of Address<br/>\r\n4) Proof of Income<br/>\r\n5) Student Bank passbook /Kiosk<br/>\r\n6) Previous academic mark sheet<br/>\r\n7) Current year fees structure<br/>\r\n8) Bonafide certificate from institute<br/>\r\nAll documents uploaded shall be clear and must be in .jpeg .png file only<br/>\r\nOptional document\r\nPAN No<br/>', '', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab <br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg <br/>', '', '[\"PG-Diploma\"]', '[\"Post Graduate Diploma In Supply Chain Management\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 60.00, 60.00, 0.00, 50.00, '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', 'null', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, 'null', 600000.00, NULL, 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-03-08', '2022-04-29', '	Redington Foundation', 100000.00, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-11 13:20:27', 1, NULL, '2022-04-11 07:50:27', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1097, 'nn3wvsQPCKmbpUcQHV', 'Community Based', 'MAHADBT Post-Matric SCHOLARSHIP ', 'https://mahadbtmahait.gov.in/Login/Login', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Maharashtra government has come up with a portal through which they provide Mahadbt Scholarship to all of the students of the Maharashtra state who are not able to pay their fees because of its high rate.<br/>\r\n<li>Eligibility<br/>\r\n1) The parents/Guardian annual income shall be less than or equal to Rs. 2,50,000.<br/>\r\n2) Student category shall belong to Scheduled caste or Navbouddha.<br/>\r\n3) Student shall belong to resident of Maharashtra.<br/>\r\n4) Student should be passes SSC/equivalent Matric.<br/>\r\n5) Failure: if student fail first time then should avail Exam fees & maintenance allowance. If fails second time in same class then he/she will not get any allowance and after two drops he will pass and go to next class then he will be eligible.<br/>\r\n6) In case of student studying out of Maharashtra then same rules are applicable as per GOI.<br/>\r\n7) Only 2 professional Courses are allowed.<br/>\r\n<li>Benefits<br/>\r\nUnder this Scheme the eligible SC/ Neo Buddhist students are paid benefits as bellow.<br/>\r\n1) Maintenance Allowance is provided as per Group I, Group II, Group III, Group IV per month from date of admission to date of exam (max 10 months)<br/>\r\nDay Scholar: (Amount in Rupees per month)<br/>\r\n\r\nâ¢ Group I 550<br/>\r\nâ¢ Group II 530<br/>\r\nâ¢ Group III 300<br/>\r\nâ¢ Group IV 230<br/>\r\nHosteller (Amount in Rupees per month)<br/>\r\nâ¢ Group I 1200<br/>\r\nâ¢ Group II 820<br/>\r\nâ¢ Group III 570<br/>\r\nâ¢ Group IV 380<br/>\r\n2) Additional allowances for SC students with disabilities(Type wise disabilities) as mentioned in GR are as follows, Type of Disability Allowances(Rs per month) Remark<br/>\r\nBlindness/Low vision Grp I & II â 150/-<br/>\r\nGrp III â 125/-<br/>\r\nGrp IV â 100/- As per GR (A) of additional allowances\r\nLeprosy cured All Groups:<br/>\r\ni) Transportation Allowance upto 100/-(Students residing outside hostel campus)<br/>\r\nii) Escort Allowance 100/-<br/>\r\niii) Special Pay allowance for hostel employee as care taker. 100/- As per GR (B, C, D) of additional allowances\r\nHearing Impaired All Groups:<br/>\r\ni) Transportation Allowance up to 100/-(Students residing outside hostel campus)\r\nAs per GR (B) of additional allowances<br/>\r\nLocomotor Disability All Groups:<br/>\r\ni) Transportation Allowance up to 100/-(Students residing outside hostel campus)\r\nAs per GR (B) of additional allowances<br/>\r\nMental Retardation/ Mental Illness All Groups:<br/>\r\ni) Transportation Allowance upto 100/-(Students residing outside hostel campus)<br/>\r\nii) Escort Allowance 100/-<br/>\r\niii) Special Pay allowance for hostel employee as care taker. 100/-<br/>\r\niv) Extra Coaching allowance 150/- As per GR (B, C, D, E) of additional allowances<br/>\r\nOrthopaedic Disability All Groups:<br/>\r\ni) Transportation Allowance upto 100/-(Students residing outside hostel campus)<br/>\r\nii) Escort Allowance 100/-<br/>\r\niii) Special Pay allowance for hostel employee as care taker. 100/- As per GR (B, C, D) of additional allowances<br/>\r\n3) In addition to the maintenance allowance all mandatory fees/ compulsory payable fees i.e. (Tuition Fees, Exam Fees & other Fees) by the student to the institutes are covered under this scheme.<br/>\r\n<br/><hr>\r\n<li>Documents Required<br/>\r\nâ¢ Income Certificate(Provided by Tahesildar)<br/>\r\nâ¢ Cast Certificate<br/>\r\nâ¢ Mark sheet for last appeared examination<br/>\r\nâ¢ Mark sheet for SSC or HSC<br/>\r\nâ¢ Father date Certificate(if required)<br/>\r\nâ¢ Gap & Self Declaration(if required)<br/>\r\nâ¢ Hostel Certificate (if required)<br/>\r\nâ¢ Husband Income Certificate(if girl is married)<br/>\r\n', '', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab <br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg <br/>', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"Maharashtra\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"Hindu\"]', NULL, '[\"SC\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, 'null', 250000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-03-20', '2022-04-30', 'Government of India ', 3000.00, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-18 16:37:16', 1, NULL, '2022-04-18 11:07:16', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
