(1100, 'z0HSbWCo7hOS6BjJvF', 'Community Based', 'Post-matric Scholarship, Fee Concession and Vidyasiri-Food and Accommodation', 'https://ssp.postmatric.karnataka.gov.in/HSM_CA/', '', '', '', '', '', '<li> Category/Caste must be in the List of other Backward Classes Notified by Government of India or State Government<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> A citizen of India and a permanent resident of Karnataka<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> Students who are pursuing Matriculation Courses in Government Institutions affiliated to Non Governmental Organizations affiliated to the Statutory Universities of Karnataka<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The Gross Annual Income of the student\'s parent / guardian family should be within the limits set forth below, for the âPost-Matric Scholarshipâ, âFee Exemption and Education Rs. 2.50 Lakhs per students and Rs.1 Lack for backward class<br/> \r\n\r\n<li> A) Admission to the dormitory<br/> (ii) Meal and Residential Assistance Scheme <br/>(iii) Post-matric scholarship One of these students is eligible for only one facility, but the fee-deductible facility will be provided to all eligible students<br/>\r\n\r\nB) Facilities of Vidyasiri Scheme will be provided to Backward Classes students who do not have admission to any departmental / government aided student hostel and follow up in post-matric courses<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> (A) If attending more than one course in the same course, they are not eligible. Access to LB, etc.)<br/>\r\n\r\nB) Students attending postgraduate and medical courses are not eligible for this facility if they are pursuing a medical course during the course<br/>\r\n\r\nC) Degree / Master\'s Degree in Arts, Science and Commerce courses, Bachelor\'s or Master\'s Degree, if any of the recognized Professional or Technical Certificate Diploma Degree Courses are eligible and eligible under this scheme. Those who have changed courses more than once are not eligible<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> New Students: - Newly Applied Eligible Backward Classes Students - OT and Housing Assistance Scheme (Fee, Exemption / Post-Matric Scholarship, Programs)<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> Renewal Students: Already: Enter the application number submitted for the year 2020-21 and submit the renewal application for 2021-22<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Students must obtain Aadhaar cut-off credentials from UIDAI for obtaining all Aadhaar number<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> If there is a ration card, then mention the detail of that<br/> \r\n\r\n<li>In the case of blind students, the \"blindness certificate\" (UDID) must be uploaded<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> students have aadhaar number for their bank accounts. If the missed facility is not credited to the student, then it is the responsibility of the student to keep your bank accounts running<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> Only two sons of the same family are eligible for the scheme. But this restriction is not applicable for girls<br/>\r\n<br/><hr>\r\n<li>Documents required <br/>\r\n1)Students SATS Identification Number/College Registration Number<br/>\r\n2)Aadhaar Number Of Student And Parent<br/>\r\n3)Student\'s Mobile Number<br/>\r\n4)Enrollment Number of National Scholarship Portal(Applicable Only To Minority Students)<br/>\r\n5)Number Of Certificates(RD____)Of The Caste/Income/Economically Weaker Section(for Brahmin Students only) Starting With RD In The Students Name<br/>\r\n6)Number Of e-authenticated Documents<br/>\r\n7)Disability Card Number Issued By The Government Of India<br/>\r\n8)FRUITS Identification Number of Students Of Parents<br/>\r\n9)Student e-mail ID<br/>\r\n10)There Is No Need Of e-authentication of fee receipts For Students Studying In The Karnataka State  <br/>\r\nNote : It is mandatory to apply for National scholarship software before a minority of students apply for state scholarship software<br/>\r\nLink : https://scholarships.gov.in/fresh/PmscNewStudentRegFrm.action    <br/>', '', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab <br/>\r\n3. Fo