(1105, 'XLPgSkyJMqTsPU1jml', 'Educational Based', 'e-Medhabruti PG Merit', 'https://scholarship.odisha.gov.in/website/student-registration?state=1', '', '', '', '', '', 'Eligibility Conditions<br/>\r\n<li>The student must be a permanent resident of Odisha state.<br/>\r\n<li>The income of the parents of the student from all sources shall not exceed Rs. 600000 per annum.<br/>\r\n<li>The student must have secured a minimum of 60% marks in the previous qualifying examination for different categories of merit scholarships as mentioned against each.<br/>\r\n<li>Students shall apply for medhabruti only in the year of joining (1stYr. of the Degree course).<br/>\r\n<li>Student must have passed +3 degree or equivalent exam with 60% or more marks from a recognized institute and pursuing regular course in one of the disciplines (where scholarship is offered) in any of the recognized Colleges/Institutions/Universities.<br/>\r\n<li>Courses applicable under e-Medhabruti scholarship P.G. courses in Arts/Science/Commerce/other post graduate courses which are non professional in nature and admission to such P.G. courses is Degree in Arts/Commerce/Science. <br/>\r\n<li>Courses applicable <br/>\r\n MA(Economics, English, Geography, Hindi, History, Home Science, I.R. & P.M. , Lib. & Info. Science, Linguistic, Oriya, Philosophy, political science, Psychology, Public Administration, Sanskrit, Statistics, Analytical and Applied Economics, Anthropology, Mathematics, others ).<br/> M.Sc(Botany,  Chemistry, Physics, Zoology, Electronics Science and Technology, Marine Sciences, Geology, Biotechnology, Computer Science, Life Science, Mathematics, Remote Sensing & GIS, Wildlife & Biodiversity conversation, Microbiology, Food Science, Bioinformatics, Others).<br/>\r\n<li>The scholarship meant by P.G. shall be awarded district wise and separate selection list will be prepared for each district.<br/>\r\n<li>If any of the authenticated records are found to have invalid documents, the case will be summarily rejected.<br/>\r\n<li>Any type of wrong entries made by the students, i.e. parental income, maximum and secured mark, district name mentioned in the Resident certificate, percentage of mark which lead to  rejection of application /the student fails to be in the final merit list, then he/she is solely responsible for it.<br/>\r\n<br/><hr>\r\n<li>Documents required<br/>\r\n1. Resident certificate to be issued by the competent authority, i.e. from the concerned Tahasildar/Addl. Tahasidar. The students whos parents are working under Odisha state Govt. can produce resident proof from the employer. <br/>\r\n2. Proof  of annul income issued by the competent authority, i.e. the revenue officer not below the rank of Tahasildar or Addl. Tahasildar.<br/>\r\n3. Mark sheets of last qualifying examination as required for different categories of merit.<br/>\r\n4. Bank account details of the student concerned (First page of bank account containing account number and IFSC).<br/>\r\n5. College ID card issued by the concerned authority. While in absence of the same , the student may provide Admission receipt/ Library Card/ Letter of Undertaking from concerned college authority in which the academic session is mentioned (Any one ).<br/>\r\n6. Aadhar Card of the student concerned.  \r\n \r\n ', '', 'Steps to be followed: <br/>\r\n1. Login your Account https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab <br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg <br/>', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 60.00, '[\"Odisha\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"GM\",\"SC\",\"ST\",\"OBC\\/BC\\/OC\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 600000.00, NULL, 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-01-05', '2022-05-05', 'Government Of Odisha', 10000.00, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-04-28 15:15:13', 1, 'kavitamath@triwits.com', '2022-05-02 07:09:09', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
