(1122, 'oMu3Z2pg4lM8HsntCg', 'Talent Based', 'Design a Logo & Name for the National Coastal Clean Up Campaign', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/design-logo-name-national-coastal-clean-campaign/', '', '', '', '', '', 'India has a long coastline of 7,517 km, contributing to ecological richness, biodiversity and economy. Every year thousand tons of garbage composed of plastics, glass, metals, sanitary, clothes etc. reach the oceans and plastics contribute a major portion (~ 60%) of the total garbage that finds its pathway to the ocean every year.<br/><br/>\r\nThe International Coastal Cleanup (ICC) day is celebrated globally on the third Saturday of September every year with a common goal to collect and document the trash apart from creating awareness among the public to ensure the cleanliness of the beach.<br/><br/>\r\nAs a part of the celebration of 75 years of Indiaâs independence, a mega initiative for cleaning up of 7500 Km + coast line of country is scheduled on 17th September, 2022, jointly by Government organizations, Non-Government Organizations, private Corporates and Public participation. The purpose of said initiative is âClean Sea Coast, Safe Sea Coast, Prosperous Sea Coastâ<br/><br/>\r\nAn appropriate ânameâ and âlogoâ are invited from public for this mega initiative.<br/><br/>', '', '1. Login your Account<br/>\r\nhttps://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login<br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit:<br/>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg<br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-05', '2022-06-03', ' Coastal Clean Up Campaign', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-05-26 16:54:02', 1, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-05-26 11:25:57', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1123, 'GvuFVPsLtZ5zR7iTv9', 'Talent Based', 'Future News Worldwide Journalism Competition by the British Council\\', 'https://www.britishcouncil.org/future-news-worldwide/apply', '', '', '', '', '', 'Future News Worldwide is a partnership programme between the British Council and some of the worldâs leading media organizations; BBC, Google, Reuters, The Herald, The Quint and the UK schools of journalism. Together we identify, train and connect the next generation of global journalists.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe Future News Worldwide annual summit is a central focus of the programme, and brings together 100 young journalists each July to learn from broadcasters, editors and reporters and meet their peers around the globe. Following the conference delegates join the FNW alumni network. In 2022 the summit will be held virtually.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n1. The Competition<br/>\r\nThis is a journalism competition operated by the British Council to select delegates for the Future\r\nNews Worldwide 2020 conference, taking place 14 and 15 July 2020 in Sky Central, London (the\r\nâConferenceâ).<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n2. Territory and eligibility<br/>\r\nThe Competition is open to individuals of any nationality who meet all the criteria below:<br/>\r\nâ¢ Aged 18-25 on 1 July 2020<br/>\r\nâ¢ A registered undergraduate or postgraduate student (of any subject), enrolled at a university\r\nor higher education institution OR a recent graduate who completed their course after 1 July\r\n2018<br/>\r\nâ¢ A native speaker of English OR be able to speak English at IELTS level 6.5 or equivalent<br/>\r\nâ¢ Not have participated in a previous iteration of Future NEWS or Future News Worldwide<br/>\r\nâ¢ Dedicated to a career in journalism, in any form\r\nâ¢ Available to travel to and from the UK on any date between 11 â 16 July 2020<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nOnly one entry per person is allowed.\r\nEntry to the Competition is free of charge although participants are responsible for their own costs of\r\nconnecting to the Internet.<br/>\r\nThe Competition is not open to British Council employees or contractors (or members of their\r\nimmediate families) or anyone else professionally associated with the Competition. We reserve the\r\nright not to award the prize or to select an alternative winner if we are aware or have reasonable\r\ngrounds to believe that the winner is not eligible.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n3.If the applicant is shortlisted for a place at the online conference, we will ask for evidence of eligibility\r\nby submitting Supporting Documents (identity, age, and student or graduate status) and a reference\r\nletter. Please see the below guidance on the Supporting Documents. The applicant will have one\r\nweek to provide the supporting documents to secure your place.<br/>\r\nâ¢ Age confirmation: A copy of the applicantâs identification, e.g. passport, driving license<br/>\r\nâ¢ Student/graduate status: Student ID card OR University enrolment form, showing that\r\napplicant is a current student, OR a letter on the institutionâs headed paper stating the same\r\nOR if the applicant is a graduate, a copy of the graduation certificate showing that they\r\ncompleted a course after 1 July 2021.<br/>\r\nâ¢ Reference letter: We will require a professional reference which attests to the applicantâs skills\r\nand abilities as a journalist. This should be completed by someone who knows the applicant\r\nand is familiar with the applicantâs work. This could be: an editor or line manager; teacher or\r\nlecturer; past employer. It should NOT be a friend or family member. Where possible,\r\nreferences should be on company headed paper. There is no limit to the length of the\r\nreference letter, but we recommend that one A4 page is typically sufficient. References MUST\r\nbe in English<br/>.', '', '1. Login your Account<br/>\r\nhttps://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login<br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit:<br/>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg<br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"Bachelor Of Communication Journalism - B.C.J\"]', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-16', '2022-06-12', ' British Council\\', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-05-26 17:58:17', 1, NULL, '2022-05-26 12:28:17', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1127, '2BkR4sZSlyDW1wgPMY', 'Educational Based', 'Royal Agricultural University GREAT Scholarships 2022 A', 'https://eu-quercus.elluciancloud.com/app/rau/f?p=QL4S:LOGIN:::NO:SESSION:APP_SERVICE,APP_COURSE_INSTANCE,APP_THEME:2702005,489418565,L', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Royal Agricultural University is delighted to offer three scholarships to international students. Each scholarship is worth up to Â£10,000 towards the tuition fees for a postgraduate taught Master degree programme starting in September 2022.<br/><br/>\r\nProspective postgraduates starting from the following countries can apply for a GREAT Scholarship:\r\nThe scholarships are a joint initiative by the British Council and the UK Government, designed to attract some of the brightest  postgraduate applicants from around the world to study at UK universities. These scholarships are jointly funded by the British Council, the GREAT Britain Campaign, and the RAU. The scholarship is in the form of a tuition fees waiver.<br/><br/>\r\nThe scholarship will be made available to full-time postgraduate applicants who have obtained a conditional or unconditional offer for the following full-time taught programme at the RAU:<br/>\r\nMSc Sustainable Agriculture and Food Security<br/>\r\nPlease secure an offer for a place on the course before applying for the scholarship.<br/>\r\nThe scholarship is available for one year of study (12 months).<br/>\r\nYou are eligible to apply if you:<br/>\r\n* You hold a passport from an eligible country (from list above)<br/>\r\n* Youâre planning to study the MSc Sustainable Agriculture and Food Security that begins in September 2022<br/>\r\n* You hold a suitable Bachelorâs degree\r\n* You have a background of extracurricular activities or noteworthy experience relating to your subject area<br/>\r\nGREAT scholars should be:<br/>\r\n* Motivated and academically able to follow and benefit from the RAU postgraduate taught course\r\n* Active in the field with work experience or with 