(1160, 'bTtTX39f5dYbVosPaF', 'Talent Based', 'D-Prize Challenges', 'https://d-prize.org/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The world has already invented products and services to end poverty. Yet millions of people still donât have access. Can you design a business or NGO that solves one of the Distribution Challenges below?<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>We will award the most promising teams with up to $20,000 USD to launch a pilot version of your new organization wherever extreme poverty exists, with a goal to serve millions in the years ahead.<br/>\r\n <hr>\r\n<li>Eligibility<br/>\r\n1) D-Prize challenges are open to anyone or any teams. The sole restriction is that individuals and their immediate family on the judging panel may not participate as a contestant.<br/>\r\n2) D-Prize is also open to any business model (for profit, non-profit, and everything in between).<br/>\r\n3) All winners will be awarded up to $20,000. The award is offered in the form of a convertible grant.<br/>\r\n4) You are not competing against other applicants. We typically fund at least 15 proposals per competition, regardless of which challenge track was selected.<br/\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Who Should Apply?<br/>\r\n1) You should have enormous ambition, and can\r\nimagine yourself as a successful entrepreneur. You are ready to launch your new venture, and if a pilot proves <br/>\r\n2) successful you are excited to grow it into a world changing organization<br/>\r\n3)  If you are still a student or have existing commitments, you should have a clear idea how to transition into a full-time founder.<br/>\r\n4)D-Prize is exclusively interested in ventures that will scale distribution of an already proven poverty <br/>\r\n5)Intervention in the developing world. We do not fund prototypes of promising new interventions. Please respond to one of our distribution challenges foundation<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>If you have questions, send an email to the D-Prize <br/>\r\nTeam at help@d-prize.org. Good luck!<br/>\r\n1)  Submission deadline for early decision round: May 15, 2022 at midnight PT (Pacific Time)<br/>\r\n2)  Regular submission deadline: June 5, 2022 at midnight PT<br/>\r\n3) Extension deadline (limited to people who register): June 26, 2022 midnight PT<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n ', '', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1. Login your Account <br/>\r\n https://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login<br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: <br/>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg<br/>', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01', '2022-06-26', 'proven poverty interventions.', 1555806.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-20 15:45:32', 1, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-20 11:41:33', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
