oys-5)&(Girls-5).<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA<br/>\r\n(A) Age Criteria : 13-19 Years The applicant should be above the age of 13 yrs. & below the age of 19 yrs as on 01.06.2022.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>APPLICATIONS<br/>\r\n1) The sportsperson should submit the application online necessarily in the formats given on the website with all columns duly filled along with uploading the passport size photograph, Age Proof Certificate and Performance<br/>\r\n2)Certificate as stipulated above. Once submitted online, the candidate cannot make any changes in the submitted application.<br/>\r\n\r\n3)The website will close on 30.06.2022 at 17.15 hrs and no uploading can be made after that. No applications will be entertained by Post and e-mail.<br/>\r\n\r\n4)Acknowledgement of the On-line Application Form and Final list of selected candidates will be conveyed by e-mail and SMS on the registered mobile of the candidate.<br/>\r\n\r\n ', '', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1. Login your Account <br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: <br/>\r\n', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02', '2022-06-30', 'Indian Oil proudly announces ACERs ', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-21 15:32:35', 1, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-06-28 11:10:36', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1164, 'B4RTxsM3yCcL00S43y', 'Scholarship', 'Sanskriti - Prabha Dutt Fellowships in India, 2022', 'https://www.sanskritifoundation.org/prabha-dutt-fellowship.htm', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg/videos', 'The Fellowship is only open to women who are Indian Nationals in the age group of 25 to 40.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>It is exclusively for print journalists.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Sanskriti - Prabha Dutt Fellowships in India, 2022 is offered for Training & Short courses, Conferences & Travel Grants degree in the field of Journalism. You can apply for this scholarship here. The deadline for sending your application is? -Always Open.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This scholarship is provided by the Sanskriti Foundation and the value of this scholarship is Partial Funding, Rs. 1,00,000 + Travel expenses. This scholarship is open to applicants from India.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Scholarship value: Partial Funding, Rs. 1,00,000 + Travel expenses.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Scholarship Eligibility.</b><br>\r\n<li> The fellowship is open to Indian women.<br><br>\r\n<li> The candidates applying should be between the age group of 25 to 40.<br><br>\r\n<li> The fellowship is offered to print journalists exclusively.<br><br>\r\n<li> Applicants should publish a stipulated number of articles in established publications.<br><br>\r\n<li> The applicants can work on a monograph or a book or subsequent publication within the given time frame.<br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>The candidates are asked to submit a detailed CV in a maximum of two pages.<br>\r\n<li>A write-up should be submitted, which should explain the project in a maximum of 250 - 300 words.<br>\r\n<li>Contact details of the candidate, with any e-mail ID, are required.<br>\r\n<li>Two referees, with their names and contact addresses/telephones, should also be sent.<br>\r\n', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1) Once you are logged in, you need to update your profile by filling in all the necessary information.<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application.<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents.<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application.<br/>', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Ph.D. (Journalism And Mass Communication)\"]', '\"Print journalists\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"Female\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-01', '2022-12-31', 'Sanskriti Foundation', 100000.00, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-06-21 15:48:35', 1, NULL, '2022-10-22 10:34:29', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1165, '2YvRWd8TTbh2DxqTLg', 'Scholarship', 'NATA Business Scholarship, 2022.', 'https://nataaero.wufoo.com/forms/nata-business-scholarship/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bnbx5B-Nx8c&list=PLGF-es7U0ZzHrYPTCkF2FAADSqqlb7SSt&index=5', 'The scholarship is provided by National Air Transportation Foundation (NATF)<br>\r\n<li>The NATA Business Scholarship is to be used for continuing education for employees of NATA member companies only. <br>\r\n<li>All applicable studies shall be related to furthering the skills applicable to working at an FBO, charter company maintenance <br>facility or flight school.<br>\r\n<li>Applicable training includes any aviation maintenance program under the aegis of Part 147 or 65; any pilot certificate or rating under Part 61 <br>or 141; and any aviation-related two-year, four-year or graduate degree program at an accredited college or university.<br>\r\n <li>The value of this scholarship is INR 1,95,204.<br><br>\r\n<b>Scholarship Eligibility.</b><br>\r\n<li>The candidates applying for NATA Business Scholarship, 2022 should be at least 18 years of age.<br>\r\n<li>The applicants are required to be nominated by a representative of NATAâs Regular or Associate Member Company .<br>\r\n<li>The candidates shall commit to general aviation.<br>\r\n<li>The applicants must have a Student Pilot Certificate (or higher), and a third-class medical certificate if they are applying for pilot certificates or ratings.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>The candidates should submit two  or more recommendation letters<br>\r\n<li>A 500-word maximum essay on career goals in general aviation\r\n<li>Those in flight training should provide a progress report', '\r\n1) Once you are logged in, you need to update your profile by filling in all the necessary information.<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application.<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents.<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application.<br/>', '', '[\"Aviation\"]', '[\"\",\"D.Tech-Diploma In Aviation Hospitality And Travel Management\"]', '\"Aviation\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-01', '2022-12-30', 'National Air Transportation Foundation (NATF).', 195204.00, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-06-21 16:07:15', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-05 06:21:07', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1166, 'o5bDmogenkRzxaevJN', 'Talent Based', 'Pfizer â One Young World Scholarship', 'https://www.oneyoungworld.com/scholarships/pfizer/2022', '', '', '', '', '', 'Pfizer is one of the worldâs premier biopharmaceutical companies and is committed to the pursuit of scientific breakthroughs that create a healthier world for everyone. We recognise that it takes teamwork to create life-changing improvements for the people who need them most. Thatâs why weâre pleased to partner with One Young World for the second year and support 50 young leaders to experience in the One Young World Summit 2022.<br/>\r\n<li>One Young World, empowers and develops young leaders to build a fair, sustainable future for all. The annual Summit connects young leaders from every country and every sector to solve global challenges to build a fair and sustainable world. Every leader who attends joins the One Young World Ambassador Community, a global network of 13,700+ activists, humanitarians, world-leaders, business-leaders, thought-leaders, entrepreneurs, politicians and innovators.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>This yearâs Pfizer â One Young World Scholarship 2022 will recognise the breakthrough actions of young people who are making an impact in three key areas:\r\n\r\n* Education: Increasing access to quality STEM education for all.<br/>\r\n* Environment: Tackling climate change and conserving the worldâs resources.<br/>\r\n* Health: Improving health outcomes for all.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>What does the scholarship provide?<br/>\r\n\r\n* Digital Access to the One Young World Summit 2022 which takes place from 5 â 8 September.<br/>\r\n* Permanent membership of the One Young World Ambassador community.<br/>\r\n* Participation in unique sessions including meetings with senior Pfizer executives.<br/> \r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Eligibility Criteria<br/>\r\n\r\n* Aged 18 â 30*.<br/>\r\n* Nationals of all countries will be eligible to apply for this scholarship.<br/>\r\n* English speaking.<br/>\r\n* Internet connectivity<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Who should apply?<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>You should apply for this scholarship if:<br/>\r\n* You meet the eligiblity criteria above.<br/>\r\n* You have a proven track record for leadership by fostering innovation, teamwork, personal accountability, and a commitment for results.<br/>\r\n* You have a willingness to engage with Pfizer and demonstrate Pfizerâs comittment to improving health equity.<br/>\r\n* You are a champion of diversity and inclusion.<br/>\r\n* You are creating a positive impact in one of the scholarshipâs three focus areas (Education, Environment, Health). Examples of relevant impact include:<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\nEducation:<br/>\r\n* Developing teachers and promoting innovative practises in STEM teaching.<br/>\r\n* Creating new platforms for learners to engage with STEM education.<br/>\r\n* Making STEM education more accessible and affordable.<br/>\r\n* Driving STEM education policy.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Environment:<br/>\r\n* Reducing carbon emissions.<br/>\r\n* Reducing the negative impacts of climate change through technology, activism, community programs, policy, nature-based solutions, or * other similar efforts.<br/>\r\n* Strengthening climate change resilience.<br/>\r\n* Developing circular economy approaches.<br/>\r\n* Protecting and restoring the worldâs ecosystems.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Health:<br/>\r\n\r\n* Delivering healthcare on the frontlines.<br/>\r\n* Advocating for public policies which protect \r\nvulnerable populations and advance health equity.<br/>\r\n* Creating digital solutions to enhance access to healthcare.<br/>\r\n* Providing health education that empowers people to live healthier lives.<br/>\r\n* Pioneering breakthroughs in healthcare.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship welcomes applications from candidates from a variety of professional backgrounds including; healthcare practitioners, social entreprenuers, entrepreneurs, charity leaders, academics and community activists.\r\n\r\n ', '', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1. Login your Account <br/\r\nhttps://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: <br/>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg<br/>\r\n', '', 'null', 'null', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-28', '2022-06-30', ' One Young World Summit 2022.   ', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-21 16:18:58', 1, NULL, '2022-06-21 10:48:58', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1167, 'WrGvmI1R9d29ak4lJr', 'Scholarship', 'JNCASR Visiting Fellowship Program, India, 2022.', 'https://www.jncasr.ac.in/academic/fandeprogrammes/vfp/.', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', ' This scholarship is applicable to Ph.D. holders.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li> JNCASR Visiting Fellowship Program, India, offers fellowships to research scientists working in educational institutions and R&D laboratories in India.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li> These are provided by Jawaharlal Nehru Centre for Advanced Scientific Research.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li> The applicants for JNCASR Visiting Fellowship Program, India,  should have a Ph.D. and should be research scientists.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li> The candidates should have permanent positions in R&D laboratories or educational institutions.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li> The applicants who have already applied for this fellowship should not apply again.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li> The fellowship is for a maximum of 3 months and is tenable for 1 year from the date of the offer letter.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li> The fellowship offers the applicant an honorarium of Rs 25000 per month.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li> The fields offered by JNCASR Visiting Fellowship Program India are Atmospheric Sciences, Materials Sciences (including nanoscience), Life Sciences (including molecular and developmental biology, chronobiology, genetics, ecology, behavior, neurobiology), Engineering Sciences (including fluid dynamics, nonlinear dynamics, and thermal and chemical engineering), Physical Sciences (including experimental and theoretical condensed-matter and materials physics, statistical physics, organic electronics, and experimental nanobiotechnology), Chemical Sciences (including chemical biology, interfaces of chemical science with materials, solid-state chemistry, theoretical/computational chemistry, inorganic, physical and organic chemistry).\r\n', '<li>Faculty or engineers with a Ph.D., who have permanent positions in State or Central Universities or R&D laboratories are invited to apply.<br>\r\n<li>Individuals who have applied for or utilized this Visiting Fellowship Programme earlier, need not to apply.<br>', '1) Once you are logged in, you need to update your profile by filling in all the necessary information.<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application.<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents.<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application.<br/>', '', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"PHD (All)\"]', '\"Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 100000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-01', '2022-09-01', 'Jawaharlal Nehru Centre For Advanced Scientific Research', 75000.00, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-06-21 16:27:31', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-10 04:24:32', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1169, 'uWG6dowEaZXuO6pIgN', 'Scholarship', 'Award of DBT-Research ', ' https://ra.dbtindia.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Applications are invited from eligible candidates for the award of âDBT-Research Associateshipââ for pursuing research in frontier areas of Biotechnology and Life Sciences. The Associateship is tenable in Premier Research Institutions/Universities including non-profit R&D Institutions within India. The Associateships are awarded under the âDBT-Research Associateshipââ <br/><br/>\r\n<li>Programme supported by the Department of Biotechnology, Ministry of Science & Technology, Government of India.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Aim of Fellowship</b><br/>\r\nThe objective of the DBT-Research Associateship (DBT-RA) Programme is to train and nurture young researchers, scientists and generate a critical mass of trained manpower in modern areas of biology and biotechnology and build a robust postdoctoral base for the growth of Biotechnology sectors in the country<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b><br/>\r\n* The applicants should PhD in Science, Engineering or M.D./M.S.  in any area of medicine with research interests in Biotechnology and Life Sciences and a good academic record.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* The applicants who have already submitted the Ph.D./M.D./M.S. thesis are also eligible to apply.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* The upper age limit is 40 years for male candidates and 45 years in the case of women candidates as on the last date of application.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* The applicants should be Indian citizens, NRI or OCI card holders.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* The applicants already employed are also eligible to apply. However, they are required to upload a No Objection Certificate (NOC) from the employer during the online submission of the applications.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Tenure of Fellowship</b><br/>\r\nThe Associateship is a purely temporary assignment and is tenable for 2 years only. However, in exceptional cases, depending upon the progress of the research, the fellowship may be extended upto 4 years.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>General Guidelines of DBT-RA Programme</b><br/>\r\n* DBT-RA fellowship can be availed only ONCE by a candidate in his/her career.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* The fellowship is tenable only in India in any recognized academic institutions, national laboratories and other recognized R & D institutions. The host institution must provide administrative and infrastructural support.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* Fellows are not allowed to work with their PhD guides/co-guides.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* The fellowships cannot be availed at the same institution where the candidates have earned their Ph.D./M.D./M.S. degree.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* A mentor cannot have more than 2 DBT-RA fellows at a time.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* A mentor must hold a regular academic/research position in a recognized institution in India and should hold a PhD/MD/MS degree in science, engineering or medicine.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* Superannuated faculty (e.g., Honorary Professors, Emeritus Professors/Scientists, and DBT Distinguished Professors) could also mentor as long as they can demonstrate that resources and labs are available to them.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* Applicants from North East Region (permanent residents located in the NER) can work in any university/institution in the country.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n', 'Documents to be submitted along with the Online Application Form include </b>â<br/>\r\n1. Self-attested pdf copy of DOB certificate<br/>\r\n2. Self-attested pdf copies of degree certificates<br/>\r\n3. A Consent letter from the mentor. The format for the Consent letter is available at the DBT-RA portal.<br/>\r\n4. A NOC from the employer (if applicable)<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n* Names and contact details of the Referees are to be provided by the applicant while filling out the application form.<br/>\r\n* During submission of the online application form, an email with a link to submit a letter of recommendation shall be sent by the applicant to the email addresses of all the referees who have been mentioned in the application form.<br/>', '* Application for the DBT-RA program shall be by ONLINE mode only.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* To apply, interested applicants may kindly visit DBT-RA Online Portal https://ra.dbtindia.gov.in/<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* Applicants must register on the DBT-RA Online portal, fill in complete information in the online application form and submit it before the closing date of application i.e. 15th July 2022.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n* Online application form to be filled by applicant comprises information about Personal Information, Academic Qualifications, Research Contribution, Referee Details, Proposed Research Work, Proposed Mentor Details, and Proposed Host Institution.<br/>\r\n', 'tguj', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"PHD (All)\"]', '\"PHD\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-15', '2022-07-15', 'âDBT-Research Associateshipââ', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-21 17:00:24', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-21 09:47:59', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL);
