(1170, 'zhrZ4UZBNFXe8YUf02', 'Educational Based', 'Sanofi- Future Women in Tech Scholarship ', 'https://www.oneyoungworld.com/scholarships/sanofi/2022', '', '', '', '', '', 'Gender gaps in society remain a major barrier worldwide, impeding social advancement and hampering economic growth. With a male/female ratio of 73:27, the underrepresentation of women is particularly evident in the technology workforce.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>To address these gaps, Sanofi has committed to achieving equal representation of women and men among its senior leaders by 2025. In addition, Sanofiâs Gender Balance Board supports regional networks around the globe and sponsors initiatives to promote gender balance in the company and act as role models.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Diversity is part of Sanofiâs strategic workforce plan, which includes accelerated recruitment of female talent into Digital, Date and Technology roles. For this reason, Sanofi is pleased to partner with One Young World to offer the Future Women in Tech Scholarship. This global program will enable five women leaders to participate in the One Young World Summit 2022 as part of Sanofiâs global delegation; have a fast-tracked opportunity to join Sanofiâs early careers program and receive 1:1 mentoring to support their first career steps in Sanofi.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>What does the scholarship provide?<br/>\r\n* Delegate access to the One Young World Summit 2022 which takes place in Manchester, United Kingdom from 5 â 8 September.<br/>\r\n\r\n* Hotel accommodation in Manchester from 5 â 8 September.<br/>\r\n\r\n* Return travel to Manchester.<br/>\r\n\r\n* A fast-tracked opportunity to join Sanofiâs early careers program.<br/>\r\n\r\n* 1:1 mentorship from a Sanofi Digital mentor to support their career choices.<br/>\r\n\r\n* Membership of the One Young World Ambassador community.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Who should apply?<br/>\r\n<li>You should apply for this programme if you:<br/>\r\n* Live in one of Sanofiâs operating countries. See Elligible Countries below.<br/>\r\n* Are a woman.<br/>\r\n* English speaking.<br/>\r\n* Have an undergraduate qualification related to information technology or data received within the last five years.<br/>\r\n* Are motivated to pursue a technology focussed career with Sanofi.<br/>\r\n* Are passionate about healthcare.<br/>\r\n* Have a track record of using technology for social impact.<br/>\r\n* Have a track record of high level performance and delivery.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Careers at Sanofi<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Recipients of this scholarship will be considered to join Sanofiâs early careers program.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Sanofi is leading global healthcare company, reinvention is in their DNA and reflects their quest to make life better for patients, partners, communities, and their own people.<br/>\r\n<li>At Sanofi 145 nationalities working towards common goals, stretching the possible and growing together. When you join their team, be ready to explore new ideas and embrace new opportunities and cultures. You will be part of a flexible and inclusive workplace â based on trust and respect â so you can live your life the way you want to.<br/>', '', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1. Login your Account <br/>\r\nhttps://www.theglobalscholarship.org/student-login<br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit: <br/>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg<br/>', '', 'null', 'null', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, NULL, 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01', '2022-06-27', 'Sanofi- Future ', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-21 17:33:11', 1, NULL, '2022-06-21 12:03:11', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1171, 'PGEYm0ZPoR9KFXOxHc', 'Scholarship', 'Redington Scholarship', 'https://www.vidyasaarathi.co.in/Vidyasaarathi/scholarship', '', '', '', '', '', 'Course Level: Post Graduate/PG Diploma  (Supply Chain Management)<br/>													\r\n																							\r\n<hr>																									\r\n<li>Redington Foundation a philantropic arm of Redington (India) Ltd. has joined hand  for helping students to avail scholarship as they cannot afford quality education due to high fees structure. Redington scholarship would encourage them to counter their financial constraints and pursue academic excellence and career opportunities. Please note that this scholarship would not be applicable for Redington (India) Ltd employees and their children<br/>																									\r\n																									\r\n<hr>																									\r\n1) <b>Who should apply ?</b><br/>																									\r\nStudent pursuing Supply Chain Management Course<br/><br/>																									\r\n																									\r\n2) <b>Which Courses are covered under the scheme ?</b><br/>																									\r\nSupply Chain Management Course from recognized institutes of India<br/><br/>																									\r\n																									\r\n3) <b>Whether compulsory to have a bank account ?</b><br/>																									\r\nYes<br/><br/>																									\r\n																									\r\n4) <b>Any preference to Caste religion ?</b><br/>																									\r\nNo (Open to all Students)<br/><br/>																									\r\n																									\r\n5) <b>Is this gender based scholarship?</b><br/>																									\r\nNo<br/>	<br/>																								\r\n																									\r\n6) <b>Any preference will be given based on the location?</b><br/>																									\r\nNo, Scholarship is for Pan India<br/><br/>																									\r\n																									\r\n7) <b>What is the maximum scholarship amount that will be awarded?</b><br/>																									\r\nINR 1,00,000 Total fees whichever is lower.<br/><br/>																																																		\r\n																							\r\n																									\r\n\r\n																									\r\n																									', '1) Applicant Photo<br/>\r\n2) Proof of Identity<br/>																									\r\n3) Proof of Address<br/>																									\r\n4) Proof of Income<br/>																									\r\n5) Student Bank passbook /Kiosk<br/>																									\r\n6) Previous academic mark sheet<br/>																									\r\n7) Current year fees structure<br/>																									\r\n8) Bonafide certificate from institute<br/>	<br/>																								\r\nAll documents uploaded shall be clear and must be in .jpeg .png file only<br/>		', '1) Once you are logged in, you need to update your profile by filling in all the necessary information.<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application<br/>', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Masters (All)\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 600000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-08', '2022-07-29', 'Redington Foundation a philantropic arm of Redington (India) Ltd', 100000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-23 15:22:36', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-07-19 08:00:32', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1172, 'kNlenIj5qWpCqBvYt8', 'Competitions and Awards', 'PhonePe SET Hiring Challenge', 'https://assessment.hackerearth.com/challenges/hiring/phonepe-hiring-challenge/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Objective: To build a strong team of SET(Automation).<br/>\r\n<li>This challenge will test individuals on Problem Solving related to Algorithms and Data Structures. One coding question will be of Easy complexity. The Medium question will include bonus weightage. Goal of this challenge is to understand the individualâs technical depth, as well as problem-solving ability.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>Eligibility Criteria:<br/>\r\n* Years of experience: 0-3 years, and 3-7 years<br/>\r\n\r\n* Skills: Data Structures, UI Automation/API Automation, CICD, Performance Testing<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Challenge Format:<br/>\r\n\r\n* 2 Programming Questions (any language)<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li> Recruitment process<br/>\r\nShortlisted candidates will be interviewed by the PhonePe team. Technical interviews will focus on problem solving, automation and functional testing.<br/>\r\n\r\n ', '<li><b>Documents Required:</b><br>\r\n1) Skills: Data Structures, UI Automation/API Automation, CICD, Performance Testing<br/>\r\n2) Programming Questions (any language)<br/>\r\n', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1. Login your Account<br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit:<br/>\r\n', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-24', '2022-07-03', 'Hiring Challenge', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-24 17:51:31', 1, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-07-04 10:33:32', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1173, '7zPweVYiO4zyqK91wh', 'Scholarship', 'Post Matric Scholarship 2022.', 'http://socialjustice.nic.in/SchemeList/Send/25?mid=24541', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', '<b>Note:</b><br> \r\nThis SC Scholarship will be funded by the Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment. The central government will pay tuition fees and  non-refundable charges directly to the institution via DBT, and other expenses will be paid straight into the studentâs bank account via DBT.<br><hr>\r\n\r\n<li>The objective of this scholarship is to award scholarships to meritorious students belonging to economically weaker sections of minority communities to provide them with better opportunities for higher education and great career prospects. Here is a list of some scholarship programs under this scholarship scheme offered by different institutions and organizations:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The Ministry of Minority Affairs, Government of India launched the Post Matric Scholarship which is a centrally sponsored scheme implemented through the state government and UT administration. It is provided to those Indian students who want to pursue higher education but need financial assistance. Students applying for secondary education, undergraduate, postgraduate, and masterâs degree programs in Indian government colleges can avail of this scholarship. The scholarship is offered by various state governments and educational organizations to provide financial support to those aspiring to study in Indian academic institutions.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Post Matric Scholarship Amount.</b><br>\r\n<li>Full-Tuition Fees (including non-refundable charges): INR 2 Lakhs per annum for students studying in private sector institutions and INR 3.72 Lakhs per annum for private sector flying club.<br>\r\n<li>Living Expenses: INR 3,000 per month per student.<br><br>\r\n<li>Books and Stationary: INR 5,000 per annum per student.<br><br>\r\n<li>For Computer/Laptop: INR 4,500 one time assistance.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Important Provisions Under Post Matric Scholarship.</b><br>\r\n<li>All institutions must include the SC Post Matric Scholarship 2022 in their prospectus.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The central government is planning to operate entirely online.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This online platform will check for eligibility, caste status, Aadhaar verification, and timely delivery of support.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Students can apply for scholarships through the National Scholarship Portal.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The applications will be verified by the institutes on the NSP portal.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>All institutions must adhere to the number of slots allotted to them.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The new members will be chosen based on their performance in the admission exams.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Before sending it to the ministry, the institution should double-check all of the facts.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>In the first year, students must purchase a computer or laptop.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>When applying for the award, students must produce a bill of purchase.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>If any institution is found to violate the schemeâs provisions, it will be denotified.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>If an institution de-notifies, the scholarship will be available to SC students who have already been admitted under this scheme until the end of the term.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Scholarship Eligibility.</b><br>\r\n\r\nBefore applying your application for this scholarship, you are required to fulfill certain essentials to be deemed eligible by the specific institution. Here are the major eligibility criteria you need to keep in mind:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship is only applicable to citizens of India.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This is a scholarship program that aids the minority section of society. Thus, students belonging to minority communities, i.e. Muslim, Sikh, Buddhist, Jain, Parsi are eligible to apply for the scholarship program.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Students who have secured an aggregate of 50% in the previous examinations can apply for the scholarship.<br><br> \r\n\r\n<li>The annual household income of studentsâ parents/ guardians can not exceed INR 8 Lakh.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Candidates are required to have a bank account by their name in a nationalized bank.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Caste Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Identity Proof.<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar Card.<br>\r\n<li>Income Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bank Details.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate Photographs.<br>\r\n<li>Ration Card.<br>\r\n<li>Age Proof.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate mobile number.<br>', '1. Visit the official website.<br>\r\n2. Tap on the new registration option.<br>\r\n3. Tick the declaration after reading all the rules and regulations.<br>\r\n4. Click on continue.<br>\r\n5. A new form will appear before you.<br>\r\n6. Add all your credentials such as name, DOB, mobile number, gender, etc.<br>\r\n7. Tap on the register.<br>\r\n8. Now, log in from your Student ID.<br>\r\n9. Tap on the application form icon.<br>\r\n10. Select the scholarship category.<br>\r\n11. Enter the information on the form such as name, DOB, Fatherâs name, Aadhar Card Number, Mobile no., etc.<br>\r\n12. After filling up, tap on save and continue.<br>\r\n13. Upload all the required documents.<br>\r\n14. Click on final submission.<br>', '', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Class 11, Class 12\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 800000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-01', '2022-12-31', 'Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment(central government).', 372000.00, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-06-28 16:16:31', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-10 04:48:01', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1174, 'Z9T8qLZkn7on2UZRyn', 'Scholarship', 'SDF Vidyadhan Scholarship                                        ', 'https://www.vidyadhan.org/apply', '', '', '', '', '', 'The students are selected after completion of 10th grade/SSLC through a rigorous selection process. Those selected will be eligible for a two-year scholarship from the Foundation. Applications are invited for scholarships in Intermediate education. vidyadhan has announced that it is inviting applications for Scholarships from talented and financially disadvantaged students.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Scholarship amount in SDF Vidyadhan Scholarship 2022: The scholarship amount for graduation courses varies from Rs 10,000 to Rs 60,000 per year depending on the course and duration. The selected students will be required to attend the mentoring programs from the Foundation.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<li><b>Eligibility<br/></b>\r\nStudents whose family annual income is less than Rs. 2 Lakh and who have completed their 10th grade/SSC exam in the year 2022 from <b>Andhra Pradesh</b>. They should also have scored 90% or obtained 9 CGPA in their 10th Grade/SSC examination. The cut-off mark for students with disability is 75%. Please select the correct program Andhra Intermediate 1st year when you apply.<br/>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<li><b>Selection Process<br/></b>\r\nSDF will shortlist the applicants based on their academic performance and the information provided in the application form. The shortlisted candidates will be invited for a short test/interview. The exact locations for the test and interview will be informed to the shortlisted students individually. SDF will reimburse the out-of-district travel expense of the student and a parent for eligible cases.<br/>\r\n', '10th Marksheet   (If original marksheet is not available you can upload provisional /online marksheet from the SSLC/CBSE/ICSC website)<br/>\r\n<li>Income Certificate   (from a competent authority; ration card not accepted; this is mandatory at the time of interview only)<br/>\r\n<li>Photograph<br/>\r\n<li>Disability Certificate   (for those applying in disability category)<br/>', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1. Login your Account<br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit:<br/>', '', '[\"Class 11-PUC 1\"]', '[\"Class 11 - PUC 1\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01', '2022-07-10', 'Sarojini Damodaran Foundation', 10000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-28 16:27:57', 1, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-07-06 09:57:14', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1175, '6vRhQVvpohjFo0OEo7', 'Educational Based', 'Indraprastha Institute of Information Technology IIIT-Delhi Teaching Fellow Positions.', 'https://iiitd.ac.in/careers/tfpositions', '', '', '', '', '', '<b>Description :</b><br>\r\n1) Works as a co-instructor for undergraduate courses (normally 2 per semester), which involves taking tutorials and labs, helping students, managing teaching assistants (TA) of the courses, preparing/conducting/grading exams and tests etc., as well as course administration. The Fellow may also be the primary instructor for short duration as desired by the course instructor or for the summer modules.<br>\r\n<li>An applicant must have M.Tech degree from a reputed Institute/University in ECE/ Electronics/ CSE.<br>\r\n<li>Should have good programming skills (C, Python, Matlab etc.) and a good academic record throughout.<br>\r\n<li>Preference will be given to candidates with TA experience.<br>\r\n<li>It is best suited for those who are looking for teaching careers.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n2) <b>Desirable Skills:</b><br>\r\n<li>PhD in relevant discipline.<br>\r\n<li>Basic knowledge of EDA tools like Virtuoso, Vivado etc, and experience in hardware,Embedded systems etc. will be an advantage.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n3) <b>Compensation & Terms</b><br>\r\n<li>The term of appointment will be for one year, which can be renewed after the first year based on performance. No extension will be given after two years.<br>\r\n<li>The compensation in the first year will be Rs 45,000/- per month with free hostel accommodation or Rs. 50,000 per month without hostel accommodation. In the second year, Rs. 50,000/- per month with free hostel accommodation or Rs. 55,000/- per month without hostel accommodation.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>The Institute gives top priority to the ongoing academic activities and does not promote leaving the offered position during an ongoing semester. To ensure this, a monthly deposit of Rs. 22,500/- from the salary of the first two months will be kept with the institute. This deposit will be paid on completion of the offered tenure.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n4) <b>Duties and responsibilities.</b><br>\r\n<li>To teach tutorials, manage tutorials and other tutors/teaching assistants.<br>\r\n<li>To manage course related labs and inventory required during the semester and performing the experiments.<br>\r\n<li>To conduct extra classes on the topics where students are facing difficulties.<br>\r\n<li>To conduct regular lectures, when the instructor is on leave.<br>\r\n<li>Maintaining office hours to clarify course related doubts.<br>\r\n<li>To assist professor in making learning materials, assignments, answer keys and rubric for grading.<br>\r\n<li>To assist professor in preparing exam question papers / lab exam practical questions and conducting quizzes, mid-semester exam and final exams.<br>\r\n<li>To assist professor in final semester grading, paper checking.<br>\r\n<li>To mentor and guide students in class-course projects, Assigning the rubric and grading the progress throughout the semester.<br>\r\n<li>To conduct refresher modules for M.Tech/BTech students in summer.<br>\r\n<li>To provide extra technical support to weak students.<br>\r\n<li>Providing support to lab engineers for smooth conduct of course labs.<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n5) <b>How to apply : </b><br>https://iiitd.ac.in/careers/tfpositions<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 'Steps to be followed:<br>\r\n1. Login your Account<br>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit:<br>', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Master Of Engineering \\/ Master Of Technology - M.E.\\/ M.Tech\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, NULL, 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-01-01', '2022-07-03', 'IIIT-Delhi Teaching Fellow Positions.', 5000.00, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-06-28 17:26:14', 1, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-06-28 12:21:04', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1176, 'SZByIlHZXg8g4bxW3S', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Youth Excel Photo Contest', 'https://www.scholarshipsinindia.com/awards/youth-excel-photo-contest.html', '', '', '', '', '', 'Are you a young changemaker between 15-35 years old? Do you have photography skills? Do you want to showcase your photography skills to the world?<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>THEMES (AROUND YOUTH EXCEL ACTIVITIES):</b><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Youth mental health and wellness: Photos that represent how your community is working towards supporting youth mental health<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Youth at the forefront of economic development: Photos that represent how youth in your community are engaged in creating employment/employability for fellow youth<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Youth and decision-makers at work: Photos showcasing youth in your community working with diverse stakeholders to create locally-led community solutions<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Youth driving decisions through data: Photos that highlight trends or instances of youth in your community using research and data to solve local issues<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Gender and Inclusion: Photos showing marginalized youth (youth with disabilities, young women and girls, religious minorities, LGBTQI+, Indigenous youth, minority ethnicities etc.) positively participating in community development<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>TERMS AND CONDITIONS:</b><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Eligibility: Youth (15-35 years old) from Africa, Asia, Europe and Eurasia, Latin America and the Caribbean, and the Middle East and North Africa.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Photos must be an original submission. The submitter must own the rights to the photo (i.e. the photo needs to be submitted by the photographer or with permission from the photographer and have permission to use all identifiable people, buildings, objects, etc.)<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Applicants have a limited five photos per entry. Multiple entries are allowed.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Each image submitted must focus on a particular theme of the competition.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Photos can be taken with a camera or mobile phone.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Photos should be submitted in JPEG format with a minimum 1MB file size.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Tell us about your photo by including a brief description explaining the context of the photo, and where and when it was taken.<br/>\r\n<li>Winning photos will be added to Youth Excelâs stock photos and used in future communications material.<br/>\r\n<li>By submitting an entry, all participants agree that their images may be used by the Youth Excel program including IREX, consortium partners, and USAID in future communications material. Proper photo credit will be given to photographers of selected images.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>COPYRIGHTS:</b><br/>\r\nParticipation in the Youth Excelâs photo contest authorizes IREX, USAID, and the Youth Excel program to use winning images on the IREX website and other communication channels for IREX and Youth Excel such as social media, and publications, collateral, and more. Other entries may also be used by the Youth Excel program and USAID.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>SUBMISSION PROCESS:</b><br/>\r\nParticipants can submit multiple entries reflecting one or more of the five themes above. Participants can submit entries using this form.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>WINNING ENTRIES WILL BE FEATURED IN:</b><br/>\r\nâ¢ Youth Excel Summer Showcase in August 2022.<br/>\r\nâ¢ Youth Excel social media platforms.<br/>\r\nâ¢ Youth Excel external newsletter<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li><b>First place winner from each theme will receive a special prize valued at USD $200- $300.</b><br/>\r\n\r\n ', 'DO NOT submit photos with watermarks, overlays, or signatures.<br/>\r\n<li>Youth (15-35 years old) from Africa, Asia, Europe and Eurasia, Latin America and the Caribbean, and the Middle East and North Africa.<br/>\r\n<li>Each image submitted must focus on a particular theme of the competition.<br/>', 'Steps to be followed:<br/>\r\n1. Login your Account<br/>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab<br/>\r\n3. For Detailed apply process visit our YouTUbe channel', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-06', '2022-07-17', 'Youth Excel ', 23702.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-06-30 15:36:23', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-07-06 09:33:33', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
