(1181, '0uYbymN6w5PGrQGeGm', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Selfie Competition using the Indian National Flag', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/selfie-competition-using-indian-national-flag/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Government e marketplace (GeM) was launched in 2016 by the Hon\'ble Prime Minister Shri Narendra Modi with a vision to redefine the procurement system, bringing efficiency, transparency, and inclusivity. It is a one-stop shop for different goods & services procured by Government Organizations / Departments / PSUs. The vision was to have a centralized, unithe fied public procurement that has increased coverage, access, and efficiency of the public procurement in the country. To learn more about GeM click here- <a href=\"https://gem.gov.in/\" target=\"_blank\">https://gem.gov.in/</a><br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>To commemorate 75 years of independence and the glorious history of its people, culture, and achievements, Government of India marked an initiative of AZADI KA AMRIT MAHOTSAV. Under this, the initiative of âHar Ghar Tirangaâ is marked to invoke the feeling of patriotism in the hearts of the people of India and promote awareness about our National Flag<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>To commemorate 75 years of independence and the glorious history of its people, culture, and achievements, the Government of India marked an initiative of AZADI KA AMRIT MAHOTSAV. Under this, the initiative of âHar Ghar Tirangaâ is marked to invoke the feeling of patriotism in the hearts of the people of India and promote awareness about our National Flag. <br/><br>\r\n\r\n<li>To extend this initiative & celebration of nationalism and patriotism across India, a pan India âSelfie Competition using the Indian National Flagâ is being organized by GeM and hosted on MyGov to encourage and invite citizens to click their selfie images to showcase and promote the importance of the national flag across the country<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This competition is open to all Indian nationals registered with My