(1191, 'IXLZQfDRK4QEgz7LnH', 'Abroad', 'Postgraduate Conversion Courses in AI and Data Science Scholarships.', 'https://www.sussex.ac.uk/study/fees-funding/masters-scholarships/artificial-intelligence-and-data-science-apply', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'This scholarship is based on Merit.<br><br>\r\n  <li> This scholarship is applicable for the following \r\n         courses in University of Essex in UK.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  The Data Science and AI Scholarship is available \r\n           to  new Home, EU and International Postgraduate \r\n          Taught (PGT) Masters students taking up a \r\n          place to study in academic year 2022-23 on \r\n          some specific programmmes.<br>\r\n     1. MSc Data Science & Applications.<br>\r\n      2. MSc Applied Data Science.<br>\r\n    3. MSc Artificial Intelligence & Applications.<br><br>\r\n      <li>  The scholarship comprises of a Â£10,000(INR \r\n               7,89,960) award to be used on one, or a \r\n               combination of the following:-<br>    \r\n       1. Course tuition fee payment/course tuition \r\n              fee discount and any remaining balance as \r\n              stipend.<br>\r\n     2. Course stipend.<br><br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Scholarship Eligibility.</b><br><br>\r\n  <li>  Preference will be given to applicants who meet \r\n          one, or a combination of the following:<br>\r\n  (a)  Female applicants.<br>\r\n  (b)  Disabled applicants.<br>\r\n  (c)  Black applicants, specifically:<br>\r\n  (d)  Black or Black British â Caribbean.<br>\r\n  (e)  Black of Black British â African.<br>\r\n  (f)  Other Black background.<br>\r\n  (g)  Mixed â White and Black Caribbean.<br>\r\n  (h)  Mixed â White and Black African.<br><br>\r\n\r\n  <li>  No specific eligibility requirement mentioned on \r\n          the Scholarship site, student profile will be \r\n          evaluated on a case by case basis.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Students must hold an offer of admission onto \r\n          the full-time or part-time conversion \r\n          programmes in Data Science and AI \r\n          commencing in October 2022.   The offer can be \r\n          unconditional or conditional.<br><br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Application Process for this scholarship.</b><br><br>\r\n  <li>  Official transcript(s), in English or a certified \r\n          translation of your academic results to date, \r\n          showing marks or grades, must be provided at \r\n          the time students make their applications.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Proof of English language proficiency.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Copies of certificates for any degrees or other \r\n          awards already completed.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Personal statement (no more than 500 words), \r\n          including the following.<br><br>\r\n      (a)  Your personal statement needs to show why \r\n              you want to study at the University of Essex. \r\n              Clear connections between your most recent \r\n              study and experience with your chosen Masters \r\n              courses are essential and you should provide a \r\n              commentary on reasons for your choice. You \r\n              should also demonstrate how postgraduate \r\n              study will build on your current level of learning\r\n	      One academic reference will be required.<br><br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Application Process:</b>.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Meet the eligibility criteria as outlined in the \r\n         section above.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Have received an offer to study on relevant PGT \r\n          programme.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Have submitted your application for the \r\n          Postgraduate Conversion Courses in AI and Data \r\n          Science Scholarship by the published deadline.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Apply for the Scholarship using the application \r\n          form. This is separate to the application for study, \r\n          and instructions on returning the form and what \r\n          information applicants need to provide are \r\n           included in the document.<br><br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Additional Information.</b><br><br>\r\n  <li>  Successful candidates will know the outcome by \r\n          Friday 5 August for October 2022 start.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Applicants must be home (UK), and overseas \r\n          students who are entirely self-funded. It is not \r\n          available to students who are fully or partly \r\n          sponsored.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Receipt of the scholarship is subject to applicants \r\n          firmly accepting the offer of study, registering as \r\n          students of the University of Essex for the 2022-23 \r\n          academic year, and meeting all conditions of our \r\n          offer.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  This scholarship does not apply to deferred entry. \r\n           Where a student, to whom a scholarship has \r\n           been offered, requests deferred entry, the award \r\n           will be considered again in line with the terms \r\n           and conditions that apply in the new proposed \r\n           year of entry.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Only one scholarship award can be made per \r\n          student and the award cannot normally be held \r\n          in conjunction with other University of Essex \r\n          awards, including Alumni Loyalty Discount; where \r\n          a student applies for and is awarded a \r\n          scholarship and subsequently obtains full \r\n          external funding, the University will rescind the \r\n          scholarship offer.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  \r\n         \r\n         \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', ' <li>Official transcript(s), in English or a certified \r\n          translation of your academic results to date, \r\n          showing marks or grades, must be provided at \r\n          the time students make their applications.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Proof of English language proficiency.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Copies of certificates for any degrees or other \r\n          awards already completed.<br><br>\r\n  <li>  Personal statement (no more than 500 words), \r\n          including the following.<br><br>', '1. Log in to your Account.<br>\r\n2. Go to Notified Scholarships tab.<br>\r\n3. For a Detailed application process visit our Youtube channel\r\n ', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Master Of Computer Applications - M.C.A\",\"Master Of Engineering \\/ Master Of Technology - M.E.\\/ M.Tech\",\"Master Of Computer Applications - M.C.A\"]', '\"MSc (Data Science & Applications, Applied Data Science, Artificial Intelligence & Applications)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-01', '2022-09-30', 'University of Essex.', 789960.00, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-07-01 17:57:20', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-12 07:31:08', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1193, '9Bgjecca7k0ZQWZ9yA', 'Competitions and Awards', 'OnePlus Photography Awards 2022', 'https://www.oneplus.in/photography-awards-2022', '', '', '', '', '', 'Main Category winners<br/>\r\nGold Prize 5K USD *1*3<br/>\r\nSilver Prize 2K USD *1*3<br/>\r\nBronze Prize 1K USD*1*3<br/>\r\n<li>The winner will win the title of \"OnePlus Photography Ambassador\" and have the opportunity to work with OnePlus in the future.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The exchange rate will be based on the data of the Bank of China on Oct. 14th, 2022.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>Note:</b>\r\n âOnePlus Photography Expertâ will be selected from the winners of the Official Website Group and the Social Media Group, and the winner can receive both prizes.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Who is eligible to participate in the OnePlus Photography Awards 2022?</b><br/>\r\nSmartphone users worldwide who have full capacity for civil conduct as stipulated by laws and regulations in the country or region where they live. The works that have won awards in other photography contests or have been published in any public journals are unaccepted in the Awards.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>Competition categories: 3 Main Categories</b><br/>\r\n<li>The Moment: Capture special and memorable moments.<br/>\r\n<li>The People: Capture the images of special people around you.<br/>\r\n<li>The Land: Record the unlimited scenery of your city.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>Do I have to shoot my works by using a OnePlus smartphone?</b><br/>\r\nAll the entries in the OnePlus Photography Awards 2022 shall be shot using smartphones, but it is not mandatory to use OnePlus smartphones, without any limit to the photography time and the brand and model of the smartphone.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>What are the specifications for the entries?</b><br/>\r\n<li>The entries are only expected to be processed on smartphones (the third-party software installed on the smartphone is acceptable as well).<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The entries are only in JPG format. The short side of each photo shall be no less than 1000 pixels and the size of a single photo shall be no more than 20 megabytes.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>Is there any upper limit to the number of my entries?</b><br/>\r\n<li>You can join all 3 categories.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Official Website: you can submit up to 6 entries in each category.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Social Media Group: in each category, there is no limit to the number of entries.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>What should I do if my entries fail to be uploaded?</b></br>\r\nYou can submit your entries on social media if you have any problems with uploading the entries on the official website.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>Could I put my entries in more than one category?</b></br>\r\nYes, you can. The same entry can be submitted to different categories repeatedly, but it cannot be awarded repeatedly.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<b>Jury & Judging Criteria</b><br/>\r\n<li>Jury: OnePlus Photography Awards 2022 will continue to collaborate with IPA. Therefore, all professional judges from the jury will come from the IPA Jury pool.<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Judging Criteria: The jury will first choose the gold, silver, and bronze winners from each of the three categories. Then, they will choose one âPhoto of the Yearâ<br/>', '1. The Photographs are original and that they own the rights to their Photographs,<br/>\r\n\r\n2. The Photographs do not violate the rights of any third party,<br/>\r\n\r\n3. The Photographs do not convey a false or misleading impression,<br/>\r\n\r\n4. Any additional information they submit about the Photographs is accurate.<br/>\r\n\r\n5. The photos submitted by the contestant should be the initial submission. That is, this work (including but not limited to the original version, the edited derivative work and etc..) shall not be used before to participate in any photography-related public or non-public competitions, events and/or exhibitions.<br/>', '1. Method 1: Contestants can submit their entries through the official website of the OnePlus Photography Awards 2022 at <br/>\r\nhttps://www.oneplus.com/photography-awards-2022. The title of the corresponding entry (within 10 words) and the story of the entry (within 50 words) must be provided.<br/></br>\r\n\r\n2. Method 2: Contestants can post their entries on social media and use the hashtag #OnePlusPhotoAwards or #ShotonOnePlus to participate in the Awards. If you submit your entries on social media, you need to indicate the competition category, the title of the entries (10 words or less), and the description of the entries (50 words or less). Please send each entry separately, one post corresponds to one photo and accompanying text.<br/>\r\n\r\n', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-06', '2022-07-07', ' OnePlus Photography ', 394754.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-07-02 17:50:52', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-07-06 08:20:47', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1196, 'jTRXB1CS3TEEE3GO32', 'Scholarship', 'M.K.Bhan Young Researcher Fellowship Programme ', 'https://dbtindia.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The applicant should be Indian National and possess a Ph.D. in any branch of Life Sciences/ Biotechnology/allied areas.<br/><br/>\r\n<li> Applicant should not be holding a permanent position in any institute/university.<br/><br/>\r\n<li>Each applicant must identify a host institute and a mentor.<br/><br/>\r\n<li>The upper age limit will be 35 years as on the closing date of the submission of the application<br/><br/>\r\n<li>Applicants cannot have more than one fellowship at a given point of time.<br/><br/>\r\n<li>The fellowship is co-terminus with the project duration\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<b> Aim of Fellowship</b><br/>\r\n<li>To provide attractive opportunities to young researchers for developing them as independent investigators.<br/><br/>\r\n<li>This will enable young researchers to pursue their research interests within the country and develop a critical mass of trained scientists for the countryâs research institutions, universities, and major new initiative.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Duration & Number of Fellowship</b><br/>\r\n<li>Upto 50 fellowships will be provided each year. The fellowship duration will be for a maximum period of three years; in exceptional cases, the duration could be extended by another two years on a fresh appraisal.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The Beneficiary will receive  Rs. 75,000 per month for 3 years', 'Proof for date of birth.<br/>\r\n<li>Masterâs degree, and PhD Certificate.<br/>\r\n<li>One copy of each publication listed in columns 13 and 14 of the application form<br/>\r\n<li>One copy of recognition/award details mentioned in column 16 of application form<br/>\r\n<li>Consent form from mentor (as case may be) and host institute<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1. Application in the prescribed proforma should be submitted mandatorily online through the DBT portal (epromis)<a href=\"http://www.dbtepromis.nic.in/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.dbtepromis.nic.in/</a>\r\n on or  before July 25th<br/>\r\n2. Visit the official website,By clicking the above link <br/>\r\n3. It is an offline scholarship so download the form and fill in all the details <br/>\r\n4. Attach the photocopy of documents required ( ID proof mark sheet, Publications) <br/>\r\n5. Mail all the documents to the Address\r\n6. One hard copy of application along with requisite documents should be also be sent to<br/>\r\n<b>Dr Deo Prakash Chaturvedi,</b> <br/>\r\nscientist-c Department of Biotechnology <br/>\r\nMinistry of science technology <br/>\r\nRoom no 814, 8th floor , Block -2 CGO Complex <br/>\r\nLodi Road New Dehli -110003<br/>', '', '[\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"Masters (All)\",\"PHD (All)\"]', '', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-07', '2022-07-15', ' M K BHAN â YOUNG RESEARCHER FELLOWSHIP', 75000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-07-04 17:09:30', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-07-13 06:31:33', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1197, 'Iae6ZYuk8CucxJXjT1', 'Internship', 'Sahakar Mitra', 'http://sip.ncdc.in/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', '<b>NOTE:</b> This Internship is applicable for \r\n                                         Master\'s like MBA AgriBusiness / \r\n                                         MBA Coop / M.Com / MCA /MBA \r\n                                         Finance / MBA International \r\n                                         Trade / MBA Forestry/MBA Rural \r\n                                         Dev / MBA Project Management.<br><br>\r\n<li> This Internship provides Stipend up to  Rs \r\n       <b>11,250/month</b>.<br><br>\r\n<li>  Location: <b>Delhi.</b><br><br>\r\n<li>  To provide a deep immersion opportunity to \r\n        professional graduates on the role, contribution, \r\n        and impact of NCDC and also cooperatives.<br><br>\r\n<li>  To enable the professional graduates, to learn the \r\n        context and practical working of NCDC and \r\n        cooperatives.<br><br>\r\n<li>  To orient professional graduates to the \r\n         cooperative business model and engage \r\n          themselves in start-up cooperatives.<br><br>\r\n<li>  To enable professional graduates take up \r\n         leadership and /or entrepreneur roles in FPO \r\n         organized under Cooperative Acts.<br><br>\r\n<li>  To assist needy cooperatives in preparation of \r\n         business plans and projects.<br><br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Process of  Selection:</b><br><br>\r\n<li>  The internship period shall not exceed four months \r\n         for a person. A person cannot be taken as an \r\n         intern more than once.<br><br>\r\n<li>  The recommendation can be done by the Head of \r\n        the Department of the UGC / AICTE / ICAR \r\n        recognized Universities / Institutions as applicable, \r\n        to the Regional Director NCDC or Chief Director \r\n        LINAC or Head of HR Division in HO of NCDC. Online \r\n        application only shall be received. The portal is \r\n        <a href=\"http://sip.ncdc.in/\" target=\"_blank\">http://sip.ncdc.in/</a><br><br>\r\n<li>	Prospective interns will be shortlisted by \r\n        committees, as may be prescribed by MD from \r\n        time to time, on the basis of screening of their bio- \r\n        data and recommendations of the sponsoring \r\n         institutions.<br><br>\r\n<li>	Placement of interns will be made at HO / LINAC / \r\n        ROs depending upon the preference of the interns \r\n        and the requirements of NCDC.<br><br>\r\n<li>	The intern will be supervised by an officer \r\n        designated as a âMentorâ for the purpose of \r\n        providing orientation, guidance, and special \r\n        assignment, and other SIP-related activities.<br><br>\r\n<li>	In the case of interns at RO, he /she would be \r\n        expected to focus on a co-operative and prepare a \r\n        business plan/project report on the expansion of \r\n        business of the cooperative society. The intern will \r\n         submit a written report, within two weeks of \r\n         completion of his / her internship, giving \r\n         a detailed description of the work completed. He/ \r\n         she will highlight the experience gained and how \r\n         he/she plans to use it further.<br><br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<li>The business plan/project report / detailed report \r\n      submitted by the intern will be the property of NCDC \r\n      and the intern would have no claim on its use in any \r\n       manner.<br><br>\r\n<li>Findings of the study, research, and analysis by the \r\n      the intern shall not be used for publication by the intern.<br><br>\r\n<li>There shall be no liability, whatsoever, on NCDC on \r\n      account of action or inaction or on findings of the \r\n      business plan/project report / detailed report \r\n      submitted by the intern or action taken by him/ her \r\n      during SIP.<br><br>\r\n', '<li>Candidates are required to a