(1199, 'St2x2ZdUVgIBWjUfqz', 'Abroad', 'Muhammad Bin Zaid University Scholarships 2023.', 'https://crmweb-100902.campusnexus.cloud/OnlineApplication', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', '  Muhammad Bin Zaid University Scholarship 2023-2024 \r\n  is a fully-funded scholarship for international students. \r\n  This scholarship is offered for master\'s and doctoral \r\n  studies. The MBZUAI scholarship offers a 100% tuition \r\n  fee waiver, monthly stipend, accommodation, and \r\n  many more benefits.</br></br>\r\n\r\n<li>  MBZUAI offers an array of graduate programs \r\n       designed for the pursuit of advanced specialized \r\n       knowledge and skills in artificial intelligence. it \r\n       dedicated faculty and staff provide \r\n       encouragement and guidance to enable you to \r\n        make the right   choices.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Courses Offered:</b><br>\r\n<li>Computer Science<br>\r\n<li>Electrical Engineering<br>\r\n<li>Computer Engineering<br>\r\n<li>Mathematics<br>\r\n<li>Physics<br>\r\n<li>Other relevant Engineering majors<br><hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Scholarship Coverage</b> <br></br>\r\n  <li> 100% Tuition Fee Waiver.<br></br>\r\n  <li> A monthly allowance will be provided to all \r\n          admitted students during their study period at \r\n          MBZUAI. However, in order to maintain their \r\n          scholarships, stipends, and other benefits, \r\n          students are expected to maintain high \r\n          academic standing, comply with the University \r\n          code of  conduct and fulfill certain requirements \r\n          during their study tenure.<br><br>         \r\n  <li> All students are given housing accommodation in \r\n         the Masdar City campus. They will be provided \r\n        with   accommodation containing en-suite \r\n          facilities,  kitchen and living area with TV and \r\n           internet connection. Facilities on campus for all \r\n           students  include a gym, multi-purpose areas for \r\n          sports activities, restaurants, coffee shops, and \r\n          organic  food stores, plus a canteen that is open \r\n          for breakfast, lunch, and dinner.<br><br>        \r\n<hr>\r\n<li>  Required Language: English. Each applicant has to \r\n       show proof of English language ability by providing \r\n       a TOEFL iBT with a minimum total score of 90 or \r\n      IELTS Academic with a minimum overall score of 6.5.<br><br>\r\n<li>  MSc requirement: Completed Degree: Bachelor of \r\n       Science or equivalent from a top-ranked university \r\n       accredited or recognized by the UAE Ministry of \r\n       Education (MOE). Students should have a minimum \r\n      CGPA of 3.2 (on a 4.0 scale) or equivalent and \r\n       provide their complete degree certificates and \r\n      transcripts (in English) when submitting their \r\n     application.<br><br>\r\n<li>  Ph.D requirement: Master of Science or equivalent \r\n        from a top-ranked university accredited or \r\n        recognized by the UAE Ministry of Education (MOE). \r\n        Students should have a minimum CGPA of 3.2 (on \r\n        a   4.0 scale) or equivalent and provide their \r\n         complete degree certificates and transcripts (in \r\n         English) when submitting their application.<br><br>     \r\n<li>  A degree attestation (for degrees from the UAE) or \r\n       an equivalency certificate (for degrees acquired \r\n       outside the UAE) should also be furnished within \r\n       their  first semester at the university. For more \r\n       details on   the attestation and equalization \r\n        procedures, please visit the UAE MOE website.<br><br>\r\n<li>  Graduate Record Examination (GRE) General score \r\n        is a plus and would be considered in the \r\n        evaluation  of the applicants. (optional)<br><br>   \r\n      ', '  <li>Official Transcript: provide complete degree \r\n  certificates and transcripts (in English) when \r\n  submitting an application.<br><br>\r\n<li>  Statement of purpose: In a 500 to 1,000-word \r\n        essay, the applicant should present his/her \r\n        motivation for applying to the university. It may \r\n        include information regarding the applicantâs \r\n        personal and academic background as well as \r\n        his/her chosen career path; goals as a \r\n         prospective student; graduation plans.<br><br><li>    Research proposal (For Ph.D): It should be of 3-5 page \r\n        document summarizing the potential research \r\n        project an applicant is interested in working on. <br><br>\r\n<li>    proposal should clearly justify the research gap \r\n          which the applicant would like to fill in over the \r\n          course of his/her study. It must be presented in \r\n          the context of currently existing literature. The \r\n          proposal must provide an overview of how \r\n          he/she aims to investigate the underlying \r\n          research project, and what are the expected \r\n          outcomes. The proposal could also mention \r\n           his relevance and suitability for the project. \r\n           Finally, the proposal should highlight the \r\n           scientific and commercial significance of the \r\n           project. It should be noted that applicants are expected to create a proposal entirely on their own.\r\n            MBZUAI selection team will read an applicantâs \r\n            proposal and use it as one of the measures to \r\n            gauge and assess his/her skills. MBZUAI faculty \r\n            will NOT help applicants write a research \r\n            proposal for the purpose of the application.<br><br>\r\n       ', '1) Register to the online website from here.<br>\r\n2) Choose your program and fill out your application form.<br>\r\n3) Make your academic profile and submit your documents and certificates.<br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> fill all required information in the English language only.<br>', 'vnmgh', '[\"Masters\",\"Post Doctoral \"]', '[\"Masters (All)\",\"Post Doctoral \"]', '\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-01', '2023-04-30', 'Muhammad Bin Zaid University.', 400000.00, 'radrsh@triwits.com', '2022-07-07 15:55:44', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-10-25 15:39:11', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1200, 'FjNzs6aqktErfb06Na', 'Scholarship', 'Raman Kant Munjal Scholarship', 'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSce88Ao1UYLl0ufTlfn7UUcll6kRBV4pWPZl8Q8lM3qbRyK6Q/viewform', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i0GCpJ4zNys', 'Courses accepted:  BBA, BFIA, B.Com(H,E), BMS, IPM, \r\nBA (Economics) degree courses. <br/\r\nSome scholarship schemes are created by the foundation so that they can provide financial assistance to the students belonging to the economically weaker section. Raman Kant Munjal Scholarship is a scholarship created by the Raman Kant Munjal Foundation in collaboration with Hero Fincorp Group. <br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n   <b>Eligibility Criteria</b><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>An applicant must have passed the class 12th \r\n      examination<br/>\r\n<li>The age of the candidate should not exceed 19 \r\n      years \r\n      as of 31st May 2022<br/>\r\n<li>The annual family income should not exceed more \r\n      than Rs. 4 lakh per annum<br/>\r\n<li>The students should have scored at least 80% of\r\n      marks in class 10th and 12th examination<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Minimum marks in Qualifying Exams</b><br/>	\r\n\r\n<li>10th marks 70% for entrance exam route & 80% for \r\n      10th marks route.<br/>\r\n<li>12th marks 70% for entrance exam route & 80% for \r\n      12th marks route.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n      <b>NOTE</b><br/>\r\n   <li>To see the list of colleges accepted please visit \r\n         this   link â<a href=\"https://bit.ly/College_List_2021\" target=\"_blank\">https://bit.ly/College_List_2021</a><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Scholarship of Rs. 50,000 to Rs. 5,00,000 is \r\n       awarded  to each student per year for 3 years\r\n       courses  education. (The exact scholarship amount \r\n       will depend on the accepted college fees).<br/>\r\n\r\n  ', '<li>Aadhar card\r\n<li>Class 10th mark sheet\r\n<li>Class 12th mark sheet\r\n<li>Date of birth certificate/ Adhar Card\r\n<li>Family income certificate\r\n<li>Passport size photograph\r\n<li>Email ID & Mobile Number', '1) Scroll down and click Login & Apply option</br>\r\n2) Complete the form with the necessary information</br>\r\n3) Upload any necessary documents there\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr><b>Selection Process</b></br>\r\n1) Career Assessment Test<br/>\r\n2) Essay form<br/>\r\n3) 1st Round of Telephonic Interview Call<br/>\r\n4) Documents Submission including a college \r\n     acceptance letter<br/>\r\n5) Final Round of Interview (Telephone or Face to Face)\r\n      Award is given to the selected students<br/>', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\"]', '\"Undergraduate (Bachelors)\"', NULL, NULL, 70.00, 70.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 400000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-22', '2022-10-01', 'Raman Kant Munjal Foundation', 50000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-07-07 15:56:37', 1, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-09-02 06:26:33', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
