(1225, 'B1YskO2E9s2xZBhOAX', 'Scholarship', 'RGCB Senior Research Fellowship', 'https://rgcb.res.in/index.php', '', '', '', '', '', 'Applications are invited from suitable candidates for one position of Senior Research Fellow (SRF) OR Research Associate (RA) in a CSIR-sponsored research project entitled, âIdentification of Xenoestrogen induced Spontaneous Mutations and changes in Promoter Methylation Status in the Cancer-Causing Genes BRCA1, BRCA2 and p53 in Breast, Ovarian, Prostate and Pancreatic Cancersâ in the laboratory of Dr. Priya Srinivas at Rajiv Gandhi Centre for Biotechnology, Thiruvananthapuram.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b> Essential Qualifications<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<b><li>Senior Research Fellow</b> - MSc/BE/B.Tech or equivalent degree in Life Science subjects, with a 60% mark with at least two years of research experience in animal cell culture according to the last date of application. Candidates should have qualified National Eligibility Test (CSIR-UGC NET/ GATE/ DBT-JRF/ ICMR-JRF etc. Examination).<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b><li>Research Associate</b> - Ph.D. (in any branch of life sciences) or MPharm/MVSc with three years of R&D expertise according to the last date of application, evidenced from fellowship or associateship or by date of enrollment of Ph.D. Experience in animal cell culture techniques is essential. Those who had submitted their Ph.D. thesis are also qualified to apply for Research Associateship, though they will be eligible for salary at the SRF level till the award of their degree.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Desirable Qualifications<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<li>Experience in animal cell culture techniques, Proteomics, and genomics will be desirable<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b>Age<br/></b>\r\n<li>The Upper age limit for applying for the position of SRF shall be 32 years and for the position of RA shall be 35 years as of August 05, 2022. Age relaxation will be given as per Govt. of India norms<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefit<br/></b>\r\n<li>Senior Research Fellow: â¹