(1231, 'WSivLybTmwzWeeDgaj', 'Scholarship', 'Pre Matric Scholarships Scheme for Minorities 2022', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/fresh/newstdRegfrmInstruction', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The scholarship at the pre-matric level will encourage parents from minority communities to send their school-going children to school, lighten their financial burden on school education and sustain their efforts to support their children to complete school education. The scheme will form the foundation for their <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Educational attainment and provide a level playing field in the competitive employment arena. Empowerment through education, which is one of the objectives of this scheme, has the potential to lead to the upliftment of the socio-economic conditions of the minority communities.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n <hr>\r\n<b>SCOPE<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship will be awarded for studies in India in a government or private school from class I to class X, including such residential Government institutes and eligible private institutes, selected and notified transparently by the State Government and Union Territory Administration concerned.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>ELIGIBILITY<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship will be awarded to the students who have secured not less than<b> 50% marks </b>in the previous final examination and the annual income of their parents/guardian from all sources does not exceed Rs. 1.00 lakh.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n <b>https://scholarships.gov.in/public/schemeGuidelines/MoMA_Pre_Matric_2018-20.pdf<br/><br/></b>', '<li>Caste Certificate<br/>\r\n<li>Identity Proof<br/>\r\n<li>Aadhar Card<br/>\r\n<li>Income Certificate<br/>\r\n<li>Bank Details<br/>\r\n<li>Candidate Photographs<br/>\r\n<li>Ration Card<br/>\r\n<li>Age Proof<br/>\r\n<li>Candidate mobile number<br/>', '1. Visit the official website<br/>\r\n2. Tap on the new registration option<br/>\r\n3. Tick the declaration after reading all the rules and regulations<br/>\r\n4. Click on continue<br/>\r\n5. A new form will appear before you<br/>\r\n6. Add all your credentials such as name, DOB, mobile number, gender, etc<br/>\r\n7. Tap on the register<br/>\r\n8. Now, log in from your Student ID<br/>\r\n9. Tap on the application form icon<br/>\r\n10. Select the scholarship category<br/>\r\n11. Enter the information on the form such as name, DOB, Fatherâs name, Aadhar Card Number, Mobile no., etc<br/>\r\n12. After filling up, tap on save and continue<br/>\r\n13. Upload all the required documents<br/>\r\n14. Click on final submission<br/>', '', '[\"Primary\",\"Secondary\",\"Class 10\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Class 1 to 10\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 100000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-09', '2022-09-30', 'Ministry of Minority Affairs ', 1000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-03 15:32:41', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-10 04:33:01', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1232, 'CkZ12cokatg27UvcLB', 'Scholarship', 'Merit Cum Means Scholarship', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/fresh/newstdRegfrmInstruction', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The objective of the Scheme is to provide financial assistance to the poor and meritorious students belonging to minority communities to enable them to pursue professional and technical courses.<br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Scope<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship is to be awarded for studies in India in a Government or private institution, selected and notified transparently by the State Government/Union Territory Administration concerned. It will cover technical and professional courses at the undergraduate and postgraduate levels.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship will be awarded to the students who have secured not less than <b>50%</b> marks or equivalent grade in the previous final examination and the annual income of whose parents/guardians from all sources does not exceed Rs.2.50 lakh.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Students who get admission to a college to pursue technical/professional courses, based on a competitive examination will be eligible for the scholarship <b><a href=\"https://scholarships.gov.in/public/schemeGuidelines/MoMA_MCM_2018-20.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">https://scholarships.gov.in/public/schemeGuidelines/MoMA_MCM_2018-20.pdf</a></b>\r\n\r\n\r\n ', '<li>Caste Certificate<br/>\r\n<li>Identity Proof<br/>\r\n<li>Aadhar Card<br/>\r\n<li>Income Certificate<br/>\r\n<li>Bank Details<br/>\r\n<li>Candidate Photographs<br/>\r\n<li>Ration Card<br/>\r\n<li>Age Proof<br/>\r\n<li>Candidate mobile number<br/>', '1. Visit the official website<br/>\r\n2. Tap on the new registration option<br/>\r\n3. Tick the declaration after reading all the rules and regulations<br/>\r\n4. Click on continue<br/>\r\n5. A new form will appear before you<br/>\r\n6. Add all your credentials such as name, DOB, mobile number, gender, etc<br/>\r\n7. Tap on the register<br/>\r\n8. Now, log in from your Student ID<br/>\r\n9. Tap on the application form icon<br/>\r\n10. Select the scholarship category<br/>\r\n11. Enter the information on the form such as name, DOB, Fatherâs name, Aadhar Card Number, Mobile no., etc<br/>\r\n12. After filling up, tap on save and continue<br/>\r\n13. Upload all the required documents<br/>\r\n14. Click on final submission<br/>\r\n', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"Bachelors and Masters\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 250000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-31', '2022-10-30', 'Ministry of Minority Affairs   ', 20000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-03 15:56:07', 1, NULL, '2022-09-17 11:34:51', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1233, 'A6rgkGogGiKV3eDK6v', 'Scholarship', 'Venkat Panchapakesan Memorial Scholarship India', 'https://programs-scholarships.appspot.com/scholarships/venkat-panchapakesan-memorial-scholarship', '', '', '', '', '', 'Venkat was a much-loved and highly respected engineer whose career took him to YouTube, Google, and Yahoo, among other notable companies. He tragically passed away too young, after a battle with cancer. During his short time, he deeply touched the hearts and minds of his friends, family, and colleagues. He taught us to be selfless, humble, ever-optimistic, and to always find the best in people.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Are you an ever-optimistic person who believes we can make the world a more sustainable place? Are you passionate about the field of computer science and engineering? Are you already using computer science to develop solutions for some challenges or opportunities, that you see around you?<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>If yes, we invite you to apply for the Venkat Panchapakesan Memorial Scholarship. Applications will open on July 25th, 2022, please keep an eye out for the âapply now button to appear. Selected students will receive a financial award of,<b> $2,500 USD</b> towards tuition and education-related expenses, and will be invited to a virtual retreat in October 2022.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b>We are specifically looking for university students who</b><br/>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Aspire to be computer scientists and technology leaders<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Exemplify leadership skills and a demonstrated passion for computer science and technology\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n<li>Communicates their responses and message with thought and clarity<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Have a great financial need<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n <hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Terms & Conditions<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Scholarship recipients will be selected based on the overall strength of their application materials compared to the entire applicant pool.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n <li>The selection will be full and final, and the applicants will confirm they will not dispute the same at any point in time.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n <li>The Venkat Panchapakesan Memorial Scholarship award of $2,500 USD must be spent on tuition, fees, books, supplies, and equipment required for the student\'s classes at their primary university.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li> Tax liability, if any, in relation to this scholarship award will have to be borne by the scholarship recipient.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n <li>Scholarship recipients must be enrolled as full-time students for the academic years 2022-2023. Enrollment will be verified after the winners are selected, and all scholarship payments will be made directly to the student to be used towards tuition and education-related expenses.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>We will withhold the award for any scholar who no longer meets the eligibility requirements and revoke the award for any scholar who does not maintain the eligibility requirements.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n <li>Any employee of Google Inc. including its affiliates and subsidiaries is not eligible to apply for Google scholarships.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li> Persons who are (1) residents of embargoed countries, (2) ordinarily resident in embargoed countries, or (3) otherwise prohibited by applicable export controls and sanctions programs may not apply for this scholarship.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n <hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>This is a scholarship that will support university students in making the world a more sustainable place using technology and who are passionate about the field of computer science and engineering. Students who are already using computer science to develop solutions for some of the challenges, or opportunities, that they see around them are invited to apply for the Venkat Panchapakesan Memorial Scholarship.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>This scholarship is exclusively for Computer Science students who are enrolled as undergraduate students in a college/university in India, for the current academic year.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Previous applicants can re-apply. Previous recipients of any Google scholarships are not eligible to reapply, including the Venkat Panchapakesan Memorial Scholarship, and are not eligible to apply.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n ', '<li>Aadhar Card<br/>\r\n<li>Income Certificate<br/>\r\n<li>Bank Details<br/>\r\n<li>Candidate Photographs<br/>\r\n<li>Previous semester/year Mark sheet<br/>\r\n', '1) Once you are logged in, you need to update your profile by filling in all the necessary information<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application<br/>', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"Engineering (Computer Science)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-29', '2022-08-14', 'Venkat Panchapakesan Memorial ', 197756.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-03 16:37:02', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-09 06:24:21', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1234, 'xgGPWdJdGQQdU6EjIy', 'Scholarship', 'Mahindra Finance Saksham Scholarship', 'https://www.buddy4study.com/page/saksham-scholarship-program-for-drivers-children?ref=HomePageBanner', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'âSaksham Scholarship Program for Driversâ Childrenâ is an initiative of Mahindra Finance to provide financial assistance to the children of the driversâ community to support them in continuing their education. Mahindra Finance believes in empowering the academic and career goals of children of drivers by removing the financial barrier.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Under this scholarship, students from Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Kerala, and Telangana who are studying in Class 9 to 12, will be provided with a one-time (fixed) financial assistance of up to Rs 10,000 to cover their academic expenses.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The company has introduced this scholarship program as part of its CSR (Corporate Social Responsibility) Flagship program âSwabhimaanâ with an objective to financially support underprivileged children/wards of the driversâ community in continuing their education.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Eligibility for Saksham Scholarship Program<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<li>Open for students from Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Kerala, and Telangana<br/><br/>\r\n<li>Applicants must be studying in Classes 9 to 12<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<li>Applicants must have secured <b>60% </b>and above marks in their previous class<br/><br/>\r\n<li>One of the parents should be a driver (all light motor vehicles and small commercial vehicles such as Taxi, Jeep, Car & delivery vans such as Pickup, magic, school van, etc.) and should hold a <b>valid driving license<br/><br/></b>\r\n<li>The annual family income of the applicants from all sources should not be more than Rs 4,00,000<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>NOTE</b><br/>\r\nScholarships will be awarded to a maximum of two students per family<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Benefits of Saksham Scholarship Program</b><br/>\r\nFor Class 9 and 10 â<b> Rs 8,000</b> for 1 year</br>\r\nFor Class 11 and 12 â<b> Rs 10,000 </b>for 1 year', '<li>Marksheet of the previous qualifying examination<br/>\r\n<li>Photo identity proof (Aadhaar card/voter id card/driving license/PAN card)<br/>\r\n<li>Family income proof (Form 16A/income certificate from government authority/salary slips, etc.)<br/>\r\n<li>Admission proof (Fee receipt/admission letter/institution ID card/ bonafide certificate)<br/>\r\n<li>Bank account details of the applicant (cancelled cheque/passbook copy)<br/>\r\n<li>Commercial driving license (taxi, cab, minivan, school van, magic/pick-up, etc.)<br/>\r\n<li>Contract copy/income proof/employee ID card (for cab driverâs profile if they do not possess a commercial driving license)<br/>\r\n<li>Address proof (Domicile certificate/residential certificate/telephone bill/ration card)<br/>\r\n<li>Photograph of the applicant<br/>', '1) Once you are logged in, you need to update your profile by filling in all the necessary information<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application<br/>', '', '[\"Class 10\",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"Class 10 - SSLC - Matriculation\",\"Class 11 - PUC 1\",\"Class 12 - PUC 2\"]', '\"Class 10, Class 11, Class 12\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07', '2022-08-31', 'Mahindra Finance', 10000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-04 16:00:01', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-10 04:18:52', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1235, 'fIQ8fJecopzBJJCxkN', 'Scholarship', 'RVG Merit Scholarship', 'https://www.rvgef.org/scholarship.asp', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'RVG Educational Foundation (Formerly, Rajasthan Vidyarthi Griha) (RVG) has formed a Scholarship Corpus Fund and provides RVG Merit Scholarship to Meritorious RVGians who are Rank holders in CA IPC examination till the completion of their Articleship as per ICAIâs Registration Letter OR stay in RVG, whichever is earlier.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Terms of Eligibility<br/></b>\r\n\r\n\r\na) Meritorious students of RVG who are rank holders in the CA (IPC) examination (Both groups in one attempt)<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nb) Scholarship shall continue till completion of the Articleship as per ICAIâs Registration Letter or stay in RVG Hostel, whichever is earlier<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nc) If the Articleship period is extended for any reason, eligibility for the scholarship will cease on the original expiry of the Articleship as mentioned in the Registration Letter<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nd) If RVGian is found to be involved in any major or minor disciplinary violation, he/she will not be eligible for a Scholarship for the remaining stay at RVG and also be liable for penalty<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Financials<br/></b>\r\n\r\n\r\na) RVG Merit Scholarship to Meritorious RVGians will be given @ Rs.1000/- per month payable in advance for each quarter<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n ', '<li>Application form duly filled and signed<br/>\r\n\r\n<li> One passport-size photograph with signature<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Certified true copy of the IPC Mark sheet & Rank Certificate<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>A certified true copy of the Registration Letter issued by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI)<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n ', '1. Log in to your dashboard<br/>\r\n\r\n2. Click on Participate and fill in your personal details on the MyGov portal<br/>\r\n\r\n3. Upload your story with a picture and submit<br/>\r\n\r\n', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '\"Undergraduate(Bachelors)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-02', '2022-10-09', 'RVG Merit ', 1000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-04 17:14:52', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-10 04:36:23', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1236, 'tBlBY3iS71Aq6Lqz9v', 'Scholarship', 'IDA Shining Star Scholarship ', 'https://www.buddy4study.com/page/sensodyne-ida-shining-star-scholarship-programme', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Sensodyne IDA Shining Star Scholarship Programme is a CSR (Corporate Social Responsibility) initiative of HALON India (erstwhile GlaxoSmithKline Consumer Healthcare) focused on providing financial support to underprivileged and meritorious Bachelor of Dental Surgery (BDS) students across India. Under this scholarship programme, 100 deserving students will be selected who are pursuing their first year of <b>BDS</b> course in Government colleges or Government funded colleges. Each selected student will be provided with the financial assistance of INR 1,05,000 per year, for their 4 years, to support their academic and living expenses incurred towards their BDS programme.<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Eligibility<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<li>Open for students pursuing their first-year Bachelor of Dental Surgery (BDS) programme only from government and government-funded colleges<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Applicants must have scored a minimum of 60% in their Higher Secondary Education. (NOTE: Successful applicant has to maintain a minimum 60% score in each semester/year to continue availing the benefits of their 4 years course.)<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The annual family income of the applicants should not be more than INR 8,00,000/- from all sources<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Children or family members of employees of HALON India (erstwhile GlaxoSmithKline Consumer Healthcare), IDA, Goodera & Buddy4Study are not eligible<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Students from pan-India can apply<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Benefits<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<li>Each successfully selected student will receive<b> INR 1,05,000,</b> per year for<b> 4 </b>years of BDS Course<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b>NOTE<br/></b>\r\n\r\n<li> The scholarship amount can be utilized only for academic expenses such as tuition fees, hostel fees, food, internet, mobile, laptop, books, stationery, online learning, etc<br/>\r\n', '<li>Marksheet of the previous class/semester</br>\r\n</br><li>Photo identity proof (Aadhaar Card/voter id card/driving license/PAN card)<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<li>Current year admission proof (fee receipt/admission letter/institution ID card/bonafide certificate)<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<li>Family income proof (Government-issued documents such as tax return, income certificate from local administration, EWS (Economic Weaker Section) certificate)<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<li>Bank account details of the applicant or parent\r\nPhotograph of the applicant<br/></br>\r\n\r\n<li>Note: From the second year onwards, the scholar needs to submit a character certificate from College<br/>', '1) Click on the âApply Now button below<br/>\r\n2)Login with your registered ID and land on the âApplication Form Page\'<br/>\r\n3) You will now be redirected to the âSensodyne IDA Shining Star Scholarship Programmeâ application form page<br/>\r\n4) Click on the âStart Application button to begin the application process<br/>\r\n5) Fill in the required details in the online application form<br/>\r\n6) Upload relevant documents<br/>\r\n7) Accept the âTerms and Conditions and click on âPreview\'<br/>\r\n<li>If all the details filled in by the applicant are correctly showing on the preview screen, click on the âSubmitâ button to complete the application process<br/>', '', '[\"Medical\"]', '[\"Bachelor of Dental Surgery (BDS)\"]', '\"Bachelor of Dental Surgery(BDS)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 800000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-02', '2022-08-31', 'Sensodyne IDA Shining Star ', 105000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-04 18:34:55', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2022-08-10 04:20:18', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1237, '6i84ut0u0ebDFbfGsD', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Suggest a Tagline for IRDAI', 'https://www.mygov.in/home/do/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India (hereinafter referred to as âIRDAIâ) is the regulator of the Insurance Industry in India. It is also mandated with the country\'s insurance sector development It was established in the year 2000 under an act of Parliament, to ensure the protection of policyholdersâ interests as well as to promote orderly growth of the insurance industry in India.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>The IRDAI protects the policyholder\'s interests by ensuring fair and equitable terms in an insurance policy, trained and qualified insurance distributors, well-defined claims settlement processes and procedures, and robust grievance redressal mechanisms for effective and speedy resolution. The IRDAI is focused on the growth of the insurance sector and making insurance available to every part of the country and every segment of society through innovative distribution solutions in a cost-effective manner.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<li> In that context, IRDAI invites people of the country to suggest a suitable tagline that encompasses and depicts its role.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>NOTE</b>- Tagline should be in Hindi<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria are proposed as under </b><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n1- The Participants must be above 18 years and a citizen of India<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n2- Entries are open only for individuals and not groups/organizations<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n3- Entries will be judged on creativity, originality, simplicity, visual impact, vibrancy, artistic merit, and how well the theme is communicated<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>Prize details:</b><br/>\r\n \r\n\r\nThe Winning entry will be awarded cash prizes for each category (1st, 2nd, and 3rd prize)<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n1st Prize â Rs 20 lakhs<br/><br/>\r\n2nd Pri