(1245, 'ZwR3JBdfqCYmMu6tKm', 'Abroad', 'Merit Scholarship For  Students', 'https://www.ecpi.edu/international/international-scholarships', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Choosing the correct school is a major decision for overseas students, but figuring out how to pay for it may be even more difficult. We want to make sure you\'re as prepared as possible when you begin your educational experience at ECPI University. To help you, even more, we\'ve established a number of scholarships to help international students pay for their studies.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>ELIGIBILITY & AWARD CRITERIA<br/></b>\r\nProspective or enrolled international students in all programs are eligible to apply<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nApplicants must complete their admissions paperwork to be considered for this merit-based tuition scholarship<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nA completed application must be submitted by the prescribed deadline<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nCandidates must have a high school or college grade point average equivalency of 2.75 or better, based on the last degree completed<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<hr> \r\n<b>Merit Scholarship per Academic Year<br/></b>\r\nGPA	Bachelor\'s	Master\'s<br/><br/>\r\n2.75   	$3,000	        $2,000<br/><br/>\r\n3.25  	$4,000	        $3,000<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Prospective or enrolled international students in all programs are eligible to apply<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe applicant must submit evidence of their financial status, disability, or social status, and submit a one-page essay on why they would be a good candidate to receive the Founderâs Scholarship<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe Founder\'s Scholarships is highly selective and therefore, only limited scholarships will be available each academic year<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>', '1) Register Online<br/>\r\n\r\n2) Choose your program and fill out your application form<br/>\r\n\r\n3) Make your academic profile and submit your documents and certificates<br/>\r\n', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"Undergraduate (Bachelors) Postgraduate ( Masters)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-29', '2022-09-01', 'Mr. Alfred Dreyfus', 300000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-17 17:06:45', 1, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-17 11:56:39', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1246, 'aTgGRgLxZGlXSoj5xb', 'Scholarship', 'LIC HFL Vidyadhan Scholarship 2022', 'https://www.lichousing.com/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The LIC Housing Finance Limited has created the LIC HFL Vidyadhan Scholarship in order to support the education of all underprivileged students in India. The scholarship will provide an important financial incentive to the lower-income group of students who are pursuing studies at various levels. The scholarship will be available for these students who are studying in class 8th up to post-graduation level. The students will receive Rupees 30000 depending upon their level of study. Life insurance Corporation is a very prestigious organization that provides a lot of different opportunities for the underprivileged people in India. You can fill out the application form at the official website of LIC Corporation.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Scholarship Amount</b><br/>\r\n<li>LIC HFL Vidyadhan Scholarship for Class 8-10 Students- <b>INR 10,000</b><br/><br/>\r\n<li>LIC HFL Vidyadhan Scholarship for Class 10 Passed Students-<b> INR 15,000<br/><br/></b>\r\n<li>LIC HFL Vidyadhan Scholarship for Graduation Students-<b> INR 20,000<br/><br/></b>\r\n<li>LIC HFL Vidyadhan Scholarship for PostâGraduation Students-<b> INR 30,000</b><br/><br/</b>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Selection Procedure</b></br>\r\n<li>There is a very simple selection procedure that will be followed by the Life Insurance Corporation for the HFL Vidyadhan scholarship. The applicant will be selected after an assessment of their merit and their financial needs. The applicant must fill out the application form carefully. The screening of this scholarship application will be based on merit and financial need. The applicant will be called for a telephonic discussion after the shortlisting. The face-to-face interview will be the final stage of selection for this opportunity. The applicant must follow the following criteria to get selected for this scholarship<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The merit of the applicant- <b>65%</b> marks or above in the previous exam<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Crisis situation Students supported by single parents, orphans, students with critically/terminally parents, and students from families with job-loss of earning members in the last 12 months<br/><hr/>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b><li>Post Graduation</b></br>\r\n1. Students enrolled in the first year of the post-graduation program at any recognized college/university/institution in India can apply.\r\nApplicants must have scored at least 60% marks in their respective UG level programs<br/>\r\n\r\n2. The family income of the applicant must not be more than INR 3,60,000 per annum from all sources<br/>\r\n\r\n3. Preference will be given to COVID-affected children who have either lost any of their earning members/parents since January 2020 or whose earning family member(s) have lost livelihood/employment during the pandemic<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li><b> Graduation </b><br/>\r\n1. Students enrolled in the first year of a 3-year graduation program (in any stream) at any recognized college/university/institution in India can apply<br/>\r\n\r\n2. Applicants must have scored at least 60% marks in their Class 12 board examination<br/>\r\n\r\n3. The family income of the applicant must not be more than INR 3,60,000 per annum from all sources<br/>\r\n\r\n4. Preference will be given to COVID-affected children who have either lost any of their earning members/parents since January 2020 or whose earning family member(s) have lost livelihood/employment during the pandemic<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li><b> Class 10 passed students </b><br/>\r\n\r\n1. Students enrolled in Class 11 at any recognized institution in India can apply<br/>\r\n\r\n2. Applicants must have scored more than 60% marks in their Class 10 board examination<br/>\r\n\r\n3. The family income of the applicant must not be more than INR 3,60,000 per annum from all sources<br/>\r\n\r\n4. Preference will be given to COVID-affected children who have either lost any of their earning members/parents since January 2020 or whose earning family member(s) have lost livelihood/employment during the pandemic\r\n', '<li>Aadhar Card<br/>\r\n<li>Income-Caste Certificate<br/>\r\n<li>Bank Passbook <br/>\r\n<li>Candidate passport size photograph<br/>\r\n', '1) The home page will open on your screen<br/>\r\n2) You have to go to the scholarship section<br/>\r\n3) The homepage of this scholarship will open on your screen<br/>\r\n4) You have to fill out the application form available on \r\nyour screen after you click on the apply online button<br/>\r\n\r\n5) Enter all of the details and upload all of the documents.\r\n6) 0You can now successfully submit the scholarship form<br/>', '', '[\"Class 10\",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\",\"Class 8\",\"Class 9\",\"Class 10 - SSLC - Matriculation\",\"Class 11 - PUC 1\",\"Class 12 - PUC 2\"]', '\"Class 8 t 12Undergraduate ( Bachelors ), Postgraduate ( Masters ) \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 360000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-20', '2022-09-30', 'LIC', 30000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-19 09:58:50', 1, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-08-19 07:30:27', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1247, 'GaWRDS7ifevBVlbyIW', 'Scholarship', 'Begum Hazrat Mahal Scholarship 2022', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Begum Hazrat Mahal Scholarship is a very beneficial scholarship available for girls belonging to the minority community and the beneficiaries will be able to take monetary benefits on a monthly basis by using the scholarship. The last date for online registration will be 30th September 2022. You have to make sure that you apply before the last date to avoid disqualifications. Applicants are advised to visit the National Scholarship Portal to apply for the scholarship program.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>The objective of the Begum Hazrat Mahal Scholarship</b><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship scheme has been started with the objective of empowering girls from minority communities. These girls will be provided with scholarships that will help them in continuing their education and securing a better chance to stand in society. This scholarship scheme has been started with the aim of providing a better and secure future to these young girls of these minority communities.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Rewards </b><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Class	Particulars	Scholarship amount\r\nClass 9 and 10	Tuition fee, books & stationery expenses, boarding/lodging charges	INR 5,000 per student<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Class 11 and 12	College/School fee, books & stationery expenses, boarding/lodging charges	INR 6,000 per student<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The beneficiaries of the Begum Hazrat Mahal Scholarship are girls students belonging to minority communities that are Muslims, Christians, Jains, Buddhists, Sikhs, and Parsis<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Only the minority girls students who are studying from class 9th to 12th can apply for this scholarship\r\nFor availing of this scholarship scheme, the student has to secure at least 50% marks or equivalent grade in the qualifying examination<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>The credentials of the student have to be verified by the school. The student has To to fill out the school verification form and get it signed by the principal along with a stamp and signature on the photograph\r\nThe annual income of the studentâs family should not exceed Rs 2 lakh<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>There is no requirement to send hard copies to the authority<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Only two students from a family can claim the scholarships<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>This scholarship cannot be availed for studying abroad\r\nThe students are not required to pay any kind of fees for submitting the application form\r\n<hr>\r\n', '<li>Recent passport size photograph of the applicant\r\nSchool verification form attested by the Principal of the school/institute<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Mark sheet of the last exam passed attested by the Principal<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Parents/Guardiansâ income certificate issued by a competent authority declared by the State/UTs Administration<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Self-declaration of minority community certificate by the applicant<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Self-certified copy of the first page of bank/postal account passbook which should be in the name of the applicant (either single or joint account with her parents)<br/>\r\n\r\n<li>A copy of the applicantâs Aadhaar card (in case of unavailability of Aadhaar card, applicants can submit a birth certificate, BPL card, or Rashan card)<br/>\r\n\r\n<hr>', '1) The homepage will open on your screen\r\nClick on the option called Status<br/>\r\n\r\n2) A new page will display on your screen\r\nEnter the details<br/>\r\n\r\n3) Enter the captcha code<br/>\r\n\r\n4) Click on View Application Status<br/>\r\n\r\n5) The status will open on the screen<br/>', '', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"Class 9\",\"Class 10 - SSLC - Matriculation\",\"Class 12 - PUC 2\"]', '\"Class 10 to 12\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00,