(1251, 'aeyFqsj7SfR2XroYth', 'Scholarship', 'SD SEED Scholarship 2022 ', 'https://sdseed.in/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'To provide financial assistance to help economically challenged students who have demonstrated great academic potential.<br/><br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Selection Criteria<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Student should be a resident of the Jalgaon District\r\n Passed Std. 10th and above exams in the first attempt<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Eligibility Percentage<br/></b>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Std. 10th: Rural Area â Min 85%& Urban Area â Min 90%<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Std. 12th: Rural Area â Min 70%& Urban Area â Min 75%OR<br/><br/>\r\n<li> Students appeared for MH-CET or equivalent Exam: Min 120 Marks<br/><br/>\r\n<li> The combined annual income of the family should be less than Rs.1.5 Lacs<br/><br/>\r\n<li> Physically challenged students will get a particular preference<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n<b>For RENEWAL applications<br/></b>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li> A student who has been given a scholarship in previous years including drop-out<br/>\r\n<li> The beneficiary who has an ATKT in only one subject<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n <hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility Percentage<br/></b>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Std 12th to Degree (1st year): Min 75%<br/><br/>\r\n<li>Diploma (3rd year) to Degree: Min 75%<br/><br/>\r\n<li> The degree to Post-Graduate: Min 75%<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n <hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Process<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li> The Online application process starts in August and continues till the end of September every year<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Students applying for the first time register themselves on the Website and proceed to submit their online application<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Beneficiaries, who are applying for renewal, update their educational details in their online account and submit their application<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>On completion of the online application for NEW & RENEWAL applications, an acknowledgment receipt to be generated and to be sent along with copies of required documents to the SD-SEED Office<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li> The Selection Committee thoroughly scrutinizes and screens each application to ascertain eligibility<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Committee Members also visit the studentsâ residences for verification, thus ensuring that the right student is awarded the scholarship<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n <li>Selected students have conferred the scholarship, at the Annual Scholarship Distribution Ceremony held in November and for the remaining students, the scholarship amount is transferred to their bank accounts<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n<li> Beneficiary Identity Cards are issued to all beneficiaries, which serve as a Login ID to get discounts on other SD-SEED benefits, the details are available on SD-SEED Website<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li> When the Beneficiaryâs Mobile Number, E-mail ID, and Present Address is changed, it should be updated on the Website by entering Beneficiary Code in Log-in<br/>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n ', '<li>Aadhar Details<br/>\r\n<li>Proof Of Address<br/>\r\n<li>Bank passbook copy<br/>\r\n<li>Previous Class Marksheets<br/>\r\n<li>Income Certificate/ITR/Ration Card<br/>\r\n<li>Current Year Fee receipt/Fee Structure - Tuition and Non Tuition<br/>\r\n<li>Bonafide Certificate from School/College<br/>\r\n<hr>', '1) Once you are logged in, you need to update your profile by filling in all the necessary information<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application<br/>', '', '[\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 10, Class 11 & Class 12\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 150000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-15', '2022