(1264, 'nbja3Eyz8jO7Eejc1i', 'Competitions and Awards', 'NHRC Human Rights Photography Competition 2022', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/nhrc-human-rights-photography-competition-2022/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The National Human Rights Commission (NHRC) of India is an autonomous quasi-judicial body for the promotion and protection of human rights in the country.<br><br>\r\n<li>Commission spreads awareness about human rights through media, publications, training, seminar, conferences, research, and studies treaties, and international instruments on human rights and makes recommendations for their effective implementation to the Government.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The award-winning photographs attracting eyeballs on various aspects of human rights will be uploaded on the website of the NHRC and may also be suitably used/ displayed for awareness purposes.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>The Themes for the competition are as follows:</b><br>\r\nâ¢ Child Labour<br>\r\nâ¢ Challenges of destitute elderly<br>\r\nâ¢ Environmental Hazards impacting life on planet Earth<br>\r\nâ¢ Celebrating human rights & values in Indian diversity<br>\r\nâ¢ Celebrating gender equality<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>There cash prizes are as under:-</b><br>\r\nâ¢ 1st Prize 15,000/-<br>\r\nâ¢ 2nd Prize 10,000/-<br>\r\nâ¢ 3rd Prize 5,000/-<br>\r\nâ¢ 7 consolation prizes of Rs. 2000/-', '1. The Photographs should be shot in HD Standard having pixel size of 3600x5400 and an\r\naspect ratio of 3:2.<br>\r\n2. In case of selection of the photographs for awards, the applicants will be required to send a\r\nGlossy hard print of the same in 18x24 inches. <br>', '1) Click on the\"Login & apply \" button below<br>\r\n2)login to participate<br>\r\n3)Read the terms and conditions carefully<br>\r\n4)Submit the required documents.<br>', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 14, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-15', '2022-09-15', 'Government of India', 15000.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-01 09:45:47', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-02 04:02:17', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1265, 'cqLgVMYnJvkm3YrJiP', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Design a Mascot for Nasha Mukt Bharat Abhiyaan', 'https://www.mygov.in/home/do/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Nasha Mukt Bharat Abhiyaan (NMBA) was launched on 15th August 2020 by the Ministry of Social Justice & Empowerment in the 272 most vulnerable districts to substance use in the country. Through NMBA, the Ministry of Social Justice & Empowerment intends to create awareness of the mass level of substance use through the participation of its major stakeholders like youth & adolescents, women, educational institutions, and the community at large.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>Since its launch, lively discussions have started taking place on substance use in public spheres like educational institutions, community areas, and virtual spaces like social media which have prompted those who need help to seek counseling, treatment & rehabilitation services. This has helped people be more aware of substance use and the shedding of stigma related to drug abuse.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>Moshe and MyGov invite citizens to participate in mascot design competitions for the Nasha Mukt Bharat Abhiyaan (NMBA). The mascot will be used as a medium of representation on the platform and any outreach (online/printed) material.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n <hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Important Instructions<br/></b>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n1. The mascot should graphically convey the objectives of NMBA while underlining the themes or concepts of collaboration& participation among various stakeholders to create awareness and combat substance use<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n2. The mascot should mandatorily use the logo of Nasha Mukt Bharat Abhiyaan<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n3. Depiction of drugs & other illicit substances may not be used in the mascot design<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n4. Each entry must be accompanied by a brief description of the concept behind the design of the mascot and how it encapsulates the essence of the program/mission<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n5. File should be of high resolution â at least 1000 pixels per inch at 100% size<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>For more information, participants visit <br/></b>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://nmba.dosje.gov.in//\" target=\"_blank\">https://nmba.dosje.gov.in/</a><br><br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>Awards<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>A Prize of Rs 10,000 will be awarded to the winning design<br/>', '<li> High-resolution (600 dpi) image of the mascot in JPEG, PNG, BMP, TIFF formats only.<br>\r\n', '1)Press the below \"Click here to apply \"button<br>\r\n2)You will be redirected to the competition portal, Log in yourself<br/>\r\n3) Go through the terms and conditions carefully<br/>\r\n4) Attach the documents mentioned and submit<br/>', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-07', '2022-09-15', 'Nasha Mukt Bharat Abhiyaan (NMBA)', 10000.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-09-01 09:54:07', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-08 11:28:56', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1266, 'dxdwyoKomkb5hIDYfY', 'Scholarship', ' YLAC Counter Speech Fellowship', 'https://theylacproject.com/counter-speech-fellowship/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Anchored at the crossroads of arts and advocacy, the fellowship was first launched in 2017 in India and Nepal. <br/><br/><li>The YLAC Counter Speech Fellowship with Instagram engages creative teens to use the power of visual storytelling to start meaningful conversations on issues important to young citizens around the world.<br><br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>As an incubator for the future generation of leaders and activists, the fellowship is built around three pillars â awareness, support, and advocacy. <br><br>\r\n<li>Fellows are mentored to build powerful content, promoting the most inspiring work on Instagram. <br><br><li>The fellowship is designed as a fully funded engagement wherein fellows meet every alternate week for a couple of hours. The overall duration of the fellowship is two months and the schedule is easy to accommodate alongside regular school work and examinations.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n <hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility<br/></b>\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>If you are studying in a school in India in grades 8th-12th, or are being home-schooled, and are between 13 to 18 years of age, you are eligible to apply to the Counter Speech Fellowship. Students 18 years of age but have already completed school are not eligible.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Applications to the fellowship will be processed in two batches. Those applying on or before the priority deadline will be eligible for early decisions. For the others, admission decisions will be announced after the final application deadline.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n <b>Note:</b>The Counter Speech Fellowship is a very selective program. You are encouraged to apply as soon as possible.<br/>', '<li>Identity Proof\r\n<li>Previous mark sheet\r\n<li>Bank Details\r\n<li>Candidate Photographs\r\n\r\n', '1) Log in and update your profile by filling in all the necessary information<br/>\r\n2) Select the \'scholarship\' option to enter the scholarship application<br/>\r\n3) Fill in all required information and upload the supporting documents<br/>\r\n4) Finally submit the application<br/>', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"Masters\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-12', '2022-09-11', 'Young Leaders For Active Citizenship', 0.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-09-01 10:38:49', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-08 07:51:37', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1267, 'f08uNtrBmis89tPvvq', 'Abroad', 'Trustee Scholarships ', 'https://studyabroad.shiksha.com/signup?recheck31', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Boston University offers Trustee scholarships to outstanding students. In addition to exceptional academic credentials, Trustee Scholars are intellectually and creatively adventurous and demonstrate viewpoints, experiences, or achievements beyond the usual<br><br><li>Scholarship amount will be given yearly<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n<li><b>This scholarship is applicable for the following courses at Boston University in the USA</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>BS Business Administration<br>\r\n<li>BS in Biology<br>\r\n \r\n<li>BS Electrical Engineering<br>\r\n<li>BS in Computer Engineering<br>\r\n \r\n<li>BA in Computer Science<br>\r\n<li>Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Bachelor of Science in Hospitality Administration<br>\r\n<li>BS in Biomedical Engineering<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship is available to all UG programs<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility</b>\r\n<li>Applicant must have passed High School<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<b>Prerequisites</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>4 years of English<br>\r\n<li>3-4 years of mathematics (precalculus/calculus recommended)<br>\r\n<li>3-4 years of laboratory science<br>\r\n<li>3-4 years of history and/or social science<br>\r\n<li>2-4 years of a foreign language<br>\r\n<li>English Language Proficiency Proof<br>\r\n<li>TOEFL: A composite score of at least 90-100 and minimum scores of 20 in each section<br>\r\n<li>IELTS: A total/overall score of 7 or higher<br>', '<li>LOR: Submit the School Report form and the School Counselor Recommendation form\r\nEssays<br/><br/>\r\n<li>Please choose from one of the two prompts below and submit one essay, in 600 words or less, as part of your application through the Common or Coalition Application<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n1)Howard Thurman, who was the dean of BUâs Marsh Chapel from 1953-1965, once wrote: âDonât ask what the world needs. Ask what makes you come alive, and go do it. Because what the world needs is people who have come alive.â Can you describe a particular experience you have had or an activity that you participated in that made you come alive? How would you try to integrate that experience or activity into your time at BU?<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n2)Describe a time when you felt out of your comfort zone or marginalized in a situation. How did you respond to that moment and how has it informed your actions moving forward?<br/>\r\n \r\n\r\n', '1) Register to the online website from here<br>\r\n2) Choose your program and fill out your application form<br>\r\n3) Make your academic profile and submit your documents and certificates<br>', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"Bachelors and Masters\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-25', '2022-12-01', ' Boston University', 4541509.00, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-09-01 11:54:10', 1, 'prajwitagadade@triwits.com', '2022-09-02 05:53:06', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1268, 'XYlDujlEKZfRyXlvtr', 'Scholarship', 'Indus Towers Scholarship  ', 'https://www.ssscholarship.org/apply', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'This scholarship is exclusively for Students with disabilities belonging to the North-eastern states of India<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>scholarships 2022-23 will be awarded to <b>180 deserving students</b> with disabilities from North-East India .<br><br>\r\n<li>Who wish to pursue or are currently pursuing higher education in Academic or Professional courses at levels ranging from Higher Secondary to Post Graduation or Vocational/Skill Building Courses. <br><br>\r\n<li>Also, young graduates who are preparing for Government jobs or Civil services examinations can avail scholarships for preparatory coaching. <br><br><li>A few scholarships are also reserved for students with disabilities from other states in India studying in <b>Institutions of National Importance</b> recognized by the Government of India.<br><br><li><b>Online and offline</b> applications  will be accepted for the 2022-23 session <br><hr>\r\n\r\n ', '<li> Recent Coloured Passport Sized Photo <br>\r\n<li> ID Proof: Voter Id/Passport/Driving Licence <br>\r\n<li> Aadhar Card<br>\r\n<li> Disability Certificate *<br>\r\n <li>BPL Card, if applicable<br>\r\n <li>Income Certificate, if applicable<br>\r\n <li>Class 10/HSLC Marksheet <br>\r\n <li>Class 12/Higher Secondary Marksheet, if applicable\r\n Pass Certificate/Marksheet of Graduation Examination, if applicable<br>\r\n<li> Pass Certificate /Marksheet of Post-Graduation Examination, if applicable<br>\r\n<li> Admission Fee receipt of the course of the current semester, if applicable<br>\r\n <li>Marksheet of the last semester examination appeared, if applicable<br>\r\n <li>Course Prospectus-Clearly displaying fee structure, if available and applicable <br><br>\r\n<li> If you are applying online, these documents will need to be uploaded in the format as <b>.jpg,.png images, or .pdf &