(1278, 'lvn5InwuzSlJix8HDT', 'Competitions and Awards', 'The Commonwealth Short Story Prize 2023', 'https://www.commonwealthwriters.org/shortstoryprize/info/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The prize is free to enter and open to any citizen of a Commonwealth country who is aged 18 and over.  <br><br>\r\n<li>It is awarded for the best piece of unpublished short fiction (2,000â5,000 words). Regional winners each receive Â£2,500 and the opportunity to be published online by Granta magazine, and the overall winner receives Â£5,000.<br><br>\r\n<li>Stories are accepted in the English, Bengali, Chinese, Creole, French, Greek, Kiswahili, Malay, Portuguese, Samoan, Tamil, and Turkish languages. <br><br>\r\n<li>Translated entries from any language into English are also eligible. If the winning story is a translation, the translator receives the additional prize money.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Scholarship eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Entrants must be citizens of a Commonwealth country<br>\r\n<li>There is no requirement for the writer to have current residence in a Commonwealth country,\r\nproviding that they are a citizen of a Commonwealth country.<br>\r\n<li>Entrants must be aged 18 years or over on 1 November 2022.<br>\r\n<li>Entries from previous overall winners of the Commonwealth Short Story Prize are not eligible.\r\nEntries from previous regional winners are eligible.<br>\r\n<li>Entries from current members of staff at the Commonwealth Foundation are not eligible.<br>\r\n<li>Entries must be unpublished and remain unpublished in any language until 1 May 2023\r\n. <br><li>Entries, including those in translation, must be made by the original author<br>\r\n<li>Entries must be 2,000 words minimum, 5,000 words maximum (not including title).<br><hr>', '<li>Entries should be uploaded in a PDF document. Please save your document as a PDF and use the\r\ntitle of the story as the file name. Please note that the story must not be saved as\r\nâCommonwealth Storyâ, âShort Storyâ or any other generic title. If it is not possible to save the\r\nentry as a PDF document, it may be uploaded as a Microsoft Word document, with the file name\r\nin the same format as above. The first page should include the name of the story and the number\r\nof words.<br><br>\r\n<li>All entries in English should be submitted in Arial 12-point font and double line spacing. For\r\nentries in other languages, the appropriate font should be used. All pages should be numbered.<br><br>\r\n<li>The authorâs details should be included on the entry form. They must not be given anywhere on\r\nthe uploaded document. All entries are judged anonymously.<br><hr>', '1)Click the below\" Click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2)Read the terms and conditions carefully<br>\r\n3) Add your details to the form<br>\r\n4)Attach your story (pdf/word document)<br>\r\n5)Submit the entry form.', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-01', '2022-11-01', 'Commonwealth of Nations', 457661.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-05 12:33:48', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-06 05:05:48', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1279, 'ZsDQL5rRbKV0IZHqzl', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Clean Seas: Life And Living Jingle Competition ', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/clean-seas-life-and-living-or-%E2%80%98swacch-sagar-jeevan-aur-aajeevika%E2%80%99-jingle-competition-%E2%80%93-classes/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'In this context, India, being a signatory of the UN \"Coastal Clean Seas\" campaign, a number of activities have been adopted that have direct relevance to the \"Swachh Bharat\" vision and has proved highly useful.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The \"International Coastal Clean Up Day\" is celebrated globally on the third Saturday of September, every year. This year on 17th September 2022, the Government of India along with other voluntary organizations, and the local society will run a cleanliness campaign \"Swachh Sagar, Surakshit Sagar/Clean Coast Safe Sea\" along Indiaâs entire coastline. <br><br>\r\n<li>This jingle competition is meant to test the basic awareness level of Indian citizens about our coastline, and beaches and the science behind its habitat, environment, and the negative impact of litter and pollution.<hr>', 'Participants can upload their entries in .doc, .docx, pdf (Maximum file upload limit- 10MB)<hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Regarding the Jingle:</b><br>\r\n<li>Participants have to write original lines, without copying from any online sources<br>\r\n<li>The entry must not contain any provocative, objectionable, or inappropriate content<br>\r\n<li> The participant must be the same person who has written the jingle. <br>\r\n<li>The top five entries selected by the committee will receive an attractive hamper of science books,\r\nstationery, carry bag, and certificate. <br>\r\n<li>Each of the winners will be notified through email address that they provide along with their\r\nsubmission. <br><hr>', '1)Click the below\" click below to apply\" button<br>\r\n2)Read the terms and conditions of the Competition carefully<br>\r\n3)Register/login for the competition<br>\r\n4)Attach your Jingle file<br>\r\n5)Submit the entry.', '', '[\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 9 -12\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-30', '2022-09-11', 'Government of India', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-05 13:23:18', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-06 06:08:47', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1280, 'GydVSNN2w8rUAMqg72', 'Abroad', 'Nokia Scholarship', 'https://nokiafoundation.com/grants/nokia-scholarship/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The Nokia Scholarship encourages efficient, fast-progressing doctoral studies and research. Nokia Scholarships are granted to individuals pursuing a doctoral degree in Information and Communications Technology (ICT) or in clearly related supporting scientific disciplines. Scholarships can be awarded for postgraduate studies in a Finnish university or to a Finnish applicant for doctoral studies abroad. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n<li>The applicant must receive a commitment statement from his/her principal supervisor, who must be a professor, docent, or senior scientist at the university at which the student is pursuing their degree. The statement must be submitted to the electronic application tool by the supervisor.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<li>For additional information on applying or any other questions, please send an e-mail to:\r\nnokia.foundation@nokia.com<br/>\r\n', '<li>One recent passport-size photograph<br/>\r\n<li>Photocopy of applicant\'s passbook<br/>\r\n<li>Photocopy of Aadhaar Card<br/>\r\n<li>Photocopy of class 10 certificate<br/>\r\n<li>Photocopy of class 12 certificate<br/>', '1. Log into your dashboard<br/>\r\n2. Click the Apply Now<br/>\r\n3. Click on the âStart Application button to begin the application process<br/>\r\n4. Fill in the required details in the online application form<br/>\r\n5. Upload relevant documents<br/>\r\n6. Accept the âTerms and Conditions and click on âPreviewâ<br/>\r\n7. If all the details filled in by the applicant are correctly showing on the preview screen, click on the âSubmitâ button to complete the application process.<br/>', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '\"Undergraduate (Bachelors)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL