he AY 2022-2023.<br>\r\n<li>Students studying in colleges/schools located within Mumbai / Mumbai suburban areas are eligible to apply.<br>\r\n<li> Students should have secured at least a pass class in their previous examination (ATKT students are not eligible to apply)<br>\r\n<li>A maximum of two children from the same family can apply.<br>\r\n<li>This scheme offers partial assistance to college (till graduation â except engineering stream)<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b>If you fit into the above-mentioned âEligibility Criteriaâ kindly send your request to <b><a href=\"mailto:igpedu@tatatrusts.org\">igpedu@tatatrusts.org</a></b> along with the below-listed documents.', 'Clear scanned copies of the mandatory documents must be sent to the Trust office in a single PDF<br>\r\n\r\n1. Application clearly stating the complete family and academic background<br>\r\n2. Marksheet for the academic year 2021-2022<br>\r\n3. Family income proof â Latest Pay Slip or Employer Letter.<br>\r\n4. Fee receipts for the academic year 2022-2023<br>\r\n', '1)Click the below\"Click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n2)Go through the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3)Mail your Application and necessary documents to  <b><a href=\"mailto:igpedu@tatatrusts.org\">igpedu@tatatrusts.org</a></b>', '', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '\"Class 11,  Class 12, Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-01', '2023-01-31', 'Tata Trusts ', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-09 12:06:24', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-11 08:53:52', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1286, 'l7dPovwg3awL4yjBWY', 'Abroad', 'Ritchie-Jennings Memorial Scholarship Program', 'https://www.acfe.com/about-the-acfe/acfe-foundation/scholarship', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The scholarship program was established in 1992 to provide opportunities for students who had demonstrated achievement in fraud-related studies. <br><br>\r\n<li>The Ritchie-Jennings Memorial Scholarship provides an opportunity for students to advance their education and anti-fraud career paths.<br><br><li> Additionally, it supports its anti-fraud interests by providing a full year of ACFE membership. Award amounts are $10,000, $5,000, $2,500 and $1,000, and are paid directly to the recipientâs university or college.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Eligibility Requirements:</b><br>\r\nThe next application period will provide scholarships for the 2023-2024 academic year. Interested students must demonstrate a desire to pursue a career in fraud examination or similar anti-fraud profession and:<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Have a declared major or minor in accounting, business administration, finance, criminal justice or other fraud-related disciplines.<br>   <br>\r\n<li>Be currently enrolled full-time at an accredited, four-year college or university and be enrolled through the 2023-2024 academic year.<br><br>\r\n<li>Undergraduates must be enrolled in 9 semester hours (or equivalent) per term and must be a junior, senior, or at least in the second half of their sophomore year when applying.   <br><br>\r\n<li>Graduates must be enrolled in 6 semester hours (or equivalent) per term.', '<li>A completed application.<br>\r\n<li>Fraud-related interests, activities, goals and desired career path.<br>\r\n<li>Overall academic achievement demonstrated by transcripts.<br>\r\n<li>Recommendation forms.<br>\r\n', '1)Click on the \"click here to apply button\"<br>\r\n2)Read the details of the scholarships carefully<br>\r\n3)Click on \"scholarship application portal\" under the How to apply