(1295, 'hcCQu7GjiYBxrblEqS', 'Internship', 'NITI Aayog Internship', 'https://www.niti.gov.in/internship', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The internship is aimed at allowing  short-term exposure of \"selected candidates\" work with the different Verticals/ Divisions/Units of NITI Aayog, Government of India as \'Interns\'<br><br>\r\n<li>To a1low young academic talent to be associated with the NITI Aayog\'s work for mutual benefit.<br><br>\r\n<li>The interns shall have an opportunity to know about the Government functioning and Developmental Policy issues in the Government of India and contribute to the Policy formulation by generating policy inputs\r\nsuch as empirical analysis, briefing reports, policy papers, etc.<br><br><li>The period of Internship shall be at least six weeks but not\r\nexceeding six months<br><br>\r\n<li>Internship shall be available throughout the year based on the requirements of NITI Aayog and the application link is open from <b>1st - 10th of every month</b><br><br>\r\n<li> A <b>certificate</b> regarding successful completion of\r\ninternship sha11 be issued <br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> Under-graduate students, having completed/appeared in the term end\r\nexams of the second year/4th, semester of the bachelor\'s degree course and\r\nsecured not less than 85% or equivalent marks in the 12th class.<br><br>\r\n<li> Graduate students having completed/ appeared in the term end exams of first year/2nd semester of their post-graduate program or perusing research/Ph.D. and secured not less than 70% or equivalent\r\nmarks in Graduation.<br><br>\r\n<li>The students who have appeared in the final exam or just completed Graduation/PG and waiting for admission for higher studies may also\r\nbe considered for internship provided that they have secured 70% or more cumulative marks in all the years/\r\nsemesters of their graduation/ post-graduation till the date of application<br>\r\n', '<li>The selected applicant has to produce original mark sheets<br>\r\n<li> NOC from the college/institution at the time of joining.<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> For Detailed information click <b><a href=\"https://www.niti.gov.in/sites/default/files/2018-12/NITI_Internship_Guidelines.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></b>\r\n', '1)Click on the below \"click here to apply button\"<br>\r\n2)Read the terms and conditions of the Internship<br>\r\n3)Fill out the application and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4)Submit', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\",\"PHD (All)\"]', '\"Bachelors, Masters, PHD\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-01', '2022-12-10', 'Government of India', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-13 12:47:19', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-21 09:34:11', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1296, 'mFurNt2tEq2M24PRqN', 'Internship', 'Teach for India', 'https://teachforindia.secure.force.com/careers/job?id=a0i9C000000023IQAQ', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=the+global+scholarship', 'Teach For India is on a journey to reach an India free of poverty and filled with love by ending educational inequity in our country. <br><br><li>Twelve years into our journey we are a movement of 3800 Alumni working at all levels of the education system, who are reaching 1 in 10 children across the country. <br><br><li>These Alumni have graduated from our two-year Fellowship Program where they taught in under-resourced classrooms to put 32,000 low-income children on a different life path. <br><br><li>Today, we have 970 Fellows and are the largest pipeline of driven, skilled talent into the educational ecosystem in India.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Benifits:</b><br>\r\n<li> Certificate of internship and a letter of recommendation.<br>\r\n<li>Being part of the Teach For All network, our staff get support from partner organizations globally which includes access to resources, opportunities for thought partnering, invitations to participate in conferences\r\nWell-being Initiatives.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Position Summary:</b><br>\r\nThe Intern will play a key role in supporting city operations, thus playing a crucial role in shaping Teach For Indiaâs work for the next decade. Working directly with the city leadership team, the intern will have a front-row seat to key strategic decisions and operations in the city and will support the team with data analysis, design of presentations, communications, and operations. The duration of the internship will be <b>6 months</b>. You are the right fit for this internship if designing creative presentations and communicating impactfully are your strengths, and you have a deep desire to contribute to deep and impactful work in the education sector.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Responsibilities:</b><br>\r\nSupport the City Director with developing and executing priorities, cultivate a weekly plan of action\r\nSupport the leadership team with strategic decisions through data analysis and presentations\r\nDesign newsletters, and mailers for communication to internal and external stakeholders<br><hr>\r\n\r\n<b>Knowledge and Technical Skills:</b><br>\r\n<li>Proficiency in MS PowerPoint<br>\r\n<li>Proficiency in Canva<br>\r\n<li>Proficiency in Design software (optional)<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Competencies and Abilities:</b>\r\n<li>Excellent spoken and written communication skills<br>\r\n<li>Ability to manage time across different projects<br> \r\n<li>Ability to work with, and invest, multiple stakeholders toward common outcomes<br><hr>', '<li>An essay of a minimum of 150 words<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> For more details regarding the internship click <b><a href=\"https://teachforindia.secure.force.com/careers/job?id=a0i9C000000023IQAQ\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></b>\r\n\r\n', '1) Hit the below \"click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n2) Go through the Internship details<br>\r\n3) Click on the apply button<br>\r\n4) Fill out the application<br>\r\n5) Submit', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-10', '2022-10-30', 'Teach for India', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-14 10:29:34', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-14 05:34:21', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1297, 'lIh0vx0Iwa9ZF7PXmI', 'Internship', 'ISEC Internship', 'http://www.isec.ac.in/Project-internship.htm', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Institute for Social and Economic Change (ISEC) is one of the earliest and largest premier inter-disciplinary research institutions working on social science research in India<br><br>\r\n<li>It has also been providing valuable policy feedback to bring about integrated social, economic, and political transformation<br><hr>\r\n<b>Objective:</b><br>\r\nThe core objective of this initiative is to provide opportunities to young students who have completed post-graduation or M.Phil to work on any of the research projects of the Institute. This would enable them to understand the nuances of and participate in interdisciplinary research projects in social science.<br><br>\r\n <b>Duration:</b><br>\r\n\r\nTenure of internship shall be for three months initially and is extendable further subject to project requirement. The term, however,  is coterminous with the tenure of the project<br><br>\r\n <b>Allowance:</b><br>\r\n\r\nThe selected interns will be paid a salary of <b>Rs.8,000/-, per month</b>.  No traveling allowance shall be paid to the interns.  Subject to availability, food and accommodation could be provided at prevailing charges. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b> Essential qualifications:</b><br>\r\n\r\nPG/M. Phil completed candidates of humanities/arts/social sciences are preferred. <br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> -\r\nThere is no limiting date for the application but the interns will be taken as and when the vacancy and the preferred time of the student match.', '<li>The application copy<br>\r\n<li>Marksheet<br>\r\n<li>Statement of purpose<br>\r\n<li>two references <br>\r\n<li>medical fitness certificate <br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b>- Above mentioned documents are to be posted on: <br>\r\n<p style=\"color:blue;\">The Registrar, Institute for Social and Economic Change<br>\r\n Dr. VKRV Rao Road<br>\r\nNagarabhavi  P O<br>\r\nBangalore, 560 072</p>\r\n<br>', '1) Hit the below \" click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n2) Read the guidelines of the internship carefully<br>\r\n3) Download the application form <br>\r\n4) Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n5) Post it to the above-given address<br>', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"PG or M. Phil (humanities, arts, social sciences)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-15', '2022-12-31', 'Institute for Social and Economic Change', 8000.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-14 12:39:37', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-14 07:41:49', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1298, 'IohzjAlkTM87Dr4uSC', 'Internship', 'Dream girl Foundation Internship', 'https://dreamgirlfoundation.ngo/internshiptraining-registration/?gclid=Cj0KCQjw94WZBhDtARIsAKxWG-9SKuxgRCZtzg2EN1f4L1YebI9fCZGGt6U8OKRyAhMmvAsd1CXo0I0aAontEALw_wcB', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Dream Girl Foundation works for a selfless cause by joining hands with people who want to work selflessly for our nation. <br><br>\r\n<li>We have been able to provide help to a lot of needy children so that they live happy life and become noble citizens of our country.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Dream Girl Foundation provides Internship/Training to Students of courses like MSW, It also included the virtual Internship for students residing outside Delhi-NCR.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Duties:</b><br>\r\n<li>Teach Poor & Needy Children under the age of 14<br>\r\n<li>Manage all the related activities related to the center as per instructions from Head Office<br>\r\n<li>Attract new Children to the Non-Formal Education (NFE) Center.<br>\r\n<li>Arranging Refreshments, Stationary, etc. items that are needed for the NFE Center program\r\nAnd to perform all such related activities which are required in Day to Day running of the NFE Center<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b><br>\r\n1)The timing of the job is 09:30 AM to 12 Noon and the job is <b>unpaid</b>. <br>\r\n2)You will be entitled to get the <b>volunteer certificate</b> from the organization if you perform the above task for <b>at least 2 months</b>.<br>\r\n3)Location of Job:<br>\r\n<p style=\"color:blue;\">Dream Girl Foundation â NFE Center<br>\r\n99F, B Block, Surya Vihar<br>\r\nNr. Sec-4 Police Sation<br>\r\nGurgaon, Haryana-122001<br></p>\r\n4)<b>WFH</b> Internships are available for graphic designers, content writers, social media managers, etc', '<li>University name<br>\r\n<li>Transcripts<br>\r\n', '1) Hit the below \"click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n2) Go to the  <b>\"Volunteer\"</b> section under <b>\"Get involved\"</b> and read