(1303, 'fh8WGgy4s6Mry8emaq', 'Internship', ' National Urban Digital Mission fellowship', 'https://niua.in/cdg/NUDM-Fellowship/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'MoHUA is looking for capable leaders from diverse backgrounds and disciplines who are committed to making a positive difference in the world. <br><br>\r\n<li>The NUDM Fellows will have an opportunity to lead the adoption of a transformative Mission across the nation. Participating in a fast-paced work experience program such as the NUDM Fellowship will be a challenging, but rewarding experience for young professionals. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Fellows interested in governance will have an opportunity to lead the implementation of a transformative mission on e-governance, work closely with domain experts and Mission leadership across all levels of governance; and experience a tangible expansion in their technical and professional skills including in-depth knowledge of the application of policy, technology, and urban program management.<br><hr>\r\n<b>Note:</b><br>\r\n<li>The maximum age of the candidate should not be more than 32 years as on 31 July 2022. <br>\r\n<li>Candidates must enlist their fluency (written and verbal) in Indian regional languages; with preference shown for candidates with fluency in more than 1 regional language. <br>\r\n<li>All Fellows must necessarily display critical thinking and problem-solving abilities in an assignment as part of the recruitment process. <br>\r\n<li> professionals with 1st Division or minimum 60% marks in their highest qualification.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates must possess a minimum of 06 months of indicative experience (in project coordination, business development, or sales) after the completion of their graduation degree; and a minimum of 02 years of cumulative work experience after graduation. <br>\r\n<li>The candidate should be available to commence the Fellowship on 01 January 2023 (tentative). Attending the induction program is ma