(1313, 'ADTL1ighsMOv4gV1CL', 'Scholarship', 'Geddes Scholarship For Town Planning & Architecture', 'http://www.sanskritifoundation.org/Geddes-Fellowship.htm', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xtxZXXnh3Pg&list=PLGF-es7U0ZzHrYPTCkF2FAADSqqlb7SSt&index=19', 'The Sanskriti Foundation invites applications for its annual Geddes Scholarship for the study of the methodology and principles of Geddes town planning from students of planning and architecture/young professionals.<br><br>\r\n<li>Sanskriti has also expanded the scope by including other institutions, like schools that would be interested in sensitizing school children at a time when they are reading history and social sciences. By way of a School Project, incorporating Geddesâ ideas, children will be introduced to the concepts of architecture and town planning.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Indian Nationals in the age group of 20 to 30<br>\r\n<li>Student of planning and architecture at a graduate/postgraduate/research level / young practicing professionals<br>\r\n<li>The applicants can be an individual or can be collaborative work of a group of individuals.<br>\r\n\r\n ', '<li> 2 page CV<br>\r\n <li> Full postal and telephonic contact details together with E-mail id<br>\r\n<li>The proposal which would advance the application of the Geddes ideas, a plan of action including field visits, and the availability of archival material relevant to that study. <br>\r\n<li>A bibliography of the reports and websites browsed should accompany the proposal.<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b>\r\n<li> The names and contact addresses/telephones of two referees should also be sent. The application should bear the title âSanskriti â Geddes Scholarship â on the envelope if sent by post to the <b> <a href=\"http://www.sanskritifoundation.org/contactus.htm\" target=\"_blank\">head office address</a></b>\r\nand in the subject line if e-mailed on <b><a href=mailto:\"mail@example.com\">fellowships@sanskritifoundatio