(1325, 'oknp3GQVcPkAZ3Ni62', 'Abroad', 'Justus & Louise van Effen Excellence Scholarships', 'https://www.tudelft.nl/en/education/practical-matters/scholarships/justus-louise-van-effen-excellence-scholarships/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'At TU Delft a number of scholarships are available for excellent international applicants. Justus & Louise Van Effen Excellence Scholarships are financed by the legacy of Justus and Louise van Effen. Mr. van Effen studied at TU Delft in the 1940s and strongly believed technological developments will contribute to solving societal issues.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Foundation Justus & Louise van Effen was established with the aim of stimulating excellent international MSc students and financially supporting them in their wish to study at TU Delft.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility	:</b><br>\r\n<li>You are an excellent international applicant (conditionally) admitted to one of the 2-year Regular TU Delft MSc programs (not a Joint Education Programme).<br>\r\n\r\n<li>You have a cumulative grade point average (GPA) of 80 percent or higher of the scale maximum.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>You have a bachelor\'s degree from an internationally renowned university outside of The Netherlands.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>You have submitted a complete MSc application before the scholarship deadline<br><br>\r\n<b>Reward:</b><br>\r\n\r\nFull tuition fees per year for a TU Delft MSc program based on the statutory fee or institutional rate, according to the registered nationality, AND contribution for the living expenses.\r\n', '<li>Upload the English language certificate<br>\r\n <li>Complete your MSc application<br>\r\n<li>Upload two reference letters<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> For more details regarding the scholarship click  <b><a href=\"https://www.tudelft.nl/en/education/practical-matters/scholarships/justus-louise-van-effen-excellence-scholarships/\" target=\"_blank\">here<a></b>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"MSc\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-20', '2022-12-01', 'TU Delft University', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-27 10:15:27', 1, NULL, '2022-09-27 12:11:38', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1326, 'UuD8JMYyML0qfBlmqN', 'Scholarship', ' INSPIRE-Scholarship for Higher Education (INSPIRE-SHE)', 'https://www.online-inspire.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Department of Science & Technology (DST) has taken several pioneering initiatives to attract\r\nmeritorious students to study basic and natural sciences at the college and university level and to pursue<br><br>\r\n<li>Research careers in both basic and applied science areas including engineering, medicine, agriculture, and veterinary sciences through various components under INSPIRE. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> Meritorious Students with aggregate marks within the top 1% of their Class XII examination of any\r\nState/ Central Board (same year i.e. 2022) in India are eligible to apply. In addition, the student must be pursuing courses in Natural\r\nand Basic Sciences at the B.Sc., B.S., and Int. M.Sc./M.S. level.<br>\r\n                                       <b>  or</b><br>\r\n<li>Those students who have secured ranks in the JEE of IIT, AIPMT, NEET (within the top 10,000 ranks),\r\nand are presently pursuing Natural and Basic Science courses in India at the B.Sc., B.S., Int. M.Sc./M.S.\r\nlevel.<br>\r\n                                      <b> or</b> <br>\r\n<li> National Talent Search Examination (NTSE) scholars, Jagadish Bose National Science Talent\r\nSearch (JBNSTS) scholars and International Olympiad medalists pursuing Bachelor/ Master level\r\ncourses in Natural and Basic Science courses are also eligible. <br><br>\r\n', '1. Passport size photograph  (JPEG50 KB 2.)<br>\r\n2. Class X Mark Sheet or Certificate, for proof of Date of Birth. (PDF 1 MB) <br>\r\n3. Class XII Mark Sheet (PDF 1 MB)<br>\r\n4. Endorsement Form signed by the Principal of College/Director of Institute/Registrar of\r\nUniversity  (PDF 1 MB )<br>\r\n5. Eligibility Note/Advisory Note if provided by the State/Central Board  (PDF 1 MB)<br>\r\n 6. Certificate specifying Rank or Award in IIT-JEE/AIPMT/NEET\r\n/JBNSTS/ NTSE / International Olympic Medalists (if applicable) (PDF 1 MB) <br>\r\n7. Community/Caste Certificate <br>', '1. Hit the below \"click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"B.Sc. or B.S. and Int. M.Sc. or M.S.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-20', '2022-10-31', 'Government of India', 60000.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-27 10:51:21', 1, NULL, '2022-09-27 10:54:06', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1327, 'PbByUhXU7H4V1ETY3d', 'Abroad', 'Chevening South Asia Journalism Fellowship (SAJP)', 'https://www.chevening.org/fellowship/sajp/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Fellows will undertake a bespoke 8-week fellowship titled âGood Governance in a Changing World: the Media, Politics and Society. <br><br>\r\n<li>The programme explores the different ways in which the media play a part in holding democratic processes to account, including government, the civil service and security, as well as the broader political system in both the South Asia region and the UK.<br><br>\r\n<li>During this programme, fellows will explore the range of approaches taken by the UK and the South Asia region, and then use that knowledge to direct discussions that tackle the big issues challenging the field. <br><br>\r\n<li>Fellows will be challenged to discuss the evidence-based context for key policy debates, understand international positions (including appreciation of UK approaches), supply practical experience, and encourage dialogue on key issues.<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n<li>Full programme fees<br>\r\n<li> Living expenses for the duration of the fellowship<br>\r\n<li> Return economy airfare from your country of residence to the UK<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> Return to your country of citizenship at the end of the period of the fellowship<br>\r\n\r\n<li> Have a postgraduate level qualification (or equivalent professional training or experience in a relevant area) at the time of application<br>\r\n\r\n <li>Have at least seven yearsâ work experience prior to applying<br>\r\n\r\n<li> Be a mid-career journalist working in the political or economic sectors in one of the above-mentioned countries and good working knowledge of English to be assessed in your application form and if you are invited to interview<br>\r\n\r\n<li> Not hold British or dual-British citizenship<br>\r\n\r\n', '<li> Official degree certificate (original  which does not need to be translated into English.)<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> For more details click <b> <a href=\"https://www.chevening.org/fellowship/sajp/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></b>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n2. Go through the details of the competition carefully<br>\r\n3. Click on the\" apply now \" button<br>\r\n4. Fill out the application form and submit', '', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"Postgraduation\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-20', '2022-10-12', ' UK Foreign, Commonwealth, and Development Office', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-28 09:54:18', 1, NULL, '2022-09-28 04:24:18', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1328, 'k6wRcGrLDLoaWgP1vK', 'Abroad', 'International Graduate Scholarship 2023 in Japan.', 'https://www.titech.ac.jp/english/admissions/prospective-students/graduate-programs/igp-c', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Tokyo Institute of Technology is offering International scholarships for students of any nationality. Tokyo Institute of Technology Scholarships is a Fully Funded Scholarship available for the academic session of 2023-24.<br><br>\r\n<li>The university has more than 30,000 national and international students. University is ranked 3rd in the country and 20th in the global. The institute is providing high-quality education to its students also Japan is the hub of education<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Tuition Fee: Enrollment and Full Tuition Fees will be Exempted.<br>\r\n<li>Traveling Cost: Round Airfare Tickets will be given from the Home country to Japan and from Japan to the Home country.<br>\r\n<li>Monthly Stipend:<br>\r\nMasters Degree: 147,000 Yen/Month<br>\r\nDoctoral Degree: 148,000 Yen/Month<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Contact any intended Supervisor by Sending your CV  and getting an Acceptance letter and sending the same to the Admission Office<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Applicants who have completed 16 years of education (Masters\'s Degree) successfully from other than Japan or whose degree is going to complete before the enrollment date.<br>\r\n<li>International students from any part of the globe with any nationality who has diplomatic relations with Japan.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate must be born on or after 2 April 1987.\r\nStudents must apply for the academic study field that applicants studied at their previous university or a related field.<br>\r\n<li>Must have a Bachelorâs Degree Student if applying for Masters\'s Degree.<br>\r\n<li>Must complete Masterâs Degree to apply for Ph.D. Degree.<br>\r\n<li>If Student\'s native language is not English they can submit English Proficiency Certificate from their previous University & they are exempted from Language tests.', '<li>ID Photo<br>\r\n<li>Consent email/letter from Tokyo Tech Faculty Member<br>\r\n<li>Field of Study and Study Program (in designated format)<br>\r\n<li>Summary of thesis<br>\r\n<li>English Proficiency Score Report<br>\r\n<li>A copy of your passport or residence card<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Certificate of graduation and degree<br>\r\n<li>Supporting documentation from the referee<br>\r\n<li>Recommendation letter<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> For more details click <b> <a href=\"https://brightscholarship.com/international-graduate-scholarship-in-japan/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></b>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n2. Go through the details of the competition carefully<br>\r\n3. Click on the\" apply now \" button<br>\r\n4. Fill out the application form and submit<br>', '', '[\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', 'null', '\"Masters, PhD\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-20', '2022-10-16', 'Tokyo Institute of Technology', 83700.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-09-28 10:20:32', 1, NULL, '2022-09-28 04:50:32', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1329, '421Ct7XS7qIGSyDceM', 'Abroad', 'National Scholarship Program of the Slovak Republic (NSP)', 'https://www.scholarships.sk/en/main/programme-terms-and-conditions/foreign-applicants', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The Government of the Slovak Republic approved the establishment of the National Scholarship Program Slovak Republic for the support of mobility of students, Ph.D. students, university teachers, researchers, and artists in 2005. <br><br>\r\n<li>The National Scholarship Programme of the Slovak Republic (NSP) is funded by the Ministry of Education, Science, Research and Sport of the Slovak Republic.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Opportunity of Study in Slovakia for students from all over the world to continue their higher studies in the higher education institutions of Slovakia. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b> Rewards:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Food, Accommodation During their Stay<br>\r\n<li>University Student: 400 â¬<br>\r\n<li>Ph.D. Student: 734 â¬<br>\r\n<li>Travel Allowance for University and Ph.D. Students- 1 000 â¬.<br><br>\r\n<b> Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>All International Students from around the world are Eligible.<br>\r\n<li>University Students at Universities outside Slovakia.\r\nNote that this Slovakia full scholarship for international Students in 2023 is not a Full-time Scholarship for Full Bachelor Degree Programs, Master\'s Degree Programs, or Ph.D. Degree Scholarships.<br>\r\n', '<li>Academic Resume or CV<br>\r\n<li>Statement of Interest or Motivation<br>\r\n<li>Study Plan/Research Plan/Research Proposal<br>\r\n<li>Two Recommendation Letters<br>\r\n<li>Educational Documents (Results, Transcripts, Degrees)<br>\r\n<li>Admission or Offer letter<br>\r\n<li>Copy of Passport<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> For more details click <b> \r\n<a href=\"https://www.scholarships.sk/en/main/programme-terms-and-conditions/foreign-applicants target=\"_blank\">here</a></b>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n2. Go throu