(1380, 't4tOe0glz4urLY5Tyi', 'Scholarship', 'MCW Young Leaders Fellowship', 'https://mcwglobal.org/young-leaders-fellowship-2023/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The 2022 MCW Global Fellowship is hosted by MCW. This is a non-profit organization formed with a vision to improve the quality of education and health with better economic security for communities around the world. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The organization is constantly striving to meet the current needs of communities by empowering current young leaders and preparing future leaders for this purpose. It is based in New York with organizations affiliated with the African region.<br><br>\r\n<li>Applications are opened to apply for MCW Young Leaders Fellowship Program 2023 in the United States. MCW Global is going to provide a fully funded Exchange and leadership program. It\'s an International Leadership program for students from all over the world. <br><br>\r\n<li>The Young Leaders Fellowship Program is a kind of leadership opportunity for all young people between the ages of 18 and 26 from around the world who want to focus on community projects in the areas of education, health, and economic security.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Be between the ages of 18-26 at the start of the program (June 1, 2023)<br>\r\n<li>Be fluent in written and spoken English<br>\r\n<li>Commit to doing the Community Needs Assessment in June, attending the 10-day in-person program in July, and spending the following year aiming to execute their community project<br>\r\n<li>Have access to email and the internet to allow for consistent communication with the MCW Global Team and Young Leaders Fellowship alumni-mentor for the duration of the year-long program<br>\r\n<li>Adhere to Young Leaders Fellowship graduation guidelines (to be provided upon acceptance to the program)<br>\r\n<li>Be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 (and be able to provide proof) or in case of an exemption from this requirement due to a medical reason, contact MCW Global\r\nLeadership directly for further steps<br>\r\n<li>Be eligible for appropriate visa and travel documentation<br><br>\r\n<b>Reward:</b><br>\r\n<li>International Economy Flights for international participants<br>\r\n<li>Domestic Economy flights for United States participants<br>\r\n<li>Housing from the evening of July 10 â July 20, 2023, <br>\r\n<li>Three meals per day from July 11 â July 19, 2023, <br>\r\n<li>Round Trip Travel from New York, New York to Burlington, Vermont<br>\r\n<li>Public Transportation to/from JFK, LaGuardia, and Newark Airports<br>', '<li>Resume/CV<br>\r\n<li>Two Letters of Recommendation<br>', '1. Hit the below \"click here to apply\" button<br>\r\n\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the application form<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Fully Funded', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-14', '2022-11-18', ' MCW(Non- profit organization)', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-10-25 10:28:56', 1, NULL, '2022-10-25 04:58:56', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
