(1391, 'G1H29mEQC5Xe97ZZyE', 'Abroad', 'University of Saskatchewan Scholarship', 'https://admissions.usask.ca/requirements/deadlines.php', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Applications are invited to apply for the University of Saskatchewan Scholarships 2023 in Canada. All International Students from around the world are eligible to apply for International Scholarships at the University of Saskatchewan. <br><br>\r\n<li>Aspirants who want to study in Canada with scholarships to undertake their Bachelor\'s Degree, Masters\'s Degree, or Doctoral Degree are encouraged to apply.<br><br>\r\n<li>Almost all academic fields and majors offered by the University of Saskatchewan complete undergraduate or postgraduate degrees. These scholarships are enough to pursue your degree with all the expenses covered. <br><br>\r\n<li>The University of Saskatchewan is delivering lectures in English. The University of Saskatchewan Scholarships duration for Undergraduate is 4 Years, for a Master\'s is 2 Years and for Ph.D. is 3 Years.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>For Masters Degree: The candidate must hold an Undergraduate Degree, or equivalent, from a recognized institution or university to apply for Masters\'s Degree.<br>\r\n<li>For Ph.D. Degree: Must have a Masters\'s Degree, or equivalent, from a recognized university or institution to apply for Doctoral Degree in a relevant study field.<br>\r\n<li>For Postgraduate Diploma: Applicant must have a four-year bachelor\'s degree, or equivalent, from a recognized institution or university.<br>\r\n<li>English Language Proficiency: Students have to provide English Proficiency Certificate i.e IELTS, TOEFL, or Duolingo English Test<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>For undergraduates:$10,000.<br>\r\n<li>For Masterâs: $16,000 per year for up to 2 years.<br>\r\n<li>For  PhD: $20,000 per year for up to 3 years. <br><br>\r\n', '<li>Completed Application Form<br>\r\n<li>Official Transcripts o