(1406, 'FybKJXZoxs4TIXA22J', 'Scholarship', 'Vidyadhan  Disability Scholarship', 'https://www.vidyadhan.org/apply', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Vidyadhan Scholarship Program from Sarojini Damodaran Foundation supports the college education of meritorious students from economically challenged families. The students are selected after completion of 10th grade /SSLC through a rigorous selection process including tests and interviews. <br> <br>\r\n<li>Currently, the Vidyadhan program has around 5000 students across the following states: Kerala, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Pondicherry, Andhra Pradesh, Gujarat, Maharashtra, Telangana, Goa, Odisha, New Delhi, and Ladhak. <br> <br>\r\n\r\n<li>Those selected will be eligible for a two-year scholarship from the Foundation. If they continue to do well, they will be given scholarships for pursuing any degree course of their interest; these scholarships are directly through the foundation or external sponsors who have registered with the Foundation.  <br> <br>\r\n<li>The scholarship amount for graduation courses varies from Rs 10,000 to Rs 60,000 per year depending on the state, course, duration, etc. The selected students will be required to attend the mentoring programs from the Foundation. <br> <br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li> For students with a disability of having 40% <br>\r\n<li> The family annual income shall be less than Rs. 400000.00<br>\r\n<li>They should also have scored 60% or obtained a 6 CGPA in their 12th Grade/HSC examination. <br>\r\n<li>They should have joined the degree in the year 2022. <br>', 'Scanned copies of the following are required<br>\r\n<li>Photograph <br> \r\n<li>12th Marksheet  <br>\r\n<li>Income Certificate   (from a competent authority; ration card not accepted.)<br>\r\n<li>Disability Certificate   (for those applying in the disability category)<br>', '1) Hit the below \"Click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n\r\n2) Read the scholarship guidelines carefully<br>\r\n3) Click on the \"Apply now\" button<br>\r\n4) Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n5) Submit the application', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\"]', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 400000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-11-01', '2022-11-15', ' Sarojini Damodaran Foundation', 60000.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-04 11:51:03', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-04 06:25:03', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1407, 'FOVPbwfR2zNgSXQQXf', 'Scholarship', ' Mahindra All India Talent Scholarship', 'https://www.kcmet.org/what-we-do-Scholarship-Grants.aspx#bobcontent3-title', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The K. C. Mahindra Education Trust established the Mahindra All India Talent Scholarship in 1995. This scholarship is awarded to students belonging to economically disadvantaged families, who wish to pursue a job-oriented Diploma course at a recognized Government Polytechnic in India. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This Scholarship was established to encourage and support young students from rural and urban areas to pursue job-oriented Diplomas. <br>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Since its inception, the trust has promoted education mainly by way of scholarships and grants to deserving and needy students. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This Trust awards Rs. 10,000/- per annum to 550 students annually, for a maximum period of 3 years. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Candidate should have passed SSC/HSC or equivalent examinations in the 10th /12th standard with more than 60% marks.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate should have secured admission in a government or any other recognized Polytechnic Institute for the diploma course. Only first-year candidates are eligible to apply.<br>\r\n<li>The candidate should belong to a family with a low yearly income.<br>\r\n<li> Preference will be given to girl students, children from lower income group families, differently abled children, and children of armed forces personnel.<br>\r\n', '<li>Proof of admission(Eg: Admission letter,\r\nAllotment letter, Fee receipt, Bonafide student certificate, etc)<br>\r\n<li>Recommendation letter from any one of the two referees (teacher/employer)<br>\r\n<li>A short statement as to your general aptitude and interest, the type of vocation you would like to\r\npursue your ambitions and aspirations in life<br>\r\n<li>Certificate of Date of Birth <br>\r\n<li>Copy of Mark Sheet of Std. 10th and Std. 12th <br>\r\n<li>Family Income certificate copy<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar card copy<br>', '1) Hit the below \"Click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n\r\n2) Read the scholarship guidelines carefully<br>\r\n3) Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4) Submit the application', '', '[\"Diploma in Technical\"]', '[\"Diploma in Technical (All)\"]', '\"Diploma\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-12-25', '2022-11-07', 'Mahindra Education Trust ', 10000.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-05 10:27:30', 1, NULL, '2022-11-05 04:57:30', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1408, 'dIahCFFQt5CoOpIGry', 'Scholarship', 'Post-matric scholarship(Karnataka)', 'https://bcwd.karnataka.gov.in/new-page/PostMatric%20Scholarship%20Application/en', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'The Government of Karnataka has launched SSP (State Scholarship Portal) Scholarship to help students in their education. <br><br>\r\n<li>Financial assistance will be provided to students who are intelligent enough in their studies but unable to afford education due to a lack of financial means. Students can visit the SSP website and apply for this scholarship.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> Applicants must belong to a backward community to apply for post-matric scholarships.<br>\r\n<li>Should be studying in class 11th or any other course.<br>\r\n<li>There is a 30% reservation for girls.<br>\r\n<li>In the qualifying examination, the candidate should score at least 50% marks.<br>\r\n<li>The annual income of the candidate\'s family should not exceed 2 lakhs.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants must be permanent residents of Karnataka.<br>', '<li>Student\'s SATS Number / College Registration Number<br>\r\n<li>Aadhaar number of student and parent <br>\r\n<li>Family identification number of the student or parent<br>\r\n<li>Enrollment Number of National Scholarship Portal (Applicable to Minority Students Only) <br>\r\n<li>Caste or Income or Economically Weaker Section (for Brahmin students only) number of certificates starting with RD in the student\'s name.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Scorecard<br>\r\n<li>Fee Receipt<br>\r\n<li>Handicapped Card Number issued by Govt of India in case of disabled student<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Note:</b><br>\r\n<li> It is mandatory for minority students to apply to National Scholarship Program before applying to State Scholarship Program.<br>\r\n<li>Students studying in Karnataka state are not required to e-authenticate the fee receipt.<br>', '1) Hit the below \"Click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2) Login with your credentials<br>\r\n3) Read the scholarship guidelines carefully<br>\r\n4) Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n5) Submit the application', '', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-10-21', '2022-12-31', 'Government of Karnataka', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-05 16:01:55', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-05 10:35:27', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1409, 'p0b56njyr1KlISWb6v', 'Scholarship', 'Suvarna jubliee merit scholarship- Kerala', 'https://www.dcescholarship.kerala.gov.in/dce/he_ma/he_maindx.php#dialog', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Department of Collegiate Education and Government of Kerala offer Scholarships to the State\'s economically backward students of Tribal, SC, ST, OBC, and Minority Communities for Pre and Post-Matric Students in the State for the Academic year of 2022-2023.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Several Subsidiary Departments under the State Government of Kerala provide different schemes under the DCE scholarship program. The DCE scholarship\'s last date varies for each scheme. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>However, the DCE scholarship 2021 last date will fall on November(expected) for the post-matric scholarship for minorities.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Should be a first-year student of Under Graduate or Post Graduate course in Govt/ Aided colleges or University Departments.<br>\r\n<li>Should belong to the BPL family.<br>\r\n<li>Should have scored 50% or above in the qualifying Examination.<br>\r\n<li>Open to students belonging to <b>Kerala</b> state only <br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> For more information click <b><a href=\"https://www.dcescholarship.kerala.gov.in/shared_area/dce/SJMS/instruction/63266_SJMS_10%2009%202021%2005%2039%2049am_suwarna%20jubilee%20notifi%201%20.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a></b>\r\n', '1) Applicant Photo<br>\r\n2) Proof of Identity<br>\r\n3) Proof of Address<br>\r\n4) Proof of Income<br>\r\n5) Student Bank passbook/Kiosk<br>\r\n6) 10th, 12th and latest Marksheet<br>\r\n7) Current year fees receipts<br>\r\n8) Admission Letter / Bonafide certificate from the institute<br>\r\n', '1) Hit the below \"Click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n\r\n2) Read the scholarship guidelines carefully<br>\r\n3) Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4) Submit the application<br>', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\"]', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-11-08', '2022-12-31', 'Government of Kerala', 10000.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-08 09:36:21', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-08 04:17:27', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
