(1423, 'ClhrIHRfVTPLILgNhF', 'Scholarship', 'HelpOne Scholarship Programme ', 'https://www.vidyasaarathi.co.in/Vidyasaarathi/login', '', '', '', '', '', 'HelpOne is a crisis support program for students from families in distress due to a deadly health crisis. <br><br>\r\n<li>Conceptualized during the pandemic, the program continues to be relevant as children are highly susceptible to falling out of schooling when the families are dealing with a crisis and enabling the families to continue investing in their child\'s education. <br><br>\r\n<li>The support, rendered for up to 3 years, aims to act as a crutch to enable families to continue investing in their child\'s education.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligiility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Minimum 35% in Class 12<br>\r\n <li>Minimum 35% in Diploma<br>\r\n<li>Minimum 35% in Graduation<br>\r\n<li>The scheme is available to students whose family income is less than 500000.00<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship will be extended to students who:\r\nhave lost one more family member from January 2020 till date belonging to families that suffered cumulative hospitalization of 15 days more.<br>\r\n<li>Belongs to families with an annual income of upto Rs. 5,00,000 and are Indian nationals<br>\r\n<li>Currently studying in any Under Graduate course\r\nStudents must be referred by an Eaton employee or an Eaton NGO partner.\r\n<br><br>\r\n1) Which Courses are covered under the scheme?\r\n<li>Any courses from institutes recognized by AICTE/NAAC/UGC/Govt.\r\n<br><br>\r\n2) Whether applicant compulsory to have a bank account?\r\n<li>No, The sponsorship amount may be transferred to the student/parents\' legal guardians\' account.\r\n<br><br>\r\n3) Any Preference to Caste ?\r\n<li>No (Open to all Caste)\r\n<br><br>\r\n4) Is this gender based scholarship?\r\n<li>No, Irrespective of gender anyone can apply.\r\n<br><br>\r\n5) Any preference will be given based on the location?\r\nNo, Students belonging from any location can apply for the scholarship\r\n<li><br><br>\r\n6) What is the maximum scholarship amount that will be awarded?\r\n<li>Upto INR 19000\r\n<br><br>', '<li> Applicant Photo<br>\r\n<li> Proof of Identity<br>\r\n<li> Proof of Address<br>\r\n<li> Proof of Income<br>\r\n<li> Beneficiary Bank passbook/canceled cheque\r\n Current proof of admission - Admission Letter / Bonafide certificate from institute/ school fee receipt<br>\r\n<li> Latest College Marksheets (Except for first-year students)<br>\r\n<li> Proof of crisis - Death Certificate/ Medical report\r\n<li> Proof of relationship with hospitalized/ deceased (birth certificate/ ration card/ school certificate)<br><br>\r\n<li>All documents uploaded shall be clear and must be in a .jpeg .png file only<br>', '1) Hit the below \"Click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2) Login with your credentials<br>\r\n3) Read the scholarship guidelines carefully<br>\r\n4) Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n5) Submit the application', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"Bachelors (All)\",\"Masters (All)\"]', '\"Undergraduates, postgraduate\"', NULL, NULL, 50.00, 50.00, 50.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 500000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-11-10', '2022-11-30', 'Eaton India Foundation', 19000.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-11-11 12:11:17', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-05 11:43:02', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
