(1441, 'x74NLh1nTl0T6ckn1I', 'Abroad', 'Commonwealth Shared Scholarship', 'https://cscuk.fcdo.gov.uk/scholarships/commonwealth-shared-scholarships-applications/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'Applications are invited to apply for Commonwealth Shared Scholarship 2023-24 in the United Kingdom. All International Students from least-developed and lower-middle-income Commonwealth countries are eligible to apply for Commonwealth Scholarship. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Candidates who want to pursue their Masterâs Degree in the United Kingdom are highly encouraged to apply. It\'s a Fully Funded Scholarship for low-income students. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This is a great opportunity for all students to study in the UK for Free. The scholarship is available for the academic session of 2023-2024.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Be available to start your academic studies in the UK by the start of the UK academic year in September 2023<br>\r\n<li>Those who have completed their 4 Year Bachelor Degree or those who have completed 2 Years of bachelor\'s and 2 Years of Master\'s are eligible to apply for the Commonwealth UK Scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>By September 2023, hold a first degree of at least upper second class (2:1) honors standard, or a second class degree (2:2) and relevant postgraduate qualification (a Masterâs degree)<br>\r\n<li>Not have studied or worked for one (academic) year or more in a high-income country<br>\r\nBe unable to afford to study in the UK without this scholarship.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Reward:</b><br>\r\n<li>Approved Round Airfare Tickets from your home country to the UK and return at the end of your award.\r\nApproved Full tuition fees.<br>\r\n<li>Monthly Stipend (living allowance) at the rate of Â£1,236 Per Month, or Â£1,516 Per Month for those at universities in the London metropolitan area <br>\r\n<li>Warm clothing allowance, where applicable<br>\r\n<li>Thesis grant towards the cost of preparing a thesis