(1451, 'Miu54Y2YfbTU1tBkk6', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Know your Constitution Quiz 2022', 'https://quiz.mygov.in/quiz/know-your-constitution-quiz-2022/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/c/TheGlobalScholarshiporg', 'We feel proud to introduce an opportunity to engage with the constitution of India. The Constitution of India is a dynamic document that ensures the aspirations of âwe, the people of Indiaâ.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Indian Constitution enables the government to take positive welfare measures; some of which are legally enforceable. This dynamic document focuses on rules and regulations and gives the government power to pursue collective good for society. <br><br>\r\n<li>The Indian Constitution was adopted on 26 November 1949 and its implementation formally started on 26 January 1950.\r\nNCERT and MyGov are organizing a quiz on the MyGov platform to celebrate Constitution Day. The Quiz will help the citizens become aware and familiarised with the history of the making of our Constitution and the eminent people involved in it; the Preamble of the Constitution, Fundamental Rights and Duties, Directive Principles of State Policy, and other provisions of the constitution in both theory and practice. <br><br>\r\n<li>The Quiz will also help in preparing our future generations, committed to Constitutional values and nurturing democratic principles. It also attempts to encourage the citizens to engage creatively in many more activities to understand the significance of Constitution day.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Guidelines:</b><br>\r\n1. The Quiz questions are designed carefully to assess the knowledge and understanding of the Constitution of India.<br>\r\n\r\n2. Each question in the Quiz is in the Multiple Choice Format and has only one correct answer.<br>\r\n\r\n3. Each Question carries 1 mark. Participants can attempt 10 questions in 300 seconds.<br>\r\n\r\n4. The Quiz questions are in both Hindi and English<br>\r\n\r\n5. You are allowed to attempt the Quiz only once and only one option will be accepted for a question. However, you may revise your answer before the final submission<br>\r\n6. After responding to a question, click on the âNext Questionâ button to go to the next question<br>\r\n\r\n7. No negative marking will be done<br>\r\n\r\n8. After attempting questions, the final submission should be clicked. No changes can be made after the final submission.<br>\r\n\r\n9. The quiz will be open for one month, starting on 26 November till 26 December 2022.<br>\r\n\r\n10. Decision of NCERT, New Delhi will be final in all Quiz related matters.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1) Hit the below \"click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2) Read the terms and conditions carefully<br>\r\n3) Click on \"login to Play Quiz\" and fill in your personal details<br>\r\n4) Submit your entry', 'E-certificate', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-11-26', '2022-12-26', 'Government of India', 0.00, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-12-02 16:30:34', 1, 'gautamitimmapur@triwits.com', '2022-12-02 11:05:38', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
