(1511, 'psAwwJSz38oOccorcD', 'Scholarship', 'Inspire Scholarship For Higher Education SHE', 'https://online-inspire.gov.in/Account/Register?Length=7', '', '', '', '', '', 'Inspire Scholarship 2023 or Innovation in Science Pursuit for Inspired Research (INSPIRE) is a kind of endowment which is managed under the Department of Science and Technology. DST Inspire is offered online to search for talents in science and to motivate young, talented youths to involve in different science-based activities. \r\n<br>\r\n<li>The main feature of DST inspire is that it does not believe in testing abilities, the candidates are selected based on educational beliefs and knowledge.<br>\r\n<b>Inspire schemes has three formations â</b><br>\r\n<li>Inspire fellowship for Early Attraction of Talent<br>\r\n<li>DST Inspire Fellowship for Higher Education/ Inspire SHE Scholarship<br>\r\n<li>Assured Opportunity for Research Careers (AORC)<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicants must have passed 12th in 2022 and must be studying B.Sc. or M.Sc. Natural Science.<br>\r\n<li>The candidateâs age should be between 17 to 22 years of age.<br>\r\n<li>Must have a bank account in SBI (only in the name of the applicant).<br>\r\n<li>Candidates must come under 1% of successful students with a strong academic background.<br>\r\n<li>They must have enrolled themselves in Natural and Basic Sciences doing B.Sc, BS, and integrated M.Sc./ MS level in the same year when they pass 12th.<br>\r\n<li>Students must come under 10,000 ranking in JEE of IIT, AIEEE ( top 20,000) and must have cleared CBSE - Medical (AIPTM) if pursuing natural/ basic sciences courses.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants must be top 10,000 rankers in the Joint Entrance Examination of IIT, AIEEE (top 20,000 rankers) and would have cleared CBSE âMedical (AIPTM) and must be studying natural/ basic sciences.<br>\r\n<li>Students studying at the Indian Institute of Science and Research (IISER), National Institute of Science, Education, and Research (NISER), Department of Atomic Energy Centre for basic sciences (DAE-CBS) at the University of Mumbai for the courses like B.Sc. and M.Sc. degrees.<br>\r\n<li>Subjects that come under Scholarship for Higher Education (SHE) are:Physics, Mathematics, Statistics, Geology, Astrophysics, Astronomy, Electronics, Microbiology, Geophysics, Ecology, Marine Biology, Genetics, BioPhysics, Physics, Ocean Sciences, Chemistry.<br><br>\r\n <li><b> for any query contact on -0120-4676260<br></b>\r\n<li><b>Note:</b><br>\r\n<li>It should be mentioned by the head of the institute about the performance of the report for the current academic year.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship will be disseminated only after checking the performance of the student in the current year.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates already getting any other scholarships are not eligible.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li><b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n<li>INR 80,000 to the selected candidate.<br>\r\n<li>Yearly scholarship of INR 60,000 for 12 months i.e. 5000 per month.<br>\r\n<li>INR 20,000 for important summer research.\r\n<li>Inspire scholarship 2023 result i.e. the list of candidates will be announced the next year 2023 in April âMay.<br>\r\n', '<li>Your passport size photograph â 50kb size.<br>\r\n<li>Community/ Caste certificate if belongs to OBC/ SC/ ST category â size < 1 MB.<br>\r\n<li>Eligibility/ advisory note by state/ central board â size < 1 MB.<br>\r\n<li>Marksheet of class 12th < 1 MB.<br>\r\n<li>Certificate showing rank in JEE Main/ JEE Advanced/ NEET/ KVPY/ JBNSTS/ NTSE/ International Olympic medalists (if you fall under this category)- size < 1 MB.<br>\r\n<li>Your endorsement form signed by your college principal/ director of the institute/ registrar of the university- 1 MB size.<br>\r\n<li>The details of SBI bank - 1 MB size<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '60000', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 250000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-01', '2023-12-31', 'Department of Science and Technology, Govt. of India', 60000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-09 12:31:50', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-12 04:36:26', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1512, '1OMwwFVYLXQIT2wCYJ', 'Scholarship', 'Malla Reddy Scholarship', 'https://admissions.mallareddyuniversity.ac.in/', 'bachelor scholarships, technology scholarships, b tech scholarship, engineering scholarships, study grants, student funding, scholarship programs, fully funded scholarships, undergraduate scholarships, free scholarships, the global scholarship, best scholarship website, scholarships for indian students, financial help for students, student scholarship, student financial aid, grants for college, apply for scholarships, Scholarships, free scholarships to apply for, free online scholarship, scholarships for online courses, apply for scholarships online for free, scholarships for students, free scholarship, apply for college scholarships, graduate student scholarships, apply for scholarship college  scholarships for me, scholarship website, best scholarship websites, scholarship search, scholarship for indian students, university scholarship, free scholarship in india, find a scholarship, best scholarships for indian students, new scholarship, all india scholarship, scholarship after 12th, PHD Scholarship', 'Malla Reddy University Scholarship - MRU Hyderabad', 'Malla Reddy University is inviting applications for the scholarship program which is available if students are performing really well in the MUCET Examination.', 'Malla Reddy University Scholarship', '', 'Malla Reddy University is inviting applications for the scholarship program which is available if the students are performing really well in the common entrance examination which is the examination held by the concerned authorities of the university to provide animations to all of the students. 10 crore rupees will be provided in Malla Reddy University Scholarship to all of the students who are coming from the economically weaker section of society and have applied for the different types of courses available in the university. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>The students will have to give the common entrance test in order to take part in the courses available at the university and then only they will also be considered for this scholarship available by the University.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li><b>For Undergraduate Courses:</b><br>\r\n<li>Candidates must have passed their 10+2 (or) equivalent examination in relevant subjects.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates must have scored at least 60% marks (B Tech.) or 50% marks (Non-B Tech.) in the qualifying examination at 10+2 / Intermediate level and admission through the State Common Entrance Test/ MRUCET conducted by the University/ Qualifying Exam on merit.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates applying for engineering and other graduate courses should have completed 17 years as of 30th June of the year of admission.<br><br>\r\n<b>For Post Graduate Courses:</b><br>\r\n<li>Candidates must have passed 4 years duration Bachelorâs Degree from any recognized Institute or University for Engineering Streams.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates must have passed 3 years duration Bachelorâs Degree from any recognized Institute or University for any discipline to management.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates must have scored at least 60% marks in the qualifying examination at under graduation level and admission through GATE/ State Common Entrance/ MRUCET conducted by the University/Qualifying Exam on merit.<br><br>\r\n<b>For Ph.D :</b><br>\r\n<li>Candidates must have passed Mastersâs Program or equivalent qualification in the relevant field.<br>\r\n<li>Admission through NET/GATE/ Equivalent National Level Common Entrance Test/State Common Entrance Test (if any)/ Malla Reddy University Entrance Examination/ Merit & Interview conducted by the University<br><br>\r\n<b>Exam date: The common entrance examination will be held from 23rd April to 29th April 2023</b><br><br>\r\n<b>Application fee:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant will have to pay <b>Rupees 1000 </b>in order to successfully apply for the common entrance test.\r\n <br><br>\r\n<b>Programs offered:</b><br>\r\n 