(1518, 'XOim4Dv3NseyEhWYZg', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Design a logo for New India Literacy Programme', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/design-logo-new-india-literacy-programme/', 'logo, logo making contest, competition, logo maker, free logo maker, logo creator, logo maker online, contest, cash prize, win cash prize, contest reward, art and artists, artist, digital art, competitions, Logo making, free competitions, logo competition, Logo design contest, contesting, online competitions, art competition, online logo making, New India Literacy Programme, NILP', 'Logo design contest - New India Literacy Programme | Win Cash Prize', ' MyGov invites to participate in designing a logo for the New India Literacy Programme, representing the roots of the Educational system in India', 'Design a logo for NILP', '', 'Literacy is one of the essential indicators of the quality of a countryâs human capital. Literacy constitutes the backbone of development in a progressing country like India. It enhances the quality of life, awareness, and skills of people.<br><br>\r\n<li> \r\nIndia has made significant progress in the Education sector. To boost the same, the Government has announced a Centrally Sponsored Scheme, namely, the<b> âNew India Literacy Programmeâ (NILP).</b><br><br>\r\n<li>The Ministry of Education, in collaboration with MyGov, invites citizens to participate in designing a logo for the New India Literacy Programme, representing the roots of the âHolistic and Accessible Educational systemâ in India.<br><br>\r\n<li>The scheme aims to work in the following areas:<br>\r\n(i) Foundational Literacy and Numeracy.<br>\r\n(ii) Critical Life Skills.<br>\r\n(iii) Vocational Skills Development.<br>\r\n(iv) Basic Education.<br>\r\n(v) Continuing Education.<br>\r\n <br>\r\n \r\n<b>Technical Parameter</b><br><br>\r\n \r\n<li> Logo should be submitted in JPEG, PNG or PDF format only.<br>\r\n<li>The participant should submit a high-resolution (600 dpi) image of the logo in JPEG,