(1533, 'GsZlxrup8TU26qhdPo', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Microsoft Imagine Cup Competition', 'https://imaginecup.microsoft.com/en-us', 'Imagine Cup Competition, Imagine Cup Competition Microsoft, Microsoft Imagine Cup Competition, \r\ncoding contest, coding competitions, coding competitions for beginners, online coding competition, coding competitions for students, hackerrank competitive programming, hackerrank contest, coding contest online, top coding competitions, programing contest, coding competitions to earn money, coding contests for money, contest, cash prize, win cash prize, contest reward, competitions, free competitions, Free Contest, Contesting, Online competitions, Scholarship, Scholarship for all ', 'Imagine Cup Competition Â· 2023 | Microsoft', 'Imagine Cup is an annual competition sponsored and hosted by Microsoft Corp. It is a skill-based Competition | Chance to win great prizes.', 'Microsoft Imagine Cup Competition', '', 'The Imagine Cup is full of opportunities to gain new skills, access exclusive training, unlock mentorship opportunities, and have a chance to win great prizes and make a difference in the world.The Imagine Cup is more than just a technology competition. Over the past 21 years, more than two million student competitors have signed up to build and learn together, make a difference in their communities, and innovate for impact. By competing, you too can accomplish all this. Plus, you can develop your own skills as part of the journey to help prepare you for your future.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>You are at least 16 years of age as of 6 October 2022 and are actively enrolled as a student at an accredited educational institution that grants high-school or college/university (or equivalent) degrees (including home schools) at any time between 6 October 2022 and 31 May 2023.<br><br>\r\n<li>If you are 16 years of age or older but have not reached the age of majority in your legal place of residence, then you should ask your parentâs or legal guardianâs permission prior to submitting an entry into this Competition.  <br><br>\r\n<li>You are NOT a resident of Cuba, Iran, North Korea, Sudan, Syria, Russia, and the Region of Crimea; and o U.S. export regulations prohibit the export of goods and services to Cuba, Iran, North Korea, Sudan, Syria, and the Region of Crimea. Therefore, residents of these countries/regions are not eligible to participate. <br> <br>\r\n<li> You/your business has not received external funding of more than $50,000 USD, and You/your business has not used paid employee assistance in creating an Imagine Cup entry at any time. <br> <br><li> You are not an employee or intern of Microsoft Corporation, or an employee of a Microsoft subsidiary, at any time between 6 October 2022 and 31 May 2023; and  You are not involved in any part of the execution or administration of this Competition. <br> <br>\r\n<li>You are not an immediate family member of (parent, sibling, spouse/domestic partner, child) or household member of a Microsoft employee, an employee of a Microsoft subsidiary, or a person involved in any part of the administration and execution of this Competition between 6 October 2022 and May 2023. <br> <br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\nThe three (3) teams selected as winners will receive:<br>\r\n<li> $1,000 USD, to be divided equally among each officially registered member of\r\nthe Team.<br>\r\n<li> Advance to the World Finals if a working proof of concept is submitted to the\r\nOnline Semifinals.<br>\r\n<li>The top twelve (12) teams will receive:\r\n Judge feedback on their projects. <br><br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '\"Class 11, Class 12, Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-12-30', '2023-01-27', 'Microsoft Corp', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-20 15:03:36', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-21 08:07:00', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1534, 'GiDfLH0NqyV3JsHTgk', 'Scholarship', 'FFE Scholarship ', 'https://ffe.org/scholarships/', 'Student scholarship, Scholarships, Engineering scholarships, scholarship for student, study grants, Student financial aid, Student funding, Bachelor scholarships, Technology scholarships, grants for college, scholarship programs, fully funded scholarships, undergraduate scholarships, free scholarships, apply for scholarships, Scholarship for College Of Engineering Students, Study Reward for B. tech students , Bachelor of Technology scholarship, Scholarship for bachelor of technology student, High reward scholarship, Best scholarship website, Scholarships for Indian students, Professional degree course scholarships, Financial Help for students, B E Scholarship, Scholarship for MBBS Students, Scholarship for doctors, MBBS Scholarship, B. Pharm scholarship, L.L.B scholarship, M.E scholarship, M.Tech scholarship', 'Foundation For Excellence (FFE) Scholarship 2023', 'FFE Scholarship Programâs main focus is providing financial support for qualified students interested in Technology, Engineering, and Medicine.', 'FFE Scholarship', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=amGOo-Isxfg', 'FFE finds bright and deserving students with financially constrained backgrounds who performed exceptionally well at state and national level entrance exams. Once a facilitator verifies the studentâs financial need, the scholarship is awarded and their journey begins.<br><br>\r\n<li>While the Programâs main focus is providing financial support for qualified students interested in Technology, Engineering, and Medicine, FFEâs assistance extends beyond finances and includes training, mentorship, and advice from a vast network of donors and alumni. This assistance is available irrespective of the applicantâs caste, community, gender, or religion. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicants are expected to have passed their Higher Secondary Pre-University / Intermediate/ CBSE/ICSE or Equivalent Board Qualifying Examination After 2020.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Only Students who are enrolled in First-Year Studies In Professional Degree Courses like B.E., B.Tech, Integrated 5-Year Dual-Degree M.Tech, M.B.B.S, B.Pharm, And LLB are eligible.<br><br>\r\n<li>Applicants who are the first graduates of the family will be preferred over applicants who are the second or third child of the family taking up graduation.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Annual Income of the Family Should be less than Rs 3  lakh.<br><br>\r\n<li>Students must have a good Rank in the Competition Exam they have been given for the Enrollment of Course.<br><br>\r\n<li>Admission to professional degree courses or institutions is based on merit rank  awarded at the State or National level Entrance Exam or through a counseling process conducted at  the state level\r\nScholarship Amount Depends on the Education Course Scholar is Enrolled in.<br><br>\r\n<b>Note </b>Diploma Students Admitted To B.E., B.Tech Courses On A Lateral Basis. B.Arch, BDS Students Are Not Eligible.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>E-Aadhaar Card Or Original Aadhaar Card Copy.<br\r\n>\r\n<li>Domicile Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide Certificate From College / University.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th Marksheet.<br>\r\n<li>Class 12th Marksheet.<br>\r\n<li>Family Annual Income.<br>\r\n<li>Counselling Letter.<br>\r\n<li>Bank Passbook Photo Copy.<br>\r\n<li>Tuition /Hostel/ Mess Paid Bill Receipts.<br>\r\n<li>College Expenses Statement.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Engineering\",\"Masters\",\"Professional course\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"B. Pharm , L.L.B, B.E, B.Tech, M.E, M.Tech, M.B.B.S\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 300000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-03', '2023-02-04', 'Foundation For