(1536, 'TmTpBhnfkGXHWie5x7', 'Scholarship', 'India Fellow Social Leadership Program', 'https://indiafellow.org/apply-now/', 'fellowships,\r\nfellowship program in management,\r\nneuroradiology fellowship,\r\nonline fellowship,\r\njunior research fellowship,\r\nfellowship,\r\nfellowship program,\r\nresearch fellowship,\r\nthe fellows,\r\nnational fellowship,\r\nStudent scholarship, Scholarships, Engineering scholarships, scholarship for student, study grants, Student financial aid, Student funding, Bachelor scholarships, Technology scholarships, grants for college, scholarship programs, fully funded scholarships, undergraduate scholarships, free scholarships, apply for scholarships, Scholarship for College Of Engineering Students, Study Reward for B. tech students , Bachelor of Technology scholarship, Scholarship for bachelor of technology student, High reward scholarship, Best scholarship website, Scholarships for Indian students, Professional degree course scholarships, Financial Help for students, B E Scholarship', 'India Fellow Social Leadership Program 2023', 'India Fellow is an 18 month social leadership program for young Indians willing to learn from local communities and bring change.', 'India Fellow Social Leadership Program', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KUYHYHSxv9Y', 'India Fellow is an 18-month leadership program for young professionals from various walks of life, willing to work with communities and find their leadership potential to make a difference. It is an experiential journey to immerse in the social realities of our country and be your best version to build a better future.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>In the last 12 years, we have had 225 fellows from varied backgrounds having worked across the country with a total of 50 partner organizations in rural and urban areas. Fellows have been solving complex problems using frameworks in Project Management, Organizational Development, Design Thinking, Systems Practice, Community Mobilization, and Communication. In the past, we have been fortunate to be supported by <b>ICICI Foundation, Tata Trusts, Paul Hamlyn Foundation, InfoEdge Pvt. Ltd., and WaterAid.</b><br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Fellowship Design:</b><br>\r\n\r\nIndia Fellow has the following four major aspects: <br><br>\r\n<li><b> Working with Communities:</b> India Fellows spend most of their time (16.5 months) working at the grassroots with leading social organizations committed to bringing positive change. This can be anywhere across the country. The fellow is expected to live in their work area, typically a rural or a peri-urban setup, and understand the complexities at that level.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li><b>Training: </b>India Fellow has 45 days of residential training, spread across the duration of 18 months. This is divided into 3 parts of 15 days each at the start, middle, and end of the journey. The India Fellow pedagogy is unique; it engages a strong collective of various leaders, academicians, social scientists, and practitioners.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li><b>Constant engagement:</b><br> Throughout the duration, fellows document their observations, experiences, and insights; engage in intense blended learning modules, group online courses for certification and fundraising to build a holistic understanding of the development and gain crucial skill sets.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li><b>Mentor-ship: </b>Every fellow is exposed to a pool of mentors, who are experts with deep experience in their domain. Along with that, the fellowship ecosystem consists of facilitators, alumni, and experienced professionals who are available to interact with the fellows to enrich their experience.</b><br><br>\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> You are between 20 to 30 years of age.<br>\r\n<li>  You are already a graduate (in any discipline) or will be by 31st January 2023.<br>\r\n <li> You are ready for an 18-month full-time commitment to the fellowship.<br>\r\n<li>  You understand that you will be expected to engage 24*7 with the fellowship.<br>\r\n <li> You understand that you can be placed in any part of the country and in any thematic area.<br>\r\n<li> This has four steps i.e The Application, Telephonic Round, Situation Judgement Test, and Assessment day.<br>\r\n\r\n<li><b>Note: </b>Only people who make it through the entire selection process become a part of the cohort. All the above 4 steps in the process are mandatory and cannot be skipped under any circumstances.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits: </b><br>\r\nA monthly stipend of INR 16,000 in rural areas and INR 20,000 in urban areas for the duration of 18 months. This is for the fellow to arrange food and accommodation and manage other daily expenses.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Important dates :</b><br>\r\n<li>Accepting Applications: 1st Dec 2022 to 31st Jan 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Telephonic Conversations: 15th Jan 2023 to 15th Feb 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Situation Judgment Test: 1st to 20th Feb 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Assessments: 20th Feb to 5th March 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Declaration of final cohort: 10th March  2023.<br>\r\n<li>Induction: 10th April 2023.<br>\r\n', 'Documents as prescribed.', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '16000', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Bachelors\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 20, 35, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-12-01', '2023-01-31', 'ICICI Foundation, Tata Trusts, Paul Hamlyn Foundation, InfoEdge Pvt. Ltd., and WaterAid.', 16000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-21 10:06:41', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-31 03:26:12', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1537, '148NzDzd7FJ3kQeMvf', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Design a logo for 100th Episode of Mann Ki Baat', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/design-logo-100th-episode-mann-ki-baat/', 'logo, logo making contest, competition, logo maker, free logo maker, logo creator, logo maker online, contest, cash prize, win cash prize, contest reward, art and artists, artist, digital art, competitions, Logo making, free competitions, logo competition, Logo design contest, contesting, online competitions, art competition, online logo making, Design a logo for 100th Episode of Mann Ki Baat', 'Logo contest for 100th Episode of Mann Ki Baat', 'A special logo designing contest! Here\'s an opportunity for the countrymen to design a logo for the 100th Episode of #MannKiBaat!', 'Logo for Mann Ki Baat', '', 'Prime Minister Narendra Modiâs monthly Radio programme âMann Ki Baatâ has given a new lease of life to the medium of Radio, which was not very long ago increasingly becoming anachronistic. Experts in the field of mass communication consider âMann Ki Baatâ to have played a significant role in keeping Radio relevant.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Many surveys/stories have highlighted the massive impact Mann Ki Baat has had on the lives of ordinary men and women, be it vis-Ã -vis behavior change or increased awareness. This program has touched the lives of Millions across the country. It will complete its 100th edition in April 2023.<br><br>\r\n<li>Mann Ki Baat has been conceived and implemented around the idea of civic engagement and participation, right from the formulation of the name of this programme to the choice of topics and calls to action that the PM includes in this programme, for example, urging people to wear Khadi, a selfie with daughter, asking people to post pictures of places they travel, and much more.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>In the same spirit, to mark the 100th episode of Mann Ki Baat, All India Radio is seeking a logo design. <b>The logo should have an attractive design depicting the â100th episode of Mann Ki Baatâ.</b> It should be reproable in multiple formats for multiple platforms.<br><br>\r\n<b>Technical Parameters:</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Participants should upload the Logo in JPEG/ JPG/ PNG/ SVG format only.<br>\r\n<li> The Logo should be designed on a digital platform.\r\n<li> Logo should be designed in color. The size of the logo may vary from 5cm*5cm to 60cm*60cm in either portrait or landscape.<br>\r\n<li> The Logo should be usable on the website/ social media such as Twitter/ Facebook and on printed materials such as press releases, stationery and signage, labels etc.<br>\r\n<li>The Logo should be in high resolution with minimum 300 DPI.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n Cash PrizeâRs.1 Lakh\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '100000', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"\\\"All\\\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-18', '2023-02-01', 'Government of India', 100000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-21 12:28:42', 1, NULL, '2023-01-21 11:46:40', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL);
