(1545, 'qBpPfvqJ0QsKb7Cai1', 'Scholarship', 'Teach India fellowship', 'https://www.teachforindia.org/   ', 'fellowship program in management, neuroradiology fellowship, online fellowship, junior research fellowship, fellowship, post doctoral fellowship, fellowship program, research fellowship, the fellows, national fellowship, fellowship in dentistry, free scholarships to apply for, free online scholarship, free scholarship in india, find a scholarship, best scholarships for indian students, new scholarship, all india scholarship, fellowship for bachelors, Teach india fellowship', 'Teach For India Fellowship 2023 | UG', 'Teach For India Fellowship is an opportunity for India\'s brightest and most promising individuals, from the nation\'s best universities and workplaces', 'Teach India fellowship', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xPwonn4LOiE', 'Teach for India was founded in 2008 by a group of activists. The program\'s objective is to encourage the youths to share their expertise with children from low-income families and make education accessible to all.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Teach For India Fellowship is an opportunity for Indiaâs brightest and most promising individuals, from the nationâs best universities and workplaces, to serve as full-time teachers to children from underserved communities in some of the nationâs most under-resourced schools. <br><br>\r\n<li>Through this experience of teaching in classrooms and working with key education stakeholders like students, principals, and parents, our Fellows get exposed to the grassroots realities of Indiaâs education system and begin to cultivate the knowledge, skills, and mindsets necessary to attain positions of leadership in education and identify their role in building a wider movement for educational equity in the country.<br><br>\r\n<li>Teach for India Fellowship invites college students, professionals, and entrepreneurs with leadership qualities to teach underprivileged children. The Teach for India Fellowship program is for two years. The selected fellows will teach significant subjects such as English, Mathematics, Social Studies, and Science to children from class I to class X. They will work as full-time teachers in under-resourced government schools or low-income private schools. The selected fellows will receive a monthly salary and HRA as Teach for India Fellowship benefits. <br><br>\r\n<b>Important dates:</b><br>The last dates to apply for Rounds 3 and 4 are January 29th, 2023, and March 19th, 2023 respectively.<br><br> \r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The candidates should be Indian citizens or overseas citizens of India.<br>\r\n<li>They should have at least an undergraduate degree by June/July 2023, and this must be your first application to the 2023 cohort of the Teach For India Fellowship.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates who are studying or working as professionals and entrepreneurs are eligible to apply.<br>\r\n<li>The candidates should be applying to the Teach for India Fellowship for the first time.<br>\r\n<li>The candidates should be passionate and committed to the movement.<br>\r\n<li>They should possess critical thinking, problem-solving, and resolving skills.<br>\r\n<li> They must also demonstrate interpersonal skills by interacting with the stakeholders.<br>\r\n<li>The candidates should have an excellent academic record.<br>\r\n<li>They must be proficient in the English language as the selected fellows will teach in English medium schools.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:.</b><br>\r\n<li>Candidates will receive the Teach for India fellowship amount, i.e. INR 19000 per month as their salary.<br>\r\n<li>Those who are relocating will receive an amount between INR 5,300 to INR 10,000 as HRA. <br>\r\n<li>\r\nOur Fellows are placed as full-time teachers, for 2 years, in government or low-income private schools. They teach English, Mathematics, Science, and Social Studies, in English, across Grades 1 to 10. <br>\r\n<li>Teach For India Fellows teach on-ground in