(1548, 'Sckhz84nTwAXskf88X', 'Abroad', 'Government of Czech Republic Scholarships To Indian Nationals ', 'https://www.mzv.cz/public/a9/d8/db/4905142_2974245_application_form_student_2023.pdf', 'abroad scholarship, study abroad scholarships, scholarship to study, abroad for Indian students, overseas scholarship, full scholarships to study abroad, abroad scholarship for Indian students, scholarship for MBA abroad, available scholarships to study abroad, apply for scholarship to study abroad, overseas graduate scholarship, great scholarship, scholarships for Indian students, scholarship for bachelor of technology student, High reward scholarship, The global scholarship, best scholarship website, scholarships for Indian students, Professional degree course scholarships, Financial Help for students, grant for school and college students, Vice Chancellors International Excellence,     Masters abroad scholarships, Phd abroad scholarships', 'Abroad Scholarships - Study in the Czech Republic', 'The Embassy of the Czech Republic in New Delhi is announcing scholarships for the academic year 2023/2024 to graduate or postgraduate students from India', 'Government of Czech Republic Scholarships', '', 'Scholarships offered by the Government of the Czech Republic to Indian nationals under a bilateral agreement between the Czech Republic and India for the academic year 2023/2024.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>The Embassy of the Czech Republic in New Delhi is announcing scholarships for the academic year 2023/2024 to graduate or postgraduate students from India for a study stay at public universities in the Czech Republic under the bilateral agreement between the two countries.<br><br>\r\n<li>Students must submit their application and supporting documents directly (by hand/by post) to the Embassy of the Czech Republic no later than <b>15 February 2023</b> <br><br>\r\n<li>It may be noted that there is no nomination from the Government of India and the selection of recipients of scholarships is done directly by the Czech Republic.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Scholarships of this type are designed for university/college students or graduates and Ph.D. candidates (exceptionally for academic staff members) who wish to undertake study or research visits to one of the Czech public institutions of higher education. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The categories of eligible recipients are specified separately by each of the exchange programs arranged with the countries concerned. Detailed information on the entry requirements, in particular the minimum academic qualifications, can be provided by the authorities collecting applications in the eligible countries.<br><br>\r\n<li>The period of scholarship usually ranges from 2 to 10 months. Scholarships may be awarded repeatedly to the same recipients, provided that they submit a renewed application for the following academic year and are selected by the appropriate authorities in their home countries.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The documents are to be delivered in original to the address below in 2 copies (original + 1 copy) by <b>February 15, 2023:</b><br>\r\n<b>Embassy of the Czech Republic</b><br/>\r\n<b>50-M, Niti Marg, Chanakyapuri</b><br/>\r\n<b>New Delhi 110 021</b><br/>\r\n<b>India.</b><br>\r\n', '<li>A detailed plan of study/research.<br>\r\n<li>Two letters of recommendation from academic.<br><li>Supervisors or an employer.<br>\r\n<li>Photocopy of diploma (if applicable).<br>\r\n<li>Certified transcript(s) of records.<br>\r\n<li>Passport / ID copy (not required of citizens of EU/EEA countries).<br>\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates, Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 500000.00, '', '