(1551, 'lrszIdzvQVBZ6mbNyL', 'Scholarship', 'United Nations Academic Impact and MCN Millennium Fellowship ', 'https://www.millenniumfellows.org/apply', '', '', '', '', '', 'The United Nations Academic Impact and MCN proudly present the Millennium Fellowship. The Fellowship is a semester-long leadership development program on your campus to take your social impact to the next level. Access to world-class training, connections, and recognition is just an application away. \r\n<br><br>  \r\n<li>The Class of 2023 application is now open. The United Nations Academic Impact and MCN are here to elevate your leadership.<br>\r\n<li><b>CONVENE: </b>As part of a cohort of 8-20+ Millennium Fellows on your campus, convene to learn from and challenge each other. Millennium Fellows convene at least 8 times during the program.<br>\r\n<li><b>CHALLENGE: </b>Develop a plan of action for your sessions together. Meet to exchange best practices. And you could think bigger: organizing a campus-wide sustainability initiative or more.<br>\r\n<li><b>CELEBRATE: </b>When your Fellowship Campus meets the goals you made for yourselves and completed the Fellowship graduation requirements, you will earn a certificate of recognition from United Nations Academic Impact and Millennium Campus Network.<br>\r\n<li><b>CELEBRATE:</b> When your Fellowship Campus meets the goals you made for yourselves and completed the Fellowship graduation requirements, you will earn a certificate of recognition from the United Nations Academic Impact and Millennium Campus Network.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>You must be at least 18 years old, an undergraduate enrolled in a college or university, and in good standing at that academic institution for the duration of the program.<br>\r\n<li>You make a commitment to convene in person at least eight times during the Millennium Fellowship with your Campus Directors and other Fellows on your campus to share best practices and take collective action. <br>\r\n<li>Students have to meet on-campus, in person for the Fellowship sessions. If you miss sessions, this is grounds for expulsion and the forfeiture of your designation as a Millennium Fellow. Campus Directors have additional responsibilities as noted in the FAQs section on \"Campus Director Applicants.\"<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>One-to-one and small group mentorship from the MCN team, including both personal and Fellowship-based mentorship and networking opportunities to support your success in social impact work.<br>\r\n<li>Opportunities to connect with and learn from other top Campus Directors on campuses across the globe, building your global peer and professional network. <br>\r\n<li>As we expand across the globe, we will look to you as thought partners in continuing to develop this program. You can help shape a leadership development network that thousands of students around the world will benefit from.<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-12', '2023-01-31', 'United Nations Academic Impact and MCN', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 13:18:20', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-31 05:02:42', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1552, 'aKz7Clz7GHmbzgzYyw', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Biotechnology Young Entrepreneur Award ', 'https://kscste.kerala.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/BYE_Application_21.pdf', '', '', '', '', '', 'A programme to promote the commercialisation of bioscience ideas among graduate/postgraduate students in Biotechnology and to encourage them to develop biotechnology entrepreneurship.<br><br>\r\n<li> This is an annual competition organized along with a workshop. The participants, after the workshop, shall develop a Business Plan which will be judged by a panel of experts. Applications are invited twice every year during January and June.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> B.E. or B. Tech. in Biotechnology or in the area of life sciences related to biotechnology.<br>\r\n<li>Students who are pursuing post-graduate programmes (including integrated PG degree programmes) are eligible.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants having doctoral degrees are eligible to apply.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligible programs:</b><br>\r\n<li>bioinformatics, Molecular biology, microbiology, biochemistry, Genetics, and related subjects from universities/Institutes in the State of Kerala are eligible to apply.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n \r\n Cash award for winners:<br>\r\n<li>First prize -Rs. 1,00,000/-, <br>\r\n<li>Second prize -Rs. 50,000/-<br>\r\n<li>Third prize -Rs.25,000/-<br>\r\n \r\n<li> The awardees will be encouraged to establish start-ups through facilitation and support after evaluation and recommendation by an Expert Committee<br><br>\r\n<b>Application Process:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applications are to be submitted online when notified. <br>\r\n<li>The applicants should form a team of five students. \r\n At least three members in the team of five should be with a Life Science background and other members can be from disciplines other than life sciences/Biotechnology.<br>\r\n<li> The individual team member may or may not be from the same Institute / University. <br>\r\n<li>Each team should submit only one entry. A participant can be a member of only one team. Each team has to nominate a member as the team leader and may identify a mentor as a guide. <br>\r\n<li>The Proposals need to be submitted in the core areas of biotechnology which include: Agriculture, Aquaculture, Bio-energy, Biologicals and Applications, Bioprocess Engineering, Biosensors, Drug discovery & Development, Environment, Food, Medical Diagnostics/Devices, Nanobiology/Nanobiotechnology, Nutraceuticals, Vaccines, and other related areas. The proposals could be either for a product, service, or application. <br><br>\r\n<li>Each team should submit a Concept Note in response to the notification, to the given address below.<br>\r\n\r\n<b>\r\nThe Advisor Kerala Bio-Technology<br/> Commission Kerala StateCouncil for Science, <br/>Technology and Environment (KSCSTE), <br/> Sasthra Bhavan, Pattom, <br/> Thiruvananthapuram â 695 004 <br><br></b>\r\n<b>Telephone: (0471) 2548406, 2548259,</b><br>\r\n<b> E-mail: kbc.kscste(at)Kerala.gov.in</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '100000', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"Post Doctoral \"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates, Ph.D.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-10', '2023-01-31', 'Department of Biotechnology', 100000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 14:16:23', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 09:31:03', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1553, '08RYgmr3vhztg0Sdb1', 'Scholarship', 'Prathibha Scholarship Programme', 'https://prathibha.kscste.kerala.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yhlny6o_CpI', 'Scholarships are awarded to students of Kerala origin who have qualified meritoriously in the Higher Secondary Examination, for pursuing Undergraduate and Postgraduate degree courses in Basic/ Natural Science in Institutions/ Universities in India.  The objective of the program is to motivate aspiring students to higher studies and a career in Science.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicant should be of Kerala origin.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant should have qualified for Higher Secondary Examination from Kerala.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant should have qualified Higher Secondary Board Examination with minimum 90% marks or equivalent grade for all subjects put together and minimum 90% marks or equivalent grade for all Science subjects put together.<br>\r\n<li>For SC/ST reservation category, the eligibility is stipulated to minimum marks of 80% or equivalent grade for all subjects in total and minimum 80% marks or equivalent grade for all Science subjects in total.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant should have secured admission for 3 years B.Sc. /5-year Integrated M.Sc. / 5-year Integrated BS-MS course in Basic or Natural Science (23 subjects enlisted in the âguidelinesâ) in any of the Institutions or Universities in India.<br>\r\n<li>Those who have availed Prathibha Scholarship for all 3 years of the Undergraduate Course and have qualified Degree Course with a minimum of 75% marks are eligible to continue the scholarship for the Postgraduate course.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<b>\r\nU.G. Course/ First 3 years of Integrated P.G. Course.</b><br>\r\n<li>1st Year -  12,000/-<br>\r\n<li>2nd Year    -  18,000/-<br>\r\n<li>3rd Year -  24,000/-<br>\r\n<b>P.G. Course (subject to scoring a minimum of 75% marks for Undergraduate course)</b><br>\r\n<li>1st Year/ 4th Year of Integrated P.G. Course   -  40,000/-<br>\r\n<li>2nd Year/ 5th Year of Integrated P.G. Course  -  60,000/-   <br>\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th and 12th mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '25000', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"Kerala\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-12', '2023-02-16', ' Kerala State Council for Science, Technology and Environment', 25000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 15:10:25', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-03 03:38:35', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1554, 'uV0QdQn01paQP5IR7u', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Ashton Award for Student Research', 'https://arboretum.harvard.edu/research/programs-and-opportunities/ashton-award-for-student-research/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University has opened applications for its Ashton Award for Student Research. The Ashton Award for Student Research supports investigations by graduate and advanced undergraduate students working on Asian tropical forest biology.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Undergraduate and graduate students can apply.<br>\r\n<li>The award is not limited to universities in the United States or to U.S. citizens.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Documents: </b><br>\r\n1. Cover letter.<br>\r\n2. Research statement: the statement should be 1-2 pages and describe your research project and describe how additional funding via the Ashton award would further help your research. <br>\r\n3. Include the names of other collaborators ( in addition to your advisor). <br>\r\n4. Reference should be included but do not count as a part of your page limit.<br>\r\n5. Research budget: ap applicant must submit a  simple one-page budget that itemizes the research and travel costs associated with the proposed project.<br>\r\n6. Project timeline: Applicants should submit a timeline of the project and anticipated start and end dates.\r\nCurriculum vitae.<br>\r\n7. Two letters of recommendation: As part of the online submission, you must send a request to the two referees to submit a letter of recommendation (via the request section). The referee will be automatically sent an email with a link to an online submission form where they will upload a letter of recommendation. It is highly recommended that you contact your referee prior to sending the request. Please inform the referee to expect an email from<b> Admin@communityforce.com </b>with instructions for submitting a recommendation letter. <br>\r\n8. Each referee must upload his/her letter of recommendation via the link by February 1.<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-04', '2023-02-01', 'Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 15:43:46', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 10:16:26', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1555, 'FmMeYkGoh394FLbbU0', 'Scholarship', 'DBT Ramalingaswamy  Fellowship', 'https://rrfdbtindia.in/student/register', '', '', '', '', '', 'DBT-RamalingaswamI Re-Entry Fellowship 2023: The Indian Nationals who are working in Overseas Research Institutions for the Ramalingaswami Re-entry Fellowship can submit their applications as the call for this re-entry scheme is from the Department of Biotechnology DBT of the Ministry of Science & Technology, Govt. of India.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Ramalingaswamy Re-entry Fellowship Scheme has been conceptualized with the aim of attracting highly skilled researchers (Indian Nationals) working overseas in various cutting-edge disciplines of any area of Life Sciences & Biotechnology, Bioinformatics, Bio-engineering, Healthcare (human and animal), Environment, Energy, Agriculture and Veterinary biotechnology, Bio-energy, and allied areas by providing them an attractive avenue to pursue their R&D interests in Indian universities/institutions.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<b>1. Nationality: </b>Indian citizens only are eligible to apply.<br>\r\n<b>2. Age Limit:</b> The upper age limit for applying is 45 years as of the closing date of the application.<br>\r\n<b>3. Area of Research: </b>Applicants working in any area of life sciences & biotechnology, bio-engineering, healthcare (human and animal), agriculture and veterinary biotechnology, bio-energy, and allied areas will be eligible to apply.<br>\r\n<b>4. Qualification & Experience: </b>Applicant should possess a Ph.D/MD degree or equivalent in life sciences/ agriculture, bioinformatics, and allied areas or M.Tech in engineering or technology/ medicine, etc. with at least three years of post-doctoral research experience in overseas research laboratories. Applicants should have a proven/outstanding track record as evidenced by research publications and recognitions.<br>\r\n5. Those who have already returned to India within one year of the closing date of the advertisement (two years for women candidates) are also eligible to apply; however, if they have secured a permanent position in India within this period then they are not eligible to apply.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefit:</b><br>\r\n<b>Monthly Remuneration :</b><br>\r\nThe selected candidates will get consolidated monthly remuneration of Rs.1,00,000/-(One Lac) per month.<br><br>\r\n<b>House Rent Allowance :</b><br>\r\nIn addition to the above, the fellows will also get a House Rent Allowance of Rs. Eighteen Thousand Five Hundred (18500/-) (consolidate) per month. If the Host institutes provide accommodation to the selected candidates, then no HRA is admissible.<br><br>\r\n<b>Research/contingency grant:</b><br>\r\nThe selected candidates will get a research/contingency grant of Rs. 10,00,000/- (Ten lacs) for the 1st year and 2nd year, Rs. 7,50,000/- (seven lacs fifty thousand) for the 3rd  and 4th year, and Rs. 5,00,000/- (five lakhs ) for 5th year for the purchase of consumables, minor equipment, international and domestic travel, engaging manpower and other contingent expenditure to be incurred for the implementation of the research proposal.<br><br>\r\n<b>Other Benefits :</b><br>\r\nMedical benefits, transport allowance, leave travel allowance and other benefits DBT encourages host institutions to provide these as per their prevailing norms for their employees of equivalent rank.<br><br>\r\n<b>Time period/Tenure of RamalingaswamI Re-Entry Fellowship:â</b><br>\r\nThe duration of the fellowship will be for a period of three years. In exceptional cases, the duration of the award may be extended by additional two years after a fresh appraisal of performance.<br><br>\r\n', '<li>Birth  Certificate.<br>\r\n <li>  Copy of Passport (if applicable).<br>\r\n   <li> Doctoral Degree Certificate.<br>\r\n   <li> Details of Research Contribution.<br>\r\n  <li> Reprints of 5 Best Research Publications.<br>\r\n  <li>  Research Proposal detailing Proposed Research Work.<br>\r\n   <li>Certificate by Host Institute.<br>\r\n   <li>Letters of Recommendation.<br>\r\n  <li> Undertaking from the applicant/ Statement from Current Employer (certifying that applicant is not on a permanent position in India) (if applicable).<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '100000', '[\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Ph.D, M.D, M.Tech\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-09', '2023-03-31', ' Department of Biotechnology, Ministry of Science and Technology, Government of India ', 100000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 16:08:36', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 12:35:52', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1556, '4CvqytU1hzoZIorq5Y', 'Scholarship', 'Telangana E pass  scholarship ', 'https://telanganaepass.cgg.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Government of Telangana aims to financially support students for a higher level of studies especially when they face issues due to the inability to afford it. Most students belonging to Socially Backward classes or belonging to the Physically Handicapped Category are unable to pursue their higher studies due to lower income.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Must be a citizen of Telangana.<br>\r\n<li>Family income should  not be more than Rs. 2 Lakh per annum.<br>\r\n<li>The candidate must have taken admission into a recognised institution for a Post Matriculation level educational course.<br>\r\n<li>For the intermediate level of study the age of the candidate should not be more than 20 years for EBC, Minority, and Disabled candidates while for SC, ST, and BC must be 24 years.<br>\r\n<li>For studying Graduation level courses, the maximum age is 25 and 29 years for EBC/Minority/Disabled candidates and SC/ST/BC candidates respectively.<br>\r\n<li>For courses of Post Graduate or Research levels, the age of candidates should not be more than 30 years in the case of EBC, Minority, and Disabled candidates and 34 years in the case of SC, ST, and BC candidates.<br>\r\n<li>Students of BC / EBC and DW students who are studying the courses offered by the open universities, distant education mode, and category B seats in M.B.B.S and B.D.S are not eligible.<br>\r\n<li>Students who belong to other than SC, ST, BC, EBC, and Disabled categories\r\nare not eligible.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Group I:</b> Professional courses-25000/-<br>\r\n<b>Group II: </b>Other professional and technical courses.-25000/-<br>\r\n<b> GroupIII: </b>Degree courses (which are not covered in groups I and II) and NIFT courses-20000/-<br>\r\n <b>Group IV:</b>Intermediate courses, ITI / ITCs, and Vocational Courses-16000/-<br>\r\n', '<li>Secondary School Certificate Admit Card with examination roll number, passing year, and type of candidate.<br>\r\n<li>Aadhaar Card Number of the Student or Aadhar <li>Card registration number or EID.<br>\r\n<li>Caste Certificate<br>\r\n<li>Current Passport size photograph<br>\r\n<li>Income Certificate <br>\r\n<li>An order for the Common Entrance Test in case of CET courses<br>\r\n<li>\r\nBank Passbook <br>\r\n<li>Students need to submit the Mobile Passport and Passport Registration Application.<br>\r\n<li>Study Certificate or  Bonafide Certificate for the educational record of the last seven continuous years<br>\r\n<li>For an Intermediate student to register on the ePASS portal, he/she must finish the Online Admission procedures to the Board of Intermediate Education Portal with the help of the Principal of the College.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '20000', '[\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Class 11 to 12, Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-12-14', '2023-01-31', 'Social Welfare Department, Government of Telangana', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-25 17:31:55', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-31 05:05:47', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1557, 'O6jzRHQRsdTqcM6n0m', 'Scholarship', 'Foundation for Academic Excellence and Access', 'http://www.faeaindia.org/Registration2022/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LJDz6kZowtM', 'This scheme is to provide scholarships to students willing to pursue undergraduate studies in Arts/Commerce/Science/Engineering and other technical and professional disciplines at any university/institution/college in India. <br><br>\r\n<li>\r\n\r\nStudents who have passed or cleared the class 12th examination and got admission to the graduation course of studies in the different courses after getting the financial help and support offered under the FAEA Scholarship. \r\nThis scholarship amount will cover the major allowances such as hostel fees, tuition fees and mess charges. <br><br>\r\n<li>Students belonging to the socially and economically backward communities and to the BPL communities can apply online under the FAEA Scholarship for getting the scholarship amounts.<br><br><br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant must be a student. <br>\r\n<li>The student must be a permanent citizen of India.<br>\r\n<li>Students must have passed their class 12th examination. <br>\r\n<li>Students must be pursuing 1st-year graduation from a recognized university. <br>\r\n<li>Students must be belonging to the SC, ST and BPL categories.<br>\r\n<li>General categories will also be considered eligible but for this, they will need to secure 90% of the maximum marks in the class 12th examination. <br>\r\n<li>They also provide special scholarships for girls belonging to socially and economically disadvantaged section in the BPL category from <b>Karnataka, Kerala, Maharashtra, Tamil Nadu.</b><br>\r\n<li>In addition, they have some need cum merit based financial grants for General Category students, especially for those students who have obtained above 90% marks in their Higher Secondary Exam and/or have been able to get admission in the first-rate Institutions of Excellence in the country.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligible degree programs: </b><br>\r\n<li>Arts<br>\r\n<li>Commerce<br>\r\n<li>Medical Science<br>\r\n<li>Engineering.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits: </b>This scholarship will cover the allowances such as tuition fees, mess charges, hostel fees, and maintenance allowance.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Contact details:</b><br>Then you may contact these mentioned-below office address, phone number, and email Id:-<br> \r\n<b>1. Office Address:- </b><br>\r\nFoundation for Academic Excellence and Access (FAEA),<br/>\r\nC-25, Qutab Institutional Area,<br/>\r\nNew Mehrauli Road,\r\nNew Delhi â 110 016.<br/>\r\n <b>2.Phone No:-</b> +91 11 4168 9133<br>\r\n<b>3.Email Id:-</b> inquiry@faeaindia.org<br>', '<li>Aadhar card of the student is mandatory.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Educational Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Last yearâs mark sheet .<br>\r\n<li>Residence certificate issued by the competent authority.<br>\r\n<li>Proof of bank account details.<br>\r\n<li>Latest Passport size photograph of the applicant.<br>\r\n<li>Self-Declaration form.<br>\r\n<li>Course fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Active Mobile number.<br>\r\n<li>Working Email ID .<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '10000', '[\"Class 12\",\"Medical\",\"Engineering\",\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"Karnataka\",\"Kerala\",\"Maharashtra\",\"Tamil Nadu\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 250000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-03', '2023-03-17', 'Tata Group and others', 10000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-28 13:45:12', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-07 10:18:31', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1558, 'fYSgvflnapYSeRQQy8', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Program in Mathematics for Young Scientists  PROMYS India', 'https://promys.submittable.com/signup?returnUrl=%2fsubmit%2ffeffd91e-c833-47c9-b12d-0804916e862b%2fpromys-india-2023-student-application', '', '', '', '', '', 'A challenging six-week residential mathematics summer programme, PROMYS India is open to mathematically talented secondary and higher secondary students <b>(Standards IX - XII or equivalent). </b>Meticulously selected students from across India will gather on the campus of the Indian Institute of Science (IISc) Bengaluru to immerse themselves in rigorous mathematics.<br><br>\r\n<li>PROMYS India is closely modelled on its parent programme, Program in Mathematics for Young Scientists (PROMYS) which has been running at Boston University in the United States since 1989.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicants must attend secondary or higher secondary school in India in Standards IXâXII (or +1, +2, or PUC). <br><br>\r\n<li>Students must have completed (or currently be in) Standard IX before the start of the programme. <br>\r\n<li>Students are still eligible to apply if they are just completing their final year of higher secondary school (or taking a gap year) but have not yet begun their university studies.<br><br>\r\n<li>Students attending government-funded schools, government-aided private schools, unaided private or independent schools, sixth-form colleges, home schools, and other types of secondary or higher secondary schools in India are all eligible to apply.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Applicants must be at least 15 years old by 7 May 2023. (We do not anticipate that any exceptions will be made, but students who are very close to 15 can apply if they wish.) Most students will be older than 15. Students are no longer eligible if they will be older than 18 at the start of the programme.<br><br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Students who are already attending university are NOT eligible to be first-year students (though they may be eligible to apply to be undergraduate counsellors).<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Lectures, discussions, and problem sets at PROMYS India are all in English. Applicants should possess English language skills sufficient to enable full participation.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n <li>There are no financial requirements of any sort for eligibility or participation in PROMYS India. For at least the first year of the program, every student who is accepted to PROMYS India will automatically be awarded a full scholarship which will cover all costs of participation: tuition, housing and meals, approved travel, and any required books.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Please note that students may not apply to PROMYS India and to PROMYS at Boston University in the U.S. for the same summer. They may apply to only one. Please also note that while students for at least the first year of PROMYS India will all be awarded full scholarships, PROMYS in the U.S. is not free. Students who would need financial assistance to attend PROMYS Boston are expected to apply instead to PROMYS India.<br><br>\r\n<li>Both PROMYS and PROMYS India being highly selective, students in India will have a higher chance of being admitted to PROMYS India.<br><br>\r\n', '<li>As Prescribed.', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 11 to  Class 12.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-12', '2023-02-15', 'Indira Foundation, Morph.org, Mehta fellowship.', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-28 14:57:55', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-01 10:55:03', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1559, 'wOnvHyIMKKmDMxP6WH', 'Scholarship', 'Post Matric Scholarship Tripura', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/fresh/newstdRegfrmInstruction', '', '', '', '', '', 'It is being offered by the Government of Tripura. Students belonging to the OBC category can apply in the scholarship. This scholarship is applicable to those students who are studying in the post-matriculation stage. Tripura OBC scholarship\'s aim is to financially assist meritorious students belongs from economically poor families in pursuing higher education. The selected candidate will get multiple awards for their education requirements..<br>.<br>\r\n<b>.Eligibility:</b>\r\n<li>A candidate must be a domicile student of Tripura state and belongs to the Other Backward Classes (OBC) category.<br>\r\n<li>An applicant must pursue post-matriculation studies.\r\n<li>The family income of the applicant must not exceed INR 1.5 lacs per annum.<br>\r\n<b>Note:</b>Only two boys per family can apply for this scholarship. However, there is no such restriction in the case of girls.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>The selected students will receive a scholarship amount of up to INR 750/- per month.<br>\r\n<li>Also, these students will get reimbursement of the compulsory non-refundable fees, maintenance allowance, study tour, reader charges, book allowance, thesis printing/typing charges, etc.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th and 12th marksheet.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic marksheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '10000', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Class 11 to Class 12, Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 50.00, 50.00, 50.00, 60.00, '[\"Tripura\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 150000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-04', '2023-02-02', 'Government of Tripura.', 10000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-01-28 17:53:58', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 03:51:23', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
