(1565, 'sDwGJXw4CRfehIaqXq', 'Scholarship', 'IndusInd Foundation Scholarship ', 'https://www.vidhyaa.in/public/storage/files/IndusInd%20Scholarship.pdf', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Ep5IdqG0vE', 'IndusInd Foundation is offering IndusInd Foundation Scholarship 2023 for students who are meritorious and deserving. IndusInd Foundation is for candidates who have passed 12th from a recognized board having a good academic background. Indusland Foundation emphasizes the weak section of society who cannot afford studies. It is a Merit cum Means scholarship for all science, commerce, or arts students. About IndusInd Foundation 2023.<br><br>\r\n<li>IndusInd Foundation is a charitable trust which offers endowments to children belonging to the weak economic section. This includes approx 500 to 600 students every. The foundation was established in the year 1995 along with charitable organizations and the leading role of Shri SP Hinduja. The main aim is to provide education to the low economic section of society to control the dropout rates.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant must be an Indian National.<br>\r\nStudents must be 12th passed out with a minimum of 80% marks.<br>\r\n<li>One should have joined Govt. college for UG admission in B.A, B.Com, Engineering, Medical, Para-Medical, BCA, and BBA or equivalent.<br>\r\n<li>If you are 12th passed out before 2018 then you are not eligible for this scholarship.<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards: </b><br>\r\nUnder the Induslnd Foundation Scholarship Reward 2023, you will be getting INR 600 â INR 2200 cash monthly basis which will be transferred directly to your bank account.<br><br>\r\n<b>Application process:</b><br>\r\n<li>The application is in offline mode. You need to read all the instructions properly before downloading the form. You cannot apply online you have to download the form. To apply, click on the link, and download the application form. Fill out the form carefully and attach all the r