(1566, 'q5fnMEV7sZj8fE5IFc', 'Scholarship', 'Gandhi Fellowship', 'http://gandhifellowship.org/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zYoB261A8tM', 'Gandhi Fellowship 2023 is a 2-year residential program given by the Kaivalaya Education Foundation in the support of the Piramal Foundation introduced. Gandhi Fellowship 2023 is introduced to inspire inventive youth from top colleges and Universities. The shortlisted fellows of this program will be required to help the headmasters and principals of primary schools, to transform their education and school structure.<br><br>\r\n<li>With the help of 11 fellows in 2008, the Gandhi Fellowship took its first initiative. And now, it is steadily growing in popularity and the number of participants.\r\nGandhi Fellowship 2023 is a wonderful opportunity for youth, to experiment with their skills in solving social problems. This step won\'t only solve the problem, but will also help aspirants to develop their thinking process and leadership skill.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Must be a citizen of India.<br>\r\n<li>Interested candidates from any stream are eligible to participate.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligible degree programs:</b><br>\r\n<li>Commerce & Business, Applied Sciences, Social & Behavioural Science, Engineering, Maths & Journalism, Humanities, Law, Liberal Arts & Education, etc, can apply for the Gandhi Fellowship.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Applicaton process:</b><br>\r\n<li>First, register yourself through the official website.\r\nUpload your updated CV.<br>\r\n<li>After registration, you\'ll be called for an interview session.<br>\r\n<li>Besides the interview, you will also be provided with an essay-type question test.<br>\r\n<li>After that, the applicant will be required to pass an online test, to become a successful candidate.<br><br>\r\n<b>What work will be allotted to Gandhi Fellows?</b><br>\r\n<li>Aspirants will be required to put in their efforts and ideas on their own to bring transformation in school development projects.<br>\r\n<li>Fellows will be required to use several strategies because each step of them will be responsible to affect the millions of children\'s life ahead.<br>\r\n<li>Fellows will learn such effective skills through this entire fellowship, which will eventually help them in getting a better idea about their dream.<br>\r\n<li>Completing the Gandhi fellowship will denote how capable the fellow or candidate is. This will surely help the candidate in getting a deserving pay scale and designation.<br><br>\r\n<b>Partners of Gandhi Fellowship:</b><br>\r\n<li><b>Government Partners: </b>Sarv Siksha Abhiyan, Surat Municipal Corporation, and State Government of Rajasthan.<br>\r\n<li><b>Funded By:</b> UNICEF, Piramal Foundation, Michael and Susan Dell Foundation, USAID, Municipal Corporation of Greater Mumbai.<br>\r\n<li><b>Technical Partners:</b> Educational Initiatives, Harvard Graduate Schools of Education.<br>\r\n<li><b>Other Tie-Ups: </b>Jodo Gyan, IIM Ahmedabad, Echoing Green, Harvard University, Ashoka India.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Gandhi Fellowship Program Rewards</b><br>\r\n<li>Fellows in this scholarship will receive a monthly stipend of INR 14,000 Per Month. Half of the stipend amount will be given to the candidate and the other half will be retained as an interest-free reserve amount\r\nRent Free Accommodation Service.<br>\r\n<li>INR 6,00 Per Month for the mobile cost. Shared two-wheelers for fellows and reimbursement for office travels.<br>\r\n<li>Two years of the experienced certificate from the Gandhi Fellowship.<br>\r\n<li>Fellows under the Gandhi Fellowship will learn system design and certain skills to work on any other social issue.<br>\r\n<li>The placement cell of the Gandhi Fellowship will help fellows to find out excellent job or placement opportunities<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'As Prescribed', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '15000\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 250000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-26', '2023-03-12', 'Kaivalaya Education Foundation', 15000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-01 12:13:01', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-03-17 04:03:56', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1567, 'hQckqQb1fHYvjhZfru', 'Abroad', 'Judicial Fellowship Programme', 'https://www.icj-cij.org/en/judicial-fellows-program', '', '', '', '', '', 'The International Court of Justice (ICJ) invites applications from eligible universities around the world for the 2023-2024 Judicial Fellowship Programme (formerly known as the University Traineeship Programme).<br><br>\r\n<li>The Programme was established in 1999 to enable recent law graduates to gain professional experience working at the ICJ. The Fellowship Programme aims to improve participantsâ understanding of public international law and of the Courtâs procedures by actively involving them in the work of the Court and allowing them to build on their experience under the supervision of a judge.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Judicial Fellows work on a full-time basis under the supervision of a Member of the Court and alongside the primary legal assistant of the judge. The Judicial Fellows can expect to attend the Courtâs public hearings, research and write memorandums on legal questions or factual aspects of the cases pending before the Court, and perform other duties assigned by their judge. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>The duration of the Fellowship is approximately ten months, from early September to June of the following year.\r\nThe purpose of the trust fund is to grant fellowship awards to selected candidates who are nationals of developing countries from universities based in developing countries, thereby improving and guaranteeing the geographic and linguistic diversity of the participants in the Programme.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n1) Who have shown excellent results in their legal studies and who have demonstrated an interest in public international law through their studies, publications and/or work experience.<br>\r\n2) Participants must have excellent reading, writing and oral skills in at least one of them (English or French).<br>\r\n3) Candidates should be 31 years of age or younger.\r\nThe Court normally accepts up to 15 participants per year from various universities across the world.<br><br>\r\n<b> Contact :-<br>\r\nInternational Court of Justice<br/>\r\nPeace Palace,<br/>\r\nCarnegieplein 2,<br/>\r\n2517 KJ The Hague,<br/>\r\nThe Netherlands,</b><br/>\r\n<li><b>Telephone : +31 703022323.</b>\r\n\r\n', '1) A letter from the university introducing the candidate(s) to the Court: for universities financially sponsoring their nominee(s), the letter must also include information regarding the universityâs commitment to providing the candidate(s) with a stipend if selected.<br>\r\n2) ICJ Personal History Form and Candidate Profile Summary Table, filled in by the candidate.<br>\r\n3) Two to Three Letters of reference.<br>\r\n4) The Official Academic Records of the candidate(s).<br>\r\n5) One Writing Sample preferably on a topic of public international law (not more than 15 pages).<br>\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', ' Professional experience certificate.', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"LAW Courses\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-19', '2023-02-05', 'International Court of Justice ', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-01 12:21:32', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-01 07:04:42', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1568, 'PVtaPtbIjj12MUQTp0', 'Scholarship', 'Priyadarshini Academy Scholarship.', 'https://www.priyadarshniacademy.com/student-scholarships.php', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=59zsfqGllG4', 'Priyadarshni Academy provides educational scholarships to the deserving and financially needy school and college students in the Medical, Engineering, IT, Architecture, and Management fields.<br><br>\r\n<li> Priyadarshni Academy has not only given a helping hand to those who have no means to support their learning process but also provided great impetus to individuals to excel in their chosen fields.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Students Studying Under graduation courses in below mentioned courses can apply for Priyadarshani Academy scholarship.<br><br>\r\n<b>A].Eligible courses:</b><br>\r\nEngineering, B.Ed., Medicine, IT, Architecture, Management, Arts,  Humanities, Social Sciences, Law.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>B].Eligibility Criteria For Bachelors courses.</b><br>\r\n1) Applicant must have completed the first year in degree college with high performance.<br>\r\n2) Student Must have an academic record with 1st class distinction. ( SECURED MORE THAN 75% IN PREVIOUS EXAMS )<br>\r\n3) Student\'s age Should not be more than 30 years.<br>\r\n4) Student\'s Family income must not exceed Rs. Four Lakhs Per Annum.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>C] Eligibility Criteria for B. Ed. Scholarships:</b><br>\r\n1) Candidates should be committed to pursuing the profession of teaching in an educational institution and should possess an aptitude for the same.<br>\r\n2) Student\'s Academic background should be excellent. ( 1st class graduate )<br>\r\n3) Students applying for scholarships should possess leadership qualities.<br>\r\n4) Student\'s age Should not be more than 30 years.<br>\r\n5) Student\'s Family income must not exceed Rs. Four Lakhs Per Annum.<br>\r\n6) B.ed Course must be pursued in a government-recognized institute and must lead to a degree in Bachelor of Education