(1576, 'eGXZi3or1siuLAJfKn', 'Scholarship', 'Dr Ambedkar  Scholarship', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Chandigarh is one of the most expensive cities to live in India. There are many students across UT who face financial crises due to which their study suffers a lot. To support the students and help them complete their education many schemes are run by the state and central governments. today we are going to talk about one such scheme named<b> âDr. Ambedkar Scholarship Chandigarh Scholarship for Economically Backward Class Students, Chandigarhâ.</b> <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>This scheme is specially designed by the Ministry of Social Justice & Empowerment for the students of the Economically Backward Class. This scholarship is provided for classes 11th and above so that students can complete their higher education without any hurdles.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Applicant should be an Indian citizen.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate must belong to SC/ST / OBC or general category.<br>\r\n<li>Should have permanent residence in Chandigarh.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant must belong to General Category other than Schedule Caste, Schedule Tribe, and Other Backward Classes<br>\r\n<li>Annual income of the applicantâs family should not be more than INR 1 Lakh per annum.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant must be a student of post-matriculation or post-secondary courses in Government institutions\r\nOnly two boys of the same parents/guardian will get a scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants must not hold any other scholarship/ stipend.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates, after passing one stage of education and pursuing the same stage of education, is not eligible. For e.g. candidates after passing B. A is pursuing B.com.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates after passing one educational course in one stream and then pursuing another educational course in a different stream For e.g. candidates after passing LLB are now pursuing B.T /B.Ed.is not eligible.<br>\r\n<li>The students studying PG courses in medicine are eligible only if they are not allowed to practice during their course.<br>\r\n<li>Only two boys of the same parents /guardians can apply for this scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>The mentioned above restriction is not for the girl candidate.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligible courses</b><br>\r\n<b>1. Group I </b>  <br>\r\n<li>Graduates or postgraduate courses (Medicine, Engineering, Technology, Planning, Architecture, LLB, LLM, Fashion Technology, Management, Business, Finance Administration, Computer Science, Agriculture, Allied Sciences)Diploma Level Courses<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>2. Group II</b>   <br>\r\n<li>Graduates or postgraduate courses, Professional Courses, Diploma Courses, Certificate Courses, B.Pharma,LLB, Para Medical Studies, Mass Communication, Hotel Management & Catering, Tourism, Hospitality, Interior Decoration, Commercial Art, Banking Services.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>3. Group III </b>   <br>\r\n<li>UG Courses <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>4. Group IV  </b> <br>\r\n<li>post-matriculation level, Non-Degree Courses, Vocational Courses, ITI Courses, 3 Year Diploma, Polytechnic Courses.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Rewards</b><br>\r\n<li>Group I- INR 750  per month to hostellers and INR 350 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li>Group II- INR 510  per month to hostellers and INR 335 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li>Group III- INR 400 per month to hostellers and INR 210 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li>Group IV- INR  260 per month to hostellers and INR 160 per month today scholar.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:   </b> <br>\r\n<li>Maintenance allowance up to INR 750 per month to hostellers and INR 350 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li>Reader charges INR 175 P/M for blind students.<br>\r\n<li>Reimbursement of compulsory non-refundable fees.<br>\r\n<li>Study tour charges up to INR 900.<br>\r\n<li>Thesis typing and printing charges up to INR 1000.<b