(1577, '6f7oYt3xhBF8Jr8Odo', 'Scholarship', 'Post Matric Scholarship Chandigarh', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'There are lakhs of OBC students who have to leave their studies in between before their completion period due to financial instabilities, for redressing this issue <b>Chandigarh Post Matric Scholarship For OBC Students</b>. has been launched so that the students will be able to get scholarship amounts. Both scholars and hostellers will be offered variable scholarship amounts.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>The primary objective of launching the Post Matric Scholarship For OBC Students Chandigarh is to provide funds so that the students belonging to Other Backward Communities or Classes will be able to carry out classes such as 11th & 12th and UG to Ph.D. degrees in various fields such as Medicine, Engineering, Technology, Planning, Architecture, Fashion Technology, etc without suffering from the financial instabilities.<br><br>\r\n<li>Another objective of launching the Chandigarh Post Matric Scholarship For OBC Students is to provide a portal by which the students belonging to the OBC communities will be able to get the scholarship amount for pursuing UG or PG level courses with the scholarship amount offered to them.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant must belong to the OBC category.<br>\r\n<li>The applicant must be studying in schools of UT Chandigarh from Class 1 to 10.<br>\r\n<li>The applicant must be pursuing post-matriculation or post-secondary courses.<br>\r\n<li>The applicant must have an annual family income of not more than INR 1.5 lakh from all sources.<br>\r\n<li>The students pursuing Postgraduate courses in Medicine will be eligible if they are not allowed to practice during the period of their course.<br>\r\n<li>The students who pursue their studies through correspondence courses are also eligible. The term correspondence includes distant and continuous education.<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards: </b><br>Different courses are given different allowances and different scholarship amounts.\r\nRewards<br>\r\n<li>Group I- INR 750  per month to hostellers and INR 350 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li>Group II- INR 510  per month to hostellers and INR 335 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li>Group III- INR 400 per month to hostellers and INR 210 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li>Group IV- INR  260 per month to hostellers and INR 160 per month today scholar.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligible courses:</b><br>\r\n<b>1. Group I</b><br>\r\n<li>Graduates or postgraduate courses (Medicine, Engineering, Technology, Planning, Architecture, LLB, LLM, Fashion Technology, Management, Business, Finance Administration, Computer Science, Agriculture, Allied Sciences)Diploma Level Courses.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>2. Group II</b><br>\r\n<li>Graduates or postgraduate courses, Professional Courses, Diploma Courses, Certificate Courses, B.Pharma, LLB, Para Medical Studies, Mass Communication, Hotel Management & Catering, Tourism\r\nHospitality, Interior Decoration, Commercial Art, Banking Services.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>3.Group III</b><br>\r\n<li>UG Courses <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>4.Group IV</b><br>\r\n<li>post-matriculation level, Non-Degree Courses, Vocational Courses, ITI Courses, 3 Year diplomas, and Polytechnic Courses.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Contact details:</b><br>\r\n<li><b>Office address:</b><br>\r\nNational Scholarship Division,<br/>\r\nMinistry of Human Resource Development, <br/>\r\nDepartment of Higher Education,<br/>\r\nWest Block 1,2nd Floor, <br/>\r\nWing 6, Room No.6,<br/>\r\nR. K. Puram, Sector 1, <br/>\r\nNew Delhi 110066.<br/><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li><b>Help desk number</b>- 0120 â 6619540<br>\r\n<li><b>Email id</b>-helpdesk@nsp.gov.in<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Copy of 10th and 12th and another certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Annual Income Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of certificate issued by the relevant authority in Case of differently-abled candidates.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of Residence Proof.<br>\r\n