(1578, '7MmT3FusvV2GekrnOr', 'Scholarship', 'Andaman and Nicobar Scholarship', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Government of Andaman & Nicobar has launched the Andaman & Nicobar Scholarship providing the scholarship amounts to the students residing in Andaman and Nicobar. The students must be pursuing classes from 1st to 12th, Ug degree to Ph.D. degree in various courses. Students will be able to receive the major allowances.<br><br>\r\n<li><b>Post Matric Scholarship for ST Students - Andaman and Nicobar 2022-23 </b>is an initiative of the Ministry of Tribal Affairs, Government of India for ST to financially support ST students studying in Class 11 and above. The scholarship is applicable for candidates who hold a domicile in Andaman and Nicobar.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>This scholarship is especially for ST students of Class 11 and above. The scholarship is applicable to candidates who hold a domicile in Andaman and Nicobar. The key objective of the scholarship is to provide financial assistance to ST students studying at the post-matriculation or post-secondary level to enable them to complete their education.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicant must be a domicile of Andaman and Nicobar.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate must belong to Scheduled Tribe (ST) community.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate should be studying at post-matriculation or post-secondary level i.e. Class 11 to Ph.D. level.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate should have passed matriculation or higher secondary or any higher examination of a recognized University or Board of Secondary Education .<br>\r\n<li>Candidate should have an annual family income less than INR 2 lakh.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Maintenance allowance.<br>\r\n<li>Reimbursement of compulsory non-refundable fees.<br>\r\n<li>Study tour charges.<br> \r\n<li>Thesis typing .<br>\r\n<li>Book allowance .<br>\r\n<li>Book bank facility .<br>\r\n<li>Additional allowances for ST students with disabilities for the complete duratio