(1579, 'aLQ4GefnZJLUBNiPcj', 'Scholarship', 'Meghalaya Scholarship', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'To encourage meritorious and economically weak and poor students to seek their education, the Meghalaya government offers scholarships. All meritorious and needy minority group students are eligible for the Meghalaya Scholarship 2023. These programs are critical to the advancement of education for underprivileged and deserving students. <br><br>\r\n<li>These scholarships have created a real difference in the lives of students who want to pursue their studies to the next level. Furthermore, Meghalayaâs government is making changes based on a studentâs educational demands and technical requirements. IIM, Shilong, and NIT Meghalaya are among the stateâs top colleges<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The candidate should be a domicile Holder in Meghalaya.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate should be studying post-matric courses from a recognized university/school/college.<br>\r\n<li>The candidate should belong to the ST category.<br>\r\n<li>The annual income of the family should be less than 200000<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards: </b><br>\r\nDifferent courses are given different allowances and different scholarship amounts.<br>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>Group I-</b> INR 1200  per month to hostellers and INR 550 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li><b>Group II-</b> INR 820  per month to hostellers and INR 530  per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li><b>Group III-</b> INR 570  per month to hostellers and INR 300 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<li><b>Group IV-</b> INR  380 per month to hostellers and INR 230 per month today scholar.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligible courses</b><br>\r\n<b>1.Group I</b><br>\r\nGraduates or postgraduate courses (Medicine, Engineering, Technology, Planning, Architecture,  LLB, LLM, Fashion Technology, Management, Business, Finance Administration, Computer Science, Agriculture, Allied Sciences)Diploma Level Courses<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>2.Group II</b><br>\r\nGraduates or postgraduate courses, Professional Courses, Diploma Courses, Certificate Courses, B.Pharma, LLB, Para Medical Studies, Mass Communication, Hotel Management & Catering, Tourism\r\nHospitality, Interior Decoration, Commercial Art, Banking Services.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>3.Group III</b><br>\r\nUG Courses <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>4.Group IV</b><br>\r\npost-matriculation level, Non-Degree Courses, Vocational Courses, ITI Courses, 3 Year diplomas, and Polytechnic Courses.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Copy of 10th and 12th and another certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Annual Income Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of certificate issued by the relevant authority in case of differently-abled candidates.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of Residence Proof.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of Aadhaar Card.<br>\r\n<li>Annual Fee details verified by Institute.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of a bank passbook showing all the required details.<br>\r\n<li>Certificate issued by director/prin.<br>\r\n<li>Declaration by the parents.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '20000', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', 'null', '\"Class 11 and Above\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"Meghalaya\"]', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"ST\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-04', '2023-02-15', 'Government of Meghalaya', 20000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-03 14:45:16', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-03 09:20:58', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1580, 'ptisrS1HeHdrYze7VB', 'Scholarship', 'Radha Krishnan Scholarship', 'https://www.hpbose.org/Home.aspx', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ebuwIpb9zN4', 'Radha Krishnan Scholarship is an initiative of the Board of School Education in Dharamshala Himachal Pradesh. Under this scholarship program, all those students who scored well in the 10th or 12th board examination and meet the eligibility conditions set by the authority will get cash benefits. Benefits we directly transfer to the applicantâs bank account. Applicants who desired to grab the opportunity have to submit the application form. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>The motive behind starting the scholarship program is to encourage students toward education. To do so the government is going to distribute cash awards to the students who scored well in the 10th or 12th board examination.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Applicant must have passed class 10th or 12th examination from Himachal Pradesh Board of School Education.<br>\r\n<li>The annual income of the applicantâs family should not be more than INR 1 lakh per annum.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant must have secured at least 65% for more marks in the board examination. (50% marks in case of differently-abled students).<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicants who have passed the tenth standard board examination will scholarship amount of INR 2700 per annum.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants who have passed the 12th standard board examination will get a scholarship amount of INR 3000 per annum.<br><br>\r\n<b>Application procedure:</b><br>\r\n<li>Take the print of the application form.<br>\r\n<li>Fill in the details carefully and attach the required documents mentioned.<br>\r\n<li>Enclose it in an envelope and mention the name of the scholarship on top of it .<br>\r\n<li>Send the envelope to the given address below.<br><br>\r\n<b>Address:</b><br>\r\nSection Officer, Plus <br/>Two-1 and Matric-II, <br/>H.P. Board of School <br/>Education Dharamshal