(1581, 'GtHZqiAjfatqGpEH57', 'Scholarship', 'Mera Bharat Surakshit Bharat', 'https://soodcharityfoundation.org/donations/mera-bharat-surakshit-bharat/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m0mzxHDwrJo', 'The students are eligible to apply for the Sonu Sood scholarship 2023 by visiting the official website of the sood charity Foundation which is an NGO founded by the actor. People who are interested in cyber security can apply for the Mera Bharat Surakshit Bharat initiative which is created in order to help the students and professionals who are living in India but want to get a job oriented through cyber security skills.<br><br>\r\n<li> The people can get the opportunity to serve various organizations through the development of this scholarship and they can learn cybersecurity skills at 0 cost. India has witnessed a lot of cyber attacks in the last few years. In order to overcome the cyber security problem, a new scholarship is created.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant must be a permanent resident of India.<br>\r\n<li>The applicant must be above the age of 18 years and below the age of 35 years.<br>\r\n<li>The objective behind this initiative is to create a national-level program for students or enthusiasts who want to build their careers in tech and cybersecurity. With this learning, they can gain job-oriented skills without spending a fortune.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Terms And Conditions Under Sonu Sood Scholarship</b><br>\r\nThe applicant must follow the following terms and conditions in order to successfully apply for the scholarship:-<br>\r\n<li>Scholarships are limited in number and subject to availability.<br>\r\n<li>Scholarships are not available with any other discount or special pricing offer.<br>\r\n<li>Only citizens of India are eligible for this Scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>You should be at least 18 years of age and not be more than 35 years of age.<br>\r\n<li>You must inform us of any other EC-Council certification you are currently pursuing or are enrolled in. You will not be eligible for a Scholarship if you are currently pursuing other EC-Council certifications.<br>\r\n<li>You shall provide all mandatory documents, including but not limited to proof of citizenship, and proof of age. You are required to furnish true and accurate information. Any discovery of misrepresentation or fraudulent submission of documents will lead to immediate disqualification of your application.<br>\r\n<li>No correspondence is guaranteed to any candidate filling up the form.\r\n<li>You are required to regularly check our website and your email (including your spam folder) for important updates.<br>\r\n<li>Submission of the application does not assure selection for the Scholarship. Scholarships will be granted at our sole discretion.<br>\r\n<li>You shall be required to communicate your acceptance of the Scholarship within thirty (30) days from the date of the Scholarship offer, along with the list of documents set out in the offer email. Failing to do so will result in immediate forfeiture of the Scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>We reserve the right to cancel your selection in the event you are found to be misusing the opportunity in any form, not being serious about the program, or not following the guidelines, rules, and regulations, which may be revised by us at any time.<br>\r\n<li>CCT examination vouchers issued under the Scholarship cannot be redeemed for their monetary value.<br>\r\n<li>You acknowledge that the CCT examination vouchers shall be accessed for your own personal use only, and you will not share these vouchers with any third party.<br>\r\n<li>Whenever we ask you to share your experience and honest feedback you need to provide the same to us ( EC-council and Sood Charity Foundation) on completion of your program. We reserve the right to publish this feedback and testimonials on our digital channels. You further grant us the right to use/ publish your name, photograph, results and progress report on any media form- digital or offline.<br>\r\n<li>Scholarships are non-transferable.<br>\r\n<li>No false or misleading statements should be made by you about us, the Scholarship, or our management or employees.<br>\r\n<li>You must adhere to all exam regulations and policies established by EC-Council, which may change from time to time.<br>\r\n<li>We shall not be responsible or liable to any student for any reason whatsoever. You or your family members/relatives will not be entitled to any claim against us at any time during, prior to, or after the commencement of the Scholarship program.<br>\r\n<li>You shall not acquire, use, copy, create derivative works, pirate copies, reproduce, counterfeit, reverse engineer, or misappropriate any of our proprietary information and materials.<br>\r\n<li>EC-Councilâs and Sood Charity Foundationâs decisions shall be final and binding for all the matters regarding the Scholarship covered or not covered in these Terms and Conditions. No further correspondence will be considered.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Through this program scholarships up to Rs. 1 crore will be offered to help cybersecurity enthusiasts build their careers and develop skills.<br>\r\n<li>The objective behind this initiative is to create a national-level program for students or enthusiasts who want to build their careers in tech and cybersecurity. With this learning, they can gain job-oriented skills without spending a fortune.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th and 12th mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '1 Crore', '[\"Engineering\",\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates (18 years  to 35 years)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', 'Both', '[\"All\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-01', '2023-02-10', 'Sood charity Foundation', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-04 11:44:32', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-07 04:09:32', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1582, '3tg89e9TXz1fY3sCtD', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Snap It  Selfie with Nano Urea farmers', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/snap-it-selfie-nano-urea-farmers/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Nano Urea has been provisionally included in Fertilizer Control Order (FCO) 1985. In the preliminary trials, Nano-urea spray on different crops gave comparable yields to those obtained under fully recommended doses of fertilizers, with savings on top-dressed nitrogen.<br><br>\r\nNano Fertilizers hold great promise for application in plant nutrition because of their size-dependent qualities, high surface-to-volume ratio, and unique optical properties. Nano Fertilizer releases plant nutrients in a controlled manner, contributing to higher nutrient use efficiency.<br><br>\r\nCitizens are invited to post geo-tagged/non-geo-tagged selfies with farmers using Nano Urea in the field or other locations like CSC centers, Krishi Kendras, in their village/block/district/state and upload them in the description box.<br><br>\r\n<b>NOTE: - </b>Participants are required to mention their state.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Gratification</b><br>\r\nThe Cash prizes will be as follows:<br>\r\n1. First prize: INR 2,500/-<br>\r\n2. Second prize: INR 1,500/-<br>\r\n3. Third prize: INR 1,000/-<br>\r\n4.Next 5 Consolation prize: INR 500/- each<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '2,500  ', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All  \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 300000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-15', '2023-02-14', 'Government of India', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-04 12:48:42', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-04 07:46:50', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1583, 'iZ1l9Jianciggu30xM', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Design a Logo for CPGRAMS', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/design-logo-cpgrams/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Centralised Public Grievance Redress and Monitoring System (CPGRAMS) is a 24x7 online platform where citizens can lodge complaints to government agencies for any aspect of service delivery. It is a single portal that connects all Ministries/Departments of the Central Government and the States.<br><br>\r\n<li> Citizens can also access CPGRAMS via a standalone mobile application accessible from the Google Play store and a mobile application integrated with UMANG.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Department of Administrative Reforms and Public Grievances is inviting citizens to design a Logo that will depict the true potential and objective of CPGRAMS.The logo should have an attractive design and should be reproable in multiple formats for multiple platforms.<br><br>\r\n<b>Technical Parameters:</b><br>\r\n<li> Participants should upload the logo in JPEG/ JPG/ PNG format only. The logo should be designed on a digital platform. <br>\r\n<li>The winner of the competition shall be required to submit the design in an editable and open file format. br>Participants should ensure that the original designs are submitted.<br>\r\n<li> Each entry should submit a detailed logic and explanation of rational and creative thoughts (not more than 100 words) on the designed logo in a soft copy.<br>\r\n<li> Logo should be designed in a colored format. The size of the logo may vary from 5cm*5cm to 60cm*60cm in either portrait or landscape mode.<br>\r\n<li> The logo should be usable on the website/ social media such as Twitter/ Facebook, press releases, and on printable such as stationery, signage, labels, etc., magazines, commercials, holdings, standees, brochures, leaflets, pamphlets, souvenirs, and other publicity and marketing material for the promotion of CPGRAMS.<br>\r\n<li> The logo image should be in high resolution with a minimum of 300 DPI.<br>\r\n<li> Logo should look clean (not pixilated or bit-mapped) when viewed on-screen at 100%.<br>\r\n<li>Entries should not be submitted in compressed or self-extracting formats.<br>\r\n<li>The logo design should not be imprinted or watermarked.<br><br>\r\n<b>Reward:</b><br>\r\nThe winning entry (selected/approved nomenclature) will be awarded prizes of<b> Rs 51000 and an E-certificate.</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '51000 and E-certificate\r\n', '[\"All\"]', 'null', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 300000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-03', '2023-02-21', 'Department of Administrative Reforms and Public Grievances', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-04 13:02:01', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-04 07:33:12', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1584, 'mo8HyHyAT0isEy1E7u', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Suggest a New Name for CPGRAMS', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/suggest-new-name-cpgrams/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Centralised Public Grievance Redress and Monitoring System (CPGRAMS) is a 24x7 online platform where citizens can lodge complaints to government agencies for any aspect of service delivery. It is a single portal that connects all Ministries/Departments of the Central Government and the States.<br><br>\r\n<li> Citizens can also access CPGRAMS via a standalone mobile application accessible from the Google Play store and a mobile application integrated with UMANG.\r\nThe Department of Administrative Reforms and Public Grievances felt there was a need to provide the portal with a new look and feel as we approach 2023.\r\nThe Ministry encourages citizens to suggest a unique and lively name for \"CPGRAMS\".<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\nThe winning entry (selected/approved nomenclature) will be awarded a prize of<b> Rs 51,000 and an E-certificate.</b>\r\n<br><br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '51,000 and E-certificate.\r\n', '[\"All\"]', 'null', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-03', '2023-02-21', ' Department of Administrative Reforms and Public Grievances', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-04 13:11:03', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-04 07:42:15', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1585, 'P3Hx5WT0xq9R9kE6QF', 'Scholarship', 'ONGC Foundation Scholarship', 'https://www.ongcscholar.org/#/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3MjdvfGe8SA', 'NGC is a pioneering gas company with branches in many states. The companyâs impact on Indiaâs economy is significant. ONGC Foundationâs innovation projects aim to improve underprivileged peopleâs lives. The ONGC Scholarship Scheme is notable. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>ONGC Scholarship scheme is a hand extended for help to the meritorious students of all the categories around India. \r\nThis merit scholarship scheme is intending to provide economic aid to students who regardless of achieving good scores, canât get higher education due to financial barriers. Overall, 1000 students will be selected for the scholarship from different states across all the categories. This programme benefits 500 General and OBC students. 1000 Schedule Caste/Scheduled Tribe candidates will benefit. Students will receive Rs. 4000 per month.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Candidate must be a citizen of India.<br> \r\n<li>The candidate must be in 1st year of MBBS/ Engineering/ MBA/ Masterâs degree in Geophysics or Geology under a full-time course in AICTE/ MCI/UGC/\r\n<li>At least 60% marks in class 12 for Engineering/MBBS course and 60% marks in graduation for PG courses like Geology/Geophysics /MBA.<br>\r\n<li>The gross family income of the candidate should not exceed INR 4.5 Lakhs for SC/ST students and 2 Lakhs (for OBC and General category students) per annum.<br>\r\n<li>Maximum age on 1 January 2021 should not exceed 30 years.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate should be pursuing Regular full-time.\r\nStudents can not avail of any other scholarship or financial aid from any other sources.<br>\r\n<li>60% marks or 6 GPA out of 10 credit points in each semester of the entire course is mandatory in order to continue the scholarship.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>There are a total of 1000 scholarships for SC/ST category students and 500 for OBC and general category students worth rupees 48,000/- annually by the ONGC Foundation for the meritorious students pursuing professional courses in Engineering, Medical stream, and Masterâs degree course in Business Administration, Geology and geophysics.<br><br>\r\n<b>Zone Wise States.</b><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Zone -1 (North)-</b>J&K, Delhi, Punjab, Himachal Pradesh, Haryana, Chandigarh, Uttarakhand, Uttar Pradesh.<br><br>\r\n<b>Zone -2 (West)-</b>Maharashtra, Gujarat, Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh, Goa, Daman & Diu, Dadar & Nagar Haveli.<br><br>\r\n<b>Zone -3 (North East)-</b>Assam, Sikkim, Mizoram, Arunachal Pradesh, Nagaland, Manipur, Meghalaya, Tripura.<br><br>\r\n<b>Zone -4 (East)-</b>Bihar, Jharkhand, Odisha, Chhattisgarh, West Bengal.<br><br>\r\n<b>Zone -5 (South)-</b>Tamil Nadu, Kerala, Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh, Telangana, Puducherry, Lakshadweep, Andaman & Nicobar Islands.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Copy of Birth Certificate/Class 10 Mark sheet as proof of age.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Certified copy of Caste Certificate in Hindi/English.\r\n<li>Copy of Class 12-mark sheet in case of Engineering/MBBS students.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Certified copy of annual income certificate of the family in Hindi/English language.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Copy of consolidated Graduation mark sheet in case of MBA/Masters in Geology/Geophysics students.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Copy of PAN card or the tentative date for submission of PAN card copy (in case it is not available.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Bank details of the applicant in the ECS form attested by the bank as prescribed.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Copy of undertaking.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Copy of Adhaar Card.<br>\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '48000\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates.\"', NULL, NULL, 50.00, 60.00, 50.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"All\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-03-30', 'ONGC Foundation', 48000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-06 13:24:56', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 03:37:04', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1586, 'AXVOV09A2B7d1dwRkC', 'Scholarship', 'Navi Mumbai scholarship.', 'https://schemenmmc.com/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Navi Mumbai Corporation has announced scholarships in six categories for students.\r\nNMCC PRO Mahendra Konde aids those eligible comprising children of widows or divorcees, economically backward children, backward class students, children of the project affected from Navi Mumbai, children of civic sanitation and contract staff as well as children of the quarry, construction, sand, and naka workers. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n1) Only those students belonging to economically weaker sections who have secured at least 65% marks in the previous year\'s annual examination are eligible to apply for this scholarship.<br>\r\n2) Backward class students who have secured a minimum of 60% marks in the previous year\'s examination are eligible to apply for this scholarship.<br>\r\n3) There is no requirement for marks for students other than the above two categories.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Who will get the scholarship ?</b><br>\r\n(1) Children of widowed/divorced women.<br>\r\n(2) Students from class 1 to college education from economic and weaker sections.<br>\r\n(3) Backward class students studying from class 1 to college.<br>\r\n(4) Students pursuing class 1st to college education from families of local project victims in the Navi Mumbai area.<br>\r\n(5) Children of sweepers and contract workers in municipal establishments in the Navi Mumbai area.<br>\r\n(6) Children of Quarry/Construction/Sand/Naka workers in the Navi Mumbai area.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions:-</b><br>\r\n1) Students who are admitted under RTE cannot avail of this scholarship scheme.<br>\r\n2) It is mandatory for students to have an account with a nationalized bank and link it with an Aadhaar card. The said bank account should be in Navi Mumbai.<br>\r\n3) If the bank account number and IFSC code of the student is found wrong in the application, the beneficiary will be solely responsible for it.<br>\r\n4) The beneficiary family should not have benefited from any other government / non-government scheme.<br>\r\n5) The bank account must belong to the student.<br>\r\n6) Studentâs bank account must have an Aadhaar link.<br>\r\n7) Bank account must be with a nationalized bank.<br>\r\n8) Documents must be uploaded in PDF format.<br>\r\n9) Students studying from classes 1st to 10th in Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation School cannot apply for this scheme.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b> Note:-</b><br>\r\n1) Only two children from a family can avail of this scholarship scheme.<br>\r\n2) Beneficiaries must have resided in the Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation area for at least 3 years.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b> Contact Details:</b><br>\r\n<b><li>Belapur, Nerul Division â</b><br>\r\n<li>Mr. Prakash Kamble â 9969008088,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. Mohan Gaikwad â 8652441101,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. To Anupama R â 8655590465.<br><br>\r\n<b>Vashi, Turbe Division â</b><br>\r\n<li>Mr. Beautiful foreigner â 9594841666,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. Santosh Supe â 8380987456,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. Nilima Dhongde â 9326540277.<br><br>\r\n<b>Elbows, Cochlear Section â</b><br>\r\n<li>Mr. Dadasaheb Bhosle â 9372106976,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. Smita Transactions â 8689868333,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. Gajanan Chavan â 8888849220.<br><br>\r\n<b>Airoli, Digha Division â</b><br>\r\n<li>Mr. Dashrath Gambhire â 9702309054,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. Pratiksha Hundare â 8898329622,<br>\r\n<li>Mr. Manohar Raut â 9224641224.<br>\r\n\r\n', '1) Photocopy of the Aadhaar card of mother, father, and students.<br>\r\n2) Proof of residence â In case of the property owner in Navi Mumbai municipal area, current year property tax payment receipt / Election ID card / Name in voter list / Water supply / Electricity bill / Annual rent agreement / Passport / Ration card / Nationalized bank passbook as proof. (Evidence of any 1 of the above)<br>\r\n3) Photocopy of one of the bank passbooks/checks of the studentâs own Aadhaar-linked account in a nationalized bank.<br>\r\n4) Previous Year Mark Sheet.<br>\r\n5) In case of emergency (eg epidemic, natural calamity, or man-made calamity, etc.) Mark sheet of previous year / if not exam of the previous year must be attached.<br>\r\n6) For children of cleaners and contract workers in municipal establishments in the Navi Mumbai area â Certificate from concerned Contractor / Sanitation Inspector / Sanitation Officer / Head of Department regarding parent working as a contract worker in Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation establishment.<br>\r\n7) For children from families of local project victims in the Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation area â Copy of certificate/satbara copy/award to the effect that the familyâs land has been acquired by CIDCO or MIDC for Navi Mumbai project is required to be attached with the application.<br>\r\n8) For Backward Class students pursuing education from Class I to College â Caste certificate from the competent authority stating that the student is Backward Class.<br>\r\n9) Income certificate from Honâble Tehsildar Thane stating that the annual family income is within Rs.8 lakhs for students from economic and weaker sections studying up to college from Delhi residing in Navi Mumbai.<br>\r\n10) For Children of Widowed or Divorced Women â The death certificate of her husband issued by a competent authority in case of a widow and a court order regarding divorce in case of a divorced woman must be attached to a scholarship application.<br>\r\n11) For Children of Quarry / Construction / Sand / Pipe Workers in Navi Mumbai Area â Proof that the applicantâs parent is a registered owner / NGO Worker in Stone Quarry / Construction / Sand / Pipe Worker.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance\r\n', '[\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"ITI\",\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '\"Class 10, Class 11, Class 12, ITI, Bachelors\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 150000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-18', '2023-02-15', 'Mumbai Corporation ', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-06 13:38:06', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-06 10:51:13', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1587, 'I5ONpbDQ4QAnoEBKcU', 'Competitions and Awards', ' Compose Jingle for  Mann Ki Baat', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/compose-jingle-100th-episode-mann-ki-baat/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZXv_K9e9H4k', 'Prime Minister Narendra Modi\'s monthly radio programme \'Mann Ki Baat\' has brought fresh life into the medium of radio, which was rapidly becoming archaic. Experts in the field of mass communication believe that \'Mann Ki Baat\' had an important role in keeping radio relevant.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Mann Ki Baat campaign has had a large impact on the lives of ordinary men and women, whether as a result of a change in behavior or increased awareness.<br><br> It will reach its 100th Episode in April 2023.\r\n<li>As we approach the 100th episode of Mann ki Baat, MyGov is hosting a \"Jingle Contest,\" encouraging all creative minds to self-compose a Jingle for this special episode of Mann Ki Baat.\r\nThe purpose of the contest is to create a memorable, easily recognizable melody that will remain in the minds and hearts of the citizens.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Technical Parameters:</b><br>\r\n<li>Participants need to provide a script and a jingle of 25-30 seconds, that is easily understandable, is peppy, and connects with the public at large.<br>\r\n<li> The participants should upload their entry as a high-quality audio file on any media platform, such as SoundCloud, YouTube, Google Drive, Dropbox, etc., and enter the publicly accessible link in the comments section.<br>\r\n<li>The script also needs to be submitted as a PDF document<br><br>\r\n<b>Gratification:</b><br>\r\n<li> The best Entry will be rewarded with a Cash Prize of Rs 11,000/-\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '11,000\r\n', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL,