(1589, 'DOhsU16cOZ0ZkG5O5Q', 'Competitions and Awards', 'NASI-Scopus Young Scientist Awards', 'https://elsevier.awardsplatform.com/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Scopus Young Scientist Awards, first launched by Elsevier in 2006, is part of an Elsevierâs global initiative to support early career researchers in their quest to advance the frontiers of science across a broad range of disciplines. In 2009, India officially adopted the program within its scientific community through Elsevierâs collaboration with The National Academy of Sciences, India (NASI). The program honours outstanding young researchers in India who are building their careers in academic research, helping them gain recognition for their work. As of 2022, 100+ winners have been announced.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>The 14th NASI Scopus Young Scientist Awards has 5 multi-disciplinary categories â<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>1. WOMEN IN SCIENCE â</b> To recognize Indiaâs most promising woman researchers who have demonstrated excellence in a scientific field with the possibility of societal impacts. Female applications only.\r\n <br><br>\r\n<b>2. AGRICULTURE, PLANT SCIENCES, AND RURAL DEVELOPMENT â </b>To recognize Indiaâs most promising researchers who are working in the field of AGRICULTURE and are committed to developing sustainable models that help in increasing food security and improving the quality of life of people living in rural areas.\r\n <br><br>\r\n<b>3. ENVIRONMENTALLY SOUND SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT â </b>To recognize Indiaâs most promising researchers who are working in the field of EARTH, ENVIRONMENTAL, OCEANOGRAPHIC, and ECOLOGICAL STUDIES, SOCIAL SCIENCES, and ECOSYSTEM and are contributing to protecting our planet and conserving its natural resources.\r\n <br><br>\r\n<b>4. BIOMEDICAL RESEARCH AND HEALTHCARE â </b>To recognize Indiaâs most promising researchers who are working in the field of MEDICINE AND BIOMEDICAL SCIENCES and are making ground-breaking contributions toward improving the health and well-being of citizens.\r\n <br><br>\r\n<b>5. INNOVATION IN ENGINEERING AND PHYSICAL SCIENCES â </b>To recognize Indiaâs most promising researchers who are working in the field of ENGINEERING, MATHEMATICS, PHYSICS, and CHEMISTRY and are harnessing it to drive disruptive and sustainable growth, with a potential for high industrial and/or societal impact.<br><br>\r\n<b>Research metrics for each category:</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li> Quality and number of publications.<br>\r\n<li> Nature and uniqueness of research.<br>\r\n<li> Outcomes of research.<br>\r\n <li>Impact on society.<br>\r\n<li> Vision of the researcher.<br>\r\n<li>If your research (both basic and applied) is empowering or can be a helpful technological tool for the above-mentioned categories, do not forget to mention it in your application as it can give your application additional weightage.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Rewards.</b><br>\r\nThe NASI Scopus Young Scientist of the year receives: <br>\r\n<li> A citation & a plaque.<br>\r\n<li> Prize of INR 75,000.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>  An Indian citizen, residing and working in India.<br>\r\n<li> Has completed at least PhD/MD or equivalent degree.\r\n<li>  Must be born on or after January 1st, 1977.<br>\r\n<li>  Each male applicant must apply only under one category. A female applicant can apply under âWomen in Scienceâ and an additional category.<br>\r\n <li>All applicants will be expected to apply for the awards within the cut-off date.<br>\r\n<li> Activity entered for this award must have been undertaken no more than five (5) years prior to the closing date of entries published in one or more respected, externally refereed scientific journal(s), book(s) or equivalent electronic publication(s) and the publication must be indexed in Scopus.<br><br>\r\n<b>Your application for any award category must comprise:</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Personal statement(s) that complement and build on the picture that is evident from the Research Metrics associated with any category. They should tell the story that would otherwise remain untold. Applicants may use any means to share their statement, such as a document (up to 500 words) or a film (up to 5 mins). The statement must reflect the impact of your research on society and the vision of the researcher and will play an instrumental role in the selection of the winner.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li> Basic information that would include your full name, most recent affiliation, number of publications, number of publications where the applicant is the first and last author, year of first publication, and subject area focus (the most frequent three).<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li> Your Scopus ID and ORCID, a feature that has been incorporated to make it convenient for applicants since the ID will help auto-populate the applicantâs details.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '75000\r\n', '[\"Post Doctoral \"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Ph.D., M.D.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-04', '2023-09-30', 'Elsevier and National Academy of Sciences ', 75000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-06 17:00:39', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 07:45:55', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1590, 'ZfJcxufyMw4nbHvMHp', 'Scholarship', ' Vidyadhan  ladakh scholarship', 'https://www.vidyadhan.org/register/student', '', '', '', ' Vidyadhan  ladakh scholarship', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G9kclu-CRFo', 'Vidyadhan Scholarship Program is conducted by Sarojini Damodaran Foundation is for meritorious students who cannot afford higher studies. 10th and 12th passed students from states such as Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, Maharashtra, Gujarat, Karnataka, Kerala, and Telangana can apply.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Over 2800 students are presently associated with this program.For selection, each student has to perform consistently and perform well in the interview. The Sarojini Damodaran Foundation sponsors education directly with the help of registered and reliable external sources.<br><br>\r\n<li>Those selected will be eligible for a two-year scholarship from the Foundation. If they continue to do well, they will be given scholarships for pursuing any degree course of their interest; these scholarships are directly through the foundation or external sponsors who have registered with the Foundation. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Students from Ladakh are only eligible to apply for this scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>Students whose family annual income is less than Rs. 2 Lakhs.<br>\r\n<li>Students who have completed their 10th grade/SSC exam in the year 2022 from Ladakh. <br>\r\n<li>They should also have scored 65% or obtained a 6.5 CGPA in their 10th Grade/SSC examination. <br>\r\n<li> The cut-off mark for students with disability is 55%.or 5.5 CGPA.<br>\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li> The scholarship amount for 11th and 12th grade will be a maximum of Rs.10000/year.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship amount varies from Rs 10,000 to Rs 60,000 per year depending on the state, course, duration etc.<br>\r\n<li>The selected students will be required to attend the mentoring programs from the Foundation.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Important Dates:</b><br>\r\n<li>12th February 2023: Application last date<br>\r\n<li>14th February 2023: Screening Test<br>\r\n<li>15th February to 20th February 2023: Interview/Tests will be scheduled during this time frame. Exact date and location will be intimated to each of the shortlisted candidates.<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact Details</b><br>\r\nFor any clarifications send an email to <br>\r\n<li><b>vidyadhan.ladakh@sdfoundationindia.com or <br><li>call Vishwanath, Phone: 8296010803/7349354415.</b><br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>Class 10th and 12th mark sheet.  (If the original mark sheet is not available, you can upload the provisional /online mark sheet from the SSLC/CBSE/ICSC website.)<br>\r\n<li>Income Certificate   (from a competent authority; ration card not accepted.)\r\n<li>Photograph <br>\r\n<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '60000\r\n', '[\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"\\\"Class 10 to Class 12, Undergraduates\\\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-26', '2023-02-24', 'Sarojini Damodaran Foundation', 60000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 10:27:12', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 04:02:04', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1591, '7psyPFyAKvgk6GLEra', 'Competitions and Awards', 'AIYSEE 2023', 'https://www.aiysee.com/index.php', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cvnvJ-NVqKI', 'AIYSEE aims to provide financial assistance to help high-performing students from any economical background to continue and complete their education, including those whose families are going through any kind of crisis. In addition, in due course, the program will also offer selected candidates additional support which could include mentorship and access to career counseling programmes. The scholarship fund is exclusively meant for meeting the academic expenses of the selected candidates which include tuition fees and hostel fees.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Any 12th passed out or appearing candidate from a recognized board whose appearing year is 2023 or passed year is 2018 onwards and appearing in any Medical / Engineering Entrance Exam (like JEE, NEET, etc.) are eligible.<br><br>\r\n<b>Application Fee:</b><br>\r\n<li>Application Fee: 1100.00 for all Quota (General/ OBC/ SC/ ST).<br>\r\n<li>Mode of payment: Through Debit card / Credit card / Netbanking / UPI.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b> AIYSEE 2023 Exam Pattern</b><br><br>\r\n<li><b>Mode of the Exam : </b>Online mode (Computer Based) or Offline mode (Pen and Paper Based).<br>\r\n<li><b>Duration of Examination:</b> 90 Minutes.<br>\r\n<li><b>Question type: </b>Objective (Multiple Choice Question)<br><br>\r\n<b>Subjects.</b><br>\r\n<li>Physics- 30 Questions.<br>\r\n<li>Chemistry- 30 Questions.<br>\r\n<li>Mathematics/Biology â 30 Questions.<br>\r\n<li>Total question : 90.<br>\r\n<li>Each question carries one mark.<br>\r\n<li>0.25 marks will be deducted for each wrong answer\r\n.<br>', 'As Prescribed.', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance.', '[\"Class 12\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Class 12 [appearing for  Medical , Engineering Entrance Exam ]\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 300000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-19', '2023-03-22', 'All India youth scholarship entrance examination', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 13:00:46', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-28 04:22:34', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1592, 'yR1Fd8Zl6aqQTh4TTr', 'Abroad', 'ESED scholarship', 'https://www.globalelectricity.org/scholarship/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Education for Sustainable Energy Development (ESED) scholarship program inspires the next generation of innovators and thinkers to create a sustainable future. Our scholars are exceptional students from developing countries studying in sustainable energy development.<br><br>\r\n<li>Today, the need for globally-oriented practitioners and researchers is growing rapidly. Our one-of-a-kind scholarship program fosters the next generation of energy, climate, and electricity sector specialists who will be prepared to tackle the challenges of the future.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:\r\n</b><br>\r\n<li>Undertake masterâs-level studies in areas directly related to zero-carbon energy, smart grids, electric transportation, energy storage, advanced electricity technologies, public policy, economics, law, political science, Advanced Chemical Engineering MSc, Advanced Heat Engineering MSc or other relevant fields\r\n<li>Eligible applicants must be pursuing full-time studies for at least one full school year (two or three semesters), beginning in autumn. Students in the second year of a two-year program are eligible to apply, provided that they meet this requirement.<br><br>\r\n<li>Be a citizen of a developing country/territory on the List of official development aid recipients identified by the Development Co-operation Directorate (DAC) of the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD).<br><br>\r\n<li>Be committed to returning to their home country after their studies to contribute to its development.<br><br>\r\n<li>Be an outstanding student:<br>\r\n1. Graduates with excellent grades in the top 20% of their class.<br>\r\n2. Is committed to zero-carbon energy development\r\n3.Has a history of community involvement.<br>\r\n4.Is determined to advance their knowledge and understanding.<br>\r\n5. With the aim of supporting developing countries in building local expertise, GSEP will allocate a share of its scholarships to students pursuing masterâs studies in universities based in developing countries.<br>\r\n', '<li>Birth certificate or passport.<br>\r\n<li>Updated Resume (details on education, awards, work experience, participation in other activities, etc.).<br>\r\n<li>Official translated Transcripts from the university.<br>\r\n<li>Admission letter from the university.<br>\r\n<li>Scores of tests like TOEFL, IELTS, PTE, etc.<br>\r\n<li>Program outline.<br>\r\n<li>Most recent university transcript.<br>\r\n<li>Two references.<br>\r\n<li>Provide a complete copy of the Academic reference form.<br>\r\n<li>Personal or academic reference letter.<br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'up to $10,000 US per year', '[\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 500000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-04-07', ' Global Sustainable Electricity Partnership (GSEP)', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 13:36:19', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 08:46:22', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1593, 'lrvUwmoIcVjfHD8Lq6', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Climate Science Olympiad', 'https://climatescience.org/olympiad', '', '', '', '', '', 'It\'s organized by Climate Science, a London-based charity, working to provide reliable climate education to students.\r\nThe ClimateScience (CS) Olympiad is a global competition engaging youth to find solutions to some of the most challenging climate issues and empowering them to be the climate <br><br>\r\n<li>leaders/innovators of tomorrow.2021 was the first year the Olympiad was conducted to engage thousands of students from across the globe. We aimed for 10,000 participants and reached more than 12,400 from 149 countries.\r\nThe student competition to find solutions to climate change. Are you ready to step into the shoes of world leaders?  <br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Regardless of age, participants compete in the same qualifiers and answer the same type of problem statements. However, we only compare participants within their age brackets. This means we score the three brackets independently and normalize scores within each. Semi-finalists, finalists, and winners are those with the highest normalized scores. This ensures fair comparison regardless of age.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Open for free to age groups 12-16, 17-20, 21-25 years old.<br>\r\n<li>Either participate alone or in a team of two. They must have access to stable internet as the entire competition is online.<br>\r\n<li>Must be fluent in at least one of the following languages â English, Portuguese, Spanish, French, Russian, Chinese, Polish, Dutch, Japanese, Italian, German, and Romanian.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\nClimateScience Olympiad 2023 winners will receive a cash prize of Win $10,000or for a sponsored trip to Dubai during the UN Climate Summit, COP28.<br><br>\r\n<b>The competition will be conducted in the following 4 stages â</b><br>\r\n<b>Qualifiers:</b><br>\r\n<li>Format: 10 Multiple choice questions designed by educators and scientists.<br>\r\n<li>Time requirement: 25 minutes\r\n<li>Technical requirements: Fully online, students need to have access to any digital device and a stable internet connection.<br><br>\r\n<b>Quarter-Finals:</b><br>\r\n<li>Up to 50,000 students (top 5% of each monthâs qualifiers).<br>\r\n<li>Format: 15 in-depth multiple-choice questions to be completed in 25 minutes.<br><br>\r\n<b>Semi-Finals:</b><br>\r\n<li>Up to 5,000 teams. The top 10% of each monthâs quarter-finalists are invited..<br>\r\n<li>Themes:  Clean Energy, Sustainable transportation, Biodiversity, Water Resources, Sustainable agriculture, Global Development and health, Sustainable economy.<br>\r\n<li>Format: Participants receive a complex problem set based on one of the themes mentioned above, they have to write a 1000 words proposal that is socially equitable, realistic, economically feasible, and rapidly implementable.<br>\r\n<li>Time requirement â 3 hours, semi-finals are held every last Sunday of the month till August 2022.<br><br>\r\n<b>Finals</b><br>\r\n<li>Top 100 teams.<br>\r\n<li>Same format as the semi-finals plus 20 minutes presentations in addition to the essays judged by world-leading scientists, innovators, and policy-makers.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', ' $10,000', '[\"Secondary\",\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Cass 6 to Class 12, Undergraduates, Postgraduates.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-06-10', ' Climate Science, London-based charity.', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 14:33:40', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 09:05:18', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1594, 'QET7vl7IliucNOPlPu', 'Abroad', 'K C Mahindra Scholarships for Abroad Studies ', 'https://scholarship.kcmet.org/user/login', '', '', '', '', '', 'The K. C. Mahindra Education Trust was established in 1953 to promote literacy and higher learning in the country. Since its inception, the Trust has positively impacted the lives of over 800,000 deserving students with enormous potential to initiate change and shape the future of not only India but also the world.<br><br>\r\n<li> The K. C. Mahindra Scholarship for Post Graduate Studies Abroad was the first scholarship to be set up by the Trust and has been awarded to over 1600 students to date. It is an interest-free loan scholarship awarded to meritorious students who wish to pursue their post-graduate studies abroad.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Possess a First Class degree or an equivalent diploma of similar standard from a recognized University.<br>\r\n<li>Must be an Indian citizen.<br>\r\n<li>Should have secured admission or has applied for admission in reputable foreign universities for courses commencing from August 2023 but not later than February 2024.<br>\r\n<li>Candidates studying in the FINAL YEAR of the degree or diploma courses are also eligible to apply, provided they produce before the end of June their final year mark sheet or provisional certificate from the institute stating that they have completed their degree/diploma course and have secured a first class.\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Note:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applications are now open for the academic year 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Students going abroad for undergraduate studies, seminars & conferences are not eligible for this scholarship<br>\r\n<li>The deadline to apply for the scholarship is 31.03.2023<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>A maximum of Rs.10 lakh per scholar, awarded to the top 3 K.C. Mahindra Fellows.<br>\r\n<li>A maximum of Rs.5 lakh per scholar, awarded to remaining successful applicants.<br>\r\n<li>For queries on the K. C. Mahindra Scholarship for Post Graduate Studies Abroad, please email us on  kcmetscholarships@mahindra.com.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n', '<li>Copy of Admission letter.<br>\r\n<li>A signed testimonial (letter of recommendation) from any one referee.<br>\r\n<li>A short statement as to the general aptitude and interest, the type of vocation the candidate would like to pursue and his/her ambitions and aspirations in life.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of GRE/GMAT Score.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of IELTS/TOEFL Score.<br>\r\n<li>Evidence of course and degree certificates along with Mark-sheets.<br>\r\n<li>Rank certificate, if applicable.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of 10th & 12th mark sheet & School Leaving Certificate.<br>\r\n<li> Copy of Passport.<br>\r\n<li>Your latest C.V.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '5 lakhs.', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-03-31', 'K. C. Mahindra Education Trust', 500000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 16:32:55', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-07 11:30:44', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1595, 'VJzsbYX7zv5Y7rGeuh', 'Scholarship', 'Bhajan Lal Scholarship ', 'http://bhajanfoundation.org/bhajan-lal-scholarship-form/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Bhajan Lal Scholarship which has been created by the Bhajan Global Impact Foundation will provide financial assistance to students for higher education . The main aim of launching the Bhajan Lal Scholarship is to promote higher education in the field of the environment so that the student pursuing the courses will be able to learn about the environment and the related disciplines because this Foundation observes that the discipline in the field of the environment should be given preference at the institution level also.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>There are many students who have a great interest in the field of environment. So as to increase interest and encouragement towards the studies of the environment the Bhajan Global Impact Foundation has launched a new scheme known as the Bhajan Lal Scholarship. The main aim of launching this scheme is to encourage the studies of the environment at an institutional level. With the help of this scheme, the students who are pursuing the courses like M.Sc, M. Phill, and Ph. D with the subject of the environment will be able to learn disciplines, observations, and many other things related to the environment.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>An applicant must have achieved a bachelorâs degree in an environmental-related subject.<br>\r\n<li>The candidate must be pursuing the courses like M. Sc, M. Phill, and Ph. D with the environment related subject.<br>\r\n<li>An applicant must have admitted themselves to a recognized university in India.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits: </b><br>\r\n<li>This scholarship will cover the tuition fee, living expenses, travel expenses, and vice versa.<br>\r\n<li>The duration of this scholarship is for 6 months\r\n.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Terms And Conditions Under Bhajan Lal Scholarship.</b><br>\r\n<li>If the student wants to pursue the other courses under bhajanlal scholarship then it will be on behalf of justification on the course related to sustainability or the environment.<br>\r\n<li>The students who have achieved a bachelorâs degree are eligible to apply under this scheme.<br>\r\n<li>This scholarship will be reviewed at the end of each semester or every 6 months.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Last qualifying examination Marksheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bachelor Degree Marksheet.<br>\r\n<li>Residence Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Admission Receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>\r\n<li>Mobile number.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance.', '[\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"M.Sc, M.Phil, Ph.D.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 250000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-01', '2023-03-31', 'Bhajan Global Impact Foundation', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-08 13:12:33', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 10:27:40', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
