(1601, 'DuJLxBmGJsEVzSnnAi', 'Scholarship', 'L and T Build India Scholarship', 'https://www.lntecc.com/build-india-scholarship/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RvGeShlC9uc', 'L&T Build India Scholarship Scheme is an illustrious user-oriented programme with a remarkable ascendancy for the past 2 decades through which L&T molds aspiring young talents with engineering acumen into capable construction technology managers to play a more relevant part in engineering the future of L&T Construction.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>L&T is offering the âL&T Build India Scholarshipâ reassurance to students who are facing such difficulties in completing and completing engineering. It is currently offering this opportunity to students who wish to enroll in the Construction Technology and Management course at MTech for the 2022-23 academic year.L&T is undertaking this project in partnership with IITs in Chennai / Delhi and NITs in Suratkal / Trichy.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n <li>Students applying for the L&T Build India Scholarship should have passed BE / BTech (Civil / Electrical) with over 70% & above marks till the 06th Semester in the 2023 academic year  With a flair for building landmarks.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Only final year candidates (those who are pursuing their final year B.E. / B. Tech, those who are expected to graduate by June â August 2023) from core Civil Engineering & Core Electrical Engineering are eligible to apply. <br><br>\r\n<li>Mechanical Candidates are not eligible to apply. Candidates who have graduated in the year 2022 or prior to that are not eligible to apply.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li><b>Stipend (Scholarship) </b><br>For the 24-month course, we will pay you a stipend of Rs.13,400/- p.m. The sponsorship fee and tuition fee will be paid directly to the respective llTs/NlTs by L&T. The sponsored candidates need to pay Hostel Accommodation fee & Mess fee.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li><b>Undertaking</b><br>\r\nOn selection, and before entering the course, you will need to execute an undertaking for a value of Rs. 5 Lakhs to successfully complete the course and subsequently serve the company for 5 years thereafter.<br><br>\r\n<b>Programme Features:</b><br>\r\n<li>Program Name: M.Tech in Construction Technology & Management through L&T\'s Build India Scholarship.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Sponsored at:24 month sponsored course at IIT Madras, IIT Delhi, NITK Surathkal & NIT Trichy.<br>\r\n<li>Course fee borne entirely by L&T.<br>\r\n<li>Stipend is paid during the programme.<br>\r\n<li>Live projects @ L&T project sites during the course of the programme.<br>\r\n<li>Guided by buddies and mentored by BIS alumni during the programme.<br>\r\n<li>Placement on successful completion of the course.<br><br>\r\n<b>Selection Procedure: </b><br>\r\nEligible candidates will be shortlisted and an online written test will be conducted. Questions related to the subject and aptitude are asked. Those who pass this test are called for an interview. The finalists will then have a medical fitness test.<br><br>\r\n<b>BIS Important Dates:</b><br>\r\n<li>Last Date for Online application:28 March.<br>\r\n<li>Online Written Test: 19th March.<br>\r\n<li>Interview Process: Between April 2023â May 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Issue of Sponsorship Letters: May 2023-June 2023\r\nJoining in L&T-Mid August<br>\r\n<li><b>For Queries:  BIS@LNTECC.COM</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th and 12th mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '13,400/month', '[\"Engineering\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"B.E,  B. Tech,  M.E, M.Tech.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-01', '2023-02-28', 'L&T Construction', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-09 14:37:44', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-07 04:06:27', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1602, 'AJwDlQE66Kg1YCyYuL', 'Abroad', 'Mark R Graham Scholarship', 'https://jeancellentgrant.com/apply/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Mark R Graham has been managing assets since 1992 and is the founder and/or co-founder of several alternative asset funds.  Mr. Graham graduated with honors from the University of Michigan and received his Juris Doctorate from Georgetown University.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>The Mark R. Graham Scholarship is a comprehensive program that aims to provide financial assistance to students who are pursuing higher education. Our goal is to support and encourage these students as they work towards their academic and professional goals. The scholarship is open to full-time students who are enrolled in an accredited college or university in the USA. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Students who are pursuing higher education are eligible to apply for this scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>Attend an accredited US-Based university or college.<br>\r\n<li>Possess an excellent academic record\r\nDemonstrate the ability to lead.<br>\r\n<li>Grant must go to tuition purposes\r\nComplete an essay for submission (see essay guidelines below).<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>The scholarship award is $1,000.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Important Deadlines.</b><br>\r\n<li>Application Deadline: May 1, 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Announcement Date: May 15, 2023.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship will be awarded to the recipient by May 20, 2023.<br><br>\r\n<b>Essay Guidelines.</b><br>\r\nTo qualify for the scholarship, please follow the essay guidelines below:<br>\r\n<b>Essay Topic : </b><br>\r\n<li>Where do you see yourself 10 years from now?<br>\r\n<li>The essay should be 600 words.<br>\r\n<li>Any resources should be carefully noted and cited appropriately.<br>\r\n<li>Any plagiarism or fabrication will disqualify the applicant from award disbursement.<br><br>\r\n<b>Note :</b><br>\r\n<li>The application process for the Mark R. Graham Scholarship includes completing an online application form and writing a 600-word essay on the topic of [Where do you see yourself 10 years from now?]. The deadline for the scholarship is May 1, 2023.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Mark R. Graham Scholarship is designed to provide financial support to deserving students who are committed to furthering their education. By awarding this scholarship, we hope to make a positive impact on the lives of these students and help them achieve their full potential.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', 'As Prescribed.', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '$1000', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-05-01', 'Mark R Graham ', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-09 14:57:50', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-10 03:54:10', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1603, 'CLO3DRdPbrSgqKZfFG', 'Abroad', 'McGraw Fellowship for Business Journalism', 'https://www.mcgrawcenter.org/the-harold-w-mcgraw-jr-business-journalism-fellowships/application-form/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Harold W. McGraw, Jr. Center for Business Journalism provides experienced journalists with maximum grants and the editorial support needed to produce deeply reported enterprise and investigative stories that delve into critical economic, financial, or business issues across a wide array of subjects. You donât need to be a business reporter to apply; many of our previous Fellows have been generalists, or cover beats such as health care, education or the environment. Others have focused on issues such as economic inequality or corporate accountability.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>We consider proposals from both freelance and staff journalists in all forms of media â text, audio, and short-form video â and encourage those that combine formats to create a multimedia package. We look for projects that focus on important local or regional topics, as well as those that tackle compelling national or international stories or report on under-covered communities or issues. Journalists of color and those from diverse backgrounds are strongly encouraged to apply.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The McGraw Fellowship for Business Journalism is open to anyone with at least five years of professional experience in journalism.<br>\r\n<li> We support work by freelance journalists, as well as by reporters and editors currently working at a news organization or a journalism non-profit. In the latter case, reporters and editors can apply directly in the name of their organization.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>The Fellowship provides a grant of up to $15,000 for each project. The exact amount will depend on the time it takes to complete the project and the expenses needed; freelance journalists may also use some of the funding as a stipend for living expenses during the Fellowship.<br>><br>\r\n<b> How to apply?</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicants should submit a well-focused story proposal of no more than three pages through the accompanying online form. Think of it as a pitch, much like you would submit to an editor at a newspaper, magazine, audio or digital outlet: give us enough preliminary reporting and documentation to demonstrate that the story is solid. <br><br>\r\n<li>The proposal should highlight whatâs new and significant about the story, why it matters and what its potential impact might be. The proposal should also note where significant stories on the subject have run elsewhere and how the proposed piece would differ. <br><br><li>Applicants should also briefly outline a proposed reporting plan and a timeline for completing the story. And while you donât need to have a media outlet lined up for your story before you apply, if you do have one, let us know that in your proposal.<br><br>\r\n<li>In addition, applicants should enclose three journalism samples. The samples should be professionally published work that showcases your ability to tackle an in-depth story in the proposed medium. Please also provide us with an up-to-date resume.  No references are required at the time of application, but those who are chosen as finalists will be asked to provide references from two editors or others familiar with their work. Freelance applicants for whom getting references is a problem can discuss alternatives with the McGraw Center.<br><br>\r\n<b>Budget:</b><br>\r\n<li>No budget is required at the time of application. Applicants chosen as finalists will be asked to provide an estimated budget at that time.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Contact us at :</b><br>mcgrawcenter(at)journalism.cuny.edu.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'As prescribed', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '$15,000', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Bachelor of Journalism, Master in Journalism, PhD in Journalism\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-11', '2023-03-31', 'Harold W. McGraw, Jr. Center for Business Journalism ', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-09 15:19:13', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-09 10:15:57', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
