(1606, 'vxZWebxw5MkgkwvOxD', 'Scholarship', ' E Grantz Scholarship Kerala', 'https://www.egrantz.kerala.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'A new scholarship is created by the organization presented in Kerala state. Monthly benefits are provided under this scholarship presented by the Government of Kerala. The scholarship will be provided to the Post Matric students. The students will be able to get the benefit of the E-Grantz Scholarship directly in their bank accounts. A new website is also created so the students can easily apply for the scholarship presented by the Kerala Government.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>To provide scholarships to those students who belong to scheduled castes and tribes and are pursuing chartered accountant and company secretarial courses the government is implementing various kinds of schemes. Through these schemes, scholarships will also be available to those students who are in IIT, IIM, and other deemed universities.\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li> For this, the government has also issued an order revising the criteria for educational benefits of SC and ST students. Other than that the government will also introduce free ship cards for admission to educational institutions. Through these cards, students are not required to pay any fees in advance. In order to get this card beneficiaries are required to register on the e-grants portal and submit caste, income, and educational certificates.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The students studying at the post-matriculation level of studies from a recognized university/board are eligible to apply. <br>\r\n<li>They must have taken admission under the merit and reservation quota.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate must be a resident of Kerala.<br>\r\n<li>The annual income of the family should be less than 1 lakh.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligible courses:</b>\r\n<li>Degree, Diploma, Doctoral, Higher Secondary, Polytechnic, Post Graduate, Professional, and VHSE courses.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b> Eligible categories</b>\r\n<li>Scheduled Caste (SC), Other Backward Classes (OBCs), Other Eligible Communities (OECs), and other socially/economically backward communities.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits and rewards:</b>\r\n<li><b>For SC/OEC -</b> Stipend amount of INR 630 to students studying in colleges which are less than 8 km from their residence. Stipend amount of INR 750 to students whose colleges are above 8kms from their residence. INR 1500 to students pursuing professional courses and residing on their own due to a lack of hostel facilities.<br>\r\n<li><b>For OBC-</b>The scholarship amount of INR 160 was given to students pursuing 10+2 courses.<br>\r\n<li><b>For PG and professional courses-</b> Day scholars get INR 200 and hostellers get INR 250.<br>\r\n<li><b>For polytechnic courses-</b>Day scholars get INR 100 and hostellers get INR 150.<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact Details</b>\r\n<li><b>Address:</b> Directorate of Scheduled Castes Development, Museum- Nandhavanam Road, Nandhavanam, Vikasbhavan PO, Thiruvananthapuram- 695033.<br>\r\n<li><b>Email ID:</b> egrantz3.0helpline@gmail.com\r\n<li><b>Contact Number (SC Directorate):</b> 0471-2737252, 0471-2737251.<br>\r\n<li><b>Toll-free Number (ST Department): </b>1800-425-2312.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th and 12th mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'INR 750/month', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\",\"Diploma\",\"Professional course\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Higher Secondary, Diploma, Polytechnic, Undergraduates, Post Graduate, Professional,  Doctoral, and VHSE courses.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]'