(1608, '24tm7qBRE0oOBiOS1f', 'Scholarship', 'Har Chhatravritti Scholarship', 'https://harchhatravratti.highereduhry.ac.in/', '', '', '', '', '', '\"Har-Chhatravratti\" is a centralized portal developed by the Department of Higher Education that provides a one-stop solution for the end-to-end scholarship process right from submission of application, verification, and disbursal to end beneficiary. Keeping in view the State Governmentâs commitment to making beneficiary-oriented schemes easily accessible, seamless, and transparent, a centralized State Scholarship Portal has been developed by bringing in 12 scholarship schemes of 5 major departments of the government under a single platform.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Scholarships are offered to deserving and needy students to encourage them to take up Higher education. This incentive falls in line with the motto of Higher Education of the State: Access, Equity, and Quality. Generation makes a Nation. Therefore the Govt. of India and Govt. of Haryana are always putting their efforts to attract students to Higher Education.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Candidate Must have passed Matric or Higher Secondary or any higher examination from a recognized Board/University/Institute.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate must be studying in an intermediate, graduate, and postgraduate level course.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate must be domiciled in Haryana.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate Must continue studies in the same stream/group.<br>\r\n<li> the attendance should be more than 75%.<br>\r\n<li>Family Income Should not exceed more than Rs.1 lakh.<br>\r\n', '<li>Parivar pehchan patra (Famly Id).<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar card copy.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants photo and signature.<br>\r\n<li>Income caste certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Haryana domicile certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Previous mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Fee receipt(except for 1 year students).<br>\r\n<li>BPL certificate (if applicable).<br>\r\n<li> Father\'s death certificate (if applicable).<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \"