(1610, '3Yrlv3Z7q5XcCQ0bWQ', 'Abroad', ' Leuven Scholarships for International Students', 'https://wet.kuleuven.be/apps/fund/new.php', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Science@Leuven Scholarships are for motivated and talented international students who are interested in participating in an international master programme of the Faculty of Science of the K.U.Leuven.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\nApplicants must meet and prove the following requirements:<br>\r\n <li>The applicants have not studied or worked at the University of Leuven before,<br>\r\n <li>Tthe applicants have a bachelor\'s degree from a foreign university that gives them access to the master\'s programme they are applying for,<br>\r\n <li>The applicants have not yet acquired a master\'s degree or a PhD,<br>\r\n <li>The applicants can prove having had excellent study results during their former training,<br>\r\n <li>The applicants can prove a very strong knowledge of English ( TOEFL (minimum score of 94 internet-based with at least 19 for reading, 18 for Listening, 19 for speaking and 21 for writing) or IELTS (minimum score of 7 overall, whilst at least 6,5 for reading, 6 for listening, 6 for speaking and 6 for writing),<br>\r\n <li>The applicants show strong motivation to follow a master\'s programme at the Faculty of Science of the K.U.Leuven<br>\r\n <li>The applicants are willing to act as an ambassador for the programme.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits and duration:</b><br>\r\n<li>The amount of the scholarship can be up to 10.000 Euro for 1 year. The scholarship will always cover the tuition fee for 1 year, the insurance and basic health insurance coverage. The amount awarded for living expenses can vary.<br>\r\n<li>For two-year Masterâs programmes, the scholarship for the second master\'s year will only be continued on the condition that the student had outstanding results in the first master\'s year.<br><br>\r\n<b>Application instructions:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicants have to apply for the Master\'s programme of their choice through the application tool of KU Leuven. You will need to upload a screenshot that you successfully submitted the application for admissions when you register on the website of the scholarship.<br><br>\r\n<li>Only applications that have been submitted (with the International Office and registered on the website of the scholarship) before 15 February 2023 will be considered for the scholarship.<br><br>\r\n<li>It is important to read the scholarship application page and visit the official website (link found below) to access the application form and for detailed information on how to apply for this scholarship.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>\r\n', 'â¬ 10.000', '[\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Postgraduates.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-04', '2023-02-15', 'Faculty of Science and its alumni association Science', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-10 17:22:31', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-10 12:30:24', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1611, 'RaMCihVClhroYZiFoc', 'Scholarship', 'Tripura Post Matric Scholarship', 'https://scholarships.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'There are a lot of post-matric scholarships available for students who are currently studying in the Tripura state and want to get proper opportunities so that they can continue their education even if they have completed their class 12th education. The candidates will be offered a Tripura Post Matric Scholarship For SC Students by the Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment, Government of India.<br><br>\r\n<li> Post-matric Scholarship opportunities in the Tripura state will help the candidates to get a proper career and they will be able to get prestigious job opportunities if they have a good educational premise set up with the help of the Government of their particular state.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b> <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Be an Indian national. <br>\r\n<li> Must be the domicile holder of Tripura. <br>\r\n<li> Must belong to SC category. <br>\r\n<li> Family income should be not exceeding more than INR 2,50,000. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligible courses: </b> <br>\r\n<b>Group 1: </b> <br>\r\n1) Degree and Postgraduate level courses in Medicine, Engineering, Technology, Planning, Architecture, Design, Fashion, Technology, Agriculture, Veterinary and Allied Sciences, Management, Business Finance/Administration, Computer Sciences, and Applications.2) Postgraduation Diploma courses in various branches of Management and Medicine3)C.A/I.C.W.A./C.S./I.C.F.A. etc. (Applicable at Day Scholar rate only INR 550 per month)4)M. Phil., PhD and Post-doctoral Programmes (D.Lit., D.Sc. etc.),5)L.L.B, Integrated L.L.B and L.L.M.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Group 2:</b>  <br>\r\nProfessional courses leading to a degree, diploma, and certificate in Pharmacy (B. Pharma), Nursing (B.Nursing), BFS, and other para-medical branches like rehabilitation, diagnostics, etc, Mass Communication, Hotel Management, and Catering, Travel/Tourism/Hospitality Management, Interior Decoration, Commerical Arts, Finance for which entrance qualification is minimum senior secondary and vocational stream, ITI courses, and polytechnic where entrance qualification is Class 12 or above.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Group 3:</b> <br>\r\nGraduate and Postgraduate courses that are not covered under Group 1 and 2 [e.g. B.A./B.Sc./B.Com. etc, M.A./M.Sc./M.Ed./M. Pharma etc.]<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Group 4: </b> <br>\r\nAll Post-matriculation level non-degree courses for which the entrance qualification is High School (Class 10)<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits and Rewards: </b><br>\r\nThe scholarship amount vary depending on the courses and duration.<br>\r\n<li>Maintenance allowance up to 1200 per month.<br>\r\n<li>Reimbursement of compulsory fees.<br>\r\n<li>Further, includes study Tour charges.<br>\r\n<li>Book allowance will be given.<br>\r\n<li>Additional allowance is given to students with disabilities.<br><br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Attested copy of certificate/degree/diploma for all the examinations passed .<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>A caste certificate duly signed by an authorized Revenue Officer not below the rank of Tehsildar. <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>An income declaration by the self-employed parents/guardians issued by the Revenue Officer, not below the rank of Tehsildar.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '15000\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 250000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-02-20', ' Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment, Government of India', 15000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 11:04:38', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 05:36:25', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1612, '0XY0feCu84OTv1ie3n', 'Scholarship', 'KSCSTE Back To Lab Fellowship', 'https://submit.kscste.kerala.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The âBack-to-Labâ programme  of the Women Scientists Division offers Research and Post-Doctoral Fellowship to women who have a break in their careers, to facilitate their re-entry into science research. The fellowship is provided normally for a period of 2 years. The scheme is open to unemployed women. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> Only women candidates are eligible to apply.<br>\r\n<li> Applicant should be a Permanent Resident of Kerala.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant should be unemployed and should be under career-break due to family commitments or other related matters, at the time of application.<br>\r\n<li> Applicant should not receiving any emoluments from any source at the time of application.<br>\r\n<li> Those who have availed KSCSTE Back-to-Lab Fellowship earlier for their Ph.D programme are not eligible to apply.<br>\r\n<li> Age limit: 40 years â as on the date of application, relaxable for 3 years for OBC and 5 years for SC/ST.<br>\r\n<li> Applicant should have qualified Ph.D. as on the date of application and should have scored minimum 60% marks for post-graduation.<br>\r\n<li> Applicant should have chosen an institution as Research Centre subject to the following.<br>\r\n<li> The proposed Research Centre should not be the same as their Ph.D Research centre.<br>\r\n<li> Research centre should preferably be in Kerala, [however, premier National Institutions viz.,IISER, IIT, IISc etc outside the State shall also be considered ].<br>\r\n<li> Tenable in Government Institutions only.<br>\r\n<li>Tenable only in R&D institutions (National/State level) or University Departments.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Applicant should have published at least one research paper in a SCI Journal/ secured patent.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Those who have already availed one Post-Doctoral Fellowship from KSCSTE or elsewhere are not eligible to apply.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Applicant should have published at least one research paper in a SCI Journal/ secured patent.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Those who have already availed one Post-Doctoral Fellowship from KSCSTE or elsewhere are not eligible to apply.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits and Duration:</b> <br>\r\n\r\n<li> The scheme offers Post-doctoral fellowship of 45,000/-+ 10 % HRA p.m. along with an annual contingency grant of Rs.75,000/-.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<li> Duration of the Fellowship is limited to maximum 2 years.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>For queries:</b> <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<b>E-mail: </b> <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n1.wsd.kscste(at)kerala.gov.in<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n2.womenscientistkerala(at)gmail.com<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n3. wsdkscste(at)gmail.com<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Telephone: </b>0471- 2548208<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b> Address: </b><br>\r\nThe Head,\r\nWomen Scientists Division<br/>\r\nKerala State Council of <br/>Science, Technology and Environment<br/>\r\nSasthra Bhavan, Pattom (P.O), <br/>Thiruvananthapuram â 695 004<br/>\r\n<b>Phone:</b> 0471 2548208<br>\r\n<b>Fax: </b>0471 2540085, 2534605<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>E-mail: </b>womenscientistkerala(at)gmail.com<br>\r\n\r\n', '1. Photo of an applicant.<br>\r\n2. Proof of Date of Birth ( Those who claim age relaxation should submit proof on the reservation\r\ncategory- both documents can be merged).<br>\r\n3. Proof of Permanent Residency in Kerala.<br>\r\n4. Marklist and Certificate of PG ( documents can be merged as a single file).<br>\r\n5. Certificate of Ph.D.<br>\r\n6. Work & Research Experience certificate.<br>\r\n7. Reprints of latest Research Publications in SCI-indexed journals (Full-length paper maximum 2 nos).<br>\r\n8. Certificate on Break in Career- IN FORMAT ( applies to âBack-to-labâ applicants only).<br>\r\n9. Biodata of Applicant ( include List of publications) & Biodata of Scientist Mentor â (Each one not\r\nto exceed 2 pages).<br>\r\n10. Declaration by the Applicant â IN FORMAT.<br>\r\n11. Consent from Scientist Mentor â IN FORMAT.<br>\r\n12. Endorsement from the Head of Host Institution- I.<br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '75000', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Ph.D. in Science or Engineering.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 300000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-03-15', 'Kerala State Council for Science, Technology and Environment.', 75000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 11:21:34', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 11:15:04', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1613, 'mjQxbCGKWXgFc4GXlL', 'Scholarship', 'Visual Arts  Senior Fellowship Program ', 'https://www.nga.gov/research/casva/fellowships/visiting-senior-fellowships.html', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Center for Advanced Study in the Visual Arts announces its program for visiting senior fellowships. All of the fellowships are for full-time research, and scholars are expected to reside in Washington and participate in the activities of the Center throughout the fellowship period. Lectures, colloquia, and informal discussions complement the fellowship program. Each visiting senior fellow is provided with a study.<br><br>\r\n<li>In addition, fellows who relocate to Washington are provided with housing in apartments near the National Gallery, subject to availability. Fellows have access to the notable resources represented by the art collections, the library, and the image collections of the National Gallery of Art, as well as to the Library of Congress and other specialized research libraries and collections in the Washington area.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Up to two Leonard A. Lauder Visiting Senior Fellowships and up to five Paul Mellon and Beinecke Visiting Senior Fellowships will be awarded for the period September 1, 2023âFebruary 28, 2024. Qualified applicants are considered for all visiting senior fellowships.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Visiting senior fellowships are intended for those who have held the Ph.D. for five years or more at the time of application or who possess an equivalent record of professional accomplishment. <br>\r\n\r\n<li>Individuals currently affiliated with the National Gallery of Art are not eligible for the visiting senior fellowship program. <br>\r\n\r\n<li>Visiting senior fellowships are awarded without regard to the age or nationality of applicants. <br>\r\n<li>Applications are reviewed by an external selection committee composed of scholars in the history of art and related disciplines. Outside readers may assist in the evaluation of proposals.<br><br>\r\n<b>Stipend:</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Recipients of Leonard A. Lauder Fellowships are eligible for an augmented stipend of $12,500 for a two-month residency, which includes a supplement of $2,500 to support future research and publication expenses.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Recipients of Paul Mellon and Ailsa Mellon Bruce Fellowships will receive a basic stipend of $7,000 or $8,000, depending upon relocation requirements. In addition, fellows receive housing, as available.<br><br>\r\n<b>Applications:</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Candidates for visiting senior fellowships must submit, on or before the deadline, an online application that includes a proposal and a copy of one article or chapter of a book. Two letters of recommendation in support of the application are required.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Visiting senior fellows may receive awards in three consecutive years but thereafter must wait three years before reapplying to the Center. Individuals may not apply for other Center fellowships while an application is pending or once a fellowship has been awarded. Visiting senior fellowships may not be postponed or renewed.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li><b>Award period: </b>September 1, 2023âFebruary 28, 2024.<br>\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '$12,500\r\n', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Senior Fellowship (Above 40 years)\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-03', '2023-03-31', 'Center for Advanced Study in the Visual Arts', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 11:39:42', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-13 09:41:53', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1614, '0iMDKbRjBGlYSnir1D', 'Scholarship', 'Pratibha Kiran Scholarship', 'https://scholarshipportal.mp.nic.in/Index.aspx', '', '', '', '', '', 'MP Pratibha Kiran Scholarship has been announced by the Chief Minister of Madhya Pradesh Shivraj Singh Chouhan. This scheme has been announced for girl students. The scheme is implemented by the Department of Higher Education.<br><br>\r\n<li>There are many girl students who drop their qualification after 12th due to lack of finance. Pratibha Kiran Scholarship is for the girl students of Madhya Pradesh state. It is another initiative of the MP government to support the girl students and encourage them to pursue higher education. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant should be a native of Madhya Pradesh.<br>\r\n<li>Only girl students, who resides in an urban area are eligible for getting this scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant must have secured 60% or more marks in the 12th examination.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Girl applicants who grab the scholarship opportunity will get a scholarship amount of up to INR 5000 every year to pursue their higher education in the field of medicine, engineering, management, law, private sector, etc. <br><br>\r\n<li>Moreover, students will get an incentive of INR 500 per month for ten months and INR 750 per month for technical and medical courses.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>10th class marks sheet.<br>\r\n<li>12th class marks sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Admission certificate from College/University.<br>\r\n<li>Bank Account Passbook.<br>\r\n<li>BPL Ration card.<br>\r\n<li>Identity card.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Mobile number.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photo.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '10000', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Medical, Engineering, Law, and Management Courses \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 250000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-06-30', 'Department of Higher Education, Government of Madhya Pradesh.', 10000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-11 11:57:01', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-04-13 05:17:34', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL);
