(1630, 'SrCHX9cS3mwpGZ4vri', 'Abroad', 'University of Auckland ADB Scholarship ', 'https://brightscholarship.com/university-of-auckland-adb-scholarship-2023-24/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Asian Development Bank â Japan Scholarship Program (ADB â JSP) was established in April 1988 with financing from the Japanese government. The aim is to provide an opportunity for well-qualified citizens of ADBâs developing member countries to undertake postgraduate studies in economics, management, science and technology, and other development-related fields at participating academic institutions in the Asia-Pacific region.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Almost all academic fields and majors are available under Asian Development Scholarship at Auckland University. The scholarship will cover all the necessary expenses to Study Free in New Zealand.<br><br>\r\n<li>The University of Auckland is a public research university in Auckland, New Zealand. The University of Auckland is New Zealandâs leading university. It is the highest-ranked New Zealand university in the QS World University Rankings and Shanghai Jiao Tong Academic Ranking of World Universities, and together with the University of Otago is the only university included in the Times Higher Education top 250. Some 35 percent of the top-ranked academic researchers in New Zealand are at the University of Auckland.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Be a national of an ADB borrowing member. For a list of current developing member countries visit ADB â Japan Scholarship Programme.<br>\r\n<li>Have gained admission to an approved master at an approved academic institution.<br>\r\n<li>Have a bachelors degree or its equivalent with a superior academic record.<br>\r\n<li>Have at least two years of full-time professional work experience (acquired after a university degree) at the time of application.<br>\r\n<li>Be proficient in oral and written English communication skills to be able to pursue studies.<br>\r\n<li>Be under 35 years old at the time of application. In exceptional cases, for programmes which are appropriate for senior officials and managers, the age limit is 45 years.<br>\r\n<li>Be in good health.\r\n<li>Agree to return to your home country after completing the programme.<br><br>\r\n<b>Ineligibility Criteria:</b><br>\r\n<li>Executive Directors, Alternate Directors, management and staff of ADB, consultants, and relatives of the aforementioned.<br>\r\n<li>Staff of JSP-designated institutions canât apply to their own institution.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants living or working in a country other than his/her home country.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants who are already enrolled in graduate degree programmes or who have already completed graduate degree programmes.<br>\r\n<li>Undergraduate studies, distance learning programmes, short-term training, conferences, seminars, thesis writing, and research projects.\r\n<br>\r\n', '<li>Completed ADB-JSP Information Sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Completed ADB-JSP Application Form.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of your offer letter to the University of Auckland.<br>\r\n<li>Academic documentation â both academic transcripts and degree certificates.<br>\r\n<li>Certificate of Employment for the duration of employment issued by the company.<br>\r\n<li>Certificate of Income issued by the company.<br>\r\n<li>Certificate of Family Income issued by the company.<br>\r\n<li>Must be either your parents or spouses.<br>\r\n<li>annual/monthly income.<br>\r\n<li>Copy of your Passport.<br>\r\n<li>Valid IELTS test.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance.', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Postgraduates.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-09', '2023-07-21', 'University of Auckland', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 10:05:39', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 04:50:32', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1631, 'j8fBAW9HBuTuZR3Uke', 'Abroad', 'University of Otago Scholarships ', 'https://brightscholarship.com/university-of-otago-scholarships/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Applications are opened to apply for the University of Otago Scholarships 2023 in New Zealand. All International Students from any part of the Globe are eligible to apply for International Research Scholarships. This award is offered by University of Otago in New Zealand.  The students those who want to pursue their Masters Degree or PhD Degree from well reputed university. Fully Funded Scholarships are available for the academic session of 2022-23.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Almost all academic fields and majors are available at University of Otago to undertake a Postgraduate Research Degree programs. The university will provide all the expenses to study abroad.\r\nThe University of Otago was established in 1869 is a 2nd highest ranked research university in the Otago, New Zealand. More than 20,000 National and International Students studying in the university.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicants obtaining their first Masterâs qualification\r\nInternational students having any nationality\r\nDoing a thesis-based Masterâs.<br>\r\n<li>To apply for PhD Degree students seeking to obtain their first doctoral qualification.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Financial Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>The AUT International Scholarships 2022 in New Zealand are divided into the following categories:\r\n<b>Masters Degree:<br>\r\n<li>NZ$15,000 Stipend per Annum.<br>\r\n<li>Domestic Tuition Fees waiver (excludes student services fee and insurance).<br>\r\n<b>PhD Degree:</b><br>\r\n<li>NZ$27,000 stipend per annum.<br>\r\n<li>Domestic tuition fees waiver for 36 months (excludes student services fee and insurance).<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'NZ$27,000 \r\n', '[\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', 'null', '\"Postgraduates, Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-12-30', 'University of Otago', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 10:16:46', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 04:51:41', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1632, 'rggFLC0ukJPJeD9COW', 'Scholarship', 'ICMR Centenary Post Doctoral Fellowship', 'https://main.icmr.nic.in/content/post-doctoral-research#', '', '', '', '', '', 'ICMR, with its 27 state-of-the-art Institutes/Centers, is amongst the foremost research organizations in the field of Bio Medical Sciences. Over the years, the ICMR has helped in making a scientific milieu in India, creating and nurturing talent in many disciplines such as communicable and non communicable diseases, basic medical sciences, reproductive health including nutrition, human resource developments etc.<br><br>\r\n<li>\r\nICMR PDF Scheme is being instituted to foster high quality research opportunities to promising fresh Ph.D./ MD/MS holders in the cutting edge areas of basic science, communicable and non communicable diseases, and reproductive health including nutrition at ICMR Institutes /Centers. Special focus will be on fundamental research in areas of science and other priority areas identified by ICMR from time to time. ICMR intends to offer fifty (50) such fellowships every year for working in ICMR Institutes/Centers with state-of-art R&D facilities. These fellowships will be allocated by Director General, ICMR, depending upon the needs of the ICMR Institute/Centre.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Fresh PhDs/MD/MS within three years of completing their Ph.D./MD/MS degree (awarded) as on the last date of the application and also those who have received their provisional Ph.D./MD/MS degree can apply. Degree copy is to be submitted as on the last date of the application form.<br>\r\n<li>The Post Doctoral proposed research work should be the continuation of the Ph.D. or MD/MS research work. If not, then the application will not be considered.\r\nPDF Guide should be having the minimum designation of Scientist-C grade.<br>\r\n<li>Postgraduate medical students are also permitted to carry out ICMRâs PDF in MCI-recognized postgraduate medical colleges wherein a minimum of three batches have obtained their postgraduate degree.<br>\r\n<li>ICMR PDF is open to Indian nationals only.\r\n32 years, relaxable up to 5 years in case of SC/ST/OBC/PH and women candidates, as on the last date of application (30th June and 31st December).<br>\r\n<li><b>Note: </b>Result notification/certificate or Viva-voce/Thesis submitted notification will not be considered.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits and Rewards:</b><br>\r\n<li>ICMR PDFs will be paid a consolidated fellowship of <b>Rs. 65,000/-  per month.</b>  <br>\r\n<li>House Rent Allowance (HRA) as per Govt. of India rule, Non-Practicing allowance (NPA) as admissible, and<b> a contingency grant of Rs. 3.0 lakhs per annum.</b><br>\r\n<li>25% of the contingency grant can be used for travel including per diem expenses (only for National travel, related to ICMR-PDF proposed research work only).<br><br>\r\n<b>Other relevant information:</b><br>\r\n<li>The fellowship amount will be paid to ICMR institutes/centers every six months including a contingency grant.<br>\r\n<li>It is mandatory to submit the Plagiarism check report along with the declaration (click for the format) to be submitted to ICMR along with the PDF proposal and application.<br>\r\n<li>All other rules and regulations as applicable to ICMR JRF/Research Associate (can be seen at main.icmr.nic.in) will be applicable to PDFs.<br>\r\n<li>In all matters, the decision of ICMR Competent Authority shall be final.<br>\r\n<li>List of ICMR Institutes/Centers and their niche Areas/R&D activities are available on the ICMR website.<br> <li>For more information about the institute/centre, please visit the websites of the individual Institutes/ Centers.<br>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Application Process:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applications may be submitted in the format provided with all enclosures as listed in the detailed guideline and as per the eligibility criteria (only hard copy) w.e.f.  1st February 2023 to 28th February 2023 (by 05:30 pm). <br>\r\n<li> Applications duly filled in the prescribed format and complete in all respect. <br>\r\n<li>Application for ICMR CENTENARY âPost Doctoral Fellowship should clearly be written on top of the envelope containing the application form and  should be sent to:<br><br>\r\n  <b> Director General\r\n   Attention:</b></br>\r\n   <b>  Sh. Kishor Toppo,</b></br>\r\n  <b>   Technical Officer-C,</b></br>\r\n  <b>   Division of Human Resource</b></br> <b>  Planning and Development,</b></br>\r\n    <b> Indian Council of Medical </b></br> <b> Research Headquarters,\r\n   Ansari Nagar,</b></br>  <b> New Delhi-110029</b></br><br>\r\n<b>contact details:</b><br>\r\n<b>   Email :</b><br> \r\n1. toppok.hq@icmr.gov.in<br>\r\n2. mpdicmr@gmail.com \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Photograph on the application form.<br>\r\n<li>Affidavit if you carry different name/Surnames in your certificates.<br>\r\n<li>Attested copy of School Leaving/ High School/Secondary School Certificate (for date of birth).<br>\r\n<li>  Attested copies of Mark Sheets/Grade Cards & Degrees for B.Sc./M.Sc./M.Phil./B.E./ M.E/B.Pharm/M.Pharm./Ph.D./MBBS/MD/MS.<br>\r\n<li>  Attested copy of the Caste certificate, if applicable.<br>\r\n<li>  List of publications.<br>\r\n<li>Reprints of publications.<br>\r\n<li>One page summary of Ph.D. thesis.<br>\r\n<li> Attested copies of Letter(s) of Acceptance for paper(s) accepted for publication & pre-prints.<br>\r\n<li> Detailed research proposal.<br>\r\n<li> Testimonials from two Referees (One should be Ph.D. Guide).<br>\r\n<li>Plagiarism Check Report verified by ICMR-RIO.<br> \r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', ' 65,000/-  per month', '[\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"M.D, M.S, Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-08', '2023-02-28', 'Indian Council Of Medical Research (ICMR)', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 15:12:30', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 10:34:47', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1633, '6kTQ0xTgYjFCF9rikt', 'Scholarship', 'Lady Tata Memorial Junior Research Scholarship', 'https://ladytatatrust.tatatrusts.org/StaticPageIndia/Applications', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Lady Tata Memorial Trust was established by Sir Dorabji Tata in April 1932 in memory of his wife, Lady Meherbai, who was struck with leukaemia in 1930 at the age of 50, and succumbed to the disease a year later in Wales, when she passed away on 18th June 1931.\r\nTo encourage study and research in diseases of the blood, with special reference to leukaemias and furthering knowledge in connection with such diseases.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Applications are invited from Indian Nationals, from select Universities / Institutes / Laboratories, and strictly with first class academics (60% and above) from Class X up to date for the award of Junior Research Scholarship for the year 2023-2024 for scientific investigations having a bearing directly or indirectly on the alleviation of human suffering from disease. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Indian national candidates are only eligible for this scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>The age of the candidate as on 31st March 2023 should not exceed 27 years.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants who have passed their MBBS/ M.Sc/ M.Pharma/ M.Tech degree in the year 2021 and 2022 should only apply for the academic year 2023-24 for the JR award.<br>\r\n<li>Additionally, the candidates should have passed all the exams strictly with first-class academics (60% and above) from Class X up to date.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants with GATE/ NET qualifications may be given preference.<br><br>\r\n<b>Fee Processing:</b><br>\r\nA sum of Rs.100/- being processing fee(non-refundable) per application should be forwarded online in the given below account: <br>\r\n\r\n<li>Trust name: LADY TATA MEMORIAL TRUST <br>\r\n<li>Bank name: KOTAKÂ MAHINDRA BANK <br>\r\n<li>Branch:Â Â Â Â  FORT, MUMBAI <br>\r\n<li>Account no: 0711650105<br>\r\n<li>IFSC Code: KKBK0000957<br>\r\n\r\n<li>And the original transaction slips of the same should be scanned and submitted with the online application form. Any application received without the scanned slip, or forwarded through any other mode of payment will be rejected without further correspondence with the applicant. <br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Value of award (per month): Rs. 31000/-<br>\r\n<li>Contingency grant (per annum): Rs. 30000/-<br>\r\n<li>House Rent Allowance (HRA): As HRA, 25% of the basic value of the scholarship will be offered to scholars doing research work at Universities/ Institutes/ Laboratories in the metro cities of Mumbai, Pune, Ahmedabad, Delhi, Kolkata, Chennai, Bangalore and Hyderabad, being locations outside their place of permanent residence. <br>\r\n<li>Scholars from other small towns/ cities will receive HRA at the rate of 10% of the basic value of their scholarship.<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:</b>The online application should be submitted on<b> www.ladytatatrust.tatatrusts.org</b><br><li>\r\nThe interview call letters will be forwarded to short-listed applicants by the end of June/July 2023, personal interview will be held in mid-July/August 2023 and the names of the selected applicants, based on their performance at the interview, will be announced in   August/September 2023 and the selected scholars and their Supervisor / Research Guide will be intimated about the same immediately thereafter.  Selected scholars will be required to report to the respective Supervisor / Research Guide immediately on announcement of the award.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>\r\n\r\nFor any query:</b>\r\n<li> Contact via E-mail on: rdhanrao@tatatrusts.org\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'The following documents in scanned format should be uploaded into the application form:<br>\r\n<li>A letter from applicant mentioning that he/ she has enclosed all the important documents and that has read all the important information carefully.<br>\r\n<li>A letter jointly signed by the Registrar/ Director and the Head of the Department concerned stating that they have critically examined the details of the proposed research work, that they have approved of the general plan, that the university/ institute has adequate laboratory facilities and that they will provide these facilities to the applicant for his/ her research work. The letter should give the name and designation of the person who will act as Guide to the applicant.<br>\r\n<li>A letter from the Supervisor/ Research Guide, giving his/ her consent, to provide necessary guidance to the applicant and to supervise his / her research work.<br>\r\n<li>A joint letter from the three Members of the Doctoral Committee agreeing to assess and submit the annual research progress reports of the work done by the Scholar as sought by the Trust.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant must obtain a separate letter from the Head of the Department or the Research Guide giving comments on past research experience and on the competence of the applicant to carry out the proposed research work.<br>\r\n<li>Proof of age.<br>\r\n<li>Certificate of physical fitness.<br>\r\n<li>One-page Summary Information sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Letter from the Institute with a scan of the latest rent receipt for the HRA claim (where applicable).<br>\r\n<li>Detailed Research Project Proposal not exceeding 10 pages.<br>\r\n<li>A demand draft of Rs. 100/- as processing fee was drawn in favor of the Lady Tata Memorial Trust.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '31000', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"M.Sc, M.Pharma,  MBBS, M.Tech.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-03-15', 'Tata Trust', 31000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 16:18:10', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 11:08:23', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1634, 'RgIRaMoMXUZXROuoRP', 'Abroad', 'Einstein Forum Fellowship ', 'https://brightscholarship.com/einstein-forum-fellowship-germany-2023-24/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Call for the applications to apply for the Einstein Forum Fellowship 2023-24 in Germany. All International Students who are applying for the Einstein Fellowship 2023 must be under 35 years of age. This is a Fully Funded Fellowship in Germany by Einstein Forum for outstanding Young Thinkers. No Need of IELTS/TOEFL for this Fully Funded fellowship scholarship.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Applicants must have University Degree in Science, Natural Science & Humanities. The duration of this Scholarship in Germany is 5 to 6 Months. This is a scholarship for international students in Germany that will be given to Any Nationality who will propose a Unique Project. Einstein Fellowship Germany will cover your Accommodation cost and Stipend for 6 Months which is enough to cover your food and other Cost during Einstein Forum Scholarship and will Reimburse Travel Cost.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Candidates must be under 35 and hold a university degree in the humanities, in the social sciences, or in the natural sciences.<br>\r\n<li>At the end of the fellowship period, the fellow will be expected to present his or her project in a public lecture at the Einstein Forum and at the Daimler and Benz Foundation.<br>\r\n<li>A successful application must demonstrate the quality, originality, and feasibility of the proposed project, as well as the superior intellectual development of the applicant.<br>\r\n<li>It is not relevant whether the applicant has begun working toward, or currently holds, a Ph.D.<br>\r\n<li>The proposed project need not be entirely completed during the time of the fellowship but can be the beginning of a longer project.<br>\r\n<li>Candidate must submit all documents by email to fellowship@einsteinforum.de<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Accommodation in Einsteinâs summer house in Caputh.<br>\r\n<li>A stipend of 10,000 EURO For 5 to 6 Months.<br>\r\n<li>Travel Expenses will be reimbursement.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>A Detailed CV.<br>\r\n<li>A two-page project proposal.<br>\r\n<li>Two letters of recommendation.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '10,000 Euro\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', 'null', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates,Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-05-15', 'Einstein Forum', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 16:50:53', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-15 11:22:26', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1635, '8FewBFFlHyxliGKtl1', 'Scholarship', 'Z Zurich Foundation Scholarship', 'https://www.oneyoungworld.com/scholarships/z-zurich-foundation/2023', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_EUB0kymZG4', 'The Z Zurich Foundation empowers vulnerable people to better protect themselves from risk, and to adapt and thrive in a rapidly changing world. We aspire for a more equal world where everyone has independence, choice and power over their own futures.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Improving mental wellbeing, and enabling social equity are two central pillars of the Z Zurich Foundation, and these arenât causes we picked at random. We believe that the key to creating a better future is connection â fostering relationships between those in the know and those most in need and tackling societyâs challenges from the ground up. This is why we are committed to supporting impactful leaders to participate in the annual One Young World Summit, the worldâs most international community of young leaders.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Z Zurich Foundation Scholarship 2023 will allow 16 young leaders working on prevention-focused mental well-being projects, or projects enabling social equity through education, employability or entrepreneurship solutions, to participate in the One Young World Summit 2023 which takes place in Belfast, United Kingdom from 2 â 5 October.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>If you are a young leader working to champion mental well-being or create a more equal society, this scholarship could be for you. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n <li>Aged 18 to 30 at the time of the One Young World Summit 2023.<br>\r\n \r\n <li>Passion for local and global issues.<br>\r\n \r\n <li>Demonstrated commitment to creating positive change.<br>\r\n \r\n <li> Willingness to engage and collaborate with fellow scholarship recipients and employees of Zurich who are also attending the Summit.<br>\r\n \r\n <li> Demonstrated impact in a field aligned with the work of the Z Zurich Foundation namely:<br>\r\n \r\n <li>Improving Mental Wellbeing<br>\r\n \r\n <li>Enabling Social Equity<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\nAccess to the One Young World Summit 2023 in Belfast.<br>\r\n <li> Access to additional scholarship programming organized by Z Zurich Foundation. This programming is likely to include pre and post-One Young World Summit including calls and meetings with the wider Zurich Insurance Group delegation, as well as the chance to pitch for funding that can help increase your impact.<br>\r\n <li> Hotel accommodation in Belfast between 1 and 6 (inclusive) October.<br>\r\n <li> Return air travel.<br>\r\n <li>Catering which includes breakfast, lunch, and dinner.<br>\r\n <li>Ground transportation between Summit venues in Belfast.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-03-13', 'Z Zurich Foundation', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-16 14:16:54', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-09 03:37:18', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1636, '50gZZozOwN3RcUUlOs', 'Abroad', 'British Council Scholarships For Women', 'https://www.britishcouncil.org/study-work-abroad/in-uk/scholarship-women-stem', '', '', '', '', '', 'Are you a woman with a degree or PhD in a STEM subject and passionate about your study? You could receive a scholarship to study a masterâs degree, or an early academic fellowship, in a science, technology, engineering or mathematics programme at a leading UK university.Now in its third year, the British Council Women in STEM Scholarships programme is working in partnership with 19 UK universities with the aim of benefiting women from the Americas, South Asia, East Asia, Western Balkans, Central Asia, Brazil, Egypt, Mexico, and Turkey.<br><br>\r\n<li>We are looking for women with a background in STEM, who can demonstrate their need for financial support and who wish to inspire future generations of women to pursue careers in STEM.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Why a scholarship programme?</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li>This scholarship programme aims to increase opportunities in STEM for girls and women, and according to data from the UN Scientific Education and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), in 2019 fewer than 30 percent of researchers worldwide are women and only 30 percent of female students select STEM-related fields in higher education, but this number has slowly been gaining momentum with it currently siting at 35% (Anon, 2022).<br>\r\n \r\n<li>A subject breakdown between 2017-18 showed that females studying STEM subjects was particularly low. Computer Sciences, Engineering & Technology, with 19% opposed to 81% with males. Physical sciences and mathematics and statistics are stronger at 39% and 37% respectively (with their counterparts at 61 and 63% respectively).<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\nApplicants can apply from the following countries:\r\n <br>\r\n1. For both Masterâs Scholarships and Early Academic Fellowships: India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Nepal or Sri Lanka, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.<br><br>\r\n \r\n2. For Masters Scholarships only: Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kazakhstan, Kosovo, North Macedonia, Montenegro, Serbia or Uzbekistan, Turkey, Argentina, Brazil, Colombia, Cuba, Jamaica, Mexico, Peru or Venezuela, Egypt.<br><br>\r\n \r\n \r\n3. We are looking for women who:<br>\r\n Can take up a course of study in the UK for the academic year from September/October 2023 â 2024.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Can demonstrate a need for financial support.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Have an undergraduate degree that will enable them to gain access onto one of the pre-selected postgraduate courses at a UK university (for Masters level) or completed all components of PhD in the last three years (for Early Academic Fellowships).<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Can attain the level of English required for postgraduate study/research at a UK university.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Are active in the field with work experience or a proven interest in their subject area.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Are passionate about their course of study and are willing to engage as committed British Council scholarship alumni.<br><br>\r\n4.Full eligibility criteria are available below in the documents section â please note that the eligibility for a Masterâs Scholarship and Early Academic Fellowships are different.<br><br>\r\n \r\n5.If you have questions about the scholarships, please contact the British Council by emailing UK.Scholarships(at)<b>britishcouncil.org.</b><br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Acdemic prestige - the UKâs universities are amongst the worldâs leaders in STEM subjects.<br>\r\n<li>Economic support will include tuition fees, stipend, travel costs, visa and health coverage fees\r\nSpecial support for mothers.<br>\r\n<li>English language support (IELTS).<br> \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Â£30,502 per annum\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', 'null', '\"Undergraduate, Postgraduate,\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-04', '2023-03-31', 'British Council ', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-16 14:49:23', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-16 09:25:23', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1637, '5WJiA9bmvbDPiaOUQL', 'Abroad', 'Gyandhan Scholarship', 'https://www.gyandhan.com/gd-scholarship', '', '', '', '', '', 'Gyandhan Scholarship is an opportunity for students who wish to pursue their post-graduation degree from outside India. Under this scheme, students will get one-time monetary benefits. It is an initiative of the Gyandhan for Indian students who desire to pursue a Masterâs degree in the US, Canada, UK, Australia, Ireland, New Zealand & Germany. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>This scholarship is awarded to a single student. The amount of scholarship will be given to the student in his/her bank account at the beginning of the academic session. Selection of the students for the scholarship award will be made on a merit basis. The objective is to financially help students who desire to pursue higher education from abroad. Gyandhan is supporting students since 2003. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Appellants who desire to pursue a postgraduate course in the US, Canada, UK, Australia, Ireland, New Zealand & Germany. <br>\r\n<li>Appellants should be an Indian citizen.<br>\r\n<li>Appellant must hold a Graduation Degree from an Indian institute.<br>\r\n<li>Appellants who are planning to take an education loan can submit the application via one of the partner lenders of Gyandhan.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li> Gyandhan Scholarship is for Indian students who are going to pursue masterâs degree programmes from abroad.<br>\r\n<li> Under this scholarship scheme, the scholar will get INR 100000. The scholarship amount will be given to 1 scholar only. <br>\r\n<li>The amount will be given to the students one time at the beginning of the academic year<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Offer letter from the university.<br>\r\n<li>Proof of GRE/GMAT Score.<br>\r\n<li>Proof of TOEFL/ IELTS Score.<br>\r\n<li>Latest Resume.<br>\r\n<li>Statement of Purpose in 1500 words.<br>\r\n<li>Letter of recommendation (optional).<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'INR 100000.\r\n', '[\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-03-30', 'Gyandhan corporate', 100000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-16 15:01:16', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-16 09:36:48', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1638, 'xClyccyHHN2v6flSRp', 'Competitions and Awards', 'International Childrens Painting Competition', 'https://www.keralatourism.org/contest/icpc/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Kerala Tourism is excited to introduce the third edition of the International Childrenâs Online Painting Competition. The first two seasons were a roaring success with kids from across the globe sending in their creations.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>The third season promises to be more exciting and entertaining. The theme of the competition is âKerala Village Lifeâ and any child from any part of the world between the ages of 4 and 16 years can submit their entries online. Lucky winners will get a sponsored five-night family trip to visit major tourist destinations in Kerala.<br><br>\r\n<li>After two seasons of fun and excitement, the International Childrenâs Online Painting Competition is back with more prizes and challenges. The first two seasons were a roaring success with kids from across the globe sending in their creations. The third season promises to be more exciting and entertaining. The theme of season 3 is âKerala Village Lifeâ and we have put up photos and videos in the website for reference.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Any child from any part of the world between the ages of 4 and 16 years can submit their entries online. Parents or guardians can register on behalf of their wards and each participant can submit a maximum of five entries. Lucky winners and promoters will get a sponsored five-day family trip to visit major tourist destinations in Kerala. Not just that, attractive gifts are in store for best entries from all categories. Register now and get a chance to visit top destinations of Godâs Own Country!<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Lucky winners will get sponsored five-night family trips to visit major tourist destinations in Kerala.<br>\r\n<li> Lucky winners and promoters will get sponsored five-day family trips to visit major tourist destinations in Kerala.<br>\r\n<li