(1639, 'D3GsJz87jzCK4PWI35', 'Competitions and Awards', '7th International Poster Contest', 'http://www.typography-museum.gr/7th-poster-contest-2022/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pvLW9s-2Cgk', 'The museum of Typography by Giannis and elwni Garedaki announces the 7th international poster contents, titled planet Earth at the ecological crossroad. At the peak of the climate crisis, the message of environmental awareness is required to reach as many as possible. The poster as âmessengerâ plays its own part in this global effort to save the planet.<br><br>\r\n<li>The poster should be accompanied by a short explanatory text explaining its content and purpose. The invitation mainly concerns professionals and students of graphic and visual arts. The 30 posters selected by the jury (the members of which will be announced soon) will receive honorary distinctions and the first three will receive significant cash prizes.<br><br>\r\n<li>These posters will be presented in an exhibition that will be hosted in the amphitheater of the Museum of Typography for a year, until the next competition.The awarding of prizes and distinctions will take place on Saturday, 13 May 2023, in the amphitheater of the Museum of Typography, at the Park of Small Industries of Chania, Souda, Crete.<br><br>\r\n<li> The poster accompanying the announcement of the contest is Ksenia Auburnâs participation in the 6th Poster Contest by the Museum of Typography.The contest will take place from Monday, 7 November 2022 until Friday, 10 March 2023. Each participant can submit only one poster. The poster must be sent by e-mail.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Note:</b> Those interested should send their work from Monday 7 November 2022 to Friday 10 March 2023 to the email: typography.poster@gmail.com.<br><br>\r\n<b>Prizes.</b><br>\r\n<li>  1st prize: â¬ 2,000<br>\r\n<li> 2nd prize: â¬ 1,500<br>\r\n<li>  3rd prize: â¬ 1,000<br>\r\n<br> \r\n\r\n<b>Terms of participation:</b><br>\r\n<li> The poster should be accompanied by the entry form and a short description of the project (up to 100 words).<br>  \r\n<li>The dimensions should be 50 Ã 70 cm PDF, CMYK, the image at 200 ppi and should not exceed 25 MB. <br> \r\n<li>Otherwise the files should be sent by transfer. It is necessary to attach a poster file in jpg format in low resolution up to 1 MB, for web use.<br> \r\n<li>Each participant can submit only one, original project, which has not participated in another competition. The employees of âHaniotika Neaâ SA and the âMuseum of Typography by Giannis & Eleni Garedakiâ are excluded from the competition.<br>  \r\n<li>The poster must bear the museum logo, either in greek or english. You can find the logo at www.typography-museum.gr/logos.pdf<br>\r\n<li>The results of the competition will be announced at the award ceremony that will be hosted in the amphitheater of the âMuseum of Typographyâ. <br>\r\n<li>After the ceremony, the results will be announced in the newspaper âHaniotika Neaâ, at www.haniotika-nea.gr, on the site of the âMuseum of Typographyâ www.typography-museum.gr and on the official page of the âMuseum of Typographyâ on Facebook www. facebook.com/MouseioTypographias<br>  \r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'â¬ 2,000\r\n', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-03', '2023-03-10', 'Museum of Typography', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-16 15:19:17', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-07 03:38:21', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1640, '1e81fbj69PVgEVPLIe', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Jacksonâs Painting Prize', 'https://jacksonsart.awardsplatform.com/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Jacksonâs Painting Prize started in 2016 to spotlight amateur and emerging artists, and has steadily grown in size and reputation to where it is today.Jacksonâs Painting Prize is open to artists from around the world. \r\nAny artist of any age can enter the competition, no matter their previous experience or artistic education.The competition is organized annually by the Jackson\'s Art Supplies located in London.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Eligibility:\r\n\r\n<li>Artists may submit 2-dimensional fine art works in any painting or drawing media.<br>\r\n<li>There are no theme restrictions.You can submit up to a total of 5 artworks<br>\r\n<li>Open to artists worldwide.<br>\r\n<li> Material Awards (Oil, Acrylic, Watercolour, Dry Materials): Â£500 Jackson\'s Art Materials each\r\n<li> Subject Category Awards (Portrait/Figure, Land/city/seascape, Non-representational, Animal, Still Life, Botanical, Scenes of Everyday Life, Mindâs Eye): Â£500 Jackson\'s Art Materials each.<br>\r\n<li>Entry fee: Â£6 per artwork.<br>\r\n<b>Guidelines:</b><br>\r\nComplete the entry form by filling the details:\r\n<li>A category: This year, we have Subject Category Awards and our new Material Awards. Please select the relevant Material Category (e.g. Oil), and Subject Category (e.g. Portrait/Figure). All entries will automatically be put forward for the general prizes (Overall Winner, Peopleâs Choice). Specific categories (e.g Amateur, Student) must be manually selected to enter if applicable to you.<br>\r\n<li>Title of the artwork.<br>\r\n<li>An image of your artwork. (max 3MB â jpg, jpeg, tif, png). More details on images below.<br>\r\n<li>Medium/s used to make the artwork.<br>\r\n<li>Dimensions of the artwork.<br>\r\n<li>Year artwork was made.<br>\r\n<li>Artist Statement (max 200 words) and Artist Biography (max 180 words). <br>\r\n<li>The ma