(1641, 'ZZY2acrUxz3ixWOAHv', 'Competitions and Awards', 'International Essay Contest', 'https://www.goipeace.or.jp/en/work/essay-contest/', '', '', '', '', '', 'his annual essay contest for young people is organized by the Goi Peace Foundation based in Japan.This year\'s theme is âYouth Creating a Peaceful Futureâ.\r\nâ What does a peaceful world look like to you? How can young people work together, using creative ideas and approaches to realize a peaceful future? Please share your specific ideas.<br><br>\r\n<li>This annual essay contest is organized in an effort to harness the energy, creativity and initiative of the world\'s youth in promoting a culture of peace and sustainable development. It also aims to inspire society to learn from the young minds and to think about how each of us can make a difference in the world.<br><br>\r\n<b>Guidelines:</b><br>\r\n<li>Essays must be 700 words or less in English or French, or 1600 characters or less in Japanese.<br>\r\n<li>Essays must be original and unpublished. Only one entry per person is accepted.<br>\r\n<li>Entries must be submitted online.<br>\r\n<li>The competition is free to enter.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\nThe competition is open to anyone up to 25 years old.\r\nThere are two age categories: <br>\r\n<li>Children (up to 14 years old).<br>\r\n<li>Youth (15-25 years old).<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Prizes</b>\r\nThe following awards will be given in the Childrenâs category and Youth category:<br>\r\n<li> 1st prize (1 winner): certificate and prize of 100,000 Yen and gift.<br>\r\n<li> 2nd prize (3 winners): certificate and prize of 50,000 Yen and gift.<br>\r\n<li> 3rd prize (5 winners): certificate and gift.<br>\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '100,000 Yen\r\n', '[\"All\"]', 'null', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\