(1656, 'Dh6RAJ9WUKyDSvRo3x', 'Abroad', 'Republic of Slovenia Bilateral Scholarship', ' https://proposal.sakshat.ac.in/scholarship', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Embassy of the Republic of Slovenia in New Delhi is announcing scholarships for the academic year 2023/2024. The scholarships scheme is for University/College students or graduates and Ph.D. applicants who wish to accomplish a part of their study at one of the Slovenian Higher Education Institutions.,br><br>\r\n<b>Details of scholarship are as under:</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> For India, a total of 24 scholarship months is available.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> The scheme is designed for University/College students or graduates and Ph.D. applicants who wish to accomplish part of their study at one of the Slovenian Higher Education Institutions.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> The scholarship duration ranges from 3 months upwards to 10 months.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>The scholarship cannot be awarded for a complete course of study leading to a degree.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Tuition fee is not covered under this scholarship.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Majority of selected awardees are admitted for a short time study stay or research visits by doctoral students/candidates (i.e. they either attend non-degree courses of their choice, or pursue an independent research activity at the host institution).<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Applicants must contact a Slovenian Institution of their choice directly and request a letter of acceptance from the relevant department.<br>\r\n\r\n \r\n<li>Age limit for applicants of study stays is 26 years (the applicant may not complete 26 years of age before the end of the scholarship period) and 30 years for research visit.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Applicants for study stays should be proficient in the Slovene language, unless the working language is agreed upon with the mentor/supervisor.<br><br>\r\n \r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n \r\n1. 360 Euros per month.<br>\r\n2. Free accommodation in the facilities of the Student centre of the Slovenian University.<br>\r\n3. Subsidised meals: 2.82 Euros per working day.<br>\r\n4.Basic medical insurance for non-EU applicants.<br><br>\r\n<b>Nomination criteris:</b><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Applicants who can provide proof of receiving Letter of acceptance from a Slovenian Institute of Higher Education shall be considered for nomination.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Among the candidates satisfying criteria A above, points based on the following parameters will be awarded to each candidate, which will be used for further short listing for nomination from India.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Points based on the following parameters will be awarded to candidates, which will be used for further shortlisting for nomination from India:\r\n <br><br>\r\ni. Candidates who demonstration a real capacity to make a difference to home country:<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Will return to India on completion of course and work in India for at least 2 years: 4 points.<br>\r\n<li>Undecided/no: 0 points.<br><br>\r\n \r\nii. Candidate is from a disadvantaged background or to promote diversity:<br>\r\n \r\n <li>ST/ SC/ NC-OBC/ PwD/ EWS: 4 points.<br>\r\n<li>Female/ Transgender: 2 points.<br>\r\n <li>Others: 0 points.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>EWS: Annual family income Rs. 4.5 Lakh or below, which is same as the income criteria for the PM â USP Central Sector Scholarship Scheme for College and University Students.<br><br>\r\n \r\n(iii) Academic merit:<br>\r\n \r\n<li> QS Ranking 10 on below: 4 points.<br>\r\n<li> QS Ranking 10-20: 2 points.<br>\r\n<li>QS Ranking 20-50: 1 point.<br>\r\n<li> QS Ranking above 50: 0 points.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Note: </b>overall ranking/ subject ranking as per latest ranking year will be considered.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li>Cumulative points total calculated based on above parameters would be used to decide nominations. In case of points tie between 2 candidates, it is proposed that the candidate who scores higher on parameter (ii) be nominated. If there is still a tie, then that student would be nominated who has scored higher marks in last qualifying examination.\r\n <br><br>\r\n<li>Students must apply online on SAKSHAT Portal (https://proposal.sakshat.ac.in/scholarship). Applications can be submitted from 17 February 2023 to 08 March 2023 (16:00 Hrs). Along with applying online, dossier must also be sent addressed to <br>\r\n<b>The Undersecretary (Scholarships), <br/>Ministry of Education, West Block -1, <br/>Wing â 6, 2nd Floor, R.K. Puram, <br/>New Delhi â 110066. Dossier</b> <br/><br>\r\n\r\n \r\n<b>Queries may be addressed to:</b><br>\r\n<li>E-mail: s3.edu@nic.in<br>\r\n<Li>phone : 011 â 26172492. <br>\r\n \r\n', '<li>Applicants must submit a dossier to the national nominating agency which shall include 2 copies, the following documents:<br>\r\n\r\n1. Letter of acceptance from a Slovenian Institute of Higher Education<br>\r\n2. Photocopy of ID card or passport (page with photograph).<br>\r\n3. One letter of recommendation for study stays and two letters of<br> recommendation for research stay from the applicantâs home institution in India.<br>\r\n4.  Photocopy of diploma and/or certified transcript(s) of records.<br><br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '360 Euros/ month\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates, Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 450000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-17', '2023-03-08', 'Embassy of the Republic of Slovenia', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-22 12:28:54', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-22 07:19:38', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1657, 'J2PHeSmayRGs9D7stD', 'Abroad', 'Women In STEM scholarship', 'https://www.britishcouncil.org/study-work-abroad/in-uk/scholarship-women-stem', '', '', '', '', '', 'Are you a woman with a degree or PhD in a STEM subject and passionate about your study? You could receive a scholarship to study a masterâs degree, or an early academic fellowship, in a science, technology, engineering or mathematics programme at a leading UK university.\r\nNow in its third year, the British Council Women in STEM Scholarships programme is working in partnership with 19 UK universities with the aim of benefiting women from the Americas, South Asia, East Asia, Western Balkans, Central Asia, Brazil, Egypt, Mexico, and Turkey.\r\n \r\nWe are looking for women with a background in STEM, who can demonstrate their need for financial support and who wish to inspire future generations of women to pursue careers in STEM.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Why a scholarship programme?\r\n \r\n</b><br>\r\nThis scholarship programme aims to increase opportunities in STEM for girls and women, and according to data from the UN Scientific Education and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), in 2019 fewer than 30 percent of researchers worldwide are women and only 30 percent of female students select STEM-related fields in higher education, but this number has slowly been gaining momentum with it currently siting at 35% (Anon, 2022).\r\n \r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>A subject breakdown between 2017-18 showed that females studying STEM subjects was particularly low. Computer Sciences, Engineering & Technology, with 19% opposed to 81% with males. Physical sciences and mathematics and statistics are stronger at 39% and 37% respectively (with their counterparts at 61 and 63% respectively).\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:\r\n</b><br>\r\n1.Applicants can apply from the following countries:<br>\r\n \r\n<li>For both Masterâs Scholarships and Early Academic Fellowships : India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Nepal or Sri Lanka, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li> For Masters Scholarships only : Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kazakhstan, Kosovo, North Macedonia, Montenegro, Serbia or Uzbekistan, Turkey , Argentina, Brazil, Colombia, Cuba, Jamaica, Mexico, Peru or Venezuela , Egypt.<br><br>\r\n \r\n2. We are looking for women who:<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Can take up a course of study in the UK for the academic year from September/October 2023 â 2024.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Can demonstrate a need for financial support.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Have an undergraduate degree that will enable them to gain access onto one of the pre-selected postgraduate courses at a UK university (for Masters level) or completed all components of PhD in the last three years (for Early Academic Fellowships).<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Can attain the level of English required for postgraduate study/research at a UK university.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Are active in the field with work experience or a proven interest in their subject area.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Are passionate about their course of study and are willing to engage as committed British Council scholarship alumni.<br><br>\r\n<b> Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Academic prestige - the UKâs universities are amongst the worldâs leaders in STEM subjects.<br>\r\n<li>Economic support will include tuition fees, stipend, travel costs, visa and health coverage fees.<br>\r\n<li>Special support for mothers.<br>\r\n<li>English language support (IELTS) \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>For queries: </b>UK.Scholarships@britishcouncil.org.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-