(1658, 'bboGUjqhKNzQ0U7zGu', '', 'Women In STEM scholarship', 'https://www.britishcouncil.org/study-work-abroad/in-uk/scholarship-women-stem', '', '', '', '', '', 'Are you a woman with a degree or PhD in a STEM subject and passionate about your study? You could receive a scholarship to study a masterâs degree, or an early academic fellowship, in a science, technology, engineering or mathematics programme at a leading UK university.\r\nNow in its third year, the British Council Women in STEM Scholarships programme is working in partnership with 19 UK universities with the aim of benefiting women from the Americas, South Asia, East Asia, Western Balkans, Central Asia, Brazil, Egypt, Mexico, and Turkey.\r\n \r\nWe are looking for women with a background in STEM, who can demonstrate their need for financial support and who wish to inspire future generations of women to pursue careers in STEM.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Why a scholarship programme?\r\n \r\n</b><br>\r\nThis scholarship programme aims to increase opportunities in STEM for girls and women, and according to data from the UN Scientific Education and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), in 2019 fewer than 30 percent of researchers worldwide are women and only 30 percent of female students select STEM-related fields in higher education, but this number has slowly been gaining momentum with it currently siting at 35% (Anon, 2022).\r\n \r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>A subject breakdown between 2017-18 showed that females studying STEM subjects was particularly low. Computer Sciences, Engineering & Technology, with 19% opposed to 81% with males. Physical sciences and mathematics and statistics are stronger at 39% and 37% respectively (with their counterparts at 61 and 63% respectively).\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:\r\n</b><br>\r\n1.Applicants can apply from the following countries:<br>\r\n \r\n<li>For both Masterâs Scholarships and Early Academic Fellowships : India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Nepal or Sri Lanka, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.<br><br>\r\n \r\n<li> For Masters Scholarships only : Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kazakhstan, Kosovo, North Macedonia, Montenegro, Serbia or Uzbekistan, Turkey , Argentina, Brazil, Colombia, Cuba, Jamaica, Mexico, Peru or Venezuela , Egypt.<br><br>\r\n \r\n2. We are looking for women who:<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Can take up a course of study in the UK for the academic year from September/October 2023 â 2024.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Can demonstrate a need for financial support.<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Have an undergraduate degree that will enable them to gain access onto one of the pre-selected postgraduate courses at a UK university (for Masters level) or completed all components of PhD in the last three years (for Early Academic Fellowships).<br>\r\n \r\n<li> Can attain the level of English required for postgraduate study/research at a UK university.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Are active in the field with work experience or a proven interest in their subject area.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Are passionate about their course of study and are willing to engage as committed British Council scholarship alumni.<br><br>\r\n<b> Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Academic prestige - the UKâs universities are amongst the worldâs leaders in STEM subjects.<br>\r\n<li>Economic support will include tuition fees, stipend, travel costs, visa and health coverage fees.<br>\r\n<li>Special support for mothers.<br>\r\n<li>English language support (IELTS) \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>For queries: </b>UK.Scholarships@britishcouncil.org.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', NULL, '\"Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-15', '2023-03-31', ' British Council Women in STEM Scholarships programme', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-22 13:11:18', 1, NULL, '2023-02-22 07:41:18', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1659, 'fHKnO3lEMysjZa5bxg', 'Scholarship', 'AAI Sports Scholarship', 'https://www.aai.aero/en/important-links/aai-sports-control-board', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a3QC0_35U4I', 'AAI Sports Scholarship Scheme is an initiative by the Sports Control Board, Airports Authority of India for the young and meritorious students above the age of 14 years. Everyone knows that sports play an important role in our society, it helps to control diabetes, manage weight, enhance blood circulation, and manage levels of stress. Through sports, there is a good balance of physical and mental growth, which helps tone muscles and makes bones strong. Sports in school help prepare students to face the challenges of life. They enhance the physical and mental abilities of students and help them achieve the goals of their life.<br><br>\r\n<li>The objective of this scheme is to award Airports Authority of India (AAI) Sports Scholarships to promising young players with a view to enhancing sporting standards in AAI as also encouraging young talent.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Players who have represented Sub-junior/Juniour/ Senior National championships, All  India  Inter university tournaments, national school games in 2021-2022 and onwards. However the selection will be of highest achievers. <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<li>The Scholarship will be available to the sports persons between the age group of 14 to 24 as on 31.03.2023.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n<li>The number of scholarships will not exceed 42 for open category and 08 for Wards of employees of Airports Authority of India for the year 2023-24.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship will be given for a period of one year<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions:</b><br>\r\n<li>The students have to submit the no-obligation form with the application form duly signed by the parents.<br>\r\n<li>The quota of Ward under the Sports Scholarship Scheme is 20.<br>\r\n<li>The AAI Sports Scholarship Scheme for the ward is available to a sportsperson a maximum of five times only.<br>\r\n<li>The sports persons under the ward category may apply for a Scholarship Scheme from outside quota, after availing the benefit of five times under the ward category.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:</b>\r\n \r\n<li>The amount of scholarships to be granted to the awardees will be as under: â<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Age Group â Amount of Scholarship per month.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Over 14 years and under 18 years = Rs. 12,000/- per month.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>Over 18 years = Rs. 16,000/-per month<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Selection process</b><br>\r\n \r\n \r\n<li>All applications received within the stipulated time shall be considered by a committee duly constituted by the President, Airports Authority of India Sports Control Board. Cases of talented sports persons who are not students may also be taken into consideration.<br>\r\n<li>For award of scholarships subject to their meeting all requirements and verification/certification by the Secretary of the concerned State Federation/National Federation. Cases of special merit not covered under the above conditions may be considered with the approval of Chairman, AAI.<br>\r\n\r\n<li>For more  information visit Official Website : <b>https://www.aai.aero/en </b><br><br>\r\n<b>Application:</b><br>\r\n \r\n \r\n<li>The duly completed & signed application should be sent in prescribed format along with requisite enclosures in an envelope (13.5 x 9.5 inches) which should be super scribed in bold letter with âAAI SPORTS SCHOLARSHIP SCHEME 2023-24â on the top left corner of outer envelope to the under mentioned address so as to reach latest by 15th March 2023 : â<br><br>\r\n \r\n<b>Shri G.L. Verma,<br/>\r\nJt. General Manager (HR) & Secretary,<br/>\r\nAAI Sports Control Board Rajiv Gandhi Bhawan,<br/>\r\nA wing, Room No. C-208,<br/>\r\nAirports Authority of India,<br/>\r\nSafdarjung Airport, New Delhi-110003</b><br/>\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Rs. 16,000/-per month', '[\"Secondary\",\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Class 7 to Class 12, Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-15', '2023-03-15', 'Airports Authority of India', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-22 16:23:12', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-09 03:42:30', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1660, 'MALNMhfGX2mkz4MFXP', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Suggest Tagline for promoting startups and entrepreneurship', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/suggest-tagline-promoting-startups-and-entrepreneurship-newer-or-emerging-cities/', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uY5ytKAQC2E', 'The ongoing technological revolution is propelling Indiaâs economic growth and is allowing for global socioeconomic transformation. At the micro level, it has reached Tier 2/3 cities in India, and the population of lower-tier cities is becoming affluent and eager to spend. Indiaâs development has undoubtedly extended beyond the metropolises, owing to government policies, improved infrastructure, improved digital connectivity, shifting consumer attitudes, consumption growth, and increased technology adoption. Technology-driven solutions to local problems at scale, such as healthcare, education, agriculture, finance, sustainability, and so on, are critical for equitable growth. The tech revolution is driven by local talent, indigenous innovations, and aspirational youth in Tier 2 and 3 cities, developing the next generation of innovators and entrepreneurs.<br><br> \r\n<li>To galvanize the start-up community and attract attention, the government has launched a series of initiatives to enable conducive infrastructure, support ecosystems, and increase funding availability. On the 76th anniversary of Indiaâs independence, Honâble Prime Minister Sh. Narendra Modi stated from Red Fort, âToday we are witnessing the structure of Digital India. Weâre looking into new businesses. Who are these individuals? This pool of talent resides in Tier 2 and Tier 3 cities and villages and comes from low-income families. These are our youngsters coming before the world today with discoveriesâ.<br><br>\r\n<li>In this regard, STPI has planned to undertake a new initiative to promote start-ups and entrepreneurship in newer/emerging cities (Tier-II and Tier-III cities) and motivate the youth towards innovation & entrepreneurship in emerging tech/deep tech sector for a vibrant start-up ecosystem in Tier II/III cities. Under this new initiative, STPI plans to do the following in Tier II/III cities across various states:<br>\r\n1. Conduct various workshops and seminars involving leading IT/Tech companies, their CXOs and other industry leaders.<br>\r\n2. Conduct hackathons/challenges involving regional academic institutes.<br>\r\n3. Organize Bootcamps, Mock Pitch sessions, Demo Days, and VC connect events to enable start-ups to raise funds.<br><br>\r\n<li>STPI is looking forward to Tagline/Slogan for this initiative and hence conducting the Tagline/Slogan suggestion competition at MyGov.in platform. Participants need to provide a Tagline/Slogan of maximum 15 words for inspiring youths to be part of vibrant startup ecosystem in emerging technology in Tier II/III cities. The Tagline/Slogan should motivate the entrepreneur and startups to join this Techade by creating innovative and futuristic products/solutions for both local needs and international markets.<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:\r\n </b><br>\r\na) Cash Prize for the winner: Rs. 40,000/-<br>\r\nb) Cash Prize for runner up: Rs. 20,000/-<br>\r\nc) Cash Prize for second runner up: Rs. 10,000/-<br>\r\nd) Cash Prize of Rs 2,000/ â each to additional 5 best entries as consolation: Rs. 10,000/-\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Evaluation parameters:</b><br>\r\n \r\n Here applications will be selected on the basis following criteria:<br>\r\ni. Alignment to Name and overall theme.<br>\r\nii. Creativity.<br>\r\niii. Originality.<br>\r\niv. Simplicity.<br>\r\nv. Inspirational element<br>\r\nvi. Jury will rate the entries and total of 8 winners as listed above shall be awarded.<br>\r\nvii In case of more than the required winners in any category, further selection shall be done with the help of Draw.<br>\r\nviiiAll participants shall be given a digital âCertificate of Participationâ by STPI.<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '40000', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-18', '2023-04-20', 'Government of India', 40000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-22 17:10:03', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-02 12:36:57', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1661, 'WCUkXvxjjARN9YzxBr', 'Scholarship', 'Raman Kant Munjal Scholarship', 'https://forms.zohopublic.in/idreamcareer4/form/RamanKantMunjalScholarship/formperma/kA4ix4h-k4egSX0UzSURvnPorwXyXye1KEopkDyPnVI', '', '', '', '', '', 'There is a good chance for a scholarship for the students who have passed Class 12. RKM Raman Kant Munjal Foundation in association with Hero Fincorp Group. has invited applications for the RKM 2023 from students who have passed the 12th standard. This scholarship is given to talented students for their financial support in higher and vocational education. The selected students can get monetary funds for a period of 3 years. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant should have passed 12th and not exceed 19 years of age on 31 May 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Applicantâs Family income should be less than Rs 4 lakh per annum.<br>\r\n<li>The applicant must have secured at least 80 percent number in the 10th and 12th classes.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li> The selected scholars will get Rs Fifty thousand (50,000) to Rs Five lakh (5,00,000/-)  every year.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship will be available for 3 years.<br><br>\r\n<b>Selection process:</b><br>\r\nApplicants will be selected on the basis of:<br>\r\n<li>Filling the correct application form.<br>\r\n<li>Career assessment test.<br>\r\n<li>Filling essay form defining your needs.<br>\r\n<li>Full document list.<br>\r\n<li>Final interview round (telephonic or interview).<br><br>\r\n<b>Important dates:</b><br>\r\n<li>Starting date for application-January 20, 2023.<br>\r\n<li>Last date of application--June 15, 2023.<br>\r\n<li>The final list of selected students-31 July 2023.</br></br>\r\n\r\nFor more information</br>\r\n<b><a href=\"https://rkmfoundation.org/scholarships/\" target=\"_blank\">https://rkmfoundation.org/scholarships/</a> </b>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Class 12 mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar Card.<br>\r\n<li> PAN Card or Aadhaar Card.<br>\r\n<li>College acceptance letter or bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Receipt of college fees.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Father and mother bank statements.<br>\r\n<li>Affidavit.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '50000\r\n', '[\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"12th passed willingly to join  B. Com, BBA, BBM, BFIA, BBE, BMS, BA Economics\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 400000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-01-20', '2023-04-23', 'Raman Kant Munjal Foundation', 50000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-23 12:35:45', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-04-10 05:53:33', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1662, 'yzVAGSGYKKiZ92sTmo', 'Scholarship', 'Telangana Post Matric scholarship', 'https://telanganaepass.cgg.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Telangana government provides many opportunities for people of different castes and categories so that they can continue their education in prestigious universities available in India and get a chance to kick start their career if they have educational qualifications.  If you are a permanent resident of Telangana and you want to have perfect opportunities so that you can continue your education.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li> Even when you have completed your class 12th examination then you can apply for the numerous Telangana Post Matric Scholarship available at the official website of the Telangana e pass portal. The applicants will be provided with the benefit of the scholarship according to the category that they belong to but they must have the particular certificate of the category that they belong to in order to get the benefit related to the post-matric scholarships presented by the Telangana government. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The candidate must be a citizen of Telangana.<br>\r\n<li>The income of the family must not be more than Rs. 2 Lakh per annum combined from all the sources of earning.<br>\r\n<li>The candidate must have been admitted into a recognized institution for a Post Matriculation level educational course.<br>\r\n<li>For the intermediate level of study the age of the candidate must not be more than 20 years for EBC, Minority, and Disabled candidates while for SC, ST, and BC must be 24 years.<br>\r\n<li>For studying Graduation level courses, the maximum age has been fixed as 25 and 29 years for EBC/Minority/Disabled candidates and SC/ST/BC candidates respectively.<br>\r\n<li>For courses of Post Graduate or Research levels, the age of candidates must not be more than 30 years in the case of EBC, Minority, and Disabled candidates and 34 years in the case of SC, ST, and BC candidates.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligible courses:</b><br>\r\n<b>1.Group-I</b><br>\r\n<li>Professional Courses (Degree and PG Courses in Medicine, Engineering, Technology, Management, Agriculture, Veterinary and Allied Sciences, Business Finance, Business administration and Computer Applications/ Science)<br><br>\r\n<b>2. Group-II</b><br>\r\n<li>Other professional and technical graduate and PG including (M.Phil, PhD and post-doctoral research) level courses not covered in Group-I. All post-graduate, graduate-level diploma courses.<br><br>\r\n<b>3. Group-III</b><br>\r\n<li>Degree courses(not covered in groups I & II)<br><br>\r\n<b>4. Group-IV</b><br>\r\n<li>Intermediate,ITI/ITCs, Vocational courses (Intermediate level)<br><br>\r\n5. Courses not eligible-\r\n<li> Aircraft Maintenance Engineerâs Courses, Private Pilot license Courses.<br>\r\n <li>Courses at Pre-examination Training Centers of all India and State levels.<br>\r\n<li> Correspondence courses & Year Certificate Course.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n <li>Group-I: Rs. 23,000 â Rs. 90,000<br>\r\n <li>Group-II: Rs. 3,610 â Rs.50,000<br>\r\n <li>Group-III: Rs. 1,500 â Rs. 20,000<br>\r\n <li>Group-IV: Rs. 850 â Rs. 16,400<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Contact Details:</b><br>\r\n <li>General Issue- 040-23390228<br>\r\n <li>Technical Issue- 040-23120311<br>\r\n <li>Email Id- help.telanganaepass@cgg.gov.in<br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>Secondary School Certificate Admit Card with examination roll number, passing year, and type of candidate.<br>\r\n<li>Aadhaar Card.<br>\r\n<li>Caste Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest Passport size photograph<br>\r\n<li>Income Certificate of the family.<br>\r\n<li>Bank passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Students need to submit the Mobile Passport and Passport Registration Application.<br>\r\n<li>Certificate of Study or a Bonafide Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>An order for the Common Entrance Test in case of CET courses.<br>\r\n<li>For an Intermediate student to register on the ePASS portal, he/she must finish the Online Admission procedures to the Board of Intermediate Education Portal with the help of the Principal of the College.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '23,000\r\n', '[\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\",\"PHARMD\"]', 'null', '\"ITI, Diploma, Undergraduates, Postgraduates, Ph.D Vocational courses, Intermediate Courses.\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-09', '2023-03-31', 'Telangana government ', 23000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-23 13:07:10', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-02 10:00:52', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1663, 'j9bOPHH6c3MKFiDc8l', 'Scholarship', 'Jawaharlal Nehru Scholarship', 'http://www.jnmf.in/sform.html', '', '', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8ZE1osRJk3s', 'The Jawaharlal Nehru Memorial Fund Scholarship is created to help students who are not able to pursue their post-graduation degrees. The candidates must be not above the age of 35 years in order to get the benefit of this scholarship scheme. This scholarship scheme is very prestigious and will be helpful for all of the students to continue their education after they have completed their undergraduate degrees.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n1. Hold a FIRST Class Post-graduate degree with a minimum of 60% marks in aggregate in both graduate and post-graduate levels. <br>\r\n2. Already be registered/admitted for a Ph.D. degree with a recognized 	University/Institution in India.  Those who have applied for registration and have not yet been registered at the time of submission of application are not eligible to apply. <br>\r\n3. Be a full-time Ph.D. Scholar. <br>\r\n4. Age Limit and Relaxation: Candidates should not be above 35 years of age on 1st October of the year of selection. A relaxation of up to 5 years will be provided to the candidates belonging to OBC-NCL (as per the Central List of OBC available on website: www.ncbc.nic.in) /SC/ST/PwD/Third gender categories and to women applicants. A relaxation of up to 5 years will be provided to the candidates who have served in the armed forces subject to the length of service in armed forces up to 1st October of the year of selection. Total age relaxation on the above ground(s) shall not exceed five years under any circumstances.<br>\r\n5. Duration of scholarship upto 2 years.<br>\r\n6. Area of Subjects:Indian History and Civilization, Sociology, Comparative Studies in Religion & Culture, Economics, Geography, Philosophy, Ecology & Environment.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n1. Maintenance allowance including Tuition fee (Stipend)- Rs.18,000/- per month.<br>\r\n \r\n2. Contingent expenses for study tours within India, purchase of books, stationery- Rs.15,000/-per annum.<br><br>\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions</b><br>\r\nThe following terms and conditions must be followed by the candidates in this scheme:-<br>\r\n1. The scholarship is available for 2 years.<br>\r\n2. Incomplete and unsigned forms are liable to be rejected.<br>\r\n3. The Selection Committeeâs decision to call a candidate for an interview or select a candidate for the scholarship will be final and no representation in this regard will be entertained.<br>\r\n4. The fund will not be responsible for any postal delays in reaching the application by the due date.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Application Process:</b><br>\r\n<li>Attach all of the documents in the application form.<br>\r\n<li>The candidates have to send their application form along with all the required documents and a demand draft/ postal order.<br>\r\n<li>The demand draft/ postal order should be drawn in favor of the âJawaharlal Nehru Memorial Fundâ worth INR 100.<br>\r\n<li>The application forms along with the amount are to be sent to the given address below:<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Administrative Secretary</b><br/>\r\n<b>Jawaharlal Nehru Memorial Fund</b><br/>\r\n<b>Teen Murti House</b><br/>\r\n<b>New Delhi-110 011.<br/></b><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Contact Details:</b><br>\r\n<b><li>Phone: </b><br>\r\n1.+91-11-23013641<br>\r\n 2.+91-11-23017173<br>\r\n   3.+91-11-23018087<br>\r\n<b><li>Fax:  </b>     +91-11-23011102<br>\r\n<b><li>Email:  </b>  jnmf1964@gmail.com<br>\r\n\r\n', '<li> passport-sized photos <br>\r\n\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>You must also submit a 1500-word summary, \r\nas well as a report from your supervisor or guide. <br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Rs.18,000/- per month\r\n', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 300000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-09', '2023-05-31', 'Jawaharlal Nehru Memorial Fund', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-23 13:27:49', 1, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-06 05:53:54', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1664, '1XJQY4l3StwM1ZcBIm', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Suggest name for promoting startups and entrepreneurship ', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/suggest-name-promoting-startups-and-entrepreneurship-newer-or-emerging-cities/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The ongoing technological revolution is propelling Indiaâs economic growth and is allowing for global socioeconomic transformation. At the micro level, it has reached Tier 2/3 cities in India, and the population of lower-tier cities is becoming affluent and eager to spend. Indiaâs development has undoubtedly extended beyond the metropolises, owing to government policies, improved infrastructure, improved digital connectivity, shifting consumer attitudes, consumption growth, and increased technology adoption. Technology-driven solutions to local problems at scale, such as healthcare, education, agriculture, finance, sustainability, and so on, are critical for equitable growth. The tech revolution is driven by local talent, indigenous innovations, and aspirational youth in Tier 2 and 3 cities, developing the next generation of innovators and entrepreneurs.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>To galvanize the start-up community and attract attention, the government has launched a series of initiatives to enable conducive infrastructure, support ecosystems, and increase funding availability. On the 76th anniversary of Indiaâs independence, Honâble Prime Minister Sh. Narendra Modi stated from Red Fort, âToday we are witnessing the structure of Digital India. Weâre looking into new businesses. Who are these individuals? This pool of talent resides in Tier 2 and Tier 3 cities and villages and comes from low-income families. These are our youngsters coming before the world today with discoveriesâ.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>In this regard, STPI has planned to undertake a new initiative to promote start-ups and entrepreneurship in newer/emerging cities (Tier-II and Tier-III cities) and motivate the youth towards innovation & entrepreneurship in emerging tech/deep tech sector for a vibrant start-up ecosystem in Tier II/III cities. Under this new initiative, STPI plans to do the following in Tier II/III cities across various states:\r\n<br>\r\n1. Conduct various workshops and seminars involving leading IT/Tech companies, their CXOs and other industry leaders.<br>\r\n2. Conduct hackathons/challenges involving regional academic institutes.<br>\r\n3.Organize Bootcamps, Mock Pitch sessions, Demo Days, and VC connect events to enable start-ups to raise funds.<br><br>\r\n<li>STPI is hosting a name suggestion competition on the MyGov.in platform as part of this initiative. Suggest a name that allows for mass connect and reverberation in the entrepreneurial community and inspires individuals to innovate and create futuristic products and solutions. Suggested Name may focus on promoting start-ups and entrepreneurship in newer or emerging cities (Tier II and Tier III cities), as well as inspiring youths in these cities to innovate in emerging technology areas and be a part of the vibrant Indian start-up ecosystem.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n \r\na) Cash Prize for the winner: Rs. 40,000/-<br>\r\nb) Cash Prize for runner up: Rs. 20,000/-<br>\r\nc) Cash Prize for second runner up: Rs. 10,000/-<br>\r\nd) Cash Prize of Rs 2,000/ â each to additional 5 best entries as consolation: Rs. 10,000/-<br><br>\r\n<b>Evaluation parameters:</b><br>\r\n \r\n \r\n<li>Applications will be selected and rated on the basis of following criteria:<br>\r\n \r\ni. Alignment to theme<br>\r\n \r\nii. Creativity<br>\r\n \r\niii. Originality<br>\r\n \r\niv. Simplicity<br>\r\n \r\nv. Inspirational element<br>\r\n \r\n \r\n<li>Jury will rate the entries and total of 8 winners as listed above shall be awarded.<br>\r\n \r\n \r\n<li> In case of more than the required winners in any category, further selection shall be done with the help of Draw.<br>\r\n \r\n \r\n<li> All participants shall be given a digital âCertificate of Participationâ by STPI.<br>\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Rs. 40,000/-\r\n', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-20', '2023-04-20', 'Government of India', 40000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-23 14:37:27', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-01 05:12:38', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1665, 'zl4OtsVLs3c8fC3RJY', 'Abroad', 'Ambedkar Overseas Scholarship', 'https://telanganaepass.cgg.gov.in/OverseasLinks.do', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ambedkar Overseas Vidya Nidhi 2023 has been announced by the Government of Telangana. This scholarship is specifically for the students of SC/ ST/ candidates to help them complete their higher studies in foreign countries.\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Under the Ambedkar Overseas Vidya Nidhi, scholarships will be provided to the scheduled caste, and scheduled tribe students so that they can study abroad without any financial hurdles. This scheme has been started with the objective of the development of backward communities. The aim of this scholarship program is to provide these backward communities students with a secure future and ultimately lead to the development of these communities\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The annual income of the applicantâs family should not be more than 5 lahks per annum.<br>\r\n<li>Only one child of a family is eligible to grab this scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>Aspirants must hold at least 60% marks in graduation.<br>\r\n<li>Must clear the GRE/GMAT and English Proficiency Test with eligible scores.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant should be a permanent resident of Telangana state.<br>\r\n<li>Eligible countries:USA, UK, Australia, Canada, Singapore, Germany, New Zealand, Japan, France South Korea.<br><br>\r\n<b>Scholarship Grant:</b><br>\r\nBeneficiaries will get the following benefits under this scholarship scheme:<br>\r\n<li>Rs. 20 lakhs or as per the admission letter whichever is less <br>\r\n<li>One-way Economic air ticket<br>\r\n<li>Visa charges.<br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>10th Marksheet.<br>\r\n<li>GRE/GMAT scorecard.<br>\r\n<li>TOFEL/ IELTS scorecard.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size Image.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide Certificate from the institute.<br>\r\n<li>Ration Card.<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Bank Passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Admission letter from Foreign University.<br>\r\n<li>Passport Copy.<br>\r\n<li>Residence/Nativity Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Mark Sheet of Last Qualified Course .<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Rs. 20 lakh\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 500000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-09', '2023-03-31', 'Government of Telangana', 200000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-23 15:08:17', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-23 11:23:26', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1666, 'qpAMimnocqqEafqMXP', 'Abroad', 'Australia Awards Scholarships', 'https://www.dfat.gov.au/people-to-people/australia-awards/australia-awards-scholarships', '', '', '', '', '', 'Australia Awards Scholarships, formerly known as Australian Development Scholarships (ADS), provide opportunities for people from developing countries, particularly those countries located in the Indo-Pacific region, to undertake full time undergraduate or postgraduate study at participating Australian universities and Technical and Further Education (TAFE) institutions.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n To be eligible to receive a Scholarship, applicants must:<br>\r\n1. Be a minimum of 18 years of age on 1 February of the year of commencing the scholarship;<br><br>\r\n2. Be a citizen of a participating country (as listed on the Australia Awards website) and be residing in and applying for the scholarship from their country of citizenship;<br><br>\r\n3. Not be a citizen of Australia, hold permanent residency in Australia or be applying for a visa to live in Australia permanently;<br><br>\r\n4. Not be married to, engaged to, or a de facto of a person who holds, or is eligible to hold, Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency, at any time during the application, selection or mobilisation phases (note: residents of Cook Islands, Niue and Tokelau with New Zealand citizenship are eligible but must apply for a Student visa [subclass 500]);<br><br>\r\n5.Not be current serving military personnel;\r\nnot have previously received a long-term Australia Award unless they have resided outside of Australia for twice the length of the total time that they were in Australia (for example, a previous awardee who has been on an Australia Awards Scholarship in Australia for four years will not be eligible to apply for another Australia Awards Scholarship until they have resided outside Australia for eight years);<br><br>\r\n6. Not hold convictions of criminal activities (including in their home country) including those relating to Child Protection and PSEAH;<br><br>\r\n 7. Recipients under the Pacific Secondary School Scholarship Program (PSSSP) who have completed their secondary school education in Australia in the year prior are eligible to apply for a long-term Australia Award;<br><br>\r\n8. Have satisfied any specific criteria established by the Program Area or the government of the applicantâs country of citizenship (e.g. having worked a certain number of years in an appropriate\r\nsector);<br><br>\r\n9. Be able to satisfy the admission requirements of the institution at which the award is to be undertaken (this may mean that Program Areas will need to withdraw an award offer if the recipient cannot satisfy the institutionâs admission requirements. This may not be known until Program Areas request a placement at selected institutions);<br><br>\r\n10.Be able to satisfy all requirements of the Department of Home Affairs to hold a Student Visa. This may mean that the Program Area will need to withdraw an award offer if the recipient cannot satisfy the visa requirements;<br><br>\r\n11.  Not be applying for a scholarship for a course of study at an academic level lower than already achieved (e.g. be applying for a Masterâs scholarship when they already hold a PhD); and<br><br>\r\n12.Applicants must inform the Program Area of any connection or relationship to staff employed at Program Areas (including locally engaged staff at post) or with managing contractors so that the\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Scholarship value/inclusions/duration:</b><br>\r\n<li>The scholarship benefits generally include: full tuition fees, return air travel, establishment allowance, contribution to living expenses (CLE), Overseas Student Health Cover (OSHC), Introductory Academic Program (IAP), Pre-course English (PCE) fees, etc. See the complete list of benefits at the official website.<br><br>\r\n<li>The scholarships are offered for the minimum period necessary for the individual to complete the academic program specified by the Australian higher education institution, including any preparatory training.<br><br>\r\n<b>Application instructions:</b><br>\r\n<li>Check the open and close dates for your country, and select your country of citizenship/residency from the list of participating countries for specific information on eligibility, priority areas and how to apply. Applications can be done online or by mail (if unable to apply online). The deadline is 1 May 2023 11:59pm AEST.<br><br>\r\n<li>It is important to read the how to apply page and visit the country specific pages, and the official website (link found below) for detailed and updated information on how to apply for this scholarship.\r\n<br><br.\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-17', '2023-05-01', 'Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade.', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-24 13:14:52', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-24 08:38:05', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL);
