(1673, 'pB6DzLRR6uXyxk6cEM', 'Abroad', 'Birmingham Chancellors Scholarship', 'https://app.geckoform.com/public/#/modern/21FO00gwrqdpr8000fr45lmbz4', '', '', '', '', '', 'The University of Birmingham Chancellorâs Scholarship is a prestigious award that is available to outstanding international postgraduate students who have demonstrated exceptional academic merit and potential. The scholarship is offered to students in all fields of study and covers the full cost of tuition fees, as well as providing a generous living allowance. For Indian postgraduate students, the University of Birmingham Chancellorâs Scholarship for India Students 2023 represents an excellent opportunity to pursue their academic goals at one of the UKâs leading universities.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<li>In addition to the financial support provided by the scholarship, recipients will also have access to a wide range of academic resources. They can get support services, as well as the opportunity to engage with a diverse community of scholars from around the world. This will enhance their academic experience, build their professional networks, and prepare them for successful careers.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<li>Be graduates having achieved a first-class degree or equivalent or a CGPA of 7 out of 10.<br>\r\n<li>Have received an offer of admission from Birmingham for a full-time taught Masterâs degree programme at the Universityâs UK or Dubai campus starting in September 2023 and have formally accepted it.<br>\r\n<li>Meet the academic conditions of their offer to the programme.\r\n<li>Be classed as domiciled in India (i.e. habitually resident in India at the point of application).<br>\r\n<li>Be classed by the University as an overseas fee payer for tuition fee purposes and be able to pay the outstanding tuition fees that are not covered by the scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>In the case of the Â£5,000 awards, have sufficient funds to cover the full cost of living at the University of Birmingham, plus any visa/travel expenses associated with studying in the UK or Dubai. <br>\r\n<li>In the case of the tuition waiver scholarships, the candidates must have sufficient funds to cover any additional costs associated such as additional maintenance expenses and any visa/travel expenses associated with studying in the UK or Dubai.<br>\r\n<li>In the case of the Â£5,000 awards, candidates must, upon enrolment in September 2023, pay their net tuition fees for the year by 1 November, immediately following enrolment<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\nThe following benefits will be available in the University of Birmingham Chancellorâs Scholarship for India Students 2023:<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The scheme includes one scholarship covering full tuition fees and the cost of university accommodation during studies (details to be confirmed), plus four additional awards of Â£5,000 each award as tuition fee discounts.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>One scholarship covering full tuition fees plus the cost of university accommodation during studies (details to be confirmed).<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Four additional awards of Â£5,000 each were awarded as tuition fee discounts.<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Contact Details:</b><br>\r\n<li>Tel: +44 (0)121 414 3344<br><br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Â£5,000\r\n', '[\"Masters\"]', 'null', '\"Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-17', '2023-04-07', 'University of Birmingham', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-25 15:19:23', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-25 09:51:56', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1674, 'cyzdpQ3zSiPrm36KL8', 'Scholarship', 'Kerala State Higher Education Council Scholarship', 'https://www.scholarship.kshec.kerala.gov.in/he_ma/he_maindx.php', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Kerala State Higher Education Council works to promote equity and excellence in the higher education sector and serves as the state of Keralaâs primary source of higher education policy input and trendsetting. The Kerala State Higher Education Council Act, 2007, and the Kerala State Higher Education Council (Amendment) Act 2018, both passed by the Kerala State Assembly, established the Council as an apex-level statutory authority. The Council is sometimes referred to as a mandated, functioning collective of all the stakeholders of the higher education sector, including professors, administrators, and students, because of its democratic structure and participatory approach to decision-making.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Pursuing higher education is essential to avail good job opportunities and fulfill your desired dreams. To make it possible the Kerala State Higher Education Council (KSHEC) is going to implement Kerala State Higher Education Council Scholarship 2023 for the students of Kerala who must be enrolled in first-year degree programmes at a government university or a government-aided arts and science college. For the academic year 2022â2023, the Kerala State Higher Education Council is providing up to 1,000 scholarship possibilities. The application period for applying under Kerala State Higher Education Council Scholarship 2023 will start on February 17, 2023, and it will expire on March 10, 2023.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b> Eligibility Criteria </b><br>\r\nThe applicants who want to apply for the given scholarship must fulfill the following criteria which are given below:<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>1.Nationality- </b><br>\r\n<li>The candidate must be an Indian national.<br>\r\n<b>2.Academic Qualification- </b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant must be enrolled in a first-year Undergraduate Assisted Science, Social Science, Humanities, or Business course in a Government-Aided Arts & Science College or be enrolled in a course of equal or greater academic rigor at an IHRD Applied Science College in 2022â2023. <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Not eligible are those enrolled in professional or self-financed courses. <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Candidates must have passed the Plus 2/equivalent test to be eligible.<br>\r\n \r\n<li>ST applicants must receive a passing grade in the Plus 2/equivalent exam for all streams. SC applicants must have a 60% average in the business studies stream and a 55% average in the humanities, social sciences, and sciences.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> It will be 45% for the physical challenge across all streams. <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The needed minimum marks for BPL/OBC are 65% in business studies, 55% in humanities & social sciences, and 60% in science.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>3. Other Criteria- </b><br>\r\n<li>This award is not available to recipients of any other grants or stipends other than fee reductions. \r\n<li>This section does not apply to the lump amount grant given to SC/ST students or the Hindi Scholarship given by the Directorate of Collegiate Education.\r\n<b>Benefit Received under Kerala State Higher Education Council Scholarship 2023 </b><br>\r\n<li>For the first, second, and third years of the undergraduate programmes, candidates will get INR 12,000, INR 18,000, and INR 24,000, respectively.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The first year of postgraduate study will cost INR 40,000, and the second year will cost INR 60,000 for undergraduate scholarship recipients who continue on to graduate school.<br>\r\n<li>Students who have physical impairments of at least 40% will get an additional 25% of the scholarship award.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Based on the scholarâs academic progress, scholarships will be renewed each year.<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', ' INR 24,000\r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-17', '2023-03-10', 'Kerala State Higher Education Council', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-25 15:34:28', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-01 09:45:42', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1675, 'FP1pqc528I6dZvQZoy', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Ignite Awards', 'https://nif.org.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Ignite Awards has been started in the year 2008. Since then more than 200 students got the award for their innovation/ creative idea. For the competition to win Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Ignite Awards, students have to submit their entries. Students who are studying up to class 12th can submit their creative technological ideas/ innovations for the competition.<br><br>\r\n<li> Students from streams other than science like arts, commerce, etc. can also apply. The idea submitted by the candidate should be his own. Candidates cannot submit common projects/ concepts like hydropower projects, rainwater harvesting, water level indicators, etc. Students can submit a photo/ video/ sketch of their idea. There is no particular format in which students have to submit their idea. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria:</b><br>\r\n<li>Applicant must be a school student studying up to class 12th.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Age of the applicant should not be more than 17 years.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits Of Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Ignite Awards</b><br>\r\nStudents who get selected for the award will get following<br>\r\n<li>Appreciation certificate.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Top idea/innovation will appear in the exhibition.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Some ideas might attract entrepreneur.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Travel support from home to the Ahmedabad location.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Financial and mentoring support to the practical and useful idea/innovation.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>No-cost patents will be for deserving cases.<br>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Application Procedure</b><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>To apply for the Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam ignite award, you have to visit the official portal of the national innovation Foundation and submit your entry or else..<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>You can also submit your entry through the offline mode.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>You have to forward your idea to the below-given address.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Dr A P J Abdul Kalam IGNITE Awards,<br/> National Innovation Foundation â India,<br/> Grambharti, Amrapur, Gandhinagar<br/>\r\nMahudi Road, Gandhinagar-382650, Gujarat.</b><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Helpline:</b><br>\r\nIn case of any doubts, you may contact the authorities.<br>\r\n<li>Email: ignite@nifindia.org or<br>\r\n<li>Telephone:02764261131/ 32/ 38/ 39<br>\r\n<li>Fax: +91 022 39167115<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Certificate, Financial Support', '[\"Secondary\",\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 6 to Class 12\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-21', '2023-03-15', 'National Innovation Foundation', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-25 16:30:19', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-20 06:42:18', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1676, 'gZ1Ad07rODS0RrRU8w', 'Scholarship', 'Gujrat CMSS Scholarship', 'https://scholarships.gujarat.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Education Department of the Gujarat State Government has started a new scholarship scheme specially available for candidates pursuing education at the pre-matric and post-matric levels. The Chief Minister Scholarship Scheme CMSS Scholarship will be specially available for students who are economically weak.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li> CMSS Scholarship is especially available for students who are permanent residents of the Gujarat state and want to continue their education despite their weak financial background. You can start studying through the implementation of this scholarship scheme.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>CMSS Scholarship Eligibility Criteria:</b><br>\r\nThe applicant must follow the following eligibility criteria to apply for recruit\r\n<li>The applicantâs familyâs annual income should be less than 1 lakh per lakh.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Students who have a minimum of 60% in their 10th and 12th board exams from an affiliated institution or college.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Applicants should study in any PG or UG course in Gujarat state.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits :</b><br>\r\nBeneficiaries under the scheme will get benefits as mentioned below<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Students who are going to take admission in diploma after 10th will get 50% of the fixed annual tuition fee of the course or rupees 50000 whichever is less.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Students who are going to take admission in degree course after diploma will get 50% of tuition fee for engineering and professional courses or rupees 100000 whichever is less.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b> Rewards:</b><br>\r\nThe following rewards will be provided in this scholarship scheme:-<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The beneficiaries will be liable to get free education after they have successfully completed their 12th from a recognized school and University is present in the state of Gujarat.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The beneficiaries will be able to continue their education without any worry of financial expenses. <br>\r\n<br>\r\n', 'The following documents must be submitted by the candidate in this recruitment:-<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Aadhar Card of the applicant.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Candidateâs previous class mark sheet.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Income Certificate of the candidateâs family.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Caste Certificate of the student.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Residence certificate of the candidate.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Studentâs Bank Account Details.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>School/College Admission certificate of the students.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Scanned Passport Size photograph of the applicant.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '50000 \r\n', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 100000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-22', '2023-03-31', 'Education Department of the Gujarat ', 50000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 12:06:59', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 06:56:05', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1677, 'Xg1KhMcycUkqJORjSU', 'Scholarship', 'Raita Vidya Nidhi Scholarship', 'https://raitamitra.karnataka.gov.in/english', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Department of Agriculture has launched the Raita Vidya Nidhi Scholarship has been launched to provide a scholarship amount to them for pursuing higher and professional courses after the completion of their pre-matric or post-matric classes. This scholarship will only be applicable to students whose parents are undertaking their profession in the farming field. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>\r\nThe main objective of launching the Raita Vidya Nidhi Scholarship is to provide an integrated or single platform by which the students belonging to farming occupation-based families will be able to pursue their higher studies or education without suffering from poverty issues with the help of the scholarship amount offered to them in the form of DBT mode.<br><br>\r\n<li>Another objective of launching this scholarship is to issue or award students with the scholarship amount who want to pursue Higher Education but canât pursue it so due to belonging to the farming family which is becoming an obstacle in their way of grabbing education due to economical instability. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The student must be a permanent resident of Karnataka.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The student must have enrolled himself or herself in the higher education course. <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The parents of the students must have a profession or occupation of Farming. <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligible degree courses:</b><br>\r\n<li>Students pursuing general degree courses. <br>\r\n<li>Students pursuing Management Courses. <br>\r\n<li>Students undertaking Health or Medical Courses. <br>\r\n<li>Students pursuing vocational and professional courses. <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits and rewards: </b><br>\r\nRaita Vidya Nidhi Scholarship will provide social security provisions and welfare to the students belonging to the farmersâ families. <br>\r\n<li>This scholarship will be extended to some other beneficiaries such as Potters, Blacksmiths, Sculptors, Madras and some other artisans.<br>\r\n<li>Students who are carrying out postgraduation degrees will be offered an amount of Rs. 10,000/- to Rs. 11,000/- <br>\r\n<li>Students will be given an amount of Rs. 5,000/ to 5500/- for pursuing management courses. <br>\r\n<li>Financial assistance of Rs. 7500/- for pursuing Law or Paramedical courses.<br>\r\n<li>Financial assistance of Rs. 2500/- and 3000/- will be provided to the boys and girls for undertaking PUC or ITI courses.<br>\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th and 12th mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '11000', '[\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"Professional course\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates, Postgraduates, Professional Courses\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-10', '2023-03-31', 'Department of Agriculture, Govt of Karnataka', 11000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 12:14:55', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 06:54:00', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1678, 'DyyVtcbeshveBzOnYp', 'Scholarship', ' Construction Workers Children Scholarship', 'https://ssp.postmatric.karnataka.gov.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Karnataka Chief minister Basavaraj Bommaihas disclosed the new employment policy of the state. During the speech, CM said that online distribution of scholarships for students from the families of construction workers will begin to implement in Karnataka. The Karnataka Construction Workers Children Scholarship 2023 program has been implemented by the Karnataka State Building and other construction workerâs Welfare boards. .<br><br>\r\n<li>All the children of construction workers who are studying can grab the opportunity. Online applications are available on the official state scholarship portal. Detailed instructions to submit the application along with the last date eligibility criteria benefits and other information about the Karnataka Education Assistance for Construction Workers Children is given underneath..<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The student should be a child of a registered construction worker.<br>\r\n<li>The student should be e a permanent resident of Karnataka.<br>\r\n<li>Only two children from the family will get the assistance.<br>\r\n<li>The workers should not have dues payable to the board.<br>\r\n<li>Applicant must be studying currently in a recognized institution located in Karnataka.<br>\r\n<li>Distance education courses, home study courses, and online courses are not eligible.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n1.For B.E , MBBS:\r\n<li>BE Rs 25,000/- for entry and Rs 20,000/- after passing every year.<br>\r\n<li>MBBS: Rs 30,000/- for entry, and Rs 25,000/- after passing every year.<br>\r\n2. For Postgraduate Courses:After entry Rs 20,000/- for every and thereafter Rs 10,000/- Every year for a maximum of 2 years subject to the passing of each year<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n3. For Doctral coursesRs 20,000/- after completion of every year (maximum 2 years) and thereafter, an additional Rs 20,000 after acceptance of thesis.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n4. After passing 1st year PUC examination or equivalent examination:Rs. 6,000/-<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n5. After passing 2nd year PUC examination or equivalent examination: Rs. 8,000/-<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n6. After passing each year in the I.T.I/Professional Diploma course of not less than 2 years duration: Rs. 7,000/â each year of passing.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n', 'Application processing and Verification by(if required) Senior/ Labour Inspector<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Application submitted within 6 months of the next Academic year<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Details of Education for the First Child<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Details of Education for the Second Child<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Employment Certificate<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Marks card and Study Certificate.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Photo of First Child<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Photo of Second Child<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Proof of Bank Account<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Proof of Identity/Smart card issued by the Board(Attested Copy)<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Ration Card<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Review and Approval by the Labour Officer<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Subscription certificate by SLI/LI<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '\r\n', '[\"ITI\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\",\"Diploma\",\"Professional course\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"ITI, Diploma, Professional Courses, Undergraduates, Postgraduates, Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-25', '2023-04-07', 'Government of Karnataka', 3000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 13:09:46', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-03-17 04:02:05', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1679, 'oTE8Rb5SRujnh781QX', 'Scholarship', 'AMM Murugappa Chettiar Centenary Scholars', 'http://e31investments.com/clients/amm-foundation/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/AMM_ScholarshipApplication03Dec2021-converted.pdf', '', '', '', '', 'https://youtu.be/KOYBy2Rcm1o', 'The AMM Foundationâs Murugappa Scholars programme is a 360-degree support system for underprivileged students pursuing professional streams. Created with an in-depth awareness of the challenges faced by underprivileged students, the scholarship goes beyond covering fees and expenses. Started in 2013-14, the programme has benefited 263 scholars, chosen after a rigorous selection process.\r\nThe scholarship provides a comprehensive help including soft skills and communication skills training. Once a student is selected as Murugappa Scholar, besides financial support in terms of College and Hostel Fee, the scholars program will focus in honing the personality of the scholars through a series of âSkill Development Programsâ and âContact Programsâ<br><br>\r\n<li>The Foundation has launched a special scholarship. The Scholarship reaches out to poor and meritorious students pursuing professional courses in Government and Government aided colleges. This would be a full fee scholarship and would support the students through the course. The selected students would be called as Murugappa Scholars.<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship will be routed through the Educational Institutions which would felicitate selection of highly deserving candidates. The main objective is not to just extent financial support but also to provide them with opportunities to hone their skill and attitude require for a successful career and life.A.M.M. Murugappa Chettiar Centenary Scholarship is available on merit cum means basis for educational purposes from LKG to PG.\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>Appicant must be a citizen of Tamilnadu.<br>\r\n<li>Gross family income not exceeding Rs.7,500/ per month.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Marks at qualifying examination 75% and above.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Applicable only for Engineering/Medical Courses Students and from other disciplines in exceptional cases.<br>\r\n<li>Students pursuing their higher studies in Government/Government aided and educational institutions of high reputation only are eligible for the scholarship.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Application process:</b><br>\r\nThe student should be referred by the Educational Institution.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>HOD/Principal needs to certify in the application form on the academic performance /character and socio economic background of the student.<br>\r\n<li>The application must be certified by the Head of Institution.<br>\r\n<li>The received applications would be shortlisted based on the eligibility criteria.<br>\r\n<li>The shortlisted applicants and their parents would be called for an interview with a panel of experts. The expenditure for the travel and stay will be reimbursed by the Foundation.<br>\r\n<li>Based on recommendation of the panel the student would be considered for the scholarship.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Contact:</b><br>\r\n<b>Email Id:</b><br>scholarship@ammfoundation.org<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Address</b><br>\r\nNew No.3(Old # 2),<br/>\r\nSriram Nagar North Street, <br/>\r\nAlwarpet,Chennai â 600 018.<br>\r\n\r\n<b>Mob no:</b><br>\r\n<li>044 2434 1668<br>\r\n\r\n<li>044 2432 0347<br>\r\n\r\n<li>044 2433 0128<br>\r\n\r\n<li>2434 4515<br>\r\n', '<li>Please attach (scan copy) the following documents with the mail. <br>\r\n<li>Mail attachment size should not exceed 5MB <br>\r\n<li> Latest Passport size photo<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> 10th and 12th Mark sheet <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Income Certificate<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Attach statement of fee details from college & copy of the receipt of last paid <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Bank passbook  <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> Proof of admission: Fees receipt paid, ID card, Bonafide Certificate<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial assistance\r\n', '[\"Class 10 \",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 1 to Postgraduation\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 90000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-23', '2023-07-15', 'AMM Foundation', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 15:33:49', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-04-26 03:46:30', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1680, '5QQUvjvSEPSDGGWw4a', 'Scholarship', 'Late Smt Sunita Devi SK Agarwal Scholarship', 'https://nagpuricai.org/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Senior Department of  Nagpur Branch of WIRC of ICAI has published Late Smt. Sunita Devi Suresh Kumar Agrawal Scholarship 2023 form for CA final students. According to latest Official Notification this scholarship scheme a merit-cum-means which is offered twice a year.If you are also one of them whose profile match this eligibility criteria then donât miss this golden opportunity and fill the Late Smt. Sunita Devi Suresh Kumar Agrawal Scholarship 2023 \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li> Applicant must be  domiciled in Nagpur.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants Names must appear in the merit list of rank holders.<br>\r\n<li>Parents Income must not be more than 1, 80,000/-.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Important Note :</b><br><li> In case, if there is no rank container from Nagpur city, then the scholarship will be given to the maximum marks scorer in the CA IPCC examination.<br><br>\r\n<b>Scholarship Award:</b><br>\r\n<li>Shortlisted candidates will receive INR 1000/- per month for the duration of 6 months.<br><br>\r\n<li>Applicants must send the duly completed scholarship form to the following address:<br>\r\nBranch Chairperson,<br/>\r\nNagpur Branch of WIRC of ICAI,<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nICAI Bhawan, Dhantoli,<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nNAGPUR â 440 012<br/>\r\n', '<li>Attested Xerox of SSC mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Recent Passport size photograph of the candidates.<br>\r\n<li>Xerox photocopy of CPT/IPCC exam mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Physically Challenged Certificate (if any).<br>\r\n<li>ICAI Certificate that the applicant is a student of IPCC/final of ICAI (in case of not undergoing Articleship)\r\nIncome certificate.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '1000/ per month', '[\"Professional course\"]', 'null', '\"CA Degree\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 180000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-25', '2023-04-13', ' Department of  Nagpur Branch of WIRC of ICAI ', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 16:35:25', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-02-27 11:07:49', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL);
