(1682, '5TxvAFO6A0V9QWVMej', 'Scholarship', 'Odisha Mukhyamantri Medhabi Chhatrabruti Yojana', 'https://scholarship.odisha.gov.in/website/home', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Odisha Government has allocated a budget of Rs. 30,030 crores for the education sector in the Budget 2023-24. The new scheme, Odisha Mukhyamantri Medhabi Chhatrabruti Yojana 2023, will provide scholarships to undergraduate, postgraduate, technical, and professional students. The government will also offer free coaching for Civil Services Examination and free lodging and boarding facilities to 200 meritorious students selected through an entrance exam.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li> Other highlights of the budgetary allocation for the education sector include funds for school and mass education, infrastructure development of higher education institutions, skill development, technical education, and creating self-employment opportunities for unemployed youths. Overall, the budget allocation reflects the governmentâs commitment to promoting education and empowering the youth of the state.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>The Odisha Mukhyamantri Medhabi Chhatrabruti Yojana is a new scheme implemented by the state government to provide financial assistance to deserving undergraduate (UG), postgraduate (PG), technical, and professional students.The scheme offers financial assistance to students who are meritorious and economically weaker sections of society. The scheme aims to encourage students to pursue higher education by providing them with the necessary financial support. The application process is simple and can be done online through the official website of the scheme.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Note:- </b>Above given schedule is tentative as it may vary according to the situation of the country or as per the norms provided by the concerned authorities<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\nThe eligibility criteria for Odisha scholarships vary depending on the specific scholarship program. Check the eligibility criteria given 