(1693, 'nmPjk7REnVJixVnr5O', 'Abroad', 'Robert Gordon University GREAT Scholarship', 'https://www.rgu.ac.uk/study/finance-funding/funding-and-scholarships/2388-great-scholarship', '', '', '', '', '', 'The RGU GREAT Scholarship is a highly regarded scholarship program designed to attract talented students to study at partnering UK institutions. The primary objective of this scholarship is to provide students with the opportunity to study in the UK and gain valuable skills and knowledge in their respective fields of study. In addition to receiving financial support for their studies, students who are selected for the Robert Gordon University GREAT Scholarships 2023 are expected to act as ambassadors for their institution of study. This means that they will be representing their university and the UK as a whole during their time in the country, and upon completing their studies, they will be expected to share their experience and knowledge with future students who may be interested in studying in the UK. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\nThe applicants are requested to follow the eligibility criteria that is presented by the University on the official website and it is important that you follow the eligibility criteria so that you can fill out the application form and get the benefits of the scholarship accordingly:<br>\r\n<li>Citizenship of Bangladesh, Egypt, India or Pakistan.<br>\r\n<li>Hold an undergraduate degree that allows entry to a postgraduate program at a UK university.<br>\r\n<li>Motivated and academically able to pursue a UK postgraduate taught course.<br>\r\n<li>Relevant work experience or a proven interest in the proposed subject area.<br>\r\n<li>Meet the English language requirement of the UK Higher Education Institution.<br>\r\n<li>Willing to attend lectures and tutorials, engage in extracurricular activities, and act as an ambassador for UK Higher Education.<br>\r\n<li>Willing to establish an engagement with the UK as a scholar, both personally and academically.<br>\r\n<li>Represent the GREAT brand and advocate for scholarshipsb.<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact Details:</b><br>\r\n<li>Email Id: international@rgu.ac.uk <br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'There are a lot of important documents and other things which are required in order to fill out the application form which is presented for the scholarship. You can check out the essential information about the documents and the information needed from the pointers given below and prepare yourself:<br><br>\r\n<li>Completed application form â You must complete the scholarship application form available on the RGU website.<br>\r\n<li>Academic transcripts â Provide academic transcripts for all previous academic qualifications.<br>\r\n<li>Personal statement â Write a personal statement explaining why you are applying for the scholarship and how it aligns with your academic and career goals.<br>\r\n<li>Reference letters â Provide two letters of reference from individuals who can attest to your academic or professional abilities.<br>\r\n<li>Proof of English proficiency â International students whose first language is not English must provide proof of English proficiency. RGU accepts IELTS, TOEFL, and other recognized English language tests.<br>\r\n<li>Passport copy â A copy of your passport should be provided to confirm your identity.<br>\r\n<li>Curriculum Vitae (CV) â Provide a current CV highlighting your education, work experience, skills, and achievements.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \"Login & Apply\" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'â¬10000 \r\n', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-27', '2023-05-30', 'Robert Gordon University', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-01 12:55:38', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 10:04:09', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL);
