(1694, 'UiUgG3h01vni8kLEfI', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Poster and Slogan Competition on Filariasis', 'https://innovateindia.mygov.in/lymphatic-challenge/', '', '', '', '', '', 'MyGov and the National Center for Vector Borne Diseases Control Division of the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare invite students from Class 6 to 8 and from Class 9 to 12 across India to design a poster and write a slogan on the topic Letâs Eliminate Lymphatic Filariasis (Haathipawn) from India.<br><br>\r\n<li>Schools affiliated with CBSE, including Kendriya Vidyalaya, Navodaya Vidyalaya, and National Institute of Open Schooling, and schools affiliated to all State Boards can participate in the Campaign and submit the best poster designs and slogans on the MyGov portal. The competition aims to enhance awareness among students regarding Lymphatic Filariasis.<br><br>\r\n<li>Lymphatic Filariasis\r\nLymphatic filariasis (LF), commonly known as Elephantiasis/Haathipawn, is a disfiguring, disabling disease, usually acquired in childhood. In the early stages, there are either no symptoms or non-specific symptoms. The bite of an infected culex mosquito. The microfilariae are transmitted into the body of a mosquito which feeds on the blood of a person carrying microfilariae in their blood.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Theme & Participation Criteria</b><br>\r\n<li><b>Theme: </b>The poster-making and slogan-writing competition topic is âLetâs Eliminate Lymphatic Filariasis (Haathipawn) from Indiaâ.<br>\r\n<li><b>Participation Criteria: </b>The competition will be organized for the students enrolled in Grades 6th to 12th and categorized under two categories. Five entries from each category will be selected.<br>\r\n<li>Category I - Classes 6th to 8th<br>\r\n<li>Category II - Classes 9th to 12th<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards</b><br>\r\n<li>The top ten winning students (five from each category) will be appreciated by giving Digital Certificate from the National Center for Vector Borne Diseases Control (NCVBDC) Division of the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare (MoHFW).<br>\r\n<li>The top 10 posters will be tweeted along with Lymphatic Filariasis messages by the NCVBDC through the MoHFW Twitter handle.<br><br>\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions:</b><br>\r\n<li>Schools affiliated with CBSE, including Kendriya Vidyalaya, Navodaya Vidyalaya, National Institute of Open Schooling, and schools affiliated to all State Boards can participate in the Campaign.<br>\r\n<li>Students belonging to Class 6th to Class 12th can participate. <br>\r\n<li>Students should draw their ideas on full chart paper. <br>\r\n<li>Top 10 entries will be selected by a Jury.<br>\r\n<li>The top 10 selected entries will be part of Twitterthon organized by NCVBDC on the MoHFW Twitter handle. <br>\r\n<li>Creativity and design should be relevant to the contest theme. The slogan should be simple, memorable, and factually correct.<br>\r\n<li>Entries must have both posters and slogans eligible for the relevant theme for the competition.<br>\r\n<li>The entries will open from 15th January 2023 to 15th March 2023. <br><br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Digital Certificate', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-15', '2023-03-15', 'MyGov and the National Center for Vector Borne Diseases Control Division', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-01 17:22:54', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-01 11:56:37', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1695, '8mS8HvLupwHAV2Opg2', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Menstrual Hygiene Management Filmotsav', 'https://innovateindia.mygov.in/film-competition-2022/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Department of Drinking Water and Sanitation (DDWS), Ministry of Jal Shakti, Government of India is organizing National ODF Plus Film Competition for Gram Panchayats on Menstrual Hygiene Management under Phase 2 of Swachh Bharat Mission-Grameen (SBMG) and in celebration of Azadi ka Amrit Mahotsav.<br><br>\r\n<li>The Competition will encourage and enable GPsâ to showcase ground level initiatives taken for Menstrual Hygiene Management. Menstrual hygiene has continued to be a cause of concern due to lack of knowledge, persisting taboos, stigma, limited access to menstrual products and disposal mechanism of sanitary pads. It is crucial to sensitize our women and girls about the importance and significance of menstrual hygiene management (MHM) which includes providing knowledge, access to menstrual products and information about its safe disposal. This would go a long way to reduce school dropout rate among girl students while improving their health and dignity.<br><br>\r\n<li>The competition will act as a massive Information, Education and Communication (IEC) campaign to raise mass awareness on MHM and would spread the message for breaking the silence and bust the myths surrounding menstruation and raise awareness on the importance of menstrual hygiene management.<br><br>\r\n<b>Themes for Participation and Award Details</b><br>\r\n<li>Statesâ/UTsâ are requested to actively participate in the National Competition on video documentation on Menstrual Hygiene Management. Gram Panchayats may use the administrative funds available under Fifteenth Finance Commission or IEC funds of Swachh Bharat Mission Grameen Phase 2.0 to undertake video documentation (upto 3-4 minutes).<br>\r\n<li>The Statesâ/UTsâ will share three best entries with DDWS for further evaluation. Subsequently; best qualified entries will be felicitated with Certificate, Memento and Cash Prizes of:<br>\r\n<b>First Prize - Rs. 5.0 lakh<br>\r\nSecond Prize - Rs. 3.0 lakh<br>\r\nThird Prize - Rs. 2.0 lakh</b><br><br>\r\n<b>Participation Guidelines:</b><br>\r\n<li>All Gram Panchayats are eligible to participate in the competition.<br>\r\n<li>The campaign will be from 19th November, 2022 (World Toilet Day) to 8th March 2023 (International Womenâs Day).<br>\r\n<li>The film entries may be of short duration (3-4 minutes approx) and good quality (high resolution video with clear action shots and subtitles, as applicable).<br>\r\n<li>The video must capture the essence of the interventions and highlight the innovations, if any.<br>\r\nIn case the video has sections/narration in vernacular language, sub-titles in English/ Hindi may be added.<br>\r\n<li>The film entries submitted by gram panchayats to be verified & evaluated by the States/UTs for authenticity, quality, appropriateness, and the final state-wise shortlisted entries to be shared with DDWS for review and consideration of central/national awards.<br>\r\n<li>Innovation in the implementation of the ideas or presenting already implemented innovations, in the film may be given more weightage and be kept as one of the important parameters while ranking the entries.<br>\r\n<li>The States and districts to suitably felicitate the shortlisted entries at their level. Fifteenth Finance Commission Funds or SBMG IEC funds may be utilized for the same.<br>\r\n<li>DDWS will recognize the best film entries submitted in the competition suitably.<br><br>\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions:</b><br>\r\n<li>The entries are eligible in all recognized Indian languages/dialects.<br>\r\n<li>DDWS will have copyright on the submitted entries for future use on its platform (website, social media and others) without any interference or permission(s).<br>\r\n<li>DDWS will not be responsible for any legal or financial implications involved in the production of films including use of celebrities, songs, footage, etc. <br>\r\n<li>The participant is to self-certify the authenticity/claim about the original work of the submitted entries or for consideration of awards.<br>\r\n<li>Every film entry should have clear VO/dialogue/music/song etc.<br>\r\n<li>The participant may consider using local geography, issues, themes, music/folk, etc.<br>\r\n<li>The entries must have clear details of the participantâs name, contact number, and Theme/category for consideration.<br>\r\n<li>The film has to be uploaded on YouTube with a valid and active email id. The upload link needs to be filled up in the Participation form on www.mygov.in competition link.<br>\r\n<li>The best entries for each theme/category received from every state/UT will be reviewed by a National Committee constituted by DDWS, Ministry of Jal Shakti for National Awards in respective categories.<br>\r\n<li>The announcement of awardees and felicitation will be done at a National DDWS Event with memento and certificates.<br>\r\n<li>No requests relating to claims of re-evaluation of the entries will be considered.<br>\r\n<li>The decision of the committee will be final and binding to all the entries.<br>\r\n<li>At any stage of evaluation, if an entry is found to violate the guidelines rules, the entry will be removed from evaluation process without giving any intimation.<br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '500000', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2022-12-02', '2023-03-08', ' Drinking Water and Sanitation (DDWS), Ministry of Jal Shakti, Government of India', 500000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-02 09:45:31', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-02 05:38:37', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1696, 'bLeQPvcenKg9l4PPU5', 'Scholarship', 'District Merit Scholarship Kerala', 'https://www.dcescholarship.kerala.gov.in/he_ma/he_maindx.php', '', '', '', '', '', 'If you are a resident of Kerala state then you will be highly benefited from the number of scholarships that are available on the official website of the Kerala Government. You can apply for the different types of scholarships according to your education level that you are on. There are a lot of monthly incentives available for the candidates who apply for these scholarships. You can apply for the scholarship by going to the official portal of the Kerala Government easily.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Due to poor financial conditions, there are many students who left their academic qualifications. Academic qualification is a necessity nowadays.  To complete the education of students who need financial help. To educate the students, the state government of Kerala is running many schemes. In this article today we have provided detailed information related to all the DCE Scholarship Kerala currently run by the Directorate of Collegiate Education. <br><br>\r\n<b>Note:- </b>Above given schedule is tentative as it may vary according to the situation of the country or as per the norms provided by the concerned authorities<br><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\nThe applicant must follow the following eligibility criteria to apply for the scholarship:-<br>\r\n<li>Should be the first-year student of:<br>\r\ni) Plus Two/UG/PG/Ph.D. course of Higher Secondary School/College/Institutes/University, which is either a Govt/Aided/Recognized Unaided Institution.OR<br>\r\nii) 11th Class/Technical/ Vocational Course of ITI/ITC Centers affiliated to NCVT.OR<br>\r\niii) Course, other than those listed under merit-cum-means scholarship scheme.<br>\r\n<li>Should belong to Minority Community(Muslim/Christian/Buddhist/Sikh/Zoroastrians or Parsis).<br>\r\n<li>Should have secured not less than 50% marks or equivalent grade in the previous Board/University Examination.<br>\r\n<li>The annual family income should not exceed Rs. 2 Lakhs.<br>\r\n<li>Should not be availing any other Scholarship or Stipend.<br><br>\r\n<b>Awards/Rewards Details</b><br>\r\nThe applicant will be given the following awards in this scholarship:-<br>\r\n<li>Admission and tuition fee up to INR 10,000 per annum<br>\r\n<li>Maintenance allowance of up to INR 1,200 per month (for 10 months)<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact Details</b><br>\r\n<li><b>Address:</b> The Special Officer Scholarships,<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\nDirectorate of Collegiate Education,<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n6th Floor, Vikas Bhavan, <br/>\r\nThiruvananthapuram- 695033<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li><b>Helpdesk Number:</b> 0471-2306580/ 9446096580\r\n\r\n', 'You will have to submit the following documents to apply for the scholarship:-<br/>\r\n<li>Mark sheet of last qualifying examination.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Proof of admission to the educational institution.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Birth certificate/ Date of birth proof.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Domicile certificate/ Residential certificate.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Course certificate of current educational course.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Parentâs income certificate.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Caste certificate.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>ID proof of the candidate.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Electronic clearing service(ECS) form from the bank where the applicant has an account.<br/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>First-page copy of bank passbook.<br/>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '10,000 ', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"ITI\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"PHD\",\"Diploma\",\"Professional course\"]', 'null', '\"Intermediate, Technical,  Vocational Course, ITI, ITC, Diploma,  Undergraduate, Postgraduate, Ph.D\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\