(1720, 'eEwBIrN5dEdAJQ2kGj', 'Scholarship', 'ONGC Sports Scholarship Scheme', 'https://sportsscholarship.ongc.co.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The ONGC Sports Scholarship Scheme provides financial assistance to young and talented sportspeople who have the potential to excel in their respective sports. The scheme aims to help them pursue their dreams, bring accolades to the country, and inspire younger generations to engage in sports activities. The scheme covers a wide range of sports, including athletics, badminton, basketball, chess, cricket, football, golf, hockey, kabaddi, swimming, and wrestling, among others.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>The objective of the Sports Scholarship scheme of ONGC is to provide a financial boost to young and talented sportspersons who have the potential to excel in their respective sports. By offering financial assistance, the scheme aims to enable the chosen athletes to pursue their dreams, hone their skills, and achieve excellence in their chosen sport. Through this initiative, the scheme aims to bring recognition and accolades to the country through the achievements of these young sportspersons. Additionally, the scheme hopes to inspire and encourage the younger generation to engage in sports activities and pursue their passion for sports. The scheme is designed to identify and support emerging sports talent, help them overcome financial constraints, and create opportunities for them to excel at national and international levels.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility, Age Criteria & Duration of Scholarship:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant must for the following eligibility criteria in order to successfully apply for this scholarship and get all of the benefits which are available in this is scholarship:<br>\r\n<li>The sportsperson must be an Indian citizen.<br>\r\n<li>The applicant must not be receiving any scholarship or stipend from any other organization during the scholarship period.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship is open to sportspersons between the ages of 14 to 25 years old, except for Chess, Gymnastics, and Swimming, where the minimum age is 10 years old.<br>\r\n<li>The maximum age for receiving the scholarship is 25 years old, and applicants up to the age of 24 years old as of April 1 of the year of the scholarship can apply.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship will be granted for FY 2023-24.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship is merit-based, and applicants need to apply every year.<br><br>\r\n<b>Scholarship Amount:</b><br>\r\n\r\n<b>National Level:</b>\r\n<li>Sub Junior: Rs. 15,000/- p.m.<br>\r\n<li> Junior: Rs. 20,000/- p.m.<br>\r\n<li> Senior: Rs. 25,000/- p.m.<br><br>\r\n<b>International Level</b><br>\r\n<li>Sub Junior: Rs. 20,000/- p.m.<br>\r\n<li>Junior: Rs. 25,000/- p.m.<br>\r\n<li> Senior: Rs. 30,000/- p.m.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits & Facilities Available:</b><br>\r\n<li>There are a lot of benefits and a lot of facilities available in this prestigious scholarship presented by the organization. The candidates can check out the major information about the benefits and the facilities available from the pointers given below:<br><br>\r\n<li>Sportspersons who are on scholarship will have the opportunity to represent the ONGC Team in PSPB/AIPSSPB tournaments and other competitions within the country, subject to the direction of the Head of Sports.<br><br>\r\n<li>The players will be provided with TA/DA and all the necessary expenses related to their participation in the tournaments.<br><br>\r\n<li>Sportspersons on scholarship will also be given playing kits that have the ONGC logo. These kits must be worn by the players during their participation in competitions.<br><br>\r\n<li>Scholarship holders can obtain an individual health insurance cover of Rs. 5,00,000/- (Five lakhs only) for themselves. The individual must acquire the required health insurance coverage on their own, and ONGC will reimburse the premium amount up to Rs. 7,000/-.<br><br>\r\n<li>ONGC will not be held responsible for any loss, damage, injury, or disability caused to any sports scholarship holder. Additionally, ONGC will not indemnify any sports scholarship holder towards such loss, damage, injury, or disability that may arise or occur while performing any sports activity.<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact Details:</b><br>\r\n<li><b>Address : </b>Oil and Natural Gas Corporation Limited<br>\r\nPlot No. 5A- 5B Nelson Mandela Road<br>\r\nVasant Kunj, New Delhi â 110070<br>\r\n<li><b>Contact Number â</b> (011)-26750998 <br>\r\n<li><b> Email Id â</b> sports_scholarship@ongc.co.in<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '25,000/ month\r\n', '[\"Secondary\",\"Class 10 \",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Sportspersons between the ages of 14 to 25 years old\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-07', '2023-03-27', 'Oil And Natural Gas Corporation', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-09 11:57:48', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-03-13 07:11:07', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1721, 'uU15ailC7IF2GK1jHW', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Prime Ministers Awards for Yoga', 'https://innovateindia.mygov.in/pm-yoga-awards-2023/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Yoga is an invaluable gift of ancient Indian tradition. The word \"Yoga\" is derived from the Sanskrit root yuj meaning \"to join\", \"to yoke\" or \"to unite\", symbolizing the unity of mind and body; thought and action; restraint and fulfillment; harmony between human and nature, and a holistic approach to health and well-being. Yoga is known for disease prevention, health promotion and management of many life style related disorders. Recognizing its universal appeal, on 11Th December 2014, the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) passed a resolution (resolution 69/131) proclaiming 21ST June as the International Day of Yoga (IDY).\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>\r\nShri Narendra Modi, Honâble Prime Minister, on the second International Day of Yoga announced two Yoga awards â one International and other National â to be given on the occasion of International Day of Yoga. The purpose of the Award is to recognize and felicitate individual(s)/ organization(s) who have made significant impact on the society for a sustained period of time by way of promotion and development of Yoga.<br><br>\r\n<b>Categories:</b><br>\r\nThe awards would be given in two categories â National and International. The awards would be given to entities with an impeccable track record and outstanding contributions to the promotion and development of Yoga. In a particular year, the Jury may decide to give awards to one or more individuals/organizations or none. An entity which has received an award once may not be considered again for conferring an award in the same category.<br><br>\r\n1.National: The two National Awards will be given to entities of Indian origin, for their contribution to the promotion and development of Yoga.<br>\r\n2.International: The two International Awards will be given to entities of Indian or foreign origin, for their contribution to the promotion and development of Yoga across the Globe.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The intent of the awards is to recognize entities who have made significant and outstanding contributions toward the promotion and development of Yoga.<br><br>\r\n<li>In this regard, the applicants/nominees for these awards should have a rich experience in and a deep understanding of Yoga.<br><br>\r\n<li>The minimum eligible age of the applicant/nominee under the individual category for both National & International is 40 years.<br><br>\r\n<li>Minimum 20 (Twenty) years of service with an impeccable track record and outstanding contribution to the promotion and development of Yoga.<br><br>\r\n<b> Award:</b><br>\r\n<li>The name of the winners will be announced on the 9th International Day of Yoga (21st June 2023).<br>\r\n<li>The winners will be felicitated by means of a Trophy, Certificate and a Cash Award.<br>\r\n<li>The felicitation ceremony will coincide with the International Yoga Conference.<br>\r\n<li>The value of each Cash Award would be Rs. 25 lakh\r\nIn the case of joint winners, the awards would be divided amongst the winners.<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Rs. 25 lakh\r\n', '[\"All\"]', 'null', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-01', '2023-03-31', 'Government of India', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-09 13:40:38', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-09 08:13:06', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1722, 'opcjvNS5Buc1ylbS3f', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Reel on One India One Emergency Number 112', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/make-reel-one-india-one-emergency-number-112/', '', '', '', '', '', 'With a view to enable active use of technology to strengthen emergency response services, especially for safety of women in public places, the Ministry of Home Affairs (MHA) has implemented a project titled âEmergency Response Support System (ERSS)â. Government of India has notified 112 as a pan-India, single, internationally recognized number for various emergencies such as police, fire, ambulance, etc., with computer-aided dispatch of field resources accessible through calls, SMS, e-mail, panic button and the 112 India mobile app. This emergency service has now been operationalized in all States/UTs.<br><br>\r\n<li>Ministry of Home Affairs (MHA) in collaboration with MyGov invites creative ideas in the form of Reels / Short Video, in MP4, MOV Format, from the creative minds of the nation to join the Nationâs Safety and participate in the Reel Making Competition on the Theme -<b> âOne India, One Emergency Number â Dial 112â.</b>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Note: - </b>The competition is open for all citizens.<br><br>\r\n<b>Technical Parameter:</b><br>\r\n1. The length of the reel should not exceed more than 45 seconds.<br>\r\n2. The size of the attachment should not exceed 2 MB at MyGov.<br>\r\n3. Computer-generated or computer-altered/morphed videos (other than basic system work) will be disqualified.<br>\r\n4. The hashtags to be used for the reels, should be #ReelingwithDial112<br>\r\n5. The participants are required to share the link of the reels in the description box below. Also, the participants are further encouraged to share the reels on their social media accounts with the hashtag #reelingwithdial112 and share the link to the same in the description box below.<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n1. Cash Prize for 1st Winner: Rs. 3,000/-<br>\r\n2. Cash Prize for 