(1726, 'cbIDLm0ZdxGaoj16Y4', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Design Poster on One India  One Emergency Number  112', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/design-poster-one-india-one-emergency-number-112/', '', '', '', '', '', 'With a view to enable active use of technology to strengthen emergency response services, especially for safety of women in public places, the Ministry of Home Affairs (MHA) has implemented a project titled âEmergency Response Support System (ERSS)â. Government of India has notified 112 as a pan-India, single, internationally recognized number for various emergencies such as police, fire, ambulance, etc., with computer-aided dispatch of field resources accessible through calls, SMS, e-mail, panic button and the 112 India mobile app. This emergency service has now been operationalized in all States/UTs.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Ministry of Home Affairs (MHA) in collaboration with MyGov invites creative ideas in the form of posters, both digital and physical / hand drawn in PDF Format, from our creative mind to join the Nationâs Safety and participate in the Poster Making Competition on the Theme -<b> âOne India, One Emergency Number â Dial 112â.</b>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Note :- The competition is open for all.</b><br><br>\r\nTechnical Parameter:<br>\r\n1. The participants may hand draw/ sketch the poster on A3 or A4 pages for physical entry submission and create digitally designed posters through computer software for digital submission.<br>\r\n2. Posters can be submitted in PDF or JPEG format. The size of the attachment should not exceed 2 MB.<br>\r\n3. It should be ensured that the uploaded poster is clearly visible along with the text and graphics/image.<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n1. Top 5 winners will be rewarded with a Cash Prize of Rs. 3,000/- each.<br>\r\n2. Selected entries will be featured on the Ministry\'s social media handles.<br>\r\n<li><b>Last date of Submission: 08th April 2023</b><br>\r\n', '', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '3000\r\n', '[\"All\"]', 'null', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-08', '2023-04-08', 'Ministry of Home Affairs  in collaboration with Government of India', 3000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-10 14:50:04', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-10 09:21:20', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1727, 'k9OsoRZa5UdcRq66Z5', 'Scholarship', 'Saandeepani Shishya Vethana Scheme', 'https://ksbdb.karnataka.gov.in/english', '', '', '', '', '', 'Karnataka State Brahmin Development Board invites online applications from eligible brahmin students to grab the opportunity. Under this scheme, authorities are going to provide monetary help to meet the expenses of education and other fees, textbooks, electronic equipment, other study equipment, hostel, transportation, and clothing.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Several students are there who are not able to finance their education. to help such students state or central government is running many schemes. Saandeepani Shishya Vethana Scheme is one such scheme. The major objective of the Karnataka State Brahmin Development Board is to assist the education of students of the economically weaker section of the Brahmin community. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant should be a native of Karnataka.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants should be Brahmin.<br>\r\n<li>He/She should belong to the BPL category.<br> \r\n<li>Applicant must possess at least a matriculation examination certificate.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits of Saandeepani Shishya Vethana Scheme:</b><br>\r\n<li>Under this scheme, the Karnataka government is going to distribute Rs. 15000/- through direct benefit transfer (DBT) into the bank accounts of students. <br>\r\n<li>The amount will be given to meet the expenses like education and other fees, textbooks, electronic equipment, other study equipment, hostel, transportation, and clothing.<br>\r\n<li> This year a total of 9,206 students will get the benefits. The government has sanctioned Rs 13.77 crore to help such students this year. <br><br>\r\n\r\n', '<li>EWS Certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar Card.<br>\r\n<li>SSLC/10th Class Marks Card.<br>\r\n<li>PUC Registration Number (for first-year degree courses).<br>\r\n<li>Marks Card of last yearâs studies. (Eg: For 2nd year BA student, his/her first-year BA marks card).<br>\r\n<li>Eligible payment receipt as per this announcement for Fee Reimbursement.<br>\r\n<li>Study certificate attested by Principal.<br>\r\n<li>Unique Disability card for Specially abled students issued by the Government of India who is suffering from Blindness, Cerebral Palsy, Low vision, Locomotor Disability, Leprosy cured but with a disability, Mental retardation, Mental illness, or Hearing impairment.<br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '15000\r\n', '[\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 12, Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 250000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-09', '2023-04-11', 'Karnataka State Brahmin Development Board', 15000.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-10 15:03:26', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-10 09:34:49', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1728, 'XUBSfYLVbloklDZKTR', 'Abroad', 'Karnataka Prabuddha Overseas Scholarship', 'https://sw.kar.nic.in/foreignstudies/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Prabuddha Overseas Scholarship 2023 was announced by the Social Welfare Minister of Karnataka Mr. Priyank Kharge. Karnataka SC/ST Student Overseas Education Scheme will provide help in their studies. Under Prabuddha Scholarship Scheme, students of the Schedule Caste (SC) and Schedule Tribe (ST) community will get the chance to pursue their undergraduate, post-graduate and doctorate degree (Ph.D.) program in the international universities at free of cost. This Scheme will cover the entire course fee, living expenditure, hostel fee, and travel expenses. Karnataka SC-ST Students Overseas Scheme is really a golden opportunity to flourish in their dreams.<br><br>\r\n<li>The students of the SC/ST community can shine their dream with Karnataka Prabuddha Scheme. Under this scheme, the Govt of Karnataka is providing the chance to pursue their higher education abroad. There is a reservation of 33% for women (SC/ST) candidates and 4% for differently-abled persons in the community. Only No more than two students from one family can apply for the scholarship. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>Under Karnataka Prabuddha Scheme, up to 250 students for undergraduate courses and 150 students for post-graduate & doctorate courses will be selected. The Social Welfare Dept of Karnataka will release Rs 120 crore for the Prabuddha SC-ST Student Overseas Scheme. A student will be eligible to apply for the scheme only once, whether UG, PG or Ph.D.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The applicant should be an Indian citizen. <br>\r\n<li>Candidate should be a permanent resident of India\r\n<li>Students should have a valid passport. <br>\r\n<li>The applicant should have secured admission into a full-time degree program at an overseas university/college. <br>\r\n<li>The applicants for the scholarship must meet the minimum score requirements as specified by the respective countryâs embassy (for example TOEFL scores for USA).<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b><br>\r\n<li>Students whose family annual income is below Rs 8 lakh will get 100% coverage.<br>\r\n<li>Selected candidates whose family annual income is between Rs 8 to 15 lakh will get 50% coverage.<br>\r\n<li>The student whose family annual income is above Rs 15 lakh will get 33% coverage.<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact details:</b><br>\r\nSocial Welfare Department<br/> 24*7 Help line Kalyana Mitra <br/> \r\n<li>Call on 9482300400\r\n<li>Scholarship Related Queries<br>\r\n<li>24/7 HelplineNo:08022634300<br>\r\n<li>Department No:080-22340956,9480843005<br>\r\n<li>E-mail: helpswkar@gmail.com<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1)Adhar Card.<br>\r\n2)Caste Certificate.<br>\r\n3)Latest income certificate(mother and father both included).<br>\r\n4)Last 2year IT return.<br>\r\n5)Degree/master degree convocation certificate.<br>\r\n6)Degree/ master degree all semester marks card.<br>\r\n7)Offer letter from university obtained.<br>\r\n8)First and second page of passport together.<br>\r\n9)Tution fee and maintenance fee as sent by university.<br>\r\n10)I20(I twenty)/CAS number(if obtained).<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 800000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-08', '2023-04-30', 'Social Welfare Minister of Karnataka Mr. Priyank Kharge', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-10 15:14:56', 1, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-10 09:58:39', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1729, '4rbrvpS6Efj6Bg6zVX', 'Scholarship', 'Mahindrakar Charitable Trust Scholarship', 'https://www.mahindrakar-trust.org/', '', '', '', '', 'https://youtu.be/tDRGvnkomdI', 'SHRI HANMANTRAO AND SMT PARVATIBAI MAHINDRAKAR CHARITABLE TRUST (R) (est: 27-04-2018) [Reg. No.31-2018-19 DHARWAD] is soliciting new students to apply for an educational scholarship. Applications are invited from those who belong to the Bhavsar Kshatriya community. \r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\n<li>The students must reside in one of the following districts: Bagalkot, Ballari, Bidar, Gulbarga, Chitradurga, Kalaburgi, Koppal, Raichur, Shivamogga, Vijayapura, Yadgiri, Raichur, Belgavi, Koppal, Gadag, Dharwad, Uttara Kannada, Haveri or Davangere.<br><br>\r\n<li>The studentâs parents must have a low income.<br><br>\r\n<li> Students must have passed SSLC and attend some form of higher education. <br><br>\r\n<li>The scholarship is open only to Bhavasar Kshatriya Samaj students from PUC to degree, diploma, or certificate courses.<br><br>\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions:</b><br>\r\n<li>All fields in the application form must be filled.<br>\r\n<li>The form must be completed in CAPITALS.<br>\r\n<li>The scholarship is open only to Bhavasar Kshatriya Samaj students from PUC to degree, diploma, or certificate courses.<br>\r\n<li>The application must be recommended by the chairman/secretary of the local Bhavasar Kshatriya Samaj.<br>\r\n<li>The signature of the Principal of the college/institute along with the date is required.<br>\r\n<li>Photocopies of grade cards and relevant certificates are required.<br>\r\n<li>Photocopy of latest tuition fee receipt is required.<br>\r\n<li>Deadline for the application is November 30th in order to receive payment in January.<br>\r\n<li>The trustees\' decision in allotting scholarships will be final and binding.<br>\r\n<li>Please make sure your bank account is active or else you will not receive the scholarship amount.<br>\r\n<li>The students must reside in one of the following districts: Bagalkot, Ballari, Bidar, Gulbarga, Bijapur, Chitradurga, Chikkamagaluru, Kalaburgi, Koppal, Raichur, Shivamogga, Vijayapura, Yadgiri, Raichur, Belgavi, Koppal, Gadag, Dharwad, Uttara Kannada, Haveri or Davangere.<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact Details:</b><br>\r\n<li><b>Address: </b>Sadhankeri,Dharwad, Karnataka, India<br>\r\n<li><b>E mail:</b> admin@mahindrakar-trust.org<br>\r\n<li><b>WhatsApp:</b>+919449889137<br>\r\n', '<li>Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Class 10th and 12th mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>College fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>Income certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Bonafide certificate.<br>\r\n<li>Latest academic mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Bank account passbook.<br>\r\n<li>Passport size photograph.<br>', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', 'Financial Assistance', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Bachelors\",\"Diploma\"]', 'null', '\"Class 10 to Class 12, Diploma, Undergraduates\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-10', '2023-11-23', 'Mahindrakar Charitable Trust', 0.00, 'javeriyayub@triwits.com', '2023-03-10 15:40:59', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-20 04:50:04', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1730, 'v5cBTCc8F9oNLwpy3f', 'Scholarship', 'Samsung Star Scholarship Programme', 'https://images.samsung.com/is/content/samsung/p5/in/microsite/sapne-hue-bade/stories/Scholarship-New-Form.pdf', '', '', '', '', 'https://youtu.be/s9VYS6GDP1A', 'Samsung India has been running the Samsung Star Scholarship program in India for the past several years.\r\nSamsung Star Scholarship Programme 2023 is meant for the Indian students who have passed from Jawahar Novadaya Vidyalaya and currently pursuing undergraduate engineering programs (B.Tech) or dual degree programs (B.Tech + M.Tech) from IITs and NITs for the year 2023-24, who are studying in the current batch. Samsung Star Scholarship Programme 2023 is being offered by Samsung India Electronics Private Limited. This initiative of Samsung India is taken for empowering Indiaâs youth education and brings positive change in technology across the world.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<li>\r\nThe Samsung Star Scholarship program started in 2013 as a Samsung Smart Class Program in partnership with Samsung India and the JNV committee.But in the year 2016, it has been named as Samsung Star Scholar Program. Ever since Samsung launched this scholarship scheme. Since then more than 2 lakh 50 thousand students across the country have taken advantage of this.\r\nTraining is also provided to teachers under Samsung Star Scholarship. So far, over 8000 teachers have been trained to use Interactive technology under this scheme.\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b><br>\r\nHere are the eligibility conditions that aspirants have to mandatorily fulfill to apply for Samsung Star Scholar Programme:<br>\r\n<li>Only Indian citizens can apply.<br>\r\nOnly the applicants who are admitted in B.Tech/B.Tech+M.Tech dual degree programme in IITs and NITs listed by Samsung are eligible to apply for the scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>Must have completed his class 12 from any of the Jawahar Navodaya Vidyalaya (JNVs).<br>\r\n<li>Applicant must have required to receive good JEE rank to avail this scholarship.<br>\r\n<li>Maintain a Semester Grade Point Average (SGPA) or Cumulative Grade Point Average (CPGA) rating of 5 or above.<br>\r\n<li>To get scholarship continued, candidates must be in the top 50% of their class.<br>\r\n<li>Applicants must not receive any financial assistance or scholarship during the pursuance of the engineering program.<br>\r\n<li>The Samsung Star Scholars must be a student of a Jawahar Navodaya Vidyalaya or a National Institute of Technology (NIT) in India<br><br>\r\n<b>Rewards:</b><br>\r\n\r\nUnder the Samsung Star Program,the scholars will be provided with the financial assistance of up to 2 lacs per annum for five years. So that the students who get this scholarship can easily bear the expenses of Tuition, Hostel Fee and food expenses.<br><br>\r\n<b>Contact Details:</b><br>\r\nSAMSUNG STAR SCHOLAR<br/>\r\nSamsung India Electronics Pvt. Ltd.,<br/>\r\nCorporate Citizenship (CRO)<br/>\r\n20th ~ 24th Floor, Two Horizon <br/>Centre, Golf Course Road,\r\nSector â 43, <br/>DLF Phase V, Gurgaon, <br/>Haryana -122002, India\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Self-certified class 10th and 12th CBSE mark sheet.<br>\r\n<li>Self-certified copy of admission letter.<br>\r\n<li>Self-certified copy of JEE Advanced ranking certificate.<br>\r\n<li>A signed canceled cheque of bank account.<br>\r\n<li>Self-certified copy of Aadhar card.<br>\r\n<li>Self-certified copy of PAN card.<br>\r\n<li>Original copy for admission/first semester/annual fee receipt.<br>\r\n<li>A brief write-up on a separate sheet including the reason âwhy you are qualified for a scholarship and how you will be impacted if selectedâ.<br>\r\n', '1. Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button<br>\r\n2. Read the scholarship details carefully<br>\r\n3. Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents<br>\r\n4. Submit<br>', '2 lakhs/year\r\n', '[\"Engineering\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"B.Tech, B.Tech + M.Tech from IITs and NITs \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]'