(1762, 'bx6Ir77vRgOhk3L50m', 'Competitions and Awards', 'John Locke Institute Essay Competition ', 'https://essaycompetition.johnlocke.com/', '', '', '', '', 'https://youtu.be/wedCqOq_NnU', ' The John Locke Institute encourages young people to cultivate the characteristics that turn good students into great writers: independent thought, depth of knowledge, clear reasoning, critical analysis, and persuasive style</br>\r\n<li>This essay competition invites students to explore a wide range of challenging and interesting questions beyond the confines of the school curriculum</br>\r\n<li>Entering an essay in our competition can build knowledge, and refine skills of argumentation. It also gives students the chance to have their work assessed by experts. All of the essay prizes are judged by a panel of senior academics drawn from leading universities including Oxford and Princeton.</br>\r\n<li>The judges will choose their favorite essay from each of the seven subject categories, and a junior category for those under 15s, and then select an overall âbest essayâ across the seven subjects: Philosophy, Politics, Economics, History, Psychology, Theology, and Law</br></br>', '', '<li> Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button</br>\r\n<li> Read the scholarship details carefully</br>\r\n<li> Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents</br>\r\n<li> Submit</br>', '$2000', '[\"Primary\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"\\\"Primary\\\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-03', '2023-06-30', 'John Locke Institution', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-03 17:23:57', 1, 'aishwaryapatil@triwits.com', '2023-05-13 06:33:14', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1763, 'cKvdpe5i4FHgCBXFSi', 'Scholarship', 'Jilla Merit Award', 'https://www.dcescholarship.kerala.gov.in/he_ma/he_maindx.php', '', '', '', '', 'https://youtu.be/3Q9cPtPMMYE', 'If you are a resident of Kerala state then you will be highly benefited from the number of scholarships that are available on the official website of the Kerala Government.\r\n<li>You can apply for the different types of scholarships according to your education level that you are on. There are a lot of monthly incentives available for the candidates who apply for these scholarships. You can apply for the scholarship by going to the official portal of the Kerala Government easily.</li><br><br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b>\r\n<b><li>Should be the first-year student of:</li></b>\r\n<li>i) Plus Two/UG/PG/Ph.D. course of Higher Secondary School/College/Institutes/University, which is either a Govt/Aided/Recognized Unaided Institution. OR </li>\r\n<li>ii) 11th Class/Technical/ Vocational Course of ITI/ITC Centers affiliated to NCVT. OR</li>\r\n<li>iii) Course, other than those listed under merit-cum-means scholarship scheme.</li>\r\n<li>Should belong to Minority Community (Muslim/Christian/Buddhist/Sikh/Zoroastrians or Parsis).</li>\r\n<li>Should have secured not less than 50% marks or equivalent grade in the previous Board/University Examination.</li>\r\n<li>The annual family income should not exceed Rs. 2 Lakhs.</li>\r\n<li>Should not be availing any other Scholarship or Stipend.</li>\r\n\r\n', '<li>Attested copy of mark list of SSLC, attested by a Gazetted Officer</li><br>\r\n<li>Attested copy of the first page of the bank passbook in the name of the student, showing account number, name, code, etc attested by a Gazetted Officer</li><br>\r\n<li>Nativity Certificate</li><br>\r\n<li>Certificate from the Local Body to establish that the applicant belongs to the BPL category</li><br>\r\n<li>Income Certificate</li><br>\r\n<li>Copy of the Mark list of Qualifying Examination attested by a Gazetted Officer</li><br>\r\n<li>Community Certificate for SC/ST applicants</li><br>\r\n<li>Documents in support of excellence in Arts/Sports at State/National levels, attested by a Gazetted Officer</li><br>\r\n<li>Disability Certificate in case of candidates of the PWD category</li>\r\n', '<li>Hit the below âClick here & applyâ button</li>\r\n<li>Read the scholarship details carefully</li>\r\n<li>Fill out the form & attach the necessary documents</li>\r\n<li>submit</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1250', '[\"Class 12\",\"ITI\",\"Bachelors\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"11th, 12th , ITI, Diploma, Undergraduate \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 200000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-20', '2023-06-20', 'Government Of Kerala', 1250.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-03 17:25:28', 1, 'nikhil@triwits.com', '2023-05-20 09:50:05', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1764, 'm4oxdGGo3pyw6e07or', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Goi Peace Foundation International Essay Contest ', 'https://goipeace-essaycontest.org/individuals-registration/', '', '', '', '', '', '  This annual essay contest is organized in an effort to harness the energy, creativity and initiative of the worldâs youth in promoting a culture of peace and sustainable development. It also aims to inspire society to learn from the young minds and to think about how each of us can make a difference in the world.</br>\r\n<b>âYouth Creating a Peaceful Futureâ</b></br>\r\n<li> What does a peaceful world look like to you? How can young people work together, using creative ideas and approaches to realize a peaceful future? Please share your specific ideas.</br></br>\r\n', '', '<li> Before you register, please read the contest guidelines and FAQs carefully.</br>\r\n<li> Create your essay file in either MS Word (DOC/DOCX) or PDF format. Your essay file size must be 2MB or less. Your essay must be typed, with your name and essay title at the top of the first page.</br>\r\n<li> Go to either âIndividualâ or âSchool/Organizationâ Entrant Registration page.</br>\r\n<li> After entering all required information, click âSUBMITâ button at the bottom of the page to create an account.</br>\r\n<li> When your account is successfully created, you will be automatically logged in to âMy Accountâ.</br>\r\n<li> For âINDIVIDUALâ: In âMy Accountâ, click âAdd Essayâ on the side menu, attach your essay by selecting the file on your computer, and click âSUBMITâ. Only one entry per person is accepted. Once your entry is successfully submitted, you can download your certificate from the âDownload Certificateâ.</br>\r\n<li> For âSCHOOL/ORGANIZATIONâ: In âMy Accountâ, click âAdd Studentâ on the side menu, register one student per row, attach each essay by selecting the file on your computer, and click âSUBMIT.â Only one entry per person is accepted. Once your entry is successfully submitted, you can download your studentsâ certificates from the âStudent Listâ and your certificate from the âTeacherâs Certificate of Participationâ on the side menu.</br>\r\n<li> If you leave âMy Accountâ page, you can log in again with your email address and password from âEntrant loginâ on the top menu.</br>\r\n<li> Please note that you can only create one account with one email address.</br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '100,000 Yen', '[\"Primary\",\"Secondary\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Primary, Secondary\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-03', '2023-06-15', 'Goi Peace Foundation', 100000.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-03 17:35:12', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 03:44:31', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1765, 'KLJ91mfxsVm7gIZuwj', 'Competitions and Awards', 'HUMANITY  WORLD PHOTOGRAPHY COMPETITION', 'https://7cg3ksoj.paperform.co/', '', '', '', '', '', ' This international photo contest allows photographers worldwide to show their best work and impression of their lives. There is no theme for this competition. </br><li> Photographers can enter 1-3 images into any category: portrait, object, travel, architecture, design, sport, culture, creative, and landscape, lifestyle, nature or world life. Best winners will an award certificate.</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b></br>\r\n <li> This is an international competition, and it is open to all artists around the globe.</br>\r\n<li> Photographs are acceptable. Entries must be original works of art.</br>', '', '<li> Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button</br>\r\n<li> Read the information details carefully</br>\r\n<li> Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents</br>\r\n<li> Submit</br></br>\r\n', 'Digital Award Certificate', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-04-30', '2023-05-25', 'Humanity World Photography ', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 10:00:00', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 04:41:49', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1766, 'v23udJoT4bGTFQL9VS', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Patenti Technology Solutions', 'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd_nXumMmlj6L4SCoC7kuaMlovNfrfSFEnG0-HlHkrSfyfBsg/viewform', '', '', '', '', '', 'Patenti Technology Solutions is a startup in the niche sector of Intellectual Property Tools.</br>\r\n<li> We are developing an IP Tool Powered by AI. We envision to provide enriched insights on intellectual property for attorneys, corporate researchers and inventors.</br>\r\n<li> Patenti Technology Solutions seeks to celebrate World IP Day 2023 with an Essay Writing Competition.</br></br>\r\n<b>Topic for Essay:</b>âWhy is Intellectual \r\n  Property important to me?â</br>\r\n<li> This topic seeks to encourage the participants to \r\n  engage in out-of-box thinking and share what \r\n  Intellectual Property means to the writerâs daily life.</br>\r\n<li> Essays can include your personal journey and use \r\n  your literary or artistic work such as poems, short \r\n  stories, drawings or music composition to illustrate \r\n  what IP means to you.</br>\r\n<li> To help get an understanding about IP entities that \r\n  we engage with in everyday life but are oblivious, \r\n  please read the following publication.</br></br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b></br>\r\n<li> First Prize: Digital equipment or Amazon Gift card of maximum value of INR. 7500</br>\r\n<li> Second Prize: Digital equipment or Amazon Gift card of maximum value of INR. 5000</br>\r\n<li> The winning essays will have an opportunity to be published and featured on âBlogsâ section of Patenti Technology Solutions website as well as their LinkedIn/social media pages.</br>\r\n<li> The published essays will be credited to the writer as the author in its entirety</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibilities:</b></br>\r\n<li> The essay to be submitted in English language.</br>\r\n<li> The essay can include your personal journey and use your previous literary or artistic work such as poems, short stories, drawings or music composition to illustrate what IP means to you.</br>\r\n<li> The writer/ creator holds all the rights to submit the essay.</br>\r\n<li> Your writeup must not have been previously published online besides your own personal blog, nor have been recognized and/or awarded in another competition.</br>\r\n<li> The essay does not violate any copyright, trademarks, patents, trade secrets, industrial designs, distinctive signs, contractual obligations, or any other intellectual property rights, or other proprietary rights of any third party</br>\r\n<li> ChapGPT or similar Generative AI tools not to be used for composing the essay</br></br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n', '', '<li> Fill the form.</br>\r\n<li> Attach your essay and a short introduction of writer(as PDF file).</br>\r\n<li> Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button.</br>\r\n<li> Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents.</br>\r\n<li> Submit</br></br>\r\n', ' 7500', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-04-30', '2023-05-14', 'Patenti Technology Solutions ', 7500.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 10:45:16', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 05:46:44', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1767, 'v1J5pg0kEsyes28b1u', 'Competitions and Awards', 'ODOP Wall Grand Challenge', 'https://www.mygov.in/task/odop-wall-grand-challenge/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The One District One Product (ODOP) is aimed at manifesting the vision of the Honâble Prime Minister of India to foster balanced regional development across all districts of the country and to select, brand, and promote One Product from each District (One District â One Product) of the country for enabling holistic socio-economic growth across all regions.</br>\r\n<li> The Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT), in collaboration with MyGov, plans to host âODOP Wall Grand Challengeâ to highlight the unique crafts/products of India and its diversity to the world, promote Make in India and AtmaNirbhar Bharat.</br>\r\n<li> We seek to invite innovative ideas from individuals, startups, and other enterprises to design the designated space for the ODOP Wall on the theme of âNew Indiaâ.</br>\r\n<li> âNew Indiaâ is a term to describe the vision of a modern, developed, and prosperous India which aims to unveil the diverse cultural heritage and propel the idea of âHamari Sanskriti, Hamari Virasatâ to the global community.</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b></br>\r\n<li> All participants are to keep the theme in mind while submitting their designs.</br>\r\n<li> Keeping the idea of inclusivity in mind, the participants have to incorporate ODOP-identified products in their designs. The ODOP Product list can be accessed here.</br>\r\n<li> The specifications of the Wall are as follows:</br>\r\n      1. Height- 12 feet.</br>\r\n      2. Breadth- 10 feet 11 inches.</br></br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b></br>\r\n<li> The Selected Design will be rewarded with a Cash Prize of â¹ 2,00,000/-</br>\r\n<li> The Selected Design will be used at Vanijya Bhawan, Ministry of Commerce and Industry.</br></br>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n ', '', '<li> Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button.</br>\r\n<li> Read the details carefully.</br>\r\n<li> Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents.</br>\r\n<li> Submit.</br></br>\r\n', '2,00,000', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-04-30', '2023-05-10', 'One District One Product (ODOP)', 200000.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 11:29:45', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 06:09:43', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1768, 'zroBepGewUEgXWeEWo', 'Abroad', 'Boustany MBA Harvard Scholarship', 'http://www.boustany-foundation.org/', '', '', '', '', 'https://youtu.be/b-ULcSi_DYY', 'One of the top business programmes in the world is the Harvard MBA, which is offered at one of the most respected universities in the world. Once every two years, the Boustany MBA Harvard Scholarship is awarded for a two-year programme at Harvard Business School.\r\n <li>The following are included in the Scholarship:</li> \r\n<li> Financial assistance covering 75% of the cost of education</li>\r\n <li>Travel and lodging costs associated with the internship</li><br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b>\r\n<li>Candidates must have an excellent academic background and show considerable promise</li>\r\n<li>Candidates may apply for the Scholarship only after receiving an offer of admission from the Harvard MBA program</li>\r\n<li>GMAT scores as optional may be consider</li>\r\n<li>Interview: Shortlisted candidates may be invited to an interview with the Foundation</li><br><br><br>\r\nContact Details: admissions@boustany-foundation.org\r\n', '', '<li>Hit the below âLogin & Applyâ button</li>\r\n<li>Read the scholarship details carefully</li>\r\n<li>Fill out the form & attach the necessary documents</li>\r\n<li>Submit</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '$55,080 \r\n', '[\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"\\\"MBA\\\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-03', '2023-05-31', ' United States India Educational Foundation(USEIF)', 0.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 12:34:55', 1, 'aishwaryapatil@triwits.com', '2023-05-13 07:26:29', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1769, 'S8AZYAeWUOiPxYhIeo', 'Competitions and Awards', 'James Dyson Award', 'https://www.jamesdysonaward.org/en-in/register/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Design something that solves a problem. This problem may be a frustration that all people face in daily life, or a global issue. The important thing is that the solution is effective and demonstrates considered design thinking</br></br>\r\n<b> Process:</b></br>\r\n<li> Entries are judged first at the national level by a panel of external judges and a Dyson engineer. </br>\r\n<li> Each operating market awards a national winner and two National runners-up. From these winners, a panel of Dyson engineers then select an international shortlist of 20 entries</br>\r\n<li> The top 20 projects are then reviewed by Sir James Dyson who selects his international winners.</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria:</b></br> \r\n<li> Entrants must be, or have been within the last four years, enrolled for at least one semester in an undergraduate or graduate engineering/design related course</br>\r\n<li> This course must be at a university in a country or region chosen to participate in the James Dyson Award</br>\r\n<li> In the case of team entries, all members must be or have been within the last four years, enrolled for at least one semester in an undergraduate or graduate programme at a university in a country or region chosen to participate in the James Dyson Award.</br>\r\n<li> At least one team member must have studied an eligible subject in engineering or design.</br>\r\n<li> Those participating in a degree level apprenticeship at Level 6 or Level 7, and those who have completed said apprenticeship in the past four years, are eligible to enter the award.</br>', '', '<li> Candidates enter through an online application form via the James Dyson Award website</br>\r\n<li> Entrants should explain what their invention is, how it works, and their development process </br>\r\n<li> The best entries solve a real problem, are clearly explained, show iterative development, provide evidence of prototyping and have supporting imagery and a video</br></br>', 'Â£30,000', '[\"Engineering\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduate or Graduate Engineering or Design related course\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-04', '2023-06-19', 'James Dyson Award', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 12:36:39', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 09:16:19', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1770, 'Q5W7VUhG6fZM2WVk4P', 'Scholarship', 'Raman Kant Munjal Scholarship 2023', 'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfNm8zbrNsc7gTl-e02SjoxpEy44_xObORw6TyyojTgrwEoWw/viewform', '', '', '', '', '', 'Raman Kant Munjal Scholarship Foundation 2023 combining Hero Fin Group invites all the eligible candidates for Raman Kant Munjal Scholarship 2023-23. Raman Kant Munjal Scholarship is for the class 12th passed students. RKM is a 12th-pass scholarship offered with the purpose to help meritorious students who are in need of money to pursue their higher education. The selected students will be getting a scholarship up to INR 5 lakh per year for 3 years<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b>\r\n<li>Applicants must be class 12th passed out.12th pass scholarship<br>\r\n<li>Age should be 19 years as of 31/05/2020<br>\r\n<li>Family income must be less than INR 4 lakh P/ A<br>\r\n<li>Must have scored a minimum of 80% marks in class 10th and 12th<br>\r\n<b>Selection Criteria </b>\r\n<li>Filling out the correct application form<br>\r\n<li>Career assessment test<br>\r\n<li>Filling essay form defining your needs<br>\r\n<li>Full document list<br>\r\n<li>Final interview round (telephonic or interview)<br>', '<li>Class 12th Mark sheet<br>\r\n<li>Aadhar Card<br>\r\n<li>Parents\' PAN Card/Aadhar Card<br>\r\n<li>College Acceptance letter or Bonafide Certificate<br>\r\n<li>Income Certificate<br>\r\n<li>Bank statement of the parent<br>\r\n<li>Affidavit justifying true information<br>', '<li>Visit the official website and fill out the form online<br>\r\n<li>Fill in all the details which are mandatory on www.vidhyaa.in scholarship<br>\r\n<li>Submit your form online<br>', '50000.00', '[\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"\\\"12TH PASS STUDENTS\\\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 400000.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-04', '2023-11-30', 'Raman Kant Munjal ', 50000.00, 'aishwaryapatil@triwits.com', '2023-05-04 17:19:22', 1, 'humera@triwits.com ', '2023-05-15 10:21:59', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1771, 't0oofbqEWzlqhtu6hI', 'Abroad', 'Fulbright Nehru Masters Fellowships by USIEF ', 'https://apply.iie.org/apply/?sr=b29b205d-36bc-44e5-8e02-1d3e90c567a4', '', '', '', '', '', 'Fulbright-Nehru Masterâs Fellowships by USIEF is given to the most outstanding students, academics, and professionals in India and the U.S. to study, research and teach in the host country. Indian scholars are selected through a strict application and interview process. Once selected, awardees receive support navigating the visa processing and securing health insurance and a comprehensive pre-departure orientation.\r\n<li>This scholarship program is offered in the areas of Arts & Culture Management, Economics, Environmental Science/Studies, Higher Education Administration, International Affairs, International Legal Studies, Journalism & Mass Communication, Public Administration, Public Health, Urban and Regional Planning and Womenâs Studies/Gender Studies.</li><br><br><br>\r\ncontact: masters@usief.org.in', '<li>Attach your resume</li>\r\n<li>scanned copies of your mark sheets or transcripts and diploma/degree certificates from bachelorâs degree</li>\r\n<li>Attach your study/research objectives</li>\r\n<li>Attach personal statement</li>\r\n<li>Attach writing sample</li>\r\n<li>Attach passport copy </li>\r\n<li>Attach pdf copy of FNMasters Applicant Annexure </li>\r\n<li>Attach scanned photocopies of proof of your work/professional experience </li>\r\n<li>Attach portfolio, if applicable </li>\r\n<li>Attach FNMasterâs employerâs endorsement </li>   ', '<li>Hit on \"Click here & apply\" button</li>\r\n<li>Please carefully review the FNMaster\'s Applicant Instructions before starting your online application</li>\r\n<li>Please refer to FNMaster\'s Applicant Checklist before submitting the application</li>\r\n\r\n', '$20000', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Phd\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-07', '2023-05-17', ' United States- India Educational Foundation(USEIF)', 0.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-05 11:17:19', 1, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-06 06:21:10', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1772, 'fTvAJTgAX9MsOj3ohY', 'Abroad', 'Fulbright Kalam Climate Fellowships for Doctoral Research', 'https://apply.iie.org/ffsp2024/', '', '', '', '', '', 'USIEF administers the Fulbright-Kalam Climate Fellowships to build long-term capacity to address climate change-related issues in India and the U.S. The objective is to promote further mutual understanding between the two peoples by a wider exchange of knowledge and professional talents â intend to partner to build long-term capacity in the United States and India by engaging scientific and technical research scholars from both countries related to climate research and education.<br><br><br>\r\n<b> Benefits</b>\r\n<li>The fellowships provide J-1 visa support</li>\r\n <li>A monthly stipend, Accident and Sickness Program for Exchanges per U.S. Government guidelines</li>\r\n <li>Round-trip economy class air travel</li>\r\n<li>Applicable allowances and modest affiliation fees, if any </li>\r\n<li> Selected scholars will have opportunities to audit non-degree courses</li>\r\n <li>conduct research and gain practical work experience in suitable settings in the U.S. </li>\r\n<li> No allowances are provided for dependents. The grant is not sufficient to support family members.</li><br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Eligibility</b>\r\n<li>Applicants registered for their Ph.D. should have conducted adequate research in the relevant field, especially in the identification of resources in India and the U.S. Applicant must be registered for a Ph.D. at an Indian institution on or before November 1, 2022. On the online application form, one of the recommendations should be from the Ph.D. supervisor that comments on the applicantâs research, the need for the fellowship, and must indicate the Ph.D. registration date and topic.</li>\r\n<li>This grant is intended for Ph.D. students to conduct research essential to their dissertations/thesis. Therefore, the expected Ph.D. thesis submission date should at least be three months after the Fulbright-Kalam grant end date. For example, if May 2025 is the grant end date, the applicant cannot submit his/her thesis before August 2025. Please indicate the Ph.D. registration date and the expected Ph.D. thesis submission date in the Applicant Annexure. The applicant can download the Applicant Annexure from the supplemental forms section of the online application. </li>\r\n<li>If the applicant is employed, she/he must follow the instructions carefully regarding employerâs endorsement. If applicable, the applicant must obtain the endorsement from the appropriate administrative authority on the âEmployerâs Endorsement Form.The employer must indicate that leave will be granted for the fellowship period. </li>\r\n<li>The applicant must upload a copy of original published/presented paper or extracts from the Mastersâ/M.Phil. thesis in the online application form (not exceeding 20 pages). </li><br><br>\r\nIf you have any questions, please write to dr-climate@usief.org.in\r\n\r\n', '<li>curriculum vitae/resume</li>\r\n<li>study/research objectives</li>\r\n <li>personal statement </li>\r\n<li> scanned copies of your mark sheets and diploma/degree certificates</li>\r\n<li>Ph.D. registration certificate</li>\r\n <li> writing sample</li>\r\n <li> three reference letters </li>\r\n<li>letter(s) of invitation from the U.S. host institution </li>\r\n<li>employerâs endorsement, if employed </li>\r\n<li> FK-DR applicant annexure </li>\r\n<li>additional documentation</li>\r\n', '<li>Hit on Click here & apply.</li>\r\n<li>Please carefully review the Ful-bright climate Applicant Instructions before starting your online application.</li>\r\n<li>Please refer to Ful-bright climate Applicant Checklist before submitting the application.</li>\r\n<li>In addition, you must complete the FK-DR Applicant Annexure and Employerâs Endorsement Form (if applicable) and upload on your online application.</li>\r\n', '$20000', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Phd\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00,