(1816, '6xT3jmAoMuIX7JhzN1', 'Abroad', 'Malaysian International Scholarship by the Malaysian Government ', 'https://biasiswa.mohe.gov.my/INTER/index.php', '', '', '', '', '', ' Malaysian International Scholarship 2023-2024 by the Malaysian Government is an admirable option to explore the wonders of the world in dream-living land. The eligible bright minds are encouraged to become part of this MIS 2023 in Malaysia to learn and expand the horizon of knowledge in their core domains. By attracting, motivating, and retaining the talented pool of candidates in Malaysia through this Malaysian scholarship for international students, the Malaysian Government aspires to emerge as one of the global centers of academic superiority. Therefore, everyone focusing on developing their personalities and professional skills in the dynamic international environment should grab this prospect of success.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits</b> \r\n<li>There are no application fees.\r\n<li>The award will cover full tuition fees.\r\n<li>You will receive a monthly allowance of RM 1,500 per month for the whole tenure.\r\n<li>Your exposure to international dynamics will be enhanced.\r\n<li>You will be honored to study in an international environment.\r\n<li>Your personality and professional skills will be polished.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility </b>\r\n<li>Full-time Masterâs/Ph.D. students are eligible.\r\n<li> You must be a full-time postgraduate student in a Malaysian public or private university that is supported under MIS. You should have at least two semesters left before you complete your studies.\r\n<li>Graduates of developing and under-developed countries can apply.\r\n<li>Age should not be more than 40 to 45 years at the time of application.\r\n<li>Masterâs applicants should possess a CGPA of 3.0 or 2nd class upper honors degree.\r\n<li>PhD applicants should possess a CGPA of 3.0 or excellent academic results during the masterâs degree.\r\n<li>English language proficiency is required. The test score should meet the following criteria:\r\n<li>IELTS: 3.0 bands or higher.\r\n<li>TOEFL: total scores of 550 or higher.\r\n<li>The medium of instruction for a previously acquired degree <li>should be in the English Language.\r\n<li>Write a research proposal with a minimum of 1000 words.<br><br>\r\n<b>Selection Criteria</b>\r\n<li>Competitive ranking.\r\n<li>Good academic record.\r\n<li>Merit-basis.\r\n<li>Quality of research proposal.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Certified copy of passport.\r\n<li>Certified copy of academic transcripts.\r\n<li>English proficiency certificate copy.\r\n<li>Letter of recommendation .\r\n<li>Endorsement form.\r\n<li>Admission letter to Malaysian University.\r\n<li>Detailed CV.\r\n', '<li>Hit the below âClick here & applyâ button\r\n<li>Read the Scholarship details carefully \r\n<li>Fillout the form & attach necessary documents carefully\r\n<li>Submit\r\n', 'RM 18000', '[\"Masters\",\"PHD\"]', 'null', '\"\\\"MA, MSc, MBA, ME, MTech, PHD\\\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-11', '2023-05-18', 'MIS', 0.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-16 11:22:58', 1, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-16 05:54:03', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1817, 'pn4PCNB0Jwq5kBLO98', 'Competitions and Awards', ' India Happiness Photo Contest', 'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdksJZuQYpAEfyx14Ui0gMFrOgRFs9DXugqPGLLNgkPWQJsPg/viewform', '', '', '', '', '', ' With great pleasure, Happiness Strategy Foundation is inviting photography submissions to the second annual India Happiness Photo Contest 2023</br>\r\n<li> The inaugural India Happiness Photo Contest 2022 was conducted successfully last year and resulted in a book India Happiness 2022</br>\r\n<li> Through the contest, we would like to focus on the things that bring happiness to our lives</br>\r\n<li> We all have places, people, hobbies, events, and so on that brings us happiness, and we are inviting you to share these with us through this photography contest</br>\r\n<li> Successful submissions will be published in a virtual coffee table book by the Happiness Strategy Foundation</br>\r\n<li> The Happiness Strategy Foundation is a not-for-profit think tank for research on happiness and well-being and sharing the research findings with masses and industry to make a meaningful contribution to the happiness of India and the world</br>\r\n<li> The winning photos will be selected by a distinguished jury consisting of experts in happiness, design, photography, media and civil society</br></br>\r\n<b>Rules of Participation</b></br>\r\n<li> All submissions must be original and unpublished photos taken by the photographer</br>\r\n<li> All submissions must have necessary information embedded into photographs IPTC like caption (maximum word limit: 10 words), description of why it is a happy photo (maximum word limit: 30 words), creation date</br>\r\n<li> Photography captions and descriptions must be written in English. Kindly check the caption and description limits before sending your photos</br>\r\n<li> Photo specifications:  JPG format. The acceptable compression will not exceed 10. The image is to be no less than 2480 x 3508 pixels (300 dpi)</br>\r\n<li> No signatures, stamps or any other identifying mark is allowed anywhere on the entry</br>\r\n<li> Photographer\'s name or company should not be mentioned in the captions</br>\r\n<li> Photographer will be credited if the photo is published</br>\r\n<li> Digital Manipulation and any kind of Photoshop effects are not allowed; only basic colour corrections are allowed</br>\r\n<li> The file name must contain the full name of the author, state and year it was shot, separated by underscores, for example, Nitish_Kumar_Mumbai_2023</br>\r\n<li> The file size must not exceed 20 Mb. The file must also contain all the EXIF or IPTC data</br>\r\n<li> Photographers must be the copyright owner of the submitted photographs, and photographs must not violate any third party rights</br>\r\n<li> Photographer has the liability for copyrights and non-violation of any third party rights</br>\r\n<li> Photographers need to give an undertaking that this is their original, unpublished work and they have the copyright of the photograph, and they are not violating any third party rights</br>\r\n<li> For this, submit the specified photo copy right release form</br>\r\n<li> Kindly note that organisers may ask for proof of the source of the photo and a brief profile of the photographer, including a photo identity card</br>\r\n<li> The winning photos will be selected by an independent panel consisting of leading experts in happiness, design, photography, media and civil society</br>\r\n<li>  The winning photographers will be informed latest by September 30, 2023</br>\r\n<li> Winning photos will be published in a virtual coffee table book. Photographer will be identified in the publication</br>\r\n<li> Photographs should be submitted via this form: https://forms.gle/GeW7sfN2pYzqxjgH7</br>\r\n<li> The submission of entries for 2023 is open from Feburary 1, 2023 and the last date for submission is August 1, 2023</br></br>\r\n\r\n', '', '<li> Hit the below \" click here to apply \" button</br>\r\n<li> Read the scholarship details carefully</br>\r\n<li> Fill out the form and attach the necessary documents</br>\r\n<li> Submit</br></br>', 'Published in a virtual coffee table book', '[\"All\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"All\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-01', '2023-08-01', 'India Happiness', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-16 15:11:28', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-17 07:27:06', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1818, 'PdxZZ6I0zSvupR2wqO', 'Abroad', 'VAIBHAV Fellowship', 'https://scholarshiparena.in/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/VAIBHAV-Fellowships.pdf', '', '', '', '', '', ' VAIBHAV Fellowship 2023 is an opportunity offered by the Department of Science and Technology, New Delhi to Ph.D/M.D/M.S degree holders</br>\r\n<li> The main aim of this fellowship is to improve the research ecosystem of Indiaâs Higher Educational and Scientific Institutions by facilitating academic and research collaborations between Indian Institutions and the best institutions in the world through mobility of faculty/researcher from overseas institutions to India</br>\r\n<li> The selected candidates will receive USD 5,000 and other benefits</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b></br>\r\n<li> Be Non-Resident Indian (NRI), Persons of Indian Origin (PIO) and Overseas Citizen of India (OCI), currently living abroad</br>\r\n<li> Have obtained Ph.D/M.D/M.S degree from a recognized University</br>\r\n<li> Be a researcher engaged in an overseas academic/research/industrial organization with a proven track record of research & development working in the top 500 QS World University Ranking</br>\r\n<li> Be planning to pursue research work for a minimum of 1 month to a maximum of 2 months a year in a research institution/academic\r\n institution in India, spread over 3 years</br></br>\r\n<b>Benefits</b></br>\r\n<li> A fellowship USD 5,000 (in equivalent Indian currency)</br>\r\n<li> International Travel from the place of their institute to the place of work in India in business class</br>\r\n<li> Accommodation in 3 or 4-star hotel</br>\r\n<li> A contingency INR 1,00,000 per annum</br>\r\n<li> Domestic Travel for academic purposes up to two stations in a year</br></br>\r\n <b>Note - </b>The host institute will receive INR 10,00,000 lakh per year for hosting the scientist and providing office/lab accommodation and facilitation for various infrastructure support</br></br>', '<li> Biodata of Applicant</br>\r\n<li> Age Proof Certificate</br>\r\n<li> Qualification Certificate</br>\r\n<li> Undertaking Certificate by the applicant and NOC from their parent institute</br>\r\n<li> Endorsement Certificate from Host Institute\r\nPlagiarism undertaking</br></br>\r\n ', '<li> Click on the \'Apply Now\' button</br>\r\n<li> Click the \'Register\' button and fill in the required registration details. (Note - If already registered, log in using Gmail/Mobile number/Email Id.)</br>\r\n<li> Navigate to \'Electronic Project Management System (e-PMS)\' at the bottom of the page</br>\r\n<li> Navigate to \'New PI Registration\' and click on it</br>\r\n<li> Fill in the required details and submit to \'Register\'</br>\r\n<li> After successful registration, select the fellowship program and click on it</br>\r\n<li> Fill in the required details, upload the necessary documents and submit</br>', 'USD 5000', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Ph.D. M.D, M.S degree holders\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-01', '2023-07-31', 'VAIBHAV Fellowship', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-17 12:34:51', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-17 07:12:36', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1819, 'fK4pGIyWiZIBeB23la', 'Abroad', 'Schwarzman Scholars Programme', 'https://connect.schwarzmanscholars.org/apply/', '', '', '', '', '', 'Schwarzman Scholars Programme is a fully-funded one-year degree scholarship program that includes travel expenses, full tuition fee, study tours allowance, stipend, personal laptop, allowance for course books, and medical insurance. The age to apply for this scholarship is 18 to 28 years. Both national and international students from all over the world can apply for this scholarship program. The selection process for this Tsinghua University scholarship is very competitive. Candidates who have been chosen are invited to participate in in-person interviews with international panels consisting of prominent individuals such as CEOs, former heads of state, university presidents, non-profit executives, journalists, and other influential leaders from around the world. Those who are applying must have completed an undergraduate degree and must have a good command of English.<br><br>\r\n<b>Benefits:</b>\r\n<li>If selected for an interview, the program will cover your travel expenses such as economy class airfare or train tickets, group meals, and one night of hotel accommodation if necessary.\r\n<b>Scholarship Applicants:</b> Those who are selected will get the fully funded scholarship including the following:\r\n<li>All travel expenses will be covered.\r\n<li>The full tuition fee will be covered throughout the program duration.\r\n<li>Study tours allowance will be provided\r\n<li>A stipend will be provided to the scholar.\r\n<li>A Lenovo laptop will be provided.\r\n<li>An allowance for course books will be covered by the scholarship.\r\n<li>Comprehensive medical insurance will be provided.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b>\r\n<li>All international, as well as Chinese citizens, are eligible to apply.\r\n<li>A candidate must have either bachelorâs or another professional degree.\r\n<li>A candidate must be 18 to 28 years of age.\r\n<li>A