(1820, 'yxvY4mg5EecDL46oSh', 'Abroad', 'SAT Scholarship', 'https://satsuite.collegeboard.org/sat/registration', '', '', '', '', '', ' SAT examination evaluates the studentâs performance on the basis of four parameters</br>\r\n<li> Students who score well in the SAT examination will get scholarships from the universities that made the eligibility conditions</br>\r\n<li> The eligibility criteria to apply for the SAT Scholarship are mentioned below</br>\r\n<li> Under this program students can a full tuition fee scholarship for their graduate program</br>\r\n<li> You may also check the step-by-step instructions to apply for the SAT examination</br></br>\r\n<b>Benefits</b></br>\r\n<li> 50 & 90% SAT Registration fee discount voucher</br>\r\n<li> Students can win full tuition fee scholarship</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b></br>\r\n<li> For a 90% SAT Registration fee discount the students whose family annual income is less than 8 Lakh Rupees are eligible</br>\r\n<li> 50% SAT Registration fee discount for the students whose family annual income is less than 15 Lakh Rupees but more than 8 Lakh Rupees are eligible</br>\r\n<li> For scholarship the applicant should be an Indian</br>\r\n<li> Applicant must be studying in class XI & XII\r\nFamily annual income is less than 8 Lakh Rupees\r\nMust have SAT score of 1300 or higher</br></br>\r\n<b>Selection Procedure</b></br>\r\n<li> Selection for the scholarship will be made by the participating universities offering </br>\r\n<li> scholarships on the basis of SAT Score, academic background, and financial background</br></br>\r\n<b>Family Income</b></br>\r\n<li> For those students, who have a family income less than INR 8 lakh,  College Board has offered complete fee waiver for SAT test-taker</br></br>', '', '<li> Application Procedure for SAT scholarship\r\nTo apply for the SAT scholarship, a separate method is adopted by every participating University</br>\r\n<li> You have to fill out the application by visiting the univer