(1828, 'rSiKtkiepGIMeOkYmY', 'Scholarship', 'PM Scholarship ', 'https://infinitylearn.com/surge/blog/pm-scholarship-2021-eligibility-application-process-documents-required-rewards/', '', '', '', '', '', ' PM Scholarship or Prime Minister Scholarship Scheme (PMSS) is a scholarship scheme that strives at promoting higher professional and technical studies for the dependent wards and widows of Central Armed Police Forces & Assam Rifles (CAPFs & AR) and State Police Personnel</br>\r\n<li> Initiated in the year 2006-07, this scheme is run by the Welfare and Rehabilitation Board, Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India. This scheme has by far affected lakhs of students and helped many of them pursue their dream careers easily</br>\r\n<li> The Government of India (GOI) has recently introduced major changes in the scholarship by revising the scholarship reward amount for girls from Rs.2,250 to Rs.3,000 per month and for boys from Rs.2,000 to Rs.2,500 per month</br>\r\n<li> Additionally, 500 new scholarships will also be given to the wards of State Police officials who were martyred in terror or Naxal attacks.</br>\r\n<li> Under PM Modi Scholarship Scheme, 25000 Rs scholarship offering to 10th or 12th pass students by Narendra Modi. PM Scholarship Scheme for 12th pass students is Rs. 25000</br>\r\n<li> PM Scholarship Scheme for 10th pass students is Rs. 25000. Now let us know the benefits offered to students under the PM scholarship</br>\r\n<li> PM Scholarship renewalâs last date in 2022 was 15 November 2022. Also, with that, we will see here the eligibility criteria, application procedure and other related details in this article</br>\r\n<li> The Government of India has recently approved major changes in the scholarship by revising the scholarship amount for girls from INR 2,250 to INR 3,000 per month and scholarship amount for boys from INR 2,000 to INR 2,500 per month</br>\r\n<li> Adding to this, 500 new scholarships will also be given to the wards of State Police officials who are/were martyred in Naxal or terror attacks</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b></br>\r\n<li> Candidate should be a dependent ward/widow of deceased CAPFs & AR/ Ex-CAPFs & AR/ retired and serving CAPFs & AR/ State Police Personnel</br>\r\n<li> The candidate should be pursuing professional courses. (Not applicable for lateral entry and integrated courses)</\'br>\r\n<li> The minimum education qualification to apply for these courses should be class 12/ diploma/ graduation</br>\r\n<li> The candidates should have secured at least 60% marks or above in the minimum educational qualification. (For renewal in subsequent years, the Candidates need to obtain at least 50% marks in the qualifying examination)</br>\r\n<li> As per the latest decision made by the Government of India, the scholarship scheme will also cover the wards of State Police officials who are/were martyred during Naxal/terror attacks</br>\r\n<li> A total of Rs.500 scholarships in a year will be given to the wards of State Police officials.\r\nWards of Civilians including Para-Military Personnel are NOT ELIGIBLE</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligible Courses</b></br>\r\n<li> First Professional Degree Courses like BE, B.Tech, BDS, MBBS, B.Ed, B.B.A, BCA, B.Pharma, etc. duly recognized by the respective Government Regulatory Bodies, such as All India Council for Technical Education, Medical Council of India, UGC, etc</br>\r\n<li> Master Degree Courses are not eligible for PMSS except MBA / MCA Courses</br>\r\n<li> Students studying abroad are not eligible for this scheme. No distance learning course is permitted under PMSS. PMSS can be availed for ONE COURSE only</br></br>\r\n<b>Rewards</b></br>\r\n<li> The amount of which candidate will receive under the Prime Minister Scholarship Scheme and for how many years the scholarships will be disbursed are the necessary details a candidate should know</br>\r\n<li> A total of 5500 eligible candidates get benefit under this scheme every year. And these scholarships are equally distributed among boys and girls, i.e. 2750 each</br>\r\n<li> Besides, the amount of the scholarship offered to girls is Rs.3000 per month and to boys is Rs.2500 per month, every year</br>\r\n<li> Moreover, the duration of the scholarship may differ from one year to five years depending on your course span</br></br>\r\n<b>Selection Criteria</b></br>\r\n<li> Category A: The first preference is given to the wards and widows of CAPFs & AR personnel who were killed in action</br>\r\n<li> Category B: The second preference is given to the wards of Ex-CAPFs & AR personnel who got disabled in action</br>\r\n<li> Category C: The third preference is given to the wards and widows of deceased CAPFs & AR personnel who died during their service for causes attributable to Government service</br>\r\n<li> Category D: The next preference is given to the wards of Ex-CAPFs & AR personnel who got disabled during their service with disability attributable to Government service</br>\r\n<li> Category E: Further, the preference is given to the wards of Ex-CAPFs & AR personnel who have received gallantry awards</br>\r\n<li> Category F: The next preference is given to the wards of Ex-CAPFs & AR personnel (PBOR only)</br>\r\n<li>Category G: Lastly, the preference will be given to the wards of serving CAPFs & AR personnel (PBOR) subject to the availability of the scholarship</br></br>', '<li> Serving Certificate (in case of serving personnel) issued by HOO</br>\r\n<li> Certificate issued by the concerned state government indicating that the State Police personnel was killed in Naxal /Terror attacks</br>\r\n<li> Certificate of Minimum Educational Qualification (MEQ) as applicable â Class 12th mark sheet, Graduation mark sheet (for all years) or diploma mark sheets (for all semesters)\r\nPPO/Discharge Certificate/Book (Mandatory for Category A to F)</br>\r\n<li> Disability Certificate (Applicable for disabled personnel)</br>\r\n<li> Certificate of Gallantry Award (Applicable for Gallantry Award winners)</br></br>', '<li> Visit the official website</br>\r\n<li> Click on the âNew Registrationâ link</br>\r\n<li> Read the application guidelines carefully and click on continue to proceed</br>\r\n<li> Fill in all required details and click on âRegisterâ</br>\r\n<li> After getting registered the user id and password will be generated on your mobile number</br></br>', ' 2750', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Bachelors,  MBA or MCA \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-07-16', '2023-10-31', ' Welfare and Rehabilitation Board', 2750.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 09:47:17', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 04:58:17', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1829, '0hZfheeG4yPX9BLhWB', 'Competitions and Awards', 'Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam IGNITE', 'https://nif.org.in/submitidea.php', '', '', '', '', '', ' There are many such students who are talented but they can not get the platform. Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam IGNITE Award 2023  is given for such students who have the potential to change their thoughts</br>\r\n<li> Let us tell you that this scholarship award is given by the National Innovation Foundation NIF).</br>\r\n<li> If you want to apply for this award then the application form will be filled and sent</br>\r\n<li> The National Innovation Foundation asks students to submit their new technical ideas and then the ideas are tested and honored</br>\r\n<li> The participants can submit their ideas through photos/videos/ sketches</br>\r\n<li> The basic purpose of Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam IGNITE Award 2023  competition is to develop the spirit of innovation and creativity within the students</br>\r\n<li> Students selected in this competition are given the rank of the inventor of the idea by the National Innovation Foundation</br>\r\n<li> National Innovation Foundation is a part of the Department of Science and Technology of the Government of India, which organizes this competition every year in the whole country</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria </b></br>\r\n<li> Students up to the Class 12th can participate in this Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Ignite Award</br>\r\n<li> The candidateâs age should not be more than 17 years</br>\r\n<li> Students from any background viz. arts, commerce, etc. can participate in the competition</br>\r\n<li> Candidates can submit as many as you can enter to participate in the competition</br></br>\r\n<b> Benefits </b></br>\r\n<li> All practical and useful ideas/innovations may be given financial and mentoring support</br>\r\n<li> In the case of deserving cases, patents will be filed in their name at no cost to them</br>\r\n<li> It is also possible that some of the ideas might attract entrepreneurs and these may get licensed for monetary consideration</br>\r\n<li> The candidates who submit maximum properly documented entries will be awarded Appreciation Certificates</br>\r\n<li> Each innovation or traditional knowledge practice spotted and documented by them will be credited as being the Scout of a particular innovation or traditional knowledge in the record</br>\r\n<li> Only awarded entries or projects or innovations will be shown in the exhibition</br>\r\n<li> The award will be given at the Indian Institute of Management Ahmedabad</br>\r\n<li> National Innovation announces the names of the winning students by October</br></br>\r\n<b>Selection Criteria</b></br>\r\n<li> From all the received entries, the selected entries will be estimated by a group of experts and Honey Bee Network Collaborators</br>\r\n<li> All the estimation will be done on the basis of information filled by the candidates in the application form and from the entry</br>\r\n<li> The students will be contacted by phone/email, if at the time of the screening process, in case additional information is required</br></br>', '', '<li> First of all, go to the official website</br>\r\n<li>The homepage of the website will open on the screen</br>\r\n<li> Click on Apply Here link</br>\r\n<li> Once you will click on the link, a new page will open on the screen</br>\r\n<li> After that click on the Click here to Register link</br></br>\r\n', 'Certificate, Travel allowance to attend Exhibition and other Recognitions', '[\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 12\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-01', '2023-08-30', 'National Innovation Foundation (NIF)', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 09:58:28', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-20 06:43:40', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1830, 'x40LyzaMFMxpttZGlv', '', ' Nirankari Rajmata', 'NIRANKARI RAJMATA SCHOLARSHIP SCHEME 2023-24', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Sant Nirankari Charitable Foundation introduced Nirankari Rajmata Scholarship Scheme to provide financial assistance to students who wants to study higher education. The Nirankari Scholarship Scheme helps Meritorious Students to pursue Professional and Technical Courses for Graduation and Post-Graduation levels and those who excel in sports and cultural activities at State/National Level. Nirankari Scholarship For Meritorious Students 2023-24 is a âMerit-Cum-Meansâ scholarship. 50% of Scholarships are reserved for girls students.\r\nBENEFITS \r\nAll the shortlisted students will receive scholarship amount from Sant Nirankari Charitable Foundation. Selected students will get tuition fee for that year. One student can get tuition fee upto Rs. 50,000 per year. Or Foundation will pay your full course fee, if it is lesser.\r\n\r\nELIGIBILITY CRITERIA \r\nCandidate must be a regular students of any Institution/College recognized by Central/State Government, admitted through a competitive written test.\r\nFamily annual income of applicant from all sources must be less than Rs. 3.50 Lakh per annum.\r\nStudents have to scored at least 75% marks every year to continue scholarship.\r\nApplicant must have at least 90% marks in 12th Examination.\r\nStudent must studying in one out of all following courses :\r\nGraduate Degree in Medicine in Allopathic and/or Ayurvedic and/or Homeopathic.\r\nGraduate Degree in any discipline of Engineering.\r\n MBA/PGDM.\r\n Architecture.\r\nChartered Accountancy after qualifying CPT conducted by Institutions of Chartered Accountants of India.\r\nCFA after qualifying Foundation Test.\r\nLLB after passing Entrance Test for LLB or after qualifying Degree Exams.\r\nSELECTION PROCESS OF NIRANKARI SCHOLARSHIP 2023-24\r\nAll the students will selected by official authority after checking all application forms. The selection process of Nirankari Rajmata Scholarship depends on candidatesâ financial need and capability to pursue the relevant course. Only selected students will receive scholarship amount.\r\n', 'A fully filled and affixed photographed application form in prescribed format for each academic year.\r\nCopy of the family Income Certificate issued by the Area SDM or Tehsildar or BDO.\r\nAdmission Slip/letter by which the applicant has been offered admission by the University/Educational Institution.\r\nMark Sheets of all previous academic qualifications.\r\nCopy of latest fee receipts issued by the University/Institutes.\r\nCopy of results of all semestersâ examinations passed.\r\nDetails of the fee including Tuition Fee, Library, Hostel, Books etc. duly signed by the Principal/Administrator of the Institute may be attached with the application.\r\nCopy of Ration Card / Aadhar Card / Voter I-Card / Passport / Pan-Card.\r\nCopy of passbook of saving bank account of applicant.', 'NIRANKARI RAJMATA SCHOLARSHIP SCHEME 2023-24', 'NIRANKARI RAJMATA SCHOLARSHIP SCHEME 2023-24', 'null', NULL, '\"\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-18', '2023-09-18', 'Sant Nirankari Charitable Foundation ', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 10:21:25', 1, NULL, '2023-05-18 04:51:25', 0, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1831, 'ofc2mL8g1VBnaZ5VKE', 'Competitions and Awards', 'SOF International Commerce Olympiad', 'https://sofworld.org/ico', '', '', '', '', '', ' SOF International Commerce Olympiad (ICO) 2023-24 is an opportunity offered by the Science Olympiad Foundation (SOF)* in partnership with the Institute of Company Secretaries of India (a statutory body under an Act of Parliament, under the administrative control of The Ministry of Corporate Affairs)</br>\r\n<li> Students of Classes 11 and 12 are eligible to participate. It is a single-level examination conducted every year in which the students showcase their talent at the school level, zonal level, and international level. The selected students stand a chance to get up to INR 1,00,000 and other benefits</br>\r\n<li> SOF is an educational organization that was established to promote Science, Mathematics, Computer Education, English, Social Studies, General Knowledge and professional courses.</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b></br>\r\n<li> Be a student of Class 11 or 12</br></br>\r\n<b>Benefits</b></br>\r\nAt the international level - </br>\r\n<li> A total of two awards of INR 1,00,000 each, a gold medal and a certificate of outstanding performance to first-rank holders</br>\r\n<li> A total of two awards of INR 75,000 each, a silver medal and a certificate of outstanding performance to second-rank holders</br>\r\n<li> A total of two awards of INR 50,000 each, a bronze medal, and a certificate of outstanding performance to third rank holders</br>\r\n<li> A total of two awards of INR 25,000 each, a medal of distinction, and a certificate of outstanding performance to fourth-rank holders</br>\r\n<li> A total of two awards of INR 10,000 each, a medal of distinction, and a certificate of outstanding performance to fifth-rank holders</br>\r\n<b>Note - </b></br>\r\n<li> In case two or more students achieve the same international rank, cash award in the applicable category will be distributed as under:\r\nFor up to 10 students getting the same rank, the award amount will be distributed equally</br>\r\n<li> Each winner will be awarded a medal (in the applicable category) and a certificate</br>\r\n<li> In case 11 or more students get the same rank, in lieu of a cash award, each winner will be awarded gifts worth INR 1,000 each and a medal (in the applicable category) and a certificate</br></br>', '', '<li> First of all, go to the official website</br>\r\n<li> The homepage of the website will open on the screen</br>\r\n<li> Click on Apply Here link</br>\r\n<li> Once you will click on the link, a new page will open on the screen</br>\r\n<li> After that click on the Click here to Register link</br></br>', '1,00,000', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', 'null', '\"Class 11 and 12 students\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-30', '2024-01-03', ' Science Olympiad Foundation (SOF)', 100000.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 11:05:36', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-19 08:01:37', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1832, 'L1CRTnblFD8s9xDL9j', 'Abroad', 'FIG Foundation PhD Scholarships', 'http://www.fig.net/figfoundation/index.asp', '', '', '', '', '', 'The FIG Foundation is a non-profit organization that aims to provide support for the education and professional growth of surveyors and other related professionals around the world.The primary objective of the foundation is to advance the quality of surveying education and research while also promoting the utilization of surveying as a means of addressing global issues. <br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b> \r\n<li>Be enrolled in a surveying/geomatics academic program in a country that the World Bank categorizes as a low-income, lower-middle, or upper-middle income economy, be pursuing a Ph.D. degree, have a paper accepted by an international peer-reviewed journal that centers on their doctoral research project \r\n<li>have not submitted their final thesis by the scholarship application deadline.\r\n<li>Its specific goals are to facilitate academic research and training, foster international partnerships, and improve societyâs comprehension and utilization of surveying and geospatial information.\r\n\r\n', '<li>A completed check list. This checklist is provided at the end of this document and you should use this to check that all documents are included in your application and also include the checklist in your submission. Note that if one item on the checklist is missing or disqualifies the candidate, the application is unlikely to be considered.\r\n<li>A cover sheet showing the candidateâs personal details and those of his/her institution.\r\n<li>A brief description and argument as to how the applicantâs academic programme addresses the âteaches surveying and graduates surveyorsâ component of Qualification Criterion 1 above. Provide web links to programme descriptions, course outlines and details of courses.\r\n<li>A 200 word abstract. This should be written in terms understandable to the lay person; similar to a press release and which the FIG Foundation could actually use as a press release in the event of a successful application.\r\n<li>A one page research proposal as per the template below on A4 size paper. Note that the one page limit will be strictly enforced; material that extends beyond one page will be deleted.\r\n<li>For the paper accepted by a peer reviewed international journal based on their doctoral research project, provide a copy of the paper that was re-submitted to the journal after corrections have been completed, or submit the published paper.\r\n<li>A letter from the editor of the journal indicating that the paper has been accepted and that the necessary corrections have been completed satisfactorily.\r\n<li>The journalâs  refereesâ reports for the paper.\r\n<li>A list of peer reviewed journal publications over the last 6 years using the International Journal of GIS (IJGIS) reference list format. Use the following headings: Peer Reviewed Journal Papers, Peer Reviewed Conference Papers, Non- Peer Reviewed Conference Papers, Non- Peer Reviewed Journal  Papers, Books, Book Chapters and so forth. See Notes for Authors on the IJGIS website.\r\n<li>A list of research funding obtained over the past 5 years, indicating which grants are peer reviewed or not.\r\n<li>A description of research compliance, the research account and activity auditing structures and processes in their institution. For example, if a scientist spends money inappropriately, are there structures in place to refund the granting agency? Provide the names and web addresses of the administration departments and official organisation descriptions dealing with research compliance.\r\n<li>A description of the structures and processes in their institution that pertain to research ethics, in particular ethics relating to research involving human subjects, if that is relevant to the grant application. Provide the names and web addresses of the administration departments and official organisation descriptions dealing with research compliance.\r\n <li>A budget indicating how the funds will be spent and a one page justification of the budget. Note that as a general rule, equipment will not be funded. Travel to FIG Conferences to present results and tuition fees may be included in the budget. Per diems for field work will not be funded, but reasonable actual costs of field work are refundable.\r\n<li>A brief letter from the applicantâs PhD supervisor indicating that they have read this document, that they confirm that the applicant has viewed the videos on How to Write Grant Proposals to the FIG Foundation, and that they have read the applicantâs proposal and recommend (or not) that the FIG Foundation Board of Directors consider the proposal.\r\n<li>For transparency purposes, successful proposals, granteesâ final reports and progress reports on their activities and use funds will be published on the Foundation web page, and perhaps elsewhere, where appropriate. Please indicate your consent or otherwise for your proposal(s) and reports to be published. Grantees should provide compelling reasons for these documents not to be published.\r\n<li>In a separate PDF document, provide a comprehensive academic CV. Seek advice on what constitutes an academic CV.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '<li>Hit the below âClick here & applyâ button\r\n<li>Read the Scholarship details carefully \r\n<li>Fillout the form & attach necessary documents carefully\r\n<li>Submit\r\n', '3000 Euros ', '[\"PHD\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"PHD\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-03', '2023-06-01', 'FIG foundation', 0.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 11:21:25', 1, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 07:58:56', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1833, 'OqnRg5sEzjDbP7npNe', 'Abroad', 'Full Circle Scholarship', 'https://collegefund.org/students/scholarships/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The American Indian College Fund provides scholarships to American Indian and Alaska Native college students enrolled in certificate, undergraduate, or graduate program at tribal colleges and other nonprofit, accredited schools.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b>\r\n<li>To be eligible, students must be an enrolled member (or a descendant of one) of a federally or state-recognized tribe while demonstrating a cumulative grade point average of at least 2.00 and maintaining full-time enrollment.\r\n', '<li>Digital photo â a headshot or photograph of yourself\r\n<li>Tribal affiliation â Enrolled members should provide proof of their tribal enrollment (or CIB).\r\n<li> Descendants prove descent by providing a copy of their parent/grandparentâs enrollment information and a copy of the studentâs birth certificate\r\n<li>Transcript â Most recent high school or college unofficial transcript\r\n', '<li>Hit the below âClick here & applyâ button\r\n<li>Read the Scholarship details carefully \r\n<li>Fillout the form & attach necessary documents carefully\r\n<li>Submit\r\n', ' $ 15000', '[\"Bachelors\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"UG\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-02', '2023-05-31', ' American Indian College Fund', 0.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 11:46:31', 1, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-18 08:03:33', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1834, 'BynVAUKrNQrc67Tea1', 'Abroad', 'Humanity Scholarship', 'https://www.authenticid.com/careers/scholarships-spring-2023/', '', '', '', '', '', 'We are seeking bright minds with a desire to heighten national awareness via our social media campaign to end the dehumanizing forces of human trafficking and child exploitation.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b>\r\n<li>Must be a current high school senior or college freshman, sophomore, or junior.\r\n<li>Plan to attend an accredited college, university, or community college in the upcoming academic year.\r\n<li>Be a U.S. Citizen or permanent resident.\r\n<li>Have a GPA of 2.50 or higher.\r\n<li>Entries must be an original, unpublished video created by the entrant.\r\n', '<li>Record a video (maximum length of 2 minutes) sharing a persuasive pitch for why ending human trafficking is important to your generation. Follow the instructions below for uploading your video and consider the following prompts:\r\n<li>Why is it important to address human trafficking and child exploitation at this point in time?\r\n<li>Thousands of companies are unwittingly being used by organized criminals to facilitate human trafficking. Why is it critical for companies to be proactive about preventing these types of crimes?\r\n<li>How do we lower the risk of trafficking for vulnerable populations and bring visibility to those who feel invisible?\r\n<li>Why is this issue time critical?\r\n<li>How can we raise awareness and vigilance about this issue among Gen Z for themselves and others?\r\n<li>How does this campaign to end trafficking improve humanity?\r\n', '<li>Hit the below âClick here & applyâ button\r\n<li>Read the Scholarship details carefully \r\n<li>Fillout the form & attach necessary documents carefully\r\n<li>Submit\r\n', '$25,000', '[\"Bachelors\"]', 'null', '\"UG\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-02-11', '2023-05-31'