(1839, 'QyRtePnxIdhT4iXYN3', '', 'Aikyashree Scholarship', 'WORLD NATURE PHOTOGRAPHY AWARDS 2023', '', '', '', '', '', 'Aikyashree Scholarship Program is the initiative of WBMDFC (West Bengal Minority Development Finance Corporation). Its main objective is to support the education of financially weak students of Minority communities. It provides support at both the school and college levels of West Bengal. The program is operated by the West Bengal Government and its subsidiary boards. Millions of students are being given financial assistance to support their higher education.\r\nWBMDFC took the initiative and started the Aikyashree Scholarship program for minority students (Muslims, Christians, Sikhs, Buddist, Parsis and Jain) so that they can finance their education and uplift their socio-economic status. All minority students from class 1 to PhD can apply for the different scholarship schemes under WBMDFC through the help of the WBMDFC Aikyashree Portal.\r\n<b>benefits \r\nTo provide education grants to poor minority students on merit\r\nInitiate women empowerment programs for Minority communities\r\nTo give financial independence to all the deserving students\r\nTo maximize the literacy rate in West Bengal\r\nTo give substantial training for different competitive exams\r\nTo initiate a training program for skill-based learning\r\nTo uplift the economic condition of West Bengal minorities by providing quality education\r\nEligibility Criteria\r\nThe eligibility criteria vary for the different types of Aikyashree-funded scholarships. Students must apply for scholarships following their level of education.', '', '', '', 'null', NULL, '\"Class 1 to PhD\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 0.00, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, '2023-08-15', '2023-10-31', 'West Bengal Minority Development Finance Corporation', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-19 12:44:25', 1, NULL, '2023-05-19 07:14:25', 0, '', '', '', '', N