(1905, 'KVaTH0j06D9GJIhKMV', 'Scholarship', 'NTPC Scholarship ', 'https://www.ntpc.co.in/', '', '', '', '', '', 'NTPC is an Indian public sector undertaking. It was established in 1956 and is a part of the government of India. The company deals with the generation and sale of electricity to various states. NTPC Scholarship aims to empower students and help them in every possible way irrespective of their category, gender, etc.\r\n<li>Thereby the corporation has started a scholarship scheme for Scheduled caste/ scheduled tribe/Physically challenged students. NTPC Limited, formerly known as National Thermal Power Corporation Limited, is an Indian Public Sector Undertaking, engaged in generating electricity and allied activities. One of the norms of the NTPC Scholarship scheme is that the student must have at least 75% attendance in the classes. The student shouldnât involve in any ragging activity.\r\n<li>The applications for NTPC Scholarship 2023 are yet to start. The students must follow up with the official website given here. https://www.ntpc.co.in/en\r\n<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility:</b>\r\n\r\n<li>The scholarship is acceptable for students who are in the second year of the course and is acceptable till the last year of their course.\r\n<li>This scholarship is given only to those students who are studying engineering courses from<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n1)IITs (Indian Institute of Technology)<br>\r\n2)NITs (National Institute of Technology)<br>\r\n3)BITS  (Birla Institute of Technology and Science)<br>\r\n<li>2ND YEAR Student of B.E./ Btech Programme from the above institutes\r\n<li>Age below 40 years\r\n<li>From the reserved category (SC/ST/PWD)\r\n<li>Only one scholarship can be applied by one candidate.\r\n<li>Parental income should be less than 1 lakh per year and this should be issued by Tehsildar, block, or notary public.\r\n<li>Should have address proof (Domicile) of-\r\nRajasthan,Delhi,Jammu and Kashmir,Himachal Pradesh,Haryana,Chandigarh,Punjab\r\n<li>A candidate 