(1908, 'bOsNTwCAg7ZZmvKK1B', 'Scholarship', 'Sanskriti - Kalakriti Fellowship', 'https://www.sanskritifoundation.org/', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Sanskriti Pratishthan invites applications for its annual Sanskriti - Kalakriti Fellowship in Performing Arts from young performing artists who wish to contribute towards enriching their respective art form. The purpose of the Fellowship is to encourage young artists to develop their potential and enhance their skills through intensive practice and or incorporating different facets of their art. The fellowship provides an opportunity to win a scholarship worth INR 50,000 to the fellows.\r\nEligibility\r\nThe following candidates are eligible for the scholarship:\r\n\r\nThe applicant should be an Indian National.\r\nThe candidate should have at least 10 years of initial training in Indian classical dance.\r\nThe fellow must have given at least 2-3 solo performances to his/her credit in recognized forums.\r\nNote- While this fellowship especially encourages women applicants, all proposals that fulfil the objectives of the program are welcome to apply.\r\n\r\nBenefits\r\nThe selected fellows will receive a scholarship worth INR 50,000 which will be disbursed in two instalments in the following way:\r\n\r\nThe first instalment of INR 25,000 will be given at the time of commencement of the fellowship. \r\nThe second instalment of INR 25,000 will be given at the time of submission of the complete project report of the fellow when the fellow may be requested to give a dance recital.\r\n Sanskriti Pratishthan invites young performing artists for the Sanskriti Kalakriti Fellowship. It is a programme of 3 months to 10 months duration</br>\r\n<li> Under the Sanskriti, Kalakriti Fellowship will get financial aid. Aid will be given in two equal installments at the beginning of the programme and the other at the end</br>\r\n<li> Women fellows will get preference during the selection of the fellows. Fellows have to choose their guru and take guidance from him/ her to enhance their existing style</br>\r\n<li> If you are interested in becoming a fellow then submit your application as soon as you can. For more details read the further session</br></br>\r\n<b>Important Dates</b></br>\r\n<li> The applications for Sanskriti - Kalakriti Fellowship will be accepted throughout the year</br></br>\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions</b></br>\r\n<li> The applicant will have to sign an agreement with Sanskriti Pratishthan pertaining to a regular flow of work during the Fellowship period</br> \r\n<li> The candidate should not be holding another Fellowship or working on any other project at the same time</br>\r\n<li> All candidates should mail their CV and a short synopsis of their project proposal to the head office address given below:</br>\r\nSanskriti Foundation  \r\nC-11, Qutab Institutional Area  \r\nNew Delhi-110 016  \r\n<li> The candidate will be required to take guidance from another senior guru and enhance their existing style</br>\r\n<li> It would be a residency programme for a period of 3 months, which can be spread over a period of 10 months</br>\r\n<li>This will require the candidate to take consent from his/her current guru and the guru he/she would want to go to</br></br>\r\n<b>Objective</b></br>\r\n<li> To encourage young artists to develop their potential </br>\r\n<li> Enhance young artistsâ skills through intensive practice </br>\r\n<li> To incorporate different facets of young artistsâ art</br></br>', '<li> An updated curriculum vitae/resume which should not be more than 2 pages long</br>\r\n<li> A write-up of not more than 500 words explaining their project</br>\r\n<li> Few samples of previous works</br>\r\n<li> The project of performances</br>\r\n<li> The names and contact addresses/telephones of 2 referees</br></br>', '<li> To apply for the Sanskriti Kalakriti Fellowship, you have to send a two-page CV and a proposal</br>\r\n<li> The proposal should be written in not approx. 500 words explaining their project</br>\r\n<li> Must provide postal and telephonic contact details of yours along with a valid email id</br>\r\n<li> Must mention the names and contact addresses/telephones of two referees</br>\r\n<li> Mention this fellowship on top of the envelope in which the proposal and CV is\r\nSend the application to Sanskriti Foundation, C-11, Qutab Institutional Area, New Delhi-110 016 and fellowships@sanskritifoundation.org</br></br>', ' 50000\r\n', '[\"All\"]', 'null', '\"Artists in the age group of 25 to 40\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-04-30', '2023-12-31', 'Sanskriti Foundation', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-26 15:33:59', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-26 10:04:58', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1909, 'gPa2i36Eu9EW0ZDOvp', 'Scholarship', ' Kalia Scholarship', 'https://scholarship.odisha.gov.in/website/student-registration', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Odisha government started the KALIA scheme to provide benefits to the farmers and now the opportunity of KALIA Scholarship has been provided by the same government to help the children of the beneficiaries of the KALIA scheme. KALIA Scholarship will be provided by the state government and through this scheme the children of selected farmers will be provided financial assistance under the Kalia scheme. Beneficiaries will be helped so that they can pursue their higher education. Students can take admission in government and vocational colleges and all the beneficiaries will be provided scholarship on the basis of merit.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b>\r\n<li>An applicant who has taken admission on Cost sharing self financing and NRI are not eligible for the scheme.\r\n<li>The candidate who is pursuing any other scholarship is not eligible to apply.\r\n<li>Student can get this scholarship for only one professional course\r\n<li>After getting the scholarship for one professional course they are not eligible to get scholarship for a second professional course.\r\n<li>An applicant must be a permanent of the state\r\n<li>The applicant should be a child of the beneficiaries under Kalia <li>Yojana under two different components such as cultivator for cultivation and livelihood support to landless agricultural households\r\n<li>The candidate must have taken admission in government institute of the state on merit basis', '<li>Aadhaar Card of student\r\n<li>Caste Certificate of the Student\r\n<li>Residence Certificate of the Student\r\n<li>Copy of passbook of Bank account with account number and IFSC code of the bank branch\r\n<li>Passport size Photograph of student\r\n<li>Ration Card of the Parent/ guardian\r\n<li>Beneficiary Id of the Parent/ guardian\r\n<li>Matriculation Certificate of the Student\r\n<li>Marksheet of last exam passed\r\n', '<li>Hit the below âClick here & applyâ button\r\n<li>Read the Scholarship details carefully \r\n<li>Fillout the form & attach necessary documents carefully\r\n<li>Submit\r\n', '1200/- per month', '[\"ITI\",\"Medical\",\"Engineering\",\"Bachelors\",\"Diploma\"]', 'null', '\"MBBS,BDS, BHMS,BAMS,BSC,B Pharma, BSc, DPharma, DMLT,DMRT,ANM,GNM,AGRI POLYTECHNIC\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 0.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-24', '2023-05-31', 'Government Of Odisha', 0.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-26 15:35:13', 1, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-26 10:08:51', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1910, '8MRzC6TZhQhcNEue5W', 'Scholarship', 'eMedhabruti Scholarship', 'https://scholarship.odisha.gov.in/website/student-registration ', '', '', '', '', '', 'e-Medhabruti is one the best scholarship scheme offer by the Government of Odisha. To encourage and meritorious students to pursue their education in the field of General, Technical and Professional education who canât bear the higher education due to financial crisis. Government of Odisha is awarding different scholarship every year through Higher Education Department on merit-cum-means basis. e Medhabruti scholarship 2023 last date is 30 October 2023.<br><br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b>\r\n<li>Students must be a resident of India for the scholarship.\r\n<li>In class X students are compulsory 60% marks.\r\n<li>Studentsâ family income should not be above six lakhs.\r\n<li>The candidate should have one of the lower grades like A1, A2, B1, and B2 or its equivalent percentage like A1-95%, A2-85%, B1- 75% and B2- 65%.', '<li>Aadhaar Card of student\r\n<li>Income Certificate of the Parent/ guardian\r\n<li>Residence Certificate of the Student\r\n<li>Copy of passbook of Bank account with account number and IFSC code of the bank branch\r\n<li>Passport size Photograph of student\r\n<li>College Id Card of the Student\r\n<li>Marksheet of last exam passed\r\n', '<li>Hit the below âClick here & applyâ button\r\n<li>Read the Scholarship details carefully \r\n<li>Fillout the form & attach necessary documents carefully\r\n<li>Submit\r\n', '20000', '[\"Engineering\",\"Bachelors\",\"Masters\",\"Professional course\"]', 'null', '\"BBA, BCA,BDS, BEd, BSc BJMC,BE, BTech, MA, LLM, MCom, MSc, MBA, MFC \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 'null', 'null', 'null', NULL, 'null', NULL, 'null', 0, 0, 'null', 600000.00, '', 'null', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-03-11', '2023-05-31', 'Government Of Odisha', 0.00, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-26 15:53:25', 1, 'yadwadaishwarya@triwits.com', '2023-05-26 10:26:05', 1, '', '', ''