(1916, 'xyB57gnuMKC9cU5RPJ', 'Scholarship', 'Anant Scholarship 2023', 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/15fPw19X2wRGtQp5PEYOzAdgPC89ZNo0T/view', '', '', '', '', '', ' Anant Scholarship 2023 | Important Dates, \r\nApplication Process, Eligibility Criteria\r\nMay 14, 2023 by Bhagya Anant Scholarship 2023: Anant Scholarship falls under the purview of the Anant Education Initiative, a CSR initiative of the Infinity Group. The primary aim of this scholarship is to empower education and remove economic hurdles that stand in the way of education. Anant Scholarship is awarded to meritorious students from economically weaker sections of society, irrespective of their caste, creed, or faith. Moreover, poverty is one of the biggest banes of society. One of the most effective ways to eliminate poverty is by providing education. Moreover, education improves employment rates, which negates the effects of poverty to some extent</br></br>\r\n<b> Eligibility Criteria</b></br>\r\n<li> Candidates MUST be studying in schools located in West Bengal</br>\r\n<li> Candidates must have secured not less than 70% aggregate in their class 10 and class 12</br>\r\n<li> The candidateâs total family from all sources should not exceed INR 5,000 per month\r\n<li> Madhyamik/ICSE /CBSE/Higher Secondary/ISC/College Students are eligible for the scholarship.\r\nBenefiys</b></br>\r\n<li> Anant Scholarship disperses an amount of INR 6,000 in monthly installments of INR 500</br>\r\n<li> Special preference will be given to deserving physically challenged students</br>\r\n<li> 50% of the scholarships are reserved for girl students</br></br>\r\n<b>Selection Procedure</b></br>\r\n<li> Anant Education Initiative selects deserving candidates from its pool of applicants</br>\r\n<li> Special preferences are given to deserving physically handicapped students</br>\r\n<li> Anantâs call center initiates them for interviews</br>\r\n<li> Selected students will complete banking formalities, with the Initiative opening an individual bank account for each student</br>\r\n<li> The scholarship amount will then be disbursed to these accounts</br>\r\n<li> In case any of the above-prescribed documents are missing from the application form, the institution will cancel the candidature of the applicant without any prior notice</br>', '<li>Attested Copy of Antyodaya Card or a BPL </br>\r\n<li>Card/OR Income Certificate (in original) issued by  Panchayat Pradhan or the Councillor</br>\r\n<li>Attested Copy of Mark Sheet of CBSE/Madhyamik /ICSE/CBSE+/Higher Secondary/ISC/Others</br>\r\n<li>Attested Copy of Proof of Residence or Ration Card</br>\r\n<li>Proof of Date of Birth â Birth Certificate or Attested Copy of Class 10 and 12 Admit Card\r\nOriginal Income Certificate</br>\r\n<li>Disability certificate (in the case of disabled candidates)</br>\r\n<li>Aadhar Card (attested copy)</br>\r\n', '<li>Students can apply for a scholarship from Anant Education Initiativeâs official website</br>\r\n<b>Note:</b> The candidates must possess a Google account to fill and submit the online form\r\nAlternatively, an offline form can be downloaded from the website and sent by mail after duly filling all details. The address to send the application is as follows:</br>\r\nANANT EDUCATION INITIATIVE</br>\r\nInfinity Think Tank, Tower II, 3rd Floor</br>\r\nPlot A3, Block GP, Sector V, Salt Lake, Kolkata â 700091</br></br>', '6,000 ', '[\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\",\"Class 11\",\"Class 12\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Undergraduate \"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-04-30', '2023-07-31', 'The Department of Higher Education', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-29 11:39:00', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-31 09:31:03', 1, '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL),
(1917, 'UU6D4Eli1ICNPf7R2B', 'Scholarship', 'Pratibha Kiran Scholarship ', 'http://www.scholarshipportal.mp.nic.in/Index.aspx', '', '', '', '', '', ' The main objective of this Pratibha Kiran Scholarship 2023 of the state government is to encourage girl students to pursue higher education in the state</br>\r\n<li> If a girl passes class 12th with 60% or more, then she will be eligible for the Pratibha Kiran program of Madhya Pradesh government and financial assistance is provided to such talented girl students under the government</br>\r\n<li> Now you will not have to stop the education of girl students in the state because of your economic condition. Now the girl students of the state will not have to depend on others for education</br>\r\n<li> She will be able to get education through the scholarship provided by the Government of Madhya Pradesh</br></br>\r\n<b> Features</b></br>\r\n<li> The government has started this scheme for the girl students of poor families</br>\r\n<li> Financially weak students will be given the benefit of the scheme</br>\r\n<li> 500 rupees will be provided every month under the scheme</br>\r\n<li> Under Pratibha Kiran Scholarship, financial assistance of more than Rs 5000 will be available every year</br>\r\n<li> Under this scheme, the girl students will get the scholarship amount for 10 months</br>\r\n<li> Girl students of urban areas are also eligible to take advantage of the scheme</br>\r\n<li> Girl students who have secured 60% or more marks in 12th are eligible to get the benefit of this scholarship scheme </br>\r\n<li >The benefit of the scheme can be availed by applying online</br>\r\n<li> Eligible girl students will get scholarship through DBT mode in direct account</br>\r\n<li> With this scheme of the government, girls from poor families will be encouraged to study further</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility</b></br>\r\n<li> The girl student should be a resident of urban area of ââMadhya Pradesh</br>\r\n<li> The student must have secu