(1941, '13UPyvL3sNO8RD4dAe', 'Scholarship', 'ONGC Scholarship ', 'https://ongcscholar.org/#/', '', '', '', '', '', ' Oil and Natural Gas Corporation Limited is Indiaâs first public enterprise corporation. It is the countryâs largest producer of crude oil and natural gas. This corporation has launched its scholarship program known as ONGC Scholarship. It aims to provide 2000 per annum scholarships to less privileged students of India. Students currently enrolled in the first year of engineering/Medical/MBA/Geophysics/Geology can apply for this scholarship. Scheduled classes (SC), Scheduled tribes (ST) and Other Backward Classes (OBC), which the Government of India classifies, are eligible for this scholarship. There is also a general category</br></br>\r\n<b>Eligibility Criteria</b></br>\r\n<li> Indian Nationality</br>\r\n<li> They must be currently enrolled in the first year of Engineering/Medical/MBA/Geophysics/Geology <li> departments</br>\r\n<li> For Engineering/Medical, qualifying examinations marks should be 60% or more</br>\r\n<li> For MBA/Geology/Geophysics, they must have graduated with 60% or a 6 GPA/OGPA on a 10-point scale grading system</br>\r\n<li> Annual gross income for SC/ST students must be 4.5 lac/annum maximum</br>\r\n<li> Annual gross income for the General category and Other Backward Classes (OBC) must be 2 lac/annum maximum</br>\r\n<li> To continue the scholarship, students must maintain 60% marks in examinations.\r\n<li> Age of the candidate must not exceed 30 as of July 1st, 2023</br></br>\r\n<b>Selection Process</b></br>\r\n<li> If you are applying for Engineering and Medical, your 12th examination marks will be considered for selection</br>\r\n<li> If you are applying for MBA/Geophysics/Geology, your graduation performance will be assessed for selection</br>\r\n<li> If multiple candidates have equal examination marks, then students having a lower annual income will be preferred for selection</br>\r\n<li> In the case of students belonging to BPL (Below Poverty Line) families, they will be preferred over others automatically</br></br>\r\n\r\n', '<li> Copy of Aadhaar card</br>\r\n<li> Copy of matriculation result sheet</br>\r\n<li> Copy of undertaking</br>\r\n<li> Copy of Intermediate result sheet for students who are applying for Engineering and Medical</br>\r\n<li> Copy of Graduation mark sheet for students who are applying for MBA and Geophysics/Geology</br>\r\n<li> Copy of certificate of scheduled caste</br>\r\n<li> Bank details</br>\r\n<li> Copy of PAN Card. If students donât have PAN Cards, they must submit the expected date on which they will get their PAN Cards</br>\r\n<li> Copy of the family annual income certificate</br></br>', '<li> Open the official website of the ONGC Foundation scholarship portal.</br>\r\n<li> Click on the âApply Scholarshipâ</br>\r\n<li> Start the Application procedure</br>\r\n<li> Click âagreeâ to the terms and conditions of this scholarship</br>\r\n<li> Start filling out the application form</br>\r\n<li> Upload the scanned copies of the required documents</br>\r\n<li> After checking the uploaded documents and information, submit the application form</br>\r\n<li> Print out the application form</br>\r\n<li> Now send this printed application form and hard copies of the required documents to the zoning office of scholarship providers</br>\r\n<b>Note: </b>ONGC has multiple zone offices. Students have to submit their application form to that zone office based on their last education institute rather than on the bases of their domiciles.</br></br>\r\n\r\n\r\n', ' 4,000 ', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '\"Engineering, Medical, MBA, Geophysics, Geology Departments\"', NULL, NULL, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', NULL, '[\"\"]', 0, 0, '[\"\"]', 0.00, '', '[\"\"]', 'null', 0.00, 0, 0, 0, '2023-05-31', '2023-09-21', 'Oil and Natural Gas Corporation Limited', 0.00, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-31 11:54:53', 1, 'asham@triwits.com', '2023-05-31